name: Daniel Magnusson
description: Daniel Magnusson is a Swedish professional ice hockey centre who currently plays for Modo Hockey of the Elitserien.

name: Daniel Mannberg
description: Daniel Mannberg (born December 27, 1992) is a Swedish professional ice hockey player. He played with Luleå HF in the Elitserien during the 2010–11 Elitserien season.

name: Daniel Mashamaite
description: Daniel "Black Diamond" Mashamaite (born 6 December 1976) is a kickboxer, Muay Thai fighter and mixed martial artist from Polokwane, South Africa. He is currently based in Johor Bahru, Malaysia.

name: Daniel McCartan
description: Daniel McCartan is a Gaelic football player from County Down, Northern Ireland. He plays for the Down senior inter county football team and with his local club Burren GAA. He is the younger brother of current Down manager James McCartan. He started at right corner back in the 2010 All-Ireland Football Final where Down were defeated 0-15 to 0-16 by Cork. Dan has won 2 down championship in 2010 & 2011 .

name: Daniel McKinney
description: Daniel McKinney (9 November 1898 – 1956), also known as Dan McKinney and Danny McKinney, was an Irish international footballer who played professionally in England as a forward.

name: Daniel Mina
description: Daniel Nevil Mina Arisola (born December 9, 1980 in Santa Ana) is an Ecuadorian football midfielder currently playing for Barcelona.

name: Daniel Minea
description: Daniel Adrian Minea (born 26 December 1961) is a Romanian footballer who played as a midfielder in the 1980s and 1990s. He started his career with Steaua Bucharest, before moving to FC Olt Scorniceşti. He returned to Steaua in 1989 and he went on to play for them in their 1989 European Cup Final defeat by Milan. He was still at the club in 1990–91 when he played two games in that season's Cup Winners Cup, one of which was the 1st round, 2nd leg match against Glentoran. Minea played a total of 243 Divizia A matches for Steaua Bucharest and FC Olt, scoring 17 goals. In 1991 he joined Belgian side K. Sint-Niklase S.K.E. and he remained with them for five seasons before retiring. He made 118 league appearances for them scoring 10 goals. His brother, Iulian, also played professional football.

name: Daniel Moen Hansen
description: Daniel Moen Hansen (born 18 November 1983) is a Norwegian football striker who currently plays for Strømmen. He has played for a number of clubs in Scandinavia and Southern Europe.

name: Daniel Mracka
description: Daniel Mracka is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Daniel Muñoz de la Nava
description: Daniel Muñoz de la Nava is a Spanish professional tennis player.

name: Daniel Mudau
description: Daniel Mudau (born 4 September 1968) is a South African former footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a striker.

name: Daniel Nešpor
description: Daniel Nešpor (born 28 September 1987) is a Czech football player who currently plays for Vlašim.

name: Daniel Newton (cricketer)
description: Daniel Charles Alexander Newton (born 14 December 1990) is an English cricketer. Newton is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born in Westminster, London and educated at Kings School, Wimbledon. While studying for his degree in Geography at Durham University, Newton made his first-class debut for Durham MCCU against Nottinghamshire in 2010. In his only first-class match, he batted once and was dismissed for a duck by Ryan Sidebottom.

name: Daniel Nordmark
description: Karl Daniel Nordmark (born 4 January 1988) is a Swedish football player who is currently playing for Helsingborgs IF in Allsvenskan.

name: Daniel Novac
description: Daniel Ionuţ Novac (born 26 September 1987) is a Romanian football midfielder. He currently plays for Liga I club Sportul Studențesc.

name: Daniel Ohrn
description: Daniel Ohrn (born January 27, 1993) is a Swedish ice hockey player. He is currently playing with Timrå IK in the Elitserien.

name: Daniel Orozco Álvarez
description: Daniel Orozco Álvarez is a Spanish footballer who plays as a central defender.

name: Daniel Orton
description: Daniel Joseph Orton is an American professional basketball player who currently plays for the Oklahoma City Thunder of the NBA. He is a 6-foot 10-inch, 255-pound center who played for the University of Kentucky Wildcats.

name: Daniel Panizzolo
description: Daniel Panizzolo (born 25 March 1986) is a Swiss footballer who plays for Locarno in the Swiss Challenge League. Previous clubs include Eupen, Prato and Genoa.

name: Daniel Pascoe
description: Daniel "Dan" Pascoe (born 7 July 1900 Llanharan — died 19 May 1971 in Leeds) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1920s, playing representative level rugby union (RU) for Wales, and at club level for Bridgend RFC and Neath RFC, captaining both, as a Flanker, i.e. number 6 or 7, and playing club level rugby league (RL) for Leeds.

name: Daniel Peacock (cricketer)
description: Daniel James Peacock is an English-born former cricketer. Peacock was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm off break. In January 1999 Peacock made his first-class debut for Mashonaland A against Matabeleland in the 1998/99 Logan Cup. Peacock represented Mashonaland A just once in the Logan Cup that season, but did represent a Zimbabwe Cricket Union President's XI against England A and for a Matabeleland Invitation XI against the Australian Cricket Academy. In the same season Peacock made his List-A debut for Zimbabwe A against England A in February 1999. In March, Peacock represented a Matabeleland Invitation XI against the Australian Cricket Academy. Peacock represented Zimbabwe A in the 1999/2000 ICC Emerging Nations Tournament, where Peacock played three matches against the national sides of Denmark, Kenya and Ireland. Later in 2000, Peacock played four List-A matches for Zimbabwe A on their tour of Sri Lanka. Peacock played five first-class matches on the tour, against Sri Lanka A in three matches and a Sri Lanka Board XI in two matches In the 2000 Logan Cup, Peacock made his debut for Mashonaland against CFX Academy. Peacock represented Mashonaland in five first-class matches in 2000, including the final of the Logan Cup against Manicaland, which Mashonaland won by 257 runs. Peacock's final first-class match came against the touring New Zealanders in September 2000. In his first-class career Peacock scored 312 runs at an average of 15.60, with a high score of 62. Peacock took only three wickets with his off breaks, averaging 105.33 per wicket. Increasing politicization of cricket, including selectorial policy, along with the declining situation in Zimbabwe itself resulted in a mass exodus of players from Zimbabwe, with Peacock joining the exodus. Peacock played a single List-A game for the Hampshire Cricket Board in England, during the 1st Round of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was played in 2002. Pocock also represented the Hampshire Cricket Board in two Minor Counties Trophy Matches against the Channel Islands and Surrey Cricket Board in 2002.

name: Daniel Peev
description: Daniel Peev (born 6 October 1984) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays as a midfielder for Lokomotiv Sofia. He is a left attacking midfielder. Daniel is also the younger brother of the winger of Russian Amkar Perm Georgi Peev.

name: Daniel Perez (fighter)
description: Daniel Perez (born July 16, 1984) is a Spanish-American mixed martial arts (MMA) fighter and kickboxer. He has fought for notable organizations such as Xtreme Fighting Championships, K-1, and Rage in the Cage.

name: Daniel Perreault
description: Daniel Perreault (born April 11, 1961) is a Canadian fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Daniel Pietta
description: Daniel Pietta (born December 9, 1986) is a German professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing for Krefeld Pinguine in the Deutsche Eishockey Liga (DEL).

name: Daniel Polson
description: Daniel Luke Polson, OAMis an Australian Paralympic cyclist. He won a gold medal at the 2000 Sydney Games in the Mixed Bicycle Road Race LC2 event, for which he received a Medal of the Order of Australia.

name: Daniel Pope
description: Daniel Pope is a former professional American football player who played punter for three seasons for the Kansas City Chiefs, Cincinnati Bengals, New York Jets, and New England Patriots.

name: Daniel Ramsay
description: Daniel Ramsay is a rugby union footballer who plays as a lock for Section Paloise in the Pro D2.

name: Daniel Ramseier
description: Daniel Ramseier (born 1963) is a Swiss equestrian. He won a silver medal in team dressage at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul, together with Otto Josef Hofer, Christine Stückelberger and Samuel Schatzmann. He also competed at the 2000 Summer Olympics and the 2004 Summer Olympics.

name: Daniel Rehák
description: Daniel Rehák (born 2 April 1985 in Slovakia) is a Slovak defender who currently plays for FK Slovan Duslo Šaľa. He is a former Slovakia U-21 international. He came through the ranks of FK Slovan Duslo Šaľa of the Slovak 2nd Division and caught the eye of top Czech club Slovan Liberec with his impressive performances. They signed the 21 year old international in 2006. After finding it hard to establish himself in the first team and making only 1 substitute appearance in the league he went on loan to České Budějovice. However he spent his loan spell on the bench and playing for the 'B' side before returning to Liberec. He was released by the club in 2010 and joined FK Fotbal Třinec to get first team football.

name: Daniel Rock (cricketer)
description: Daniel John Rock (born 26 October 1981) is a former English cricketer. Rock is a left-handed batsman who fields as a wicket-keeper. He was born in Ipswich, Suffolk. Rock made his debut for Suffolk in the 1998 MCCA Knockout Trophy against the Essex Cricket Board. Rock made 4 further MCCA Knockout Trophy appearances, with his last appearance coming in 2000 against Hertfordshire. He made no appearances in the Minor Counties Championship for Suffolk, but did make a single List A appearance against the Lancashire Cricket Board in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. In this match, he scored 7 runs before being run out. He has previously played Second XI cricket for the Leicestershire, Northamptonshire and Derbyshire Second XI's.

name: Daniel Rosas
description: Daniel Rosas Reyes is an undefeated Mexican professional boxer in the Bantamweight division and is the current WBC CABOFE Super Flyweight Champion.

name: Daniel Rubin
description: Daniel Rubin (born July 29, 1985) is a Swiss professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for SC Bern in Switzerland's National League A. He is participating at the 2011 IIHF World Championship as a member of the Switzerland men's national ice hockey team.

name: Daniel Salvatierra
description: Daniel Salvatierra (born 23 February 1990 in Rosario) is an Argentine football central defender currently playing for Atlético Tucumán.

name: Daniel Sanders (American football)
description: Daniel Sanders (born February 3, 1986) is an American football center for the Baltimore Ravens of the National Football League. He was signed by the St. Louis Rams as an undrafted free agent in 2009. He played college football at Colorado.

name: Daniel Sandoval
description: Daniel Sandoval Navarro is a Mexican professional boxer and is considered one of the best prospects in the Welterweight division.

name: Daniel Sarafian
description: Daniel Sarafian Gantman (Born August 21, 1982 in Sao Paulo, Brazil) is a Brazilian-Armenian mixed martial artist who competes in the middleweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship. A professional MMA competitor since 2006, Sarafian has fought mostly in Brazil and in the United States, including a one-fight stint in Bellator Fighting Championships. He was a competitor on Globo's The Ultimate Fighter: Brazil.

name: Daniel Sarmiento
description: Pablo Daniel Sarmiento (born June 10, 1971 in Las Varillas, Cordoba, Argentina) is an Argentine professional boxer in the Light Welterweight division and is the former IBO Light Welterweight Champion. He's also the brother of boxing trainer Gabriel Sarmiento.

name: Daniel Schorn
description: Daniel Schorn (born 21 October 1988) is an Austrian professional road bicycle racer who rides for UCI Professional Continental Team Team NetApp-Endura. Born in Zell am See, Schorn has competed as a professional since 2008, competing for the Elk Haus-Simplon team, prior to joining Team NetApp for the start of the 2010 season. Schorn, and Team NetApp, made their Grand Tour début at the 2012 Giro d'Italia, where Schorn took fifth place during the ninth stage of the race. The result came after Schorn avoided a crash with around 400 m to go, that eliminated several other sprinters from contention.

name: Daniel Semenzato
description: Daniel Semenzato (born 11 January 1987) is an Italian footballer who plays for Lega Pro Prima Divisione club Treviso.

name: Daniel Sengewald
description: Daniel Sengewald is a retired German professional football player. He played his entire career as a tall defender. Sengewald played most of his career in the lower leagues of German football. His first taste of non-German football came with Belgian club Royal Antwerp, before moving to Scotland to play for top-flight side Motherwell. He made 7 appearances at Fir Park, but also got sent-off in his final game. He then left Scotland to play for another batch of lower-league German clubs, before then moving to Albania with Partizani.

name: Daniel Severino
description: Daniel Severino (born 11 February 1982 in Sydney, Australia) is an Australian football (soccer) player who is a left footed central midfielder. He plays for Marconi Stallions.

name: Daniel Sliper
description: Daniel Sliper (born 23 April 1987) is a Swedish footballer who plays for GIF Sundsvall as a midfielder.

name: Daniel Smith (footballer born 1982)
description: Daniel Smith (born 17 August 1982) is an English footballer who played in The Football League for Bournemouth and currently plays for Gosport Borough.

name: Daniel Soares Neves
description: Daniel Baroni Soares Neves (Born in 3 June 1980 at Minas Gerais, Brazil), simply known as Daniel Baroni, is a Brazilian footballer who currently unattached. He formerly plays as a Striker for Kedah FA in the Malaysia Super League for the 2012 season. His contract was terminated, along with another Kedah import player Danilo Vivaldo after only five games into the season. Daniel is a product of the Clube Atlético Mineiro youth academy. Daniel also played in Martyr's Memorial A-Division League for Machhindra Football Club where he was unable to perform his best because of poor ground condition claims his agent Nabin Chitrakar.

name: Daniel Sparre
description: Daniel Sparre (born October 16, 1984) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing for Straubing Tigers in the Deutsche Eishockey Liga (DEL).

name: Daniel Spivak
description: Daniel Spivak (born 9 August 1988) is a Canadian amateur ice hockey defenceman. He played college ice hockey for the Rochester Institute of Technology, which plays in Atlantic Hockey, part of the NCAA's Division I. Born in Netanya, Israel, he also played for the Israel national ice hockey team in the 2009 IIHF World Championship Division II. Before enrolling at RIT as a Business/Finance major, he played four seasons for the Stouffville Spirit of the Ontario Provincial Junior Hockey League. As of December 2012, he is currently playing for the Fort Worth Brahmas in Fort Worth, Texas.

name: Daniel Stana
description: Daniel Stana (born 2 December 1982) is a Romanian professional football player. He currently plays for Romanian Liga I team Ceahlăul Piatra-Neamţ.

name: Daniel Stensland
description: Daniel Stensland is a Norwegian footballer who currently plays for Levanger. He made his debut against SK Brann in April 2009. Born in Fauske, Stensland has played for Fauske/Sprint in the Norwegian Third Division in 2006 and 2007, before he transferred to Bodø/Glimt in 2008.

name: Daniel Tătar
description: Daniel Vasile Tătar (born 21 October 1987, Blaj) is an Romanian footballer under contract with Liga I side FC Brașov. First match in Liga I was played for CSU Voința Sibiu against Astra Ploieşti.

name: Daniel Tapeta
description: Daniel Tapeta (born 25 October 1974) in Tahiti is a footballer who plays as a Goalkeeper. He currently plays for AS Manu-Ura in the Tahiti Division Fédérale and the Tahiti national football team.

name: Daniel Te'o-Nesheim
description: Daniel Te'o-Nesheim (born Daniel Nesheim on June 12, 1987) is an American football defensive end for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Philadelphia Eagles in the third round of the 2010 NFL Draft. He played college football at Washington.

name: Daniel Tetrault
description: Daniel Tetrault (born September 4, 1979) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman for the Evansville IceMen of the ECHL. Tetrault won the Central Hockey League Most Outstanding Defenseman in the 2001–02 CHL season.

name: Daniel Udsen
description: Daniel Udsen (born 2 September 1983) is a Faroese footballer of Danish descent, whose primary position is in midfield. He currently plays for FC Helsingør and the Faroe Islands national football team.

name: Daniel Williams (cricketer)
description: Daniel Mark Williams (born December 1981) is an English cricketer. Williams is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium-fast. He was born in Newbury, Berkshire. Williams made his debut for Berkshire in the 2001 Minor Counties Championship against Dorset. He made a further appearance for Berkshire in the 2003 Minor Counties Championship against Cheshire. Later, while studying for his degree at Loughborough University, Williams made his first-class debut for Loughborough UCCE against Surrey in 2008. He made a further appearance for the team in 2008, against Gloucestershire. In his two first-class matches, he scored 25 runs at an average of 8.33, with a high score of 11.

name: Daniel Zeleny
description: Daniell Zeleny (born 19 October 1988) is an Australian association footballer of Czech and Italian descent. He last played for Gresik United in the Indonesia Super League in Indonesia. He plays as a defender or defensive midfielder. Zeleny possesses dual passports due to his European heritage.

name: Daniela Sabatino
description: Daniela Sabatino is an Italian football striker currently playing for ACF Brescia in Serie A. She previously played for AC Bojano and ACF Reggiana in Serie A and Rapid Lugano in the Swiss Nationalliga A. She was the 2011 Serie A's second top scorer with 25 goals. She is a member of the Italian national team.

name: Daniela Tasch
description: Daniela Tasch is an Austrian football midfielder. She currently plays for SV Neulengbach in the ÖFB-Frauenliga, and is also a member of the Austrian national team

name: Daniele Buzzegoli
description: Daniele Buzzegoli (born May 7, 1983 in Florence) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Novara He played 2 seasons (4 games, no goals) in the Serie A for Empoli F.C. His grandfather Ivo Buzzegoli played in the Serie A in the 1940s.

name: Daniele Carnasciali
description: Daniele Carnasciali (born September 6, 1966 in San Giovanni Valdarno) is a retired Italian professional football player. He played for 7 seasons (150 games, 2 goals) in the Serie A for ACF Fiorentina, Bologna F.C. 1909 and A.C. Venezia. In July 1997, he was sold to Bologna for 1.75 billion Italian lire, as part of Andrea Tarozzi's deal. He made his debut for the Italy national football team on December 21, 1994 in a game against Turkey.

name: Daniele Cilli
description: Daniele Cilli (born March 19, 1988 in Barletta) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Lega Pro Seconda Divisione team F.C. Igea Virtus Barcellona on loan from A.S. Bari.

name: Daniele Fiorentino
description: Daniele Fiorentino (born November 4, 1988 in Terlizzi) is an Italian professional football player.

name: Daniele Fruci
description: Daniele Fruci (born 6 June 1988 in Rome) is an Italian footballer who currently plays as a defender for Pergocrema.

name: Daniele Giordano
description: Daniele Giordano (born 4 March 1991) is an Italian footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Italian Lega Pro Seconda Divisione club A.C. Perugia Calcio.

name: Daniele Giorgini
description: Daniele Giorgini is an Italian professional tennis player.

name: Daniele Granata
description: Daniele Granata (born 13 June 1991 in Ortona) is an Italian footballer who plays as a defender for S.S. Teramo Calcio on loan from Pescara.

name: Daniele Gregori
description: Daniele Gregori (born February 18, 1977 in Foligno) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Foligno Calcio. He played 14 games in the Serie A in the 2002/03 season for Calcio Como. In July 2003, after Enrico Preziosi acquired Genoa, he was sold to the club for free but in January 2004 returned to Como for 750,000. In 2008 Preziosi was found guilty and his football ban was upheld.

name: Daniele Mattielig
description: Daniele Mattielig is an Italian footballer who plays as a midfielder. Mattielig is 1.75 metres and weigh 71 kilograms .

name: Daniele Messina
description: Daniele Messina (born 19 March 1992 in Adrano) is Italian footballer who currently plays for Foligno on loan from U.C. Sampdoria. Messina started his career at Sampdoria youth categories, and made his debut for Samp on UEFA Europa League match against Debrecen, in 26 January 2011.

name: Daniele Musa
description: Daniele Musa (born 10 September 1972) is a former professional tennis player from Italy.

name: Daniele Prato
description: Daniele Prato (born 25 May 1991) is an Italian footballer who plays for Prima Divisione club Monza.

name: Daniele Rosania
description: Daniele Rosania (born 22 March 1991) is an Italian footballer who plays for Italian Serie B club Lanciano.

name: Daniele Sciarra
description: Daniele Sciarra (born 12 July 1991 in Atri) is an Italian footballer who plays as a forward for Chieti on loan from Serie B side Pescara.

name: Daniele Secci
description: Daniele Secci (born 9 March 1992) is an Italian shot putter.

name: Daniele Tacconi
description: Daniele Tacconi (born November 18, 1960 in Pelago) is a retired Italian professional football player. He played for 3 seasons (56 games, 1 goal) in the Serie A for Perugia Calcio and A.C. Milan. He represented Italy at the 1980 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship.

name: Danielle Carter (footballer)
description: Danielle Carter is an English football striker, currently playing for Arsenal LFC in the FA WSL.

name: Danielle Dube
description: Danielle Dube (born March 10, 1976) played for the Canadian National women's ice hockey team from 1994 to 1998 and from 2000 to 2002. She was a late cut from the 1998 and 2002 Canadian Olympic teams. On December 11, 2002, Danielle Dube became the third female goaltender to start in goal for a professional men's team. Dube was the goalie for the Long Beach Ice Dogs in a loss against the San Diego Gulls. She stopped 12 of 13 shots for the Ice Dogs. In 2008, she had considered approaching the Vancouver Canucks, with hopes of earning a recommendation to play for the ECHL's Victoria Salmon Kings. On August 26, 2011, she participated in the Longest Ice Hockey Game 4 CF, at Canlan Ice Sports Burnaby 8 Rinks in Burnaby, British Columbia. The goal was to play for the next 10 days as 40 women attempted to set a new Guinness World Record for playing the longest hockey game while also raising funds and awareness for the Canadian Cystic Fibrosis Foundation.

name: Danielle Johnson
description: Danielle Johnson (born 17 November 1987) is an American football (soccer) defender who currently plays for the Vancouver Whitecaps FC. She had previously played for the Melbourne Victory and the Atlanta Beat. She previously attended the University of Mississippi. In January 2012, Johnson signed with Atlanta Beat. Head coach James Galanis said of Johnson, "She is strong and fearless, and she also has good ball handling skills."

name: Danielle Murphy
description: Danielle Murphy (born 4 June 1981) is an English footballer. She plays as a midfielder or defender for Barnet Ladies and has represented England at senior international level.

name: Daniil Belotserkovskiy
description: Daniil Aleksandrovich Belotserkovskiy (Russian: Даниил Александрович Белоцерковский; born July 24, 1994) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Khimki. He made his debut in the FNL for FC Khimki on May 30, 2011 in a game against FC Alania Vladikavkaz.

name: Daniil Nagovitsin
description: Daniil Andreyevich Nagovitsin (Russian: Даниил Андреевич Наговицин; born September 16, 1993) is a Russian football forward, who currently plays for FC Zenit-Izhevsk Izhevsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Zenit-Izhevsk Izhevsk on April 24, 2012 in a game against FC Tyumen.

name: Daniil Shlepanov
description: Daniil Konstantinovich Shlepanov (Russian: Даниил Константинович Шлепанов; born March 3, 1989) is a football forward who last played for FC Znamya Truda Orekhovo-Zuyevo. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Znamya Truda Orekhovo-Zuyevo on August 2, 2011 in a game against FC Dynamo Kostroma.

name: Daniils Turkovs
description: Daniils Turkovs (born 17 February 1988 in Jūrmala) is a Latvian footballer who currently plays for the Latvian Higher League club FK Ventspils and Latvia football team.

name: Danijel Brezič
description: Danijel Brezič (born 15 February 1976 in Murska Sobota) is a Slovenian football midfielder, who last played for Grazer AK in the Austrian Regional League Central. He previously played for R.W.D. Molenbeek in the Belgian First Division.

name: Danijel Kovacic
description: Danijel Kovacic (born July 3, 1987) is a German professional ice hockey goaltender. He is currently playing for Krefeld Pinguine in the Deutsche Eishockey Liga (DEL).

name: Danijel Miličević
description: Danijel Miličević (born 5 January 1986) is a Swiss footballer of Bosnian descent who plays for Charleroi at Belgian Second Division. His family is from Ugljevik, Bosnia and Herzegovina.

name: Danijel Popović (footballer)
description: Danijel Popović (6 March 1982 – 23 October 2002) was a Croatian footballer who played as a forward. Playing for Vukovar '91, Popović established himself as one of the most talented Croatian footballers of his generation. After impressing in the first two seasons, he was loaned to Bastia. After the transfer to Bastia fell through, Popović then joined Osijek where he played in only eleven matches before his tragic death in a road accident in the evening of 23 October 2002.

name: Danijel Premerl
description: Danijel Premerl (23 January 1904 – 1 October 1975) was a Croatian football player. He was one of few players to play for all four major Zagreb clubs prior to the Second World War. He is buried in Mirogoj Cemetery.

name: Danijel Zagorac
description: Danijel Zagorac (born 7 February 1987 in Drniš) is a Croatian football player, currently playing for RNK Split in the Prva HNL.

name: Danika Bourne
description: Danika Bourne (born 9 July 1981 in Brisbane) is an Australian ice dancer. With partner Alexander Pavlov, she competed at two Four Continents Championships.

name: Danil Lyamin
description: Danil Serafimovich Lyamin (Russian: Данил Серафимович Лямин; born January 17, 1992) is a Russian football goalkeeper, who currently plays for FC Saturn Moscow Oblast. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Saturn Moscow Oblast on May 12, 2012 in a game against FC Sheksna Cherepovets.

name: Danil Nosov
description: Danil Vladimirovich Nosov (Russian: Данил Владимирович Носов; born June 5, 1990) is a Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Saturn-2 Moscow Oblast.

name: Danil Paybarshev
description: Danil Alekseyevich Paybarshev (Russian: Данил Алексеевич Пайбаршев; born May 7, 1994) is a Russian football forward, who currently plays for FC Rubin-2 Kazan. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Rubin-2 Kazan on April 18, 2012 in a game against FC Volga Ulyanovsk.

name: Danila Korolkov
description: Danila Alekseyevich Korolkov (Russian: Данила Алексеевич Корольков; born November 29, 1986) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Dynamo Kirov in the Russian Second Division.

name: Danilo Alves de Freitas
description: Danilo Alves de Freitas or simply Danilo (born February 12, 1989 in Mato Grosso), is a Brazilian centre midfielder. He currently plays for Vitória F.C. in the Portuguese Primeira Liga.

name: Danilo Cóccaro
description: Erardo Danilo Cóccaro Díaz (born 22 August 1991) is a Uruguayan footballer who plays for Dinamo Minsk in Belarusian Premier League.

name: Danilo Dias
description: Danilo Leandro Dias is a Brazilian professional footballer, who plays as a striker for Marítimo in Portugal.

name: Danilo Fernandes
description: Danilo Fernandes Batista was born in Guarulhos.

name: Danilo Gomes
description: Danilo Gustavo Vergne Gomes (born 15 October 1981) is a Brazilian football player.

name: Danilo Marcelino
description: Danilo Marcelino (born 8 March 1966) is a former professional tennis player from Brazil.

name: Danilo Moreno Asprilla
description: Danilo Moreno Asprilla (born January 12, 1989 in Medellín) is a Colombian footballer currently playing for Santa Fe in the Categoría Primera A.

name: Danilo Sousa Campos
description: Richard Danilo Maciel Sousa Campos (born 13 January 1990) is a Brazilian-born Belgian professional footballer who plays for Metalurh Donetsk as an attacking midfielder. His father is former Standard Liège player Wamberto.

name: Danilo Teixeira
description: Danilo Martins Teixeira (born December 2, 1983 in São Paulo) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for the Omani side Al-Oruba SC.

name: Danique Stein
description: Danique Stein is a Swiss football defender, currently playing for FC Basel in the Nationalliga A. She has also played for Concordia Basel (Nat. A), SC Freiburg and SC 07 Bad Neuenahr. She has been a member of the Swiss national team. As an Under-19 international she took part in the 2009 U-19 European Championship.

name: Danis Salman
description: Danis Salman (Turkish: Danış Salman; born 12 March 1960) is a Turkish Cypriot-born British former professional footballer who played as a defender, making over 500 appearances in the Football League.

name: Danka Podovac
description: Danka Podovac is a Serbian football midfielder currently playing for ÍBV Vestmannaeyar. She began her career in Serbian powerhouse Masinac Nis, with who she also played the European Cup and later moved to Iceland's Úrvalsdeild in 2006, playing three seasons for Keflavík and one for Fylkir and Þór-KA Akureyri before signing for ÍBV in 2011. She is a member of the Serbian national team.

name: Danner Pachi
description: Danner Jesús Pachi Bozo (born April 1, 1984 in Caranavi) is a Bolivian football midfielder that is currently without a club. Pachi began his career in 2001 with Bolivian giant Bolívar. He spent nearly 7 years with the club with over 200 league appearances throughout this period. In the winter of 2007 he was loaned to Wilstermann, but after six months Bolívar claimed back his services. In his return to the academia, Pachi had an outstanding 2008 season. His good performance awoke the interest of many clubs abroad. In January 2009, he signed for Ecuadorian club LDU Portoviejo, which was relegated at the end of the season. The next year he returned to Bolívar, but did not get much playing time. In 2011 he signed for club Guabirá.

name: Dannes Coronel
description: Dannes Arcenio Coronel Campoverde (born May 24, 1973 in Naranjal) is a retired football defender from Ecuador, who made 27 appearances for the Ecuador national team between 1992 and 2000. He played for several clubs in his native country, including Club Sport Emelec.

name: Dannix Ring
description: Daniel "Dannix" Ring (born 1898, date of death unknown) was an Irish hurler who played as a centre-back for the Cork senior team. Ring made his first appearance for the team during the 1919 championship and was a regular member of the starting fifteen until his retirement after the 1925 championship. During that time he won one All-Ireland medal and two Munster medals. At club level Ring was a multiple county championship medalist with St. Finbarr's.

name: Danny Aiken
description: Daniel Lee Aiken (born August 28, 1988) is an American football long snapper for the New England Patriots of the National Football League. He played high school football at Cave Spring High School in Roanoke, Virginia. He was signed by the Buffalo Bills as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football for Virginia after a prep year at Fork Union Military Academy.

name: Danny Alderman
description: Daniel 'Danny' Alan Alderman (born 14 August 1976) is an English cricketer. Alderman is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born at Cuckfield, Sussex. Alderman represented the Sussex Cricket Board in List A cricket. His debut List A game came against Hertfordshire in the 1999 NatWest Trophy. From 1999 to 2001, he represented the Board in 6 List A matches, the last of which came against Essex Cricket Board in the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2001. In his 6 List A matches, he scored 38 runs at a batting average of 12.66, with a high score of 14*. With the ball he took 3 wickets at a bowling average of 56.00, with best figures of 1/15. He currently plays club cricket for Three Bridges Cricket Club in the Sussex Cricket League.

name: Danny Allen-Page
description: Danny Liam Allen-Page (born 30 October 1983) is an English footballer who plays as a defender, but is currently unattached after being released by Hayes & Yeading United. Allen-Page started his career as a trainee with Brentford, making one first team appearance, before being released in 2004. He joined Farnborough Town and after two full seasons with them he left to join Yeading. They merged with Hayes in 2007 to form Hayes & Yeading United, with whom he won promotion to the Conference National in 2009.

name: Danny Andrew
description: Daniel Kenny Andrew is an English footballer, currently playing for Gloucester City. Andrew signed a professional contract during the summer of 2009 and impressed the Peterborough management team during a week-long training camp in Marbella. Predominantly a left-back, Andrew can also operate in the centre of midfield and progressed through the youth ranks at London Road. Injuries to Scott Griffiths and Jamie Day saw Andrew play the final two games of Peterboroughs season. He made his debut in the 1–0 defeat at home to Blackpool and continued at left-back for the final game of the season away to Plymouth Argyle which ended in a 2–1 win for Peterborough. Andrew was not offered a new contract at London Road and therefore left the club. He signed a 2 year contract at Cheltenham Town. After his first season at Whaddon Road he was rewarded with a one-year contract extension after missing just 3 League games in the whole season. On 13 September 2012, he joined Football Conference side Cambridge United on an initial one-month loan.

name: Danny Barnes (rugby league)
description: Danny Barnes is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1990s, playing at club level for Stanley Rangers ARLFC, and Halifax, as a Hooker.

name: Danny Barrera
description: Daniel Francisco "Danny" Barrera (born 8 January 1990) is a Colombian-American professional soccer player currently playing for Atlanta Silverbacks in the North American Soccer League.

name: Danny Biega
description: Danny Biega (born September 29, 1991) is a Canadian ice hockey defenceman. He was selected by the Carolina Hurricanes in the 3rd round (67th overall) of the 2010 NHL Entry Draft. Biega is currently playing for the Harvard Crimson in the a NCAA Men's Division I ECAC Hockey conference. In his junior year, Biega's outstanding play was recognized when he was named the ECAC's best defensive defenceman and selected to the 2011–12 ECAC Hockey First Team.

name: Danny Brabham
description: Danny Brabham (February 25, 1941 – January 22, 2011) was an American football player who played collegiately at linebacker for the University of Arkansas, and for six seasons in the American Football League for the Houston Oilers and the Cincinnati Bengals. Brabham died in his home in Prairieville, Louisiana, on January 22, 2011.

name: Danny Brannagan
description: Danny Brannagan (born July 4, 1986 in Burlington, Ontario) is a professional Canadian football quarterback who is currently a free agent. He most recently played for the Toronto Argonauts of the Canadian Football League.

name: Danny Cameron (footballer)
description: Daniel Cameron, is a Scottish footballer who played as a left back in the Football League.

name: Danny Campbell (rugby league)
description: Danny Campbell is a New Zealand former rugby league player who played professionally for Wigan.

name: Danny Chew Ji Xiang
description: Danny Chew is a defender who last played in the S. League for Woodlands Wellington FC. A relatively late bloomer, he only turned professional in 2012 and is played in his debut season with the Rams. He is known for his overlapping runs on the right flank to provide cover for his teammates and to add bite to any attacking moves. On 20 April 2012, Danny played for the first team squad for the first time in a friendly against NFL Division 2 side, Katong Football Club and he made his competitive debut on 27 April 2012 in a S-League match against Brunei DPMM FC. On 23 November 2012, it was announced by Woodlands Wellington that he would not be retained for the 2013 season.

name: Danny Coale
description: Daniel Kinsman Coale (June 27, 1988) is an American football wide receiver who is currently a member of the Dallas Cowboys practice squad. He was drafted by the Cowboys in the fifth round of the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at Virginia Tech, where he played wide receiver for the Hokies in addition to punting.

name: Danny Cox (cricketer)
description: Danny Jo Cox (born 30 July 1992) is an English cricketer. Cox is a right-handed batsman who fields occasionally as a wicket-keeper. He was born in Wolverhampton, Staffordshire. While studying for his degree in Mathematics and Sport Science at Loughborough University, Cox made his first-class debut for Loughborough MCCU against Northamptonshire in 2011. He made a further first-class appearance in 2011, against Leicestershire. His two first-class appearances have so far seen him score 32 runs at an average of 8.00, with a high score of 18.

name: Danny Crerand
description: Daniel "Danny" Crerand (born 5 May 1969) is an English former professional footballer who played as a midfielder.

name: Danny Crossman
description: Danny Crossman (born January 17, 1967 in El Paso, Texas) is an American football coach who is currently the special teams coordinator for the Buffalo Bills of the National Football League. Previously, he served in the same capacity for the Carolina Panthers (2007–2009).

name: Danny Curzon
description: Danny Curzon (born May 19, 1987 in Phoenix, Arizona) is an American pair skater who competed with partner Chelsi Guillen.

name: Danny Desriveaux
description: Danny Desriveaux (born December 20, 1981, in Laval, Quebec) is a former professional Canadian football slotback in the Canadian Football League for the Montreal Alouettes and the Toronto Argonauts. He was drafted by the Alouettes in the sixth round of the 2006 CFL Draft. He played college football for the Richmond Spiders. Desriveaux holds two university degrees; a bachelor's degree in finance from the University of Connecticut and an MBA from the University of Richmond.

name: Danny Duffy
description: Daniel Richard Duffy (born December 21, 1988) is an American pitcher in professional baseball. He has pitched in Major League Baseball (MLB) for the Kansas City Royals since 2011.

name: Danny Espinosa
description: Daniel Richard "Danny" Espinosa (born April 25, 1987) is a Major League Baseball Second baseman for the Washington Nationals.

name: Danny Fitzgerald
description: Danny Fitzgerald (1961–2010) was an Irish sportsperson. A dual player at the highest levels, he played hurling and Gaelic football with his local club Claughaun and was a member of the LImerick senior inter-county teams in both codes between 1983 and 1993.

name: Danny Friend
description: Daniel Sebastian Friend (April 18, 1873 – June 1, 1942) was a Major League Baseball pitcher who pitched for the Chicago Colts (later renamed the Chicago Cubs) of the National League from 1895 through 1898.

name: Danny Gardiner
description: Robert B. Daniel "Danny" Gardiner is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1960s, playing at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Wigan, as a Prop, or Second-row, i.e. number 8 or 10, or, 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums.

name: Danny Green (footballer born 1990)
description: Daniel "Danny" Joe Green (born 4 August 1990) is an English footballer who plays for Bishop's Stortford as a midfielder.

name: Danny Groves
description: Daniel Richard "Danny" Groves (born 10 December 1990) is an English footballer. He is a midfielder or right back.

name: Danny Handling
description: Danny Handling (born 6 February 1994) is a Scottish footballer, who currently plays for Scottish Premier League club Hibernian. Handling has also previously played for Berwick Rangers.

name: Danny Hoesen
description: Daniel "Danny" Hoesen (born 15 January 1991 in Heerlen) is a Dutch footballer to a Moroccan father and a Dutch mother who plays as a striker for AFC Ajax in the Dutch Eredivisie.

name: Danny Hudson
description: Danny Hudson (born 25 June 1979) is an English footballer who played in The Football League for Rotherham United. He also played non-League football for Doncaster Rovers, Halifax Town and Belper Town.

name: Danny Hultzen
description: Daniel Alexander Hultzen (born November 28, 1989 in Bethesda, Maryland) is an American professional baseball pitcher in the Seattle Mariners organization. Hultzen was drafted and selected second overall by the Seattle Mariners in the 2011 MLB draft.

name: Danny Hurcombe
description: Daniel "Danny" Hurcombe was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1910s and '20s, playing club level rugby union (RU) for Talywain RFC, and playing representative level rugby league (RL) for Great Britain, and Wales, and at club level for Wigan, as a Wing, Centre, Stand-off/Five-eighth, or Scrum-half/Halfback, i.e. number 2 or 5, 3 or 4, 6, or 7.

name: Danny Jones (rugby league)
description: Danny Jones (born 6 March 1986 in Halifax) is a professional rugby league footballer, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Halifax, and Keighley Cougars, as a Stand-off/Five-eighth, or Scrum-half/Halfback.

name: Danny Kedwell
description: Daniel Trevor Kedwell is an English footballer who plays as a forward for Gillingham in Football League Two.

name: Danny Kerrigan
description: Daniel "Danny" Anthony Kerrigan (born 4 July 1982) is an English semi-professional footballer who plays as a defender or midfielder. He played in the Football League with Southend United, before dropping into non-League football.

name: Danny Kravitz
description: Daniel Kravitz (born December 21, 1930) is a retired American professional baseball player. He was a catcher in Major League Baseball from 1956–60 for the Pittsburgh Pirates and Kansas City Athletics. Kravitz batted left-handed, threw right-handed, stood 5 feet 11 inches tall and weighed 195 pounds . Kravitz was a reserve catcher for the Pirates from 1956 through 1959, and he also began the 1960 season with the Bucs, but was traded to the Athletics on June 1, 1960 and therefore was not with the Pirates during the 1960 World Series. With the Athletics the remainder of the season, Kravitz was part of a catching platoon with Pete Daley and received the most playing time of his career, batting .234 with 4 home runs and 14 runs batted in in 175 at-bats. After the 1960 season, his contract was sold to the Cincinnati Reds. However, he never again played in the major leagues. Kravitz played three more seasons in the minor leagues before retiring. His first major league home run occurred on May 11, 1956 in the bottom of the ninth inning with the bases loaded and the Pirates trailing the Philadelphia Phillies 5-2. Kravitz' walk-off grand slam gave the Pirates a 6-5 win.

name: Danny Kristo
description: Danny Kristo (born June 18, 1990) is an American ice hockey player with the North Dakota Fighting Sioux men's ice hockey which competes in the WCHA. He was selected by the Montreal Canadiens in the 2nd round (56th overall) of the 2008 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Danny Lecours
description: Danny Lecours (born October 5, 1955) is a Canadian retired professional ice hockey player. Born in 1955 in Princeville, Quebec, Lecours played three seasons in the Quebec Major Junior Hockey League with the Quebec Remparts and Chicoutimi Saguenéens. Lecours also played two seasons in the semi-pro USHL (with the Milwaukee Admirals) before he began his professional career in 1977 with the Milwaukee Admirals of the International Hockey League where over nine seasons he played 554 regular season games and registered 360 goals and 282 assists for 642 points, while earning 345 penalty minutes. Lecours also played 45 playoff games for the Admirals, scoring 16 goals and 15 assists for 31 points, with 27 minutes in penalties.

name: Danny Mayor
description: Daniel John "Danny" Mayor (born 18 October 1990 in Leyland, Lancashire) is an English footballer who currently plays for Sheffield Wednesday, where he plays in midfield as an attacking winger. He came through Preston North End's youth ranks. On 15 December 2008 he was given his first professional two-and-a-half-year contract with fellow youngster, Adam Barton. On 5 March 2009 he joined Tranmere Rovers on a one month loan deal. Tranmere manager Ronnie Moore was reported to say: "He is a hard working winger with the ability to go past people and has a trick up his sleeve. " He was handed his League One début against Northampton Town on 7 March 2009. Mayor made his debut for Preston North End on 16 January 2010 against Bristol City. He came on as a substitute in the 70th minute for Richard Chaplow. Preston lost the match 4–2. It was Darren Ferguson's debut as Preston manager. He was handed his full home debut in a game against Scunthorpe United on 10 April 2010, a game which Preston won 3–2. Danny scored his first League goal for Preston against his old club Tranmere Rovers on 26 September 2011. His next goal came against Hartlepool United, which went on to win the goal of the season for the club's 2011/12 season. Mayor allegedly told manager Graham Westley before the 2012/13 season that he would like to play at a higher level, with fellow team-mate Jamie Proctor making the same statement, despite the pair both being contracted to the club and part of the manager's plans. He joined Southend United on an initial 28 day loan deal on Tuesday 12 February 2013, going straight into the first team to play against Cheltenham Town that night. Mayor played 5 games before returning to Sheffield Wednesday.

name: Danny McCray
description: Danny DeWayne McCray (born March 3, 1988) is an American football defensive back for the Dallas Cowboys of the National Football League. He was signed by the Cowboys as an undrafted free agent in 2010. He played college football at LSU.

name: Danny Morris
description: Danny Eugene Morris (born Sept 25, 1949 at Toledo, Ohio) is a retired American professional baseball player, a left-handed pitcher who appeared in six Major League games for the 1968–1969 Minnesota Twins. He stood 5 feet 7 inches tall and weighed 175 pounds during his active career. He was a top prospect with a 98 mph fastball until an arm injury ended his career. Morris played seven seasons (1966–1972) of professional baseball, all in the Twins' organization. He twice won 16 games in the minor leagues, going 16–8 with an earned run average of 2.16 with the Wisconsin Rapids Twins of the Class A Midwest League in 1966, and 16–15 (3.94) with the Denver Bears of the Triple-A Pacific Coast League in 1968. After the latter season, he received his first trial with the 1968 Twins, working in three September games, two as a starting pitcher, and losing his only decision in a September 18, 1968, starting assignment against the California Angels. Morris spent most of 1969 with Denver, but was recalled by the Twins in June and appeared in three more games. In his only start for the 1969 Twins, he again faced the Angels and again absorbed the defeat, giving up two earned runs and three hits in three innings of work. As a Major Leaguer, Morris worked in 16 complete innings, allowing 16 hits and nine runs (five earned), with three bases on balls and twenty seven strikeouts.

name: Danny Mrwanda
description: Danny Mrwanda (born 6 April 1983) is a Tanzanian international footballer who plays as a striker for Vietnamese club Hoàng Anh Gia Lai.

name: Danny Muller
description: Daniël "Danny" Muller (born 11 August 1969) is a Dutch former footballer who played as a midfielder. During a 12-year professional career he amassed Eredivisie totals of 118 games and 18 goals, over the course of six seasons. He also played in Spain and Belgium.

name: Danny Murphy (catcher)
description: Daniel Joseph Murphy (1864–1915) was a professional baseball catcher. He played part of one season in Major League Baseball for the New York Giants of the National League in 1892. In 8 games with the Giants, he had a .115 batting average.

name: Danny Newall
description: Danny Newall was a Welsh professional footballer. A wing half, he progressed through the youth team at Newport County making his first team debut in 1938. He went on to make 233 appearances for Newport scoring 4 goals between 1938 and 1955.

name: Danny Nicklas
description: Danny Nicklas is an English rugby league player for Hull in the European Super League competition. He plays as a stand-off.

name: Danny Payne
description: Danny Payne was an American soccer midfielder who spent six seasons in the American Soccer League and one in the North American Soccer League.

name: Danny Perez
description: Danny Perez is a former Major League Baseball outfielder. Perez was drafted by the Milwaukee Brewers in the twenty-first round of the 1992 Major League Baseball Draft. He played at the Major League level with the team in 1996. Perez played at the collegiate level at Oklahoma State University-Stillwater.

name: Danny Perez Ramírez
description: Danny Perez (born January 4, 1977 in Ventura County, California) is a professional Mexican-American boxer in the Light Middleweight division. He's the former NABF Welterweight, USBA, and WBO NABO Light Middleweight . He holds wins over contender Julio César García, the 2006 winner of ESPN's The Contender Grady Brewer, and former IBA Middleweight Champion Jose Luis Zertuche.

name: Danny Pilkington
description: Daniel Luke "Danny" Pilkington (born 25 May 1990) is an English footballer who plays for Kidderminster Harriers as a winger. He formerly played for Atherton Collieries, Kendal Town, Chorley, Stockport County and York City.

name: Danny Rose (footballer born 1988)
description: Daniel Stephen "Danny" Rose (born 21 February 1988) is an English footballer who plays as a midfielder for Conference National champions Fleetwood Town. He also captained the England C team in 2012. A former captain of Manchester United Reserves, he joined Oxford United in 2007 following a four-month loan spell. He switched to Newport County the following year, and helped Newport to the Conference South title in 2009–10. He was sold to Fleetwood Town in January 2012, and helped the club to the Conference National title in 2011–12.

name: Danny Schell
description: Clyde Daniel Schell (December 26, 1927 – May 11, 1972) was an outfielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Philadelphia Phillies.

name: Danny Schreurs
description: Danny Schreurs (born 28 August 1987), is a Dutch footballer who currently plays as a forward for Dutch Eerste Divisie club MVV Maastricht. He has by commentators been dubbed as Messi Schreurs, because of his pace, good ball control and ability to score goals.

name: Danny Steel
description: Daniel 'Danny' Steel (born May 2, 1884 in Newmilns–died 1931) was a Scottish professional footballer who played for clubs including Airdrieonians, Rangers, Tottenham Hotspur, Third Lanark and Clapton Orient.

name: Danny Steele
description: Danny Steele is an English footballer who played in The Football League as a defender.

name: Danny Sutcliffe
description: Danny Sutcliffe (born 24 February 1992) is a current senior hurler with Dublin and St. Judes. Sutcliffe was part of the Dublin minor football team in 2009 whom he won a Leinster title.

name: Danny Thomson
description: Danny Thomson (born 24 February 1991 in Edinburgh) is a Scottish footballer who last played for Heart of Midlothian, as a midfielder. He has also played for Clyde and Raith Rovers on loan.

name: Danny Trainor
description: Danny Trainor (12 July 1944 – 10 August 1974) was a Northern Irish international footballer.

name: Danny Trevathan
description: Danny Trevathan (born March 24, 1990) is an American football linebacker for the Denver Broncos of the National Football League (NFL). He was named an All-American by College Football News in 2010 as well as first team all-Southeastern Conference. Following the 2010 season, Trevathan completed the 2011 NFL Draft evaluation process but chose to return to Kentucky for his final season.

name: Danny Vaughn (soccer)
description: Danny Vaughn is a retired American soccer player who played professionally in the North American Soccer League. In 1978, Vaughn signed with the Detroit Express of the North American Soccer League. He remained with the Express through the 1979-1980 indoor season before moving to the Memphis Rogues for the 1980 outdoor season. In 1981, the team came under new ownership which moved it to Calgary, Canada and renamed it the Boomers. In the fall of 1981, Vaughn signed as a free agent with the Jacksonville Tea Men. He is a member of the Tacoma-Pierce County Sports Hall of Fame.

name: Danny Verity
description: Daniel Richard Verity (born 19 April 1980) is an English professional footballer who plays as a central defender.

name: Danny Wagner
description: Daniel Earnest "Danny" Wagner (August 1, 1922 – December 27, 1997) was an American guard who played in the National Basketball Association. He played with the Sheboygan Red Skins during the 1949-50 NBA season. Wagner had also played in the National Basketball League.

name: Danny Walsh (footballer)
description: Danny Walsh is a former football (soccer) player who represented Australia seven times.

name: Danny Warden
description: Daniel Warden (born 11 April 1973 in Stepney) is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League, as a midfielder.

name: Danny Watkins
description: Danny William Watkins (born November 6, 1984) is a Canadian offensive guard for the Philadelphia Eagles of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted by the Eagles in the first round (23rd overall) of the 2011 NFL Draft. He was drafted fourth overall by the BC Lions of the Canadian Football League in the 2010 CFL Draft, but played out his last year at Baylor University, the 2010 season.

name: Danny Wimprine
description: Daniel "Danny" Wimprine (born August 6, 1981) is a former American football quarterback who was most notably a member of the New Orleans VooDoo of the Arena Football League.

name: Danny Wofford
description: Danny Wofford was a jobber in the heavyweight division for 20 years beginning in 1987 and retiring in 2007. He was incredibly short for a heavyweight at 5'7" and had an incredible chin only being knocked out 23 times in his 102 loss career. He was used to stretch out young fighters moving up in the heavyweight ranks and provide a good warm up for veteran fighters between big fights. He fought such contenders and champions as Phil Jackson, Bruce Seldon, Joe Hipp, Orlin Norris, Alex Stewart, Oliver McCall, Michael Dokes, James "Bonecrusher" Smith, Pinklon Thomas, Michael Bentt, Shannon Briggs, Trevor Berbick, Andrew Maynard, Michael Grant, James Warring, Peter McNeeley, Corey Sanders, Cedric Boswell, Courage Tshabalala, Robert Daniels, Maurice Harris, Ezra Sellers, Vaughn Bean, Alonzo Butler, Tim Witherspoon, Mitch Green, and Tony Tubbs http://boxrec. com/list_bouts. php?human_id=1965&cat=boxer. Wofford had an incredible heart and his record reflects that of an incredibly undersized fighter in an era of super sized heavyweights.

name: Danny aus den Birken
description: Danny aus den Birken (born February 15, 1985) is a German professional ice hockey goaltender. He is currently playing for Kölner Haie in the Deutsche Eishockey Liga (DEL).

name: Danta Whitaker
description: Danta Whitaker (born March 14, 1964 in Atlanta, Georgia) is a former professional American football tight end. He was drafted by the New York Giants in the seventh round of the 1988 NFL Draft. He played college football at Mississippi Valley State. Whitaker has also played for the Kansas City Chiefs, San Antonio Riders, Minnesota Vikings and Chicago Bears.

name: Dante Stipica
description: Dante Stipica (born 30 May 1991) is a Croatian football goalkeeper, currently playing for Primorac 1929 in the Druga HNL.

name: Danwel Demas
description: Danwel Demas (born 15 October 1981) is a South African rugby union player. He previously played for Italian club Aironi in the Pro 12, and for the Bulls and Cheetahs in Super Rugby. He represented South Africa in sevens, in 2003 and from 2005 to 2007. In 2012 he joined the Pumas and currently represents them in the Vodacom Cup and the Currie Cup competitions. Demas also represented the Emerging Springboks from 2006 to 2009.

name: Dany Haddad
description: Dany Haddad (born 16 September 1960) is a Lebanese fencer. He competed at the 1980 and 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Danza Hyatt
description: Danza Pacino Hyatt (born 17 March 1983) is a Jamaican cricketer. A right-hand batsman and occasional medium pace bowler, Hyatt made his first-class cricket debut for West Indies B against Kenya in January 2004. He made his One Day International debut for the West Indies against India at Sir Vivian Richards Stadium in Antigua and Barbuda on 11 May 2011. Hyatt was selected as part of the West Indies cricket team to tour England in 2011.

name: Daoyod Dara
description: Daoyod Dara, (born February 9, 1954 in Phitsanulok) is a Famous Thai - Vietnamese football player and former Thailand national team player. He has played for national team since 1975-1986. Dara played for Thailand in qualifying matches for the 1982 FIFA World Cup.

name: Darío Amaral
description: Darío Amaral (born 23 May 1932) is a Brazilian fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1952 and 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Darío Delgado (footballer born 1969)
description: This article is about the Uruguayan football player. For the Costa Rican football player of the same name, see Darío Delgado (Costa Rica). Ruben Darío Delgado (born December 3, 1969 in Durazno) is a former Uruguayan footballer.

name: Darío Delgado (footballer born 1985)
description: This article is about the Costa Rican football player. For the Uruguayan football player of the same name, see Darío Delgado (footballer born 1969). Dario Delgado{{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=|size=|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}}Personal informationFull nameDario Delgado MoraDate of birth (1985-12-14) December 14, 1985 (age 27)Place of birthCosta RicaHeight6 ft 0 in Playing positionDefenderClub informationCurrent clubGuangdong Sunray CaveNumber5Youth career1996–2007SaprissaSenior career*YearsTeamApps(Gls)2007–Puntarenas61(6)2010→ Chivas USA (loan)21(0)2011-→ Guangdong Sunray Cave(loan)7(0)National team2009–Costa Rica15(0)* Senior club appearances and goals counted for the domestic league only and correct as of October 30, 2011. † Appearances (Goals). ‡ National team caps and goals correct as of August 14, 2010 Dario Delgado Mora (born December 14, 1985) is a Costa Rican footballer who currently plays for Guangdong Sunray Cave F.C. in the China League One.

name: Darío Figueroa
description: Darío Damián Figueroa is an Argentine football midfielder who plays for Caracas FC of Venezuela.

name: Darío Muchotrigo
description: Darío Muchotrigo (born 17 December 1970 in Lima) is a former Peruvian footballer.

name: Darío Villalba
description: Darío Villalba Flores (born February 22, 1939 in San Sebastián) is a Spanish figure skater. He represented Spain at the 1956 Winter Olympics were he placed 14th at the age of 16.

name: Darby Loudon
description: Darby Briton Loudon (12 March 1897 – c. 1963) was a New Zealand born rugby union player, a flanker who made sixteen representative appearances for the New South Wales state team in the 1920s. Four of the these matches have since been decreed as Test matches by the Australian Rugby Union and Loudon, who led the side in one such match in 1922, was therefore a captain of the Australian national team.

name: Darcy Brown
description: Darcy Brown (born May 29, 1986 in Mississauga, Ontario) is a professional Canadian football fullback and tight end for the Edmonton Eskimos of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted by the Hamilton Tiger-Cats in the first round of the 2009 CFL Draft. He played CIS football for the Saint Mary's Huskies.

name: Darcy Kuemper
description: Darcy Kuemper (also spelled Kümper) (born May 5, 1990) is a German-Canadian ice hockey goaltender who currently plays for the Houston Aeros of the American Hockey League (AHL) as a prospects for the Minnesota Wild of the NHL. He was selected by the Wild in the 6th round (161st overall) of the 2009 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Darcy Lussick
description: Darcy Lussick is an Australian rugby league player who currently plays for the Parramatta Eels. He previously played for the Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles and made his debut game in Round 14 2011 against the North Queensland Cowboys, a game which the Sea Eagles ran out easy 24-4 winners at Brookvale Oval against the previously in-form Cowboys. Lussick played his junior football for the Beacon Hill Bears. On June 14 2012, Lussick signed a 3-year deal with the Parramatta Eels worth 270K a year.

name: Darcy Robinson
description: Darcy Robinson (May 3, 1981 – September 27, 2007) was an Italian/Canadian professional ice hockey defenseman who was a former Pittsburgh Penguins draft pick. Robinson split five seasons between the AHL and ECHL, playing for both Pittsburgh Penguins' affiliates in Wilkes-Barre and Wheeling before joining HC Asiago in 2005.

name: Dardan Rexhepi
description: Dardan Rexhepi is a Swedish footballer playing for Malmö FF in Allsvenskan as a striker. He is of Kosovan-Albanian origin.

name: Daren Foster
description: Daren Joseph Foster (born 14 March 1966) played first-class and List A cricket for Somerset and Glamorgan between 1986 and 1993. He was born in Tottenham, London.

name: Daren Machesney
description: Daren Machesney (born December 13, 1986) is a Canadian professional ice hockey goaltender who is currently playing for the Braehead Clan in the Elite Ice Hockey League (ECHL). He was selected by the Washington Capitals in the 5th round (143rd overall) of the 2005 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Daria Kasperska
description: Daria Kasperska is a Polish football midfielder currently playing for Pogoń Szczecin in the Ekstraliga. She previously played for Czarni Sosnowiec, Gol Częstochowa and Unia Racibórz, playing the Champions League with Unia. She has been a member of the Polish national team.

name: Daria Popova
description: Daria Popova is a Russian pair skater who currently represents France with partner Bruno Massot. Together, they are the 2012 French national champions.

name: Darimosuvito Tokijan
description: Darimosuvito Tokijan is a Singaporean football Midfielder who played for Singapore in the 1984 Asian Cup. He also played for Jurong Town.

name: Darin Andonov
description: Darin Georgiev Andonov (Bulgarian: Дарин Георгиев Андонов) (born 2 August 1986) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Kaliakra Kavarna as a defender.

name: Dario Baccin
description: Dario Baccin (born 27 August 1976) is a former Italian footballer.

name: Dario Dolci
description: Dario Dolci (born March 5, 1947 in Marostica) is a retired Italian professional football player. He played 6 seasons (105 games, no goals) in the Serie A for Varese F.C. , A.C. Milan and Ternana Calcio.

name: Dario Dussin
description: Dario Dussin (born 13 April 1989 Switzerland) is a Swiss professional footballer who currently plays as a defender for FC Biel-Bienne in the Swiss Challenge League.

name: Dario Marinović
description: Dario Marinović (born 24 May 1990), is a Croatian futsal player who plays for MNK Split Brodosplit Inženjering and the Croatia national futsal team.

name: Dario Rugašević
description: Dario Rugašević (born 29 January 1991 in Vinkovci) is a Croatian football player who plays as defender, currently with Cibalia in Prva HNL. He is a Croatia youth international having earned caps with all of the youth teams beginning with the Croatia under-16 team. A product of Cibalia academy, Rugašević joined the first team in the 2009–10 season and had his professional debut on 25 July 2009 in a league match against NK Zadar, and went on to appear in 17 matches for the club in his first professional season.

name: Dario Simion
description: Dario Simion (born May 22, 1994) is a Swiss professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing for the HC Lugano of Switzerland's National League A. Simion participated at the 2012 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships as a member of the Switzerland men's national junior ice hockey team.

name: Darius Florin Brăguși
description: Darius Florin Brăguși (born June 18, 1993) is a Romanian professional tennis player playing on the ITF Men's Circuit and current member of the Romania Davis Cup Team. On January 30, 2012, he reached his highest ATP singles ranking of 936.

name: Darius Hill
description: Darius E. Hill (born August 26, 1985 in St. Charles, Missouri) is an American football tight end who is currently a free agent. He was signed by the Cincinnati Bengals as an undrafted free agent in 2009. He played college football at Ball State.

name: Darius Miller
description: Darius Miller (born March 21, 1990) is an American professional basketball player who currently plays for the New Orleans Hornets of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He played at the University of Kentucky and finished his senior season by winning the 2012 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament on the 2011–12 Kentucky Wildcats team. Miller graduated from Mason County High School in 2008 after leading the school to a state championship. After his senior season in high school, Miller was named the KHSAA's men's basketball player of the year, commonly known as "Kentucky Mr. Basketball". Following Kentucky's 2012 national championship win Miller was chosen to present a commemorative Kentucky jersey and championship ring to President Barack Obama during the team's visit to the White House on May 4, 2012. During the visit, Obama noted that Miller is the only player from Kentucky to have been named Kentucky's "Mr. Basketball" (high school player of the year in the state), win a KHSAA state championship (Mason County High School) and claim an NCAA title with the University of Kentucky. Miller finished his college career having played more games for the University of Kentucky than any other player. The Wildcats' championship game and Miller's last collegiate match, was his 152nd appearance for the team, surpassing Wayne Turner's previous record of 151 games. The Hornets selected Miller in the second round of the 2012 NBA Draft. On December 31, 2012, Miller was assigned to the Iowa Energy. He was recalled on January 27, 2013.

name: Dariush Mikaeili
description: Asadollah Mikaeili, better known as Dariush Mikaeili is an is an Iranian footballer who plays for Naft Tehran F.C. in the Iranian Premier League.

name: Dariusz Cudny
description: Dariusz Cudny (born 27 February 1983 in Zielona Góra) is a Polish footballer.

name: Dariusz Góral
description: Dariusz Góral (born April 20, 1991 in Wrocław) is a Polish footballer who currently plays for Śląsk Wrocław.

name: Dariusz Koseła
description: Dariusz Koseła (born February 12, 1970 in Zabrze) is a retired Polish football player.

name: Dariusz Sztylka
description: Dariusz Sztylka (born May 28, 1978 in Wrocław) is a retired Polish footballer who spent the most of his career at Śląsk Wrocław. He played as a midfielder.

name: Darko Brašanac
description: Darko Brašanac is a Serbian football midfielder who plays for SuperLiga club Partizan.

name: Darko Brljak
description: Darko Brljak (born 23 December 1984) is a Slovenian football goalkeeper, who plays for Egri FC in Hungary.

name: Darko Marić
description: Darko Marić (born 2 September 1975 in Bor) is a retired Serbian football player who last played as a forward for FC Braşov. On 8 May 2005 he suffered a head injury during the First Division match between FC Braşov and FC Argeş, when he collided with Marius Radu, needing to be transported by ambulance to the hospital. The collision was however involuntary. After the retirement as a professional player, he opened up a football agency in Serbia. He is also director of BSK Borča.

name: Darko Mavrak
description: Darko Mavrak (born 19 January 1969) is a former Yugoslav footballer. Mavrak began his career with FK Velež Mostar in the Yugoslav First League. He moved to Swedish sides Djurgårdens IF and IFK Norrköping because of the War in Yugoslavia. He had a brief spell with Panachaiki F.C. in the Greek Super League. Mavrak finished his career with Walsall F.C. in England and Hapoel Tzafririm Holon F.C. in Israel.

name: Darko Vujović
description: Darko Vujović (born 21 December 1962 in Nikšić) is a former Montenegrin football player.

name: Darnell King
description: Darnell King (born September 23, 1990 in Tampa, Florida) is an American forward who currently plays for the Fort Lauderdale Strikers of the North American Soccer League.

name: Darnell Lazare
description: Darnell Lazare (born January 29, 1985) is an American professional basketball player who currently plays for the Sydney Kings of the National Basketball League (NBL).

name: Daron Kirkreit
description: Daron Jon Kirkreit is a retired American professional baseball pitcher. He pitched for the United States national baseball team in the 1992 Summer Olympics, and played Minor League Baseball from 1993 to 2001. Kirkreit was drafted in the first round, the 11th pick, of the 1993 Major League Baseball (MLB) Draft by the Cleveland Indians. He played in the Indians, Milwaukee Brewers, Kansas City Royals, Seattle Mariners, and the Anaheim Angels minor league systems until his retirement after the 2001 season.

name: Darragh Fives
description: Darragh Fives is an Irish sportsperson. He plays hurling with his local club Tourin and has been a member of the Waterford senior inter-county team since 2011.

name: Darrell Austin
description: Kenneth Darrell Austin (born November 16, 1951 in Union, South Carolina) is a former professional American football offensive lineman in the National Football League. He was drafted by the Denver Broncos in the 16th round (404th overall) in the 1974 NFL draft. He played eight seasons for the New York Jets and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.

name: Darrell Bryant
description: Darrell Bryant is a retired NASCAR Winston Cup Series driver whose claim to fame was his two "top ten" finishes in addition to racing 2389 laps - for a distance of 2,489.9 miles . Bryant has driver for Chevrolet, Dodge, Oldsmobile, and Mercury during his driving career.

name: Darrell Colbert
description: Darrell Ray Colbert (born November 16, 1964) is a former American professional football player who was a wide receiver in the National Football League (NFL) and the World League of American Football (WLAF). He played for the Kansas City Chiefs of the NFL, and the San Antonio Riders of the WLAF. Colbert played collegiately at Texas Southern University.

name: Darrell Hay
description: Darrell Hay (born April 2, 1980) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman. He was selected by the Vancouver Canucks in the 9th round (271st overall) of the 1999 NHL Entry Draft. Darrell is the son of Don Hay, who is the coach of the Vancouver Giants of the WHL. Hay played with BK Mladá Boleslav in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season.

name: Darrell Stuckey
description: Darrell Stuckey, Jr. (born June 16, 1987) is an American football safety who currently plays for the San Diego Chargers. He attended University of Kansas throughout his college career. Stuckey was an All-Big 12 First Team selection in 2008 and was considered one of the top safeties available in the 2010 NFL Draft.

name: Darrell Woodard
description: Darrell Lee Woodard (born December 10, 1956) is a former American professional baseball player. He played part of one season in Major League Baseball for the Oakland Athletics during the 1978 season. A second baseman for most of his professional career, he was primarily used by Oakland as a pinch runner, appearing in that capacity in 22 of his 33 games played.

name: Darren Allinson
description: Darren Allinson (born 13 November 1987), a Welsh professional rugby union player. Allinson is currently signed to London Irish in the Aviva Premiership and plays at scrum half.

name: Darren Anderson
description: Darren Anderson is a former professional American football player who played defensive back for seven seasons for the New England Patriots, Tampa Bay Buccaneers, Kansas City Chiefs, and Atlanta Falcons. Married to Robin Anderson, maiden name Thomas, since the 1990s.

name: Darren Carter (rugby league)
description: Darren Carter (born 8 January 1972) is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1990s and 2000s playing at club level for Normanton, Wakefield Trinity, Barrow (twice), Workington Town, and Keighley Cougars.

name: Darren Chiacchia
description: Darren Chiacchia (born 18 September 1964 in Buffalo, New York) is an American equestrian. He won a bronze medal in team eventing at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, together with Kimberly Severson, John Williams, Amy Tryon and Julie Richards. He also competed in individual eventing, placing 12th.

name: Darren Clarke (Gaelic footballer)
description: Darren Clarke is an Irish sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club St. Mary's before joining Dublin side St Sylvesters. He has been a member of the Louth senior inter-county team since 2004. He was part of the team who lined out in the Tommy Murphy Cup in 2006.

name: Darren Cole
description: Darren Cole (born 3 January 1992) is a Scottish footballer who plays as a right back for Scottish Third Division club Rangers.

name: Darren Collins (athlete)
description: Darren Collins is a Paralympic athletics competitor from Australia. He won a pair of bronze medals at the 1992 Barcelona Games in the Men's 200 m B1 event and the Men's 400 m B1 event.

name: Darren Croft
description: Darren Croft (born 5 September 1981) is an Australian ice hockey player currently playing for the Melbourne Ice in the Australian Ice Hockey League.

name: Darren Crowley
description: Darren Crowley is an Irish sportsperson. He plays hurling with his local club Bandon and has been a member of the Cork senior inter-county team since 2009 when he was called up due to the 2008-2009 Cork players strike.

name: Darren Davis (footballer)
description: Darren Davis is a former professional footballer who played in The Football League for Maidstone United, Notts County, Lincoln City and Scarborough. In June 2002 he was appointed manager of Gedling Town. He is currently Assistant Manager of the Notts County's Centre of Excellence.

name: Darren Dinneen
description: Darren Dinneen is a hurler from County Kerry. He plays hurling with Kerry and St. Brendan's, Ardfert and also plays football with Ardfert. In 2011 he helped Kerry win their first Christy Ring Cup when they beat Wicklow in the final. With Ardfert he was part of the teams that won Kerry Junior Football Championship, Munster Junior Club Football Championship and All-Ireland Junior Club Football Championship, he has also won Kerry Intermediate Football Championship, Munster Intermediate Club Football Championship and All-Ireland Intermediate Club Football Championship. He won a Kerry U21 Hurling Championship with St. Brendan's, Ardfert in 2005. References http://hoganstand. com/kerry/ArticleForm. aspx?ID=148298

name: Darren Durdle
description: Darren Durdle (born August 15, 1963) is a retired Canadian-born professional ice hockey player. Durdle was born in Gimli, Manitoba; although Durdle also holds British citizenship. Durdle began his career playing in Canada's major junior Western Hockey League's 1982–83 season. During that season he played for both the Lethbridge Broncos and the Prince Albert Raiders. During the summer of 1985, Durdle received a scholarship for Brandon University. As a result he played for the Canadian interuniversity ice hockey team the Brandon Bobcats. Durdle played there throughout the 1985–86, 1986–87 and 1987–88 seasons. After completing his studies, Durdle moved to the United Kingdom where he played for the Nottingham Panthers during the British Premier Division's 1988–89 season. Durdle continued spent eight seasons playing for various British ice hockey teams until he signed for the Berlin based ice hockey team the Berlin Polar Bears. Following three season in Germany, Durdle finally returned to the UK where he played for the Great British ice hockey team, and then for the Welsh team the Cardiff Devils.

name: Darren Freeman
description: Darren Freeman (born 22 August 1973) is an English retired professional footballer who played as a winger. Freeman made over 130 appearances in the Football League between 1995 and 2002.

name: Darren Fritz
description: Darren Fritz (born 13 March 1969) is an Australian professional rugby league footballer of the 1980s and '90s, playing at representative level for Queensland, and at club level for Canberra Raiders, Wakefield Trinity, Illawarra Steelers, North Sydney Bears, North Sydney Bears and Western Suburbs Magpies, as a Prop, or Second-row, i.e. number 8 or 10, or, 11 or 12.

name: Darren Gardiner
description: Darren Gardiner (born 19 November 1969) is an Australian Paralympic powerlifter. He has won two Paralympic silver medals in the Men's Over 100 kg powerlifting event. He did not medal at the 2012 Games.

name: Darren Harland
description: Darren Simon Harland is an English cricketer. Harland is a right-handed batsman. Harland represented the Yorkshire Cricket Board in List A cricket.
