He has won medals on the track over 10,000 metres, taking bronze at the 2005 South American Championships in Athletics and silver at the 2008 CAC Championships. In October 2011, he won the silver medal in the men's marathon event at the 2011 Pan American Games in Guadalajara, Mexico, clocking a total time of 2:17:13, behind Brazil's Solonei Silva and before the bronze winner, fellow Colombian Juan Carlos Cardona . He also won the bronze medal in the men's marathon event at the 2003 Pan American Games in Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic, clocking a total time of 2:21.48, behind Brazil's Vanderlei de Lima and Canada's Bruce Deacon . He was the first South American home at the 2011 Bogota Half Marathon, taking fourth place behind East African opposition.

name: Diego Cuéllar
description: Diego Andrés Cuéllar Duarte (born August 10, 1990 in San Salvador) is an Salvadoran football goalkeeper who plays for Atlético Marte of El Salvador's Primera División.

name: Diego Drajer
description: Diego Drajer (born 26 March 1974) is an Argentine fencer. He competed in the individual sabre event at the 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: Diego Emilio Silva
description: Diego Emilio Silva Silva (born 17 May 1987 in Montevideo) is a Uruguayan footballer currently playing for Sportivo y Biblioteca Atenas de Río Cuarto in the Torneo Argentino B.

name: Diego Evangelista dos Santos
description: Diego Evangelista dos Santos, Dieguinho (Caarapó, September 29, 1989) is a Brazilian footballer.

name: Diego Fabbrini
description: Diego Fabbrini (born July 31, 1990 in San Giuliano Terme) is an Italian footballer who plays as a second striker for Serie A club Palermo.

name: Diego Gaúcho
description: Diego Gaúcho (born 15 November 1981 in Porto Alegre) is a Brazilian footballer as a defender. He is attached to Moreirense. Previously he played for Gil Vicente F.C. and in the first half of 2011 for the Romanian Liga I team FC Braşov.

name: Diego Giaretta
description: Diego da Silva Giaretta, commonly known as Diego Giaretta (born November 27, 1983), born in Cascavel is a Brazilian footballer who plays for Atlético Clube Goianiense, as left back and center back.

name: Diego González Reyes
description: Diego Ignacio González Reyes (born 16 January 1991) is a Chilean footballer who currently plays for the Chilean Primera División side Unión Temuco as an attacking midfielder.

name: Diego Guerrero
description: Diego Guerrero (born 26 June 1986) is a Venezuelan international footballer who plays for Deportivo Táchira, as a midfielder.

name: Diego Guidi
description: Diego Martín Guidi Pierani (born 17 February 1981) is an Argentine footballer that currently plays for Chilean Primera División club Deportes La Serena as centre back.

name: Diego Inostroza
description: Diego Alfredo Inostroza Mellado is a Chilean footballer, that currently plays for Primera B team Barnechea as striker

name: Diego Israel Martínez
description: Diego Martínez (born August 7, 1993 in Mexico City) is a Mexican footballer who currently plays for the Cruz Azul. He plays as a Midfielder.

name: Diego Lima do Nascimento
description: Diego Lima full name Diego Lima do Nascimento (born 24 April 1986) is a Brazilian footballer. He currently plays as goalkeeper for Santa Cruz.

name: Diego Magdaleno
description: Diego Armando Magdaleno (born October 28, 1986) is an undefeated Mexican-American boxer in the Super Featherweight division and is the current NABF Super Featherweight Champion. He's also the brother of undefeated boxer Jesús Magdaleno. Diego has been featured in the top ten in Ring Magazine's ratings for junior lightweight.

name: Diego Manzoni
description: Diego Manzoni (born 4 August 1990) is an Italian footballer who plays for Serie A club Genoa.

name: Diego Martín Rodríguez
description: Diego Martín Rodríguez Berrini (born 4 September 1989 in Montevideo), commonly known as Diego Rodríguez, is a Uruguayan footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Defensor Sporting. He is nicknamed "Toro", for his fearsome ability at the midfield.

name: Diego Martins da Silva
description: Diego Martins da Costa e Silva (born 3 October 1989 in Barcelos), simply Diego, is a Portuguese footballer who plays for F.C. Famalicão as a goalkeeper.

name: Diego Moyano
description: Diego Moyano (born 14 March 1975) is a former professional tennis player from Argentina.

name: Diego Opazo
description: Diego Alexi Opazo González (born 2 February 1991), is a Chilean footballer who plays as Defender for San Marcos de Arica in Chile's Primera División.

name: Diego Osorio
description: Diego Osorio (born 21 July 1970) is a former Colombian footballer.

name: Diego Palomeque
description: Diego Armando Palomeque Echavarría (born 5 December 1993) is a Colombian sprinter. He tied Aldemir da Silva Junior for the 200 metres title at the 2011 South American Junior Championships in Athletics. On 28 April 2012, Palomeque broke the Colombian National Junior Record in the 400 metres with 45.62, thereby also meeting the 'B'-Standard to qualify for the 2012 Summer Olympics. He was initially suspended and later excluded from the games after testing positive for exogenous testosterone.

name: Diego Passarelli
description: Diego Matías Passarelli (born 2 August 1984 in Argentina) is an Argentinan Footballer who currently plays for Alianza F.C..

name: Diego Pizarro
description: Diego Enrique Pizarro Bosio is a Peruvian footballer who plays as a striker or winger for Torneo Descentralizado club Cienciano. He is also the younger brother of Bayern Munich striker Claudio Pizarro.

name: Diego Quintanilla
description: Diego Mauricio Quintanilla Ribadeneira (born February 2, 1991 in Quito) is an Ecuadorian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Virginia. A product of LDU Qutio's youth system, he earned his first senior cap on June 12, 2010 in the clasico capitalino against crosstown-rival Deportivo Quito.

name: Diego Restrepo
description: Diego Restrepo (born February 25, 1988 in Merida, Venezuela), is an American soccer goalkeeper who currently plays for Tampa Bay Rowdies in the North American Soccer League.

name: Diego Rodríguez Telechea
description: Diego Rodríguez (born January 8, 1991 in Montevideo) is a Uruguayan footballer who plays for Atlético Malagueño, as a defender.

name: Diego Rolán
description: Diego Alejandro Rolán Silva (born 24 March 1993 in Montevideo) is a Uruguayan footballer who plays as a striker for Bordeaux and the Uruguay U-20 national team.

name: Diego Sánchez (footballer)
description: Diego Ignacio Sánchez Carvajal (born 8 May 1987) Chilean goalkeeper that currently plays for Unión Española of the Chilean Primera División. Product of Palestino youth ranks, was promoted to the first adult team in 2007, due to the injury of the first-choice keeper Felipe Núñez, having also continuity, challenging the post to Fernando Burgos. Sorpressively, the next season, he abandoned Palestino for join to the Chilean Tercera División A side in that moment, Unión Temuco, being part of the plans of the club's owner Marcelo Salas, the famous Chilean football legend. In January 2009, Sánchez signed for Unión Temuco's rival side Deportes Temuco, playing in the Third division tournament and in the Copa Chile also. The next season, he moved to amateur club Barnechea. His performances in Barnechea made that Chilean Primera División side Unión San Felipe, signed him on replace of Jaime Bravo.

name: Diego Sacoman
description: Diego Alessandro Aparecido Silva Sacomano (born December 15, 1986), aka Diego Sacomano, is a Brazilian footballer, born in Guarulhos, São Paulo, who plays central and left back. He currently plays for Ponte Preta.

name: Diego Seoane
description: Gerardo Diego Seoane (born September 15, 1976) is a former Uruguayan football player who currently plays for Beijing Baxy.

name: Diego Simões
description: Diego de Souza Simões (born 18 January 1991) is a Brazilian footballer. He also holds a Portuguese passport.

name: Diego Terrazas
description: Diego Terrazas (born February 27, 1987 in Santa Cruz de la Sierra) is a Bolivian footballer. He currently plays as a midfielder for the Liga de Fútbol Profesional Boliviano side Oriente Petrolero.

name: Diego Veronelli
description: Diego Veronelli (born 5 December 1979) is a former professional tennis player from Argentina.

name: Diego del Rio
description: Diego del Río (also spelled Diego del Rio) (born 4 September 1972) is a former professional tennis player from Argentina.

name: Dieter Fern
description: Dieter Fern (born 1 December 1944) is a retired German football forward.

name: Dieter Jung
description: Dieter Jung (born 10 October 1940) is a German fencer. He competed at the 1968 and 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Dieter Kotlowski
description: Dieter Kotlowski (born 18 July 1957) is an Austrian fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Dieter Löhr
description: Dieter Löhr (born 15 December 1936) is a German fencer. He represented the Unified Team of Germany at the 1960 Summer Olympics in the team sabre event.

name: Dieter Schmitt
description: Dieter Schmitt (born 3 May 1940) is a German fencer. He represented the Unified Team of Germany at the 1964 Summer Olympics in the individual foil event.

name: Dieter Schneider
description: Dieter Schneider (born 20 February 1959) is a German fencer. He competed in the team sabre events at the 1984 and 1988 Summer Olympics.

name: Dieter Strack
description: Dieter Strack is a retired German professional basketball player who had a nine-year career at LTi Gießen 46ers where plays in the Basketball Bundesliga the highest German basketball division. Overall Gießen got the Cup four times. Strack won the Cup of the Basketball Bundesliga two times. He played 161 professional games for LTi Gießen 46ers and made 740 scores, his average strike rate is tending to 4,60 scores per match. Dieter Stack is known for his dangerous left pitching-hand shoots and his high jumps. He is 1,94 meter tall and played as forward and shooting forward. Today Strack is one of the Gießener legends in the "Gutt Stubb" also known as Sporthalle Gießen-Ost, the home arena of Gießen 46ers. His nickname is "Just Magic" or "The White Black Men", because of his spectacular skills and scheming game play.

name: Dietlof Maré
description: Dietlof Siegfried Maré (2 July 1885 – 14 October 1913) was a South African international rugby union player. Born in Wellington, he attended Huguenot College before playing provincial rugby for Transvaal (now known as the Golden Lions). He made his only Test appearance for South Africa during their 1906–07 tour of Britain, Ireland and France. He played as a forward in the 1st Test of the tour, a 6–0 loss to Scotland at Hampden Park. Despite breaking two fingers after six minutes, he played the entire match. Off the field, he wrote the first handbook on rugby ever to be published in Afrikaans. In 1913, in Pretoria, Maré was killed in a car accident at the age of 28. As a result of the accident his wife used a wheelchair.

name: Dietrich Hecke
description: Dietrich Hecke (born 13 February 1935) is a German fencer. He represented the Unified Team of Germany at the 1964 Summer Olympics in the individual épée event.

name: Dikki John Martinez
description: Dikki John Martinez (born October 6, 1991, in Quezon City) is a Filipino figure skater. He was the 2009 Men's Senior Champion of the Philippine National Figure Skating Championship along with Mericien Venzon who won the Ladie's Division, and the Junior Champion of the Philippines from 2006-2008.

name: Dilaver Güçlü
description: Dilaver Güçlü (born 20 February 1986) is a German–born Turkish footballer who currently plays for Göztepe S.K..

name: Dillon du Preez
description: Dillon du Preez is a South African cricketer. He currently plays for the Eagles and the Bangalore Royal Challengers. He is a right-arm fast bowler and bats right-handed.

name: Dillwyn Thomas
description: Dillwyn Thomas (13 February 1905 – 29 August 1996) was a Welsh cricketer. Thomas was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium-fast. He was born at Neath Abbey, Glamorgan. Thomas made his first-class debut for Glamorgan in 1939 against Essex, where on debut he took his only five wicket haul in first-class cricket, claiming figures of 5/64; this five wicket haul also accounted for all of his first-class wickets. He played a further first-class match for the county, against Yorkshire in the same season at Park Avenue Cricket Ground, Bradford. Thomas died at Neath, Glamorgan on 29 August 1996.

name: Dilshod Sharofetdinov
description: Dilshod Sharofetdinov (born 15 October 1985) is a Uzbekistan footballer currently playing for FC Pakhtakor Tashkent in the Uzbek League. His position is Midfielder.

name: Dilyan Kolev
description: Dilyan Kolev (born 9 November 1988) is a Bulgarian football player who plays for Montenegrin First League team FK Čelik Nikšić.

name: Dimba (footballer born 1992)
description: Marcos Vinícius Gomes de Lima, known as Dimba is a Brazilian footballer who plays for Botafogo-SP, on loan from Santos, as a forward.

name: Dimitar Dimov (footballer)
description: Dimitar Pentchev Dimov (Bulgarian: Димитьр Пенчев Димов) (born 13 December 1937) is a Bulgarian football defender who played for Bulgaria in the 1962 FIFA World Cup. He also played for FC Spartak Plovdiv.

name: Dimitar Georgiev
description: Dimitar Georgiev (born 9 February 1992) is a Bulgarian football forward who currently plays for Botev Vratsa on loan from Litex Lovech.

name: Dimitar Kapinkovski
description: Dimitar Kapinkovski (born 27 May 1975 in Bitola) is a former Macedonian football player.

name: Dimitar Kostov
description: Dimitar Ivanov Kostov (Bulgarian: Димитьр Иванов Костов) (born 26 July 1936) is a Bulgarian football defender who played for Bulgaria in the 1962 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Slavia Sofia.

name: Dimitar Marashliev
description: Dimitar Hristov Marashliev (Bulgarian: Димитьр Xристов Марашлйeв) (born 31 August 1947) is a Bulgarian football forward who played for Bulgaria in the 1970 FIFA World Cup. He also played for PFC CSKA Sofia.

name: Dimitar Pantev
description: Dimitar Pantev (born 18 July 1989) is a Bulgarian footballer, who is currently playing as a goalkeeper for Bulgarian club Vidima-Rakovski Sevlievo.

name: Dimitar Simeonov
description: Dimitar Simeonov (born 7 June 1987 is a Bulgarian football goalkeeper who currently plays for Bdin Vidin.

name: Dimitar Tsenovski
description: Dimitar Georgiev Tsenovski (Bulgarian: Димитър Ценовски; born 4 June 1984) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays for Botev Vratsa as a midfielder.

name: Dimitar Vakavliev
description: Dimitar Vakavliev (born 9 December 1990 in Stara Zagora) is an Bulgarian football player. He currently plays for Lyubimetz 2007 as a defender.

name: Dimitra Panteliadou
description: Dimitra Panteliadou is a Greek football striker currently playing in the Greek Championship for PAOK Thessaloniki, with whom she has played the Champions League. She is a member of the Greek national team, playing the 2004 Summer Olympics.

name: Dimitre Kalkanov
description: Dimitre Ganev Kalkanov (Bulgarian: Димитър Ганев Калканов; born 5 April 1966) is a Bulgarian former professional footballer who played as a defender or defensive midfielder.

name: Dimitri Foulquier
description: Dimitri Foulquier (born 23 March 1993) is a French football player who plays for French club Rennes in Ligue 1. He primarily plays as a right back, but can also be utilized as a wing-back on the same side. Foulquier is a France youth international having represented the nation at under-18 and under-19 level. Born on the mainland in Sarcelles, Foulquier was raised in Capesterre, a commune in the overseas region and department of Guadeloupe. After excelling with local clubs in the commune, he was spotted by Rennes scout Patrick Rampillon and, subsequently, joined the professional club in July 2007. After excelling in the club's academy, Foulquier was awarded the Best Academy Player award for the 2009–10 season. After appearing on the bench in matches during the 2010–11 season, he was promoted to the senior team by manager Frédéric Antonetti for the 2011–12 season. Foulquier was assigned the number 24 shirt and made his professional debut on 2 October 2011 in a league match against Lille. He started the match, but was substituted out after halftime as Rennes were defeated 2–0.

name: Dimitri Nance
description: Dimitri Othello Nance (born February 18, 1988) is an American football running back who is currently a free agent. He was signed by the Atlanta Falcons as an undrafted free agent in 2010. He played college football at Arizona State and also played high school football at Trinity High School in Euless, Texas. Nance has also been a member of the Green Bay Packers.

name: Dimitri Petratos
description: Dimitri Petratos (born 10 November 1992) is an Australian football (soccer) player who plays for Kelantan.

name: Dimitri Poliakov
description: Dimitri Poliakov (born 19 January 1968) is a former professional tennis player from Ukraine.

name: Dimitri Ratnayake
description: Dimitri Eranga Mahen Ratnayake (born 9 March 1990) is a Sri Lankan cricketer. Ratnayake is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm slow. He was born in Kandy, Central Province. Ratnayake was educated at St John's College in South Africa, before coming to England to attend Loughborough University to study for a degree. While at Loughborough University, he made his first-class debut for Loughborough MCCU against Northamptonshire in 2011. He has made two further first-class appearances for Loughborough MCCU in 2011, against Leicestershire and Kent. His three first-class appearances have so far seen him score 104 runs at an average of 17.33, with a high score of 43. With the ball, he has taken a single wicket. Back in Sri Lanka, he is a member of the Bloomfield Cricket and Athletic Club, but is yet to make any senior appearances for the club.

name: Dimitri Tsyganov
description: Dimitri Tsyganov (born February 18, 1989) is a Russian professional ice hockey player. He played with HC Karlovy Vary in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season.

name: Dimitrios Ioannou
description: Dimitrios Ioannou (Greek: Δημήτριος Ιωάννου, 1861–1926) was a senior Greek Army officer who fought in the Macedonian Front during World War I and in the opening stages of the Greco-Turkish War of 1919–1922.

name: Dimitrios Kolovetsios
description: Dimitrios Kolovetsios (Greek: Δημήτρης Κολοβέτσιος; born 16 October 1991) is a Greek professional footballer who plays for PAS Giannina, in the Greek Superleague, as Centre back.

name: Dimitrios Sotiriou
description: Dimitrios Sotiriou (Greek: Δημήτρης Σωτηρίου; born 13 September 1987) is a football goalkeeper who plays for Kalloni F.C. in the Greek Football League.

name: Dimitrios Vergos
description: Dimitrios Vergos (Greek: Δημήτριος Βέργος, Agios Efstratios May 8, 1886 - Alexandria, Egypt January 3, 1956) was a Greek champion in wrestling, weightlifting and shot put.

name: Dimitris Anakoglou
description: Dimitris Anakoglou (Greek: Δημήτρης Ανάκογλου; born 6 September 1991) is a footballer. He currently plays for AEK F.C..

name: Dimitris Diamantis
description: Dimitris Diamantis (Greek: Δημήτρης Διαμάντης; born 11 September 1979) is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Apollon Smyrni F.C. in the Football League 2.

name: Dimitris Froxylias
description: Dimitris Froxylias (born on 28 June 1993 in Larissa, Greece) is a Greek Cypriot football forward who is currently a free agent.

name: Dimitris Hasomeris
description: Dimitrios Hasomeris (born 23 June 1989 in Xanthi) is a Greek professional footballer, who plays for AEL 1964 FC, in the Greek Football League. In July 11, 2011 he signed a 1+3 years contract with the team after a successful season with Football League 2 (Greece) (3rd division) club Anagennisi Epanomi F.C.

name: Dimitris Kolovos
description: Dimitris Kolovos (Greek: Δημήτρης Κολοβός, born 27 April 1993), is a Greek football player currently playing for Panionios in the Greek Superleague. He is seen as one of the most promising players of Panionios and the team reportedly rejected a €250,000 transfer offer from Fiorentina during the January transfer period of 2012. In May 2012, he renewed his contract with the club until 2016.

name: Dimitris Kontodimos
description: Dimitris Kontodimos (Greek: Δημήτρης Κοντοδήμος, born 21 April 1982) is a professional Greek football player, currently playing for Niki Volos.

name: Dimitris Kotsonis
description: Dimitris Kotsonis (born 25 January 1989) is a Greek football player currently playing for Aris Thessaloniki F.C. , in the Superleague Greece,after starting his career in Paniliakos F.C..

name: Dimitris Kourbelis
description: Dimitris Kourbelis (Greek: Δημήτρης Κουρμπέλης, born 2 November 1993) is a professional Greek football player, currently playing for Superleague side Asteras Tripolis.

name: Dimitris Pliagas
description: Dimitrios Pliagas (born 26 March 1985 in Karditsa) is a Greek wing midfielder who play for Kavala FC.

name: Dimitris Souanis
description: Dimitris Souanis (Greek: Δημήτρης Σουάνης; born 17 November 1985) is a Greek footballer who plays for Apollon Limassol in Cyprus. Dimitris Souanis began his professional football career with Panionios F.C. in 2002.

name: Dimmy Franks
description: Dimmy Franks was a professional rugby league footballer of the 1890s and 1900s, playing at club level for Hull.

name: Dimuth Karunaratne
description: Frank Dimuth Madushanka Karunaratne (born 21 April 1988 in Colombo) is a Sri Lankan cricketer. He is a left-handed opening batsman and plays first class cricket for the Sinhalese Sports Club. Karunaratne attended the prestigious St. Joseph's College, Colombo, which has produced a number of Sri Lankan test cricketers such as Chaminda Vaas, Angelo Mathews and Thisara Perera. He was a record-breaking batsman for the school's cricket team. After featuring in Sri Lanka's Under-19 and A squads, he was called into the senior One Day International (ODI) team for the series against England and Scotland in June and July 2011. He played in two matches on the tour, scoring four runs against England in Manchester, and 60 against Scotland in Edinburgh. He was selected in Sri Lanka's Test squad for its tour of South Africa at the end of 2011, although did not play in any of the three Tests. He was recalled into the Test squad for the home Tests against New Zealand during late 2012. He got the opportunity due to Tillakaratne Dilshan being unable to make the XI because of an injury. He debuted in the first Test in that series, in Galle, only to get out for a duck in the first innings. However, he came back strongly in the 2nd innings with an unbeaten half century and hit the winning runs as well. Following the New Zealand series he was called into the test squad which was to tour Australia for a three test match series. During the first two tests in that series he failed to have an impact as he struggled against the Australian pace attack. In the final test of the series in Sydney he managed to get his highest test score of 85 in the second innings.

name: Din Joe Crowley
description: Din Joe Crowley is a former Irish sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club Rathmore and was a member of the Kerry senior inter-county team from the 1968 until 1972. His son Mike played with the Limerick intercounty team in the 2000s.

name: Dinah Pfizenmaier
description: Dinah Pfizenmaier (born 13 January 1992 in Bielefeld) is a German tennis player. Pfizenmaier has won a total of eight ITF titles (seven singles, one doubles) and her best world ranking of 121 came on 6 August 2012. Pfizenmaier played her first Grand Slam at the 2012 French Open. She qualified for the main draw by defeating Kristýna Plíšková, Misaki Doi and Mónica Puig. In the first round of the main draw she defeated local talent Caroline Garcia to set up a clash with world number one Victoria Azarenka. She lost the meeting 1–6, 1–6.

name: Dinei (footballer born 1979)
description: Vatinei César Moreira dos Santos better known simply as Dinei (born 10 December 1979 in Campos dos Goytacazes) is a Brazilian professional football player.

name: Dinesh Chandimal
description: Lokuge Dinesh Chandimal (born 18 November 1989 in Balapitiya) is a Sri Lankan international cricketer who has played first class cricket for Ruhuna and Nondescripts Cricket Club. A right-hand batsman and wicket-keeper, he scored 64, four and 109 in his first three innings for the Sri Lanka Cricket Development XI. He is an aggressive batsman and keeper who also scored two centuries for his country's U-19s, which he vice-captained, and plays for the Sri Lanka Cricket XI and Schools Invitation XI for one day and Twenty20 cricket. Dinesh Chandimal is the current Sri Lanka T20 International Cricket Captain & the current Sri Lanka Test and One Day International Cricket Vice Captain. Dinesh Chandimal started his cricket career as a teenager at Dharmasoka College, Ambalangoda. Later he moved to Ananda College, Colombo and captained Ananda College under-17 cricket team and proved his capabilities. In 2008, he was appointed as 1st XI cricket captain of Ananda College and led his team to 13 outright wins in a season, which rewrote the history of Sri Lankan school cricket. Also he became the first schoolboy cricketer to break the 1,000 run mark with a total of 1,580 runs, which makes him one of the highest run getters in a school cricket season and won Observer-Mobitel Schoolboy Cricketer of the Year Award in 2009. Shortly after completing a prolific school season for Ananda he joined NCC cricket club. He made his international debut during the 2010 ICC World Twenty20 in the West Indies, playing in Sri Lanka's group games against New Zealand and Zimbabwe in the initial group stage and then playing against Australia in the Super Eights. After also playing against New Zealand in a Twenty20 match in Florida, Chandimal was selected for an ODI tri-series in Zimbabwe, where the two sides also played India. He made his debut against Zimbabwe, scoring an unbeaten 10 as his side cruised to a nine-wicket win and then registered his maiden international century by scoring 111 runs off 118 balls against India, an innings that helped his side both win the match (by six wickets) and knock India out of the tournament. He also became the youngest Sri Lankan to score an ODI century. Chandimal made his Test debut for Sri Lanka in December 2011, in the second Test of the series against South Africa in Durban. On debut he made half-centuries (58 and 54) in each of Sri Lanka's innings. This incidentally led Sri Lanka to their first Test win in South Africa. During the 2012 Indian Premier League (IPL) auction, he was bought for $50,000 by the Rajasthan Royals. However, he never got a chance to play in any of their matches in the 2012 IPL.

name: Dinger Doane
description: Erling Eugene "Dinger" Doane (October 14, 1893 – June 5, 1949) was a professional football player. He played in the National Football League with the Cleveland Tigers, Milwaukee Badgers, Detroit Panthers, Pottsville Maroons, Providence Steam Roller and the New York Brickley Giants. Brickley's New York Giants are not related to the modern-day New York Giants. Prior to joining the NFL, Doane was a standout at Tufts University. He joined the pre-NFL Frankford Yellow Jackets briefly in 1921 for a game against the Union Quakers of Philadelphia.

name: Dinko Felić
description: Dinko Felić (born 10 November 1983) is a Bosnian-born Norwegian footballer who plays for Syrianska FC as a forward.

name: Dinko Vrabac
description: Dinko Vrabac (born 28 January 1963) is a former Bosnian football player who played for several Bosnian and Slovenian clubs during 1980s and 1990s. His brother Damir Vrabac is also a football player.

name: Dinnyuy Kongnyuy
description: Dinnyuy Kongnyuy (born 24 January 1988 in Kadji, Jakiri Kumbo province) is a professional Cameroonian footballer currently playing for Slovenian PrvaLiga team NK Triglav Kranj.

name: Dino Chiozza
description: Dino Joseph Chiozza (June 30, 1912 – April 23, 1972) was a Major League Baseball shortstop who played for one season. He played for the Philadelphia Phillies in two games during the 1935 Philadelphia Phillies season.

name: Dino Mangiero
description: Dino Mangiero was a professional American football player who played defensive lineman for six seasons for the Kansas City Chiefs, Seattle Seahawks, and New England Patriots.

name: Dino Marcan
description: Dino Marcan is a Croatian professional tennis player. On October 31, 2011, he reached his highest ATP singles ranking of 330.

name: Dino Philyaw
description: Delvic Dyvon "Dino" Philyaw (born October 30, 1970) is a retired American professional football player who served as a running back and kick returner for the National Football League's Carolina Panthers and New Orleans Saints. Originally drafted in 1995 by the New England Patriots, he signed with the team shortly after he was drafted, but was cut by the team on September 1, 1995. He later joined the expansion Carolina Panthers for one game during the 1995 season, returning one kickoff for 23 yards. The following season, he returned to the Panthers as a backup running back to Anthony Johnson. With the Panthers in 1996, Philyaw rushed for 38 yards and scored his only touchdown. After being released by the Panthers after the 1996 season, Philyaw was out of the NFL for both the 1997 and 1998 seasons, briefly playing with NFL Europe's Scottish Claymores in 1998. He returned to the NFL in 1999 serving as the New Orleans Saints primary kick returner and a backup running back. He returned 53 kickoffs for 1,165 yards and rushed for an additional 16 yards. He joined the short-lived XFL in 2000 as a member of the New York/New Jersey Hitmen before leaving pro football for good.

name: Dino Williams
description: Dino Williams (born 31 March 1990) is a Jamaican international footballer who plays for Village United, as a striker.

name: Dinty Gearin
description: Dennis John Gearin (October 15, 1897 – March 11, 1959) is a former Major League Baseball pitcher. He played two seasons with the New York Giants (1923–1924) and Boston Braves (1924).

name: Diogo Barbosa Medonha
description: Diogo Barbosa Medonha, or simply Diogo (Mato Grosso, August 17, 1992), is a Brazilian football player currently playing for Agremiação Sportiva Arapiraquense.

name: Diogo Campos Gomes
description: Diogo Campos is a brazilian striker who plays for French Ligue 1 side Évian Thonon Gaillard.

name: Diogo Correa de Oliveira
description: Diogo Correo de Oliveira, or simply Diogo (born 8 April 1984), is a Brazilian football forward.

name: Diogo Ferreira
description: Diogo Ferreira (born 5 October 1989) is an Australian footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Melbourne Victory in the A-League.

name: Diogo Figueiras
description: Diogo José Rosário Gomes Figueiras (born 7 January 1991 in Castanheira do Ribatejo, Vila Franca de Xira) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays for F.C. Paços de Ferreira as a right defender.

name: Diogo Galvão
description: Diogo Galvão de Macedo, the Diogo Galvão is a Brazilian football striker.

name: Diogo Jefferson Mendes de Melo
description: Diogo Jefferson Mendes de Melo commonly known as Diogo Melo (born 18 April 1984) in Uniao dos Palmares, Brazil is a Brazilian football (soccer) player who plays as a Midfielder. He most recently plays for Sanat Naft in the Iran Pro League.

name: Diogo Leite
description: Diogo Carvalho Pereira Leite is a Portuguese footballer. The central defender is also taking sports management.

name: Diogo Matos
description: Diogo Maria de Sousa Franco de Matos, simply known as Diogo (born 15 November 1975 in Lisbon), is a Portuguese retired footballer who played as a defensive midfielder.

name: Diogo Orlando
description: Orlando Diogo de Oliveira, known as Diogo Orlando (Volta Redonda, December 4, 1983), is a Brazilian footballer who acts as the steering wheel. Currently playing for Ceará.

name: Diogo Pinheiro
description: Diogo Pinheiro de Sousa (born 20 March 1990) is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Dutch club Fortuna Sittard.

name: Diogo Viana
description: Diogo Filipe Guerreiro Viana is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays for F.C. Penafiel as a forward.

name: Dion Brandon
description: Gary Dion Brandon (born 8 June 1986) is a Caymanian footballer who plays as a midfielder. He has represented the Cayman Islands during World Cup qualifying matches in 2008 and 2011.

name: Dion Malone
description: Dion Malone (born 13 February 1989) is a Surinamese professional footballer who plays for ADO Den Haag in the Dutch Eredivisie. He formerly played for Almere City. He also holds Dutch citizenship.

name: Dion Staring
description: Dion Staring (born June 9, 1978) is a Dutch professional mixed martial artist. Staring has fought for Strikeforce, SLAMM!! Events, Shooto, Konfrontacja Sztuk Walki, United Glory and Jungle Fight. Staring holds a notable victory over Akira Corassani.

name: Dion Stovell
description: Dion Stovell (born 12 August 1984) is a Bermudian cricketer. Stovell is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He was born in Bermuda. Stovell was selected in Bermuda's squad for the 2011 World Cricket League Division Two in the United Arab Emirates. It was during this tournament that Stovell made his List A debut against Papua New Guinea. He made five further List A appearances during the tournament, the last of which came against Uganda. He scored 243 runs during the tournament, the most by any Bermudian batsman, with these runs coming at an average of 40.50, with a high score of 77. This score was one of two half centuries he made during the tournament and came against the United Arab Emirates in a losing cause. Despite his efforts, Bermuda were relegated to the 2013 World Cricket League Division Three. He was selected as part of Bermuda's squad for the World Twenty20 Qualifier.

name: Dionatan Teixeira
description: Dionathan do Nascimento Teixeira (born 24 July 1992 in Londrina) is a Brazilian football defender who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FK Dukla Banská Bystrica. He was a former member of the Manchester City U18.

name: Diondre Borel
description: Diondre Borel (born December 12, 1988) is an American football wide receiver who is a member of the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League. He was undrafted, but signed as a free agent by the Packers and converted to wide receiver after playing both punter and quarterback in college. He played college football at Utah State University. Borel also has played for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers

name: Dionysis Makrydimitris
description: Dionysis Makrydimitris (Greek: Διονύσης Μακρυδημήτρης; born 26 January 1985) is a professional footballer who plays as a defender and defensive midfielder for Panthrakikos F.C. in the Football League.

name: Dionysius Hayom Rumbaka
description: Dionysius Hayom Rumbaka (born October 22, 1988 in Kulon Progo) is an Indonesian badminton player.

name: Dirceu Inácio da Silva Júnior
description: Dirceu Inácio da Silva Júnior (born 29 January 1989) is a Brazilian footballer.

name: Dirceu Lucas de Abreu Santos
description: Lucas full name Dirceu Lucas de Abreu Santos (born 25 February 1988) is Brazilian footballer who plays for Mirassol FC.

name: Dirk Eitzert
description: Dirk Eitzert (born 1 November 1968) is a retired German football midfielder.

name: Dirk Heirweg
description: Dirk Heirweg (born 27 September 1955) is a Belgian former racing cyclist.

name: Dirk Kuhnen
description: Dirk Kuhnen is a retired German rugby player, who played prop for the German national team from 1988 to 1998. He was the regular captain of Germany from 1995 to 1998. Kuhnen was a member of German teams which toured Canada in 1988, competed in the erstwhile FIRA Tournaments and Rugby World Cup qualification matches. He also played for Germany in the Malaysia Tens. He played club rugby for TSV Victoria Linden in Hanover, with whom he played in numerous German Championship finals, winning the Championship six times.

name: Dirk Muschiol
description: Dirk Muschiol (born 13 April 1969) is a former professional German footballer. Muschiol made 55 appearances in the 2. Fußball-Bundesliga for SpVgg Blau-Weiß 1890 Berlin and Tennis Borussia Berlin during his playing career.

name: Dirk Oberritter
description: Dirk Oberritter (born 10 July 1972) is a German former professional footballer. A defender, Oberritter began his career with Dynamo Dresden, making his debut as a substitute for Dirk Zander in a 1–1 draw with 1. FC Saarbrücken in the Bundesliga in September 1992. He made one more appearance for Dynamo during the 1994–95 season, but was part of a mass exodus from Dynamo in the summer of 1995, after the club had been relegated to the Regionalliga Nordost. He signed for Dynamo's Saxony rivals VfB Leipzig, but was back at Dynamo after only six months and one league appearance. He spent a further six years with the club, playing in the Regionalliga and the NOFV-Oberliga Süd, but his latter years were marred by injury. After brief spells with Stahl Riesa and FV Dresden 06, Oberritter's senior career ended, although he continued to play for SV Wesenitztal of the Bezirksliga.

name: Dirk Sadowicz
description: Dirk Sadowicz (born 25 February 1965) is a retired German football defender.

name: Divij Sharan
description: Divij Sharan (born 2 March 1986) is an Indian professional tennis player. He competes mainly on the ATP Challenger Tour and ITF Futures, both in singles and doubles.

name: Dixie Leverett
description: Gorham Vance "Dixie" Leverett (March 29, 1894 – February 20, 1957) was a pitcher in Major League Baseball. He played for the Chicago White Sox and Boston Braves.

name: Diyego Chapodze
description: Diyego Davidovich Chapodze (Russian: Дие́го Дави́дович Чапо́дзе; born November 27, 1991) is a Russian professional association football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Nika Moscow.

name: Diyego Malaniya
description: Diyego Tengizovich Malaniya (Russian: Диего Тенгизович Малания; born February 11, 1991) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Znamya Truda Orekhovo-Zuyevo.

name: Diyral Briggs
description: Diyral Briggs (born October 31, 1985) is an American football linebacker for the Kansas City Renegades of the Champions Professional Indoor Football League. He was signed by the San Francisco 49ers as an undrafted free agent in 2009. He played college football at Bowling Green.

name: Dizzy Nutter
description: Everett Clarence "Dizzy" Nutter (August 27, 1893 – July 25, 1958) is a former professional baseball player. In an eight-year career, Nutter participated in one Major League season with the Boston Braves in 1919. He was officially listed as standing 5 feet 9 inches and weighing 160 pounds .

name: Dizzy Sutherland
description: Howard Alvin "Dizzy" Sutherland (April 9, 1922 – August 26, 1979) was a Major League Baseball pitcher who played from 1949 with the Washington Senators. He batted and threw left-handed. He was born and died in Washington, D.C..

name: Djanal Herve Pierre
description: Herve Pierre Djanal born June 13, 1986) is a Cameroonian football Goalkeeper, he currently plays for Okkthar United FC.

name: Djeny Bembo-Leta
description: Djeny Bembo-Leta (born 9 November 1991) is a professional Congolese/Angolan/French footballer who plays as a forward for Radcliffe Borough.

name: Dmitri Akimov
description: Dmitri Sergeyevich Akimov (Russian: Дмитрий Сергеевич Акимов; born September 14, 1980 in Leningrad) is a Russian football player. Currently, he plays for FC Fakel Voronezh. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2000 for FC Zenit St. Petersburg. He was the top scorer in the Russian First Division in 2007, scoring 34 goals. He was also the top scorer in the Russian Second Division, East Zone in 2002 (22 goals) and 2004 (24 goals).

name: Dmitri Aleksandrovich Protopopov
description: Dmitri Aleksandrovich Protopopov (Russian: Дмитрий Александрович Протопопов; born January 23, 1988 in Karaganda) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Yakutiya Yakutsk.

name: Dmitri Alekseyev
description: Dmitri Vadimovich Alekseyev (Russian: Дмитрий Вадимович Алексеев; born February 28, 1973) is a Russian professional footballer. In 2010, he played for FC Dynamo Bryansk. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 1993 for FC Zhemchuzhina Sochi.

name: Dmitri Alminov
description: Dmitri Mikhailovich Alminov (Russian: Дмитрий Михайлович Альминов; born April 1, 1993) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Zenit Penza.

name: Dmitri Anatolyevich Davydov
description: Dmitri Anatolyevich Davydov (Russian: Дмитрий Анатольевич Давыдов; born January 22, 1975) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Dynamo Saint Petersburg. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 1996 for FC Zenit St. Petersburg. He is a son of the former FC Zenit St. Petersburg player and manager Anatoli Davydov.

name: Dmitri Andreyev

description: Dmitri Vladimirovich Yashin (Russian: Дмитрий Владимирович Яшин; born October 27, 1981) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 1999 for FC Volga Ulyanovsk.

name: Dmitri Yefremov
description: Dmitri Andreyevich Yefremov is a Russian football midfielder currently playing for FC Sibiryak Bratsk.

name: Dmitri Yepifanov
description: Dmitri Borisovich Yepifanov (Russian: Дмитрий Борисович Епифанов; born January 31, 1978) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Dolgoprudny.

name: Dmitri Yershov
description: Dmitri Vyacheslavovich Yershov (Russian: Дмитрий Вячеславович Ершов; born June 12, 1993) is a football midfielder who last played for FC Istra. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Istra on October 10, 2011 in a game against FC Sheksna Cherepovets.

name: Dmitri Yestekhin
description: Dmitri Valeryevich Yestekhin (Russian: Дмитрий Валерьевич Естехин; born November 18, 1987) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Gubkin.

name: Dmitri Zarva
description: Dmitri Yevgenyevich Zarva (Russian: Дмитрий Евгеньевич Зарва; born June 15, 1985) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Chelyabinsk. His father Yevgeni Zarva played in the Russian Premier League for FC Dynamo-Gazovik Tyumen.

name: Dmitri Zyuganov
description: Dmitri Viktorovich Zyuganov (Russian: Дмитрий Викторович Зюганов; born February 27, 1974) is a reitired Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Bataysk-2007.

name: Dmitriy Dudarev
description: Dmitriy Viktorovich Dudarev (born 23 February 1976) is a Kazakh professional ice hockey winger who currently plays for Metallurg Novokuznetsk of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL). He participated at the 2010 IIHF World Championship as a member of the Kazakhstan men's national ice hockey team.

name: Dmitriy Gorbushin
description: Dmitriy Andreyevich Gorbushin (Russian: Дмитрий Андреевич Горбушин; Ukrainian: Дмитро Андрійович Горбушин; born 31 May 1986 in Rubizhne) is an Ukrainian professional footballer, he also holds Russian citizenship, he last played for FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk.

name: Dmitriy Ivanov
description: Dmitriy Ivanov (Russian: Дмитрий Иванов; born October 27, 1994) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian First Division for Luch-Energiya Vladivostok.

name: Dmitriy Klochko
description: Dmitriy Klochko (born 17 February 1987), is a Ukrainian futsal player who plays for Lokomotiv Kharkiv and the Ukraine national futsal team.

name: Dmitriy Shomko
description: Dmitriy Shomko (born 9 March 1990) is a Kazakh international footballer who plays for Astana, as a defender.

name: Dmitry Akhba
description: Dmitry Zaurovich Akhba (Russian: Дмитрий Заурович Ахба; born September 6, 1985) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Avangard Kursk.

name: Dmitry Alayev
description: Dmitry Valentinovich Alayev (Russian: Дми́трий Валенти́нович Ала́ев; born December 18, 1988) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC Torpedo-ZIL Moscow.

name: Dmitry Aydov
description: Dmitry Mikhaylovich Aydov (Russian: Дми́трий Миха́йлович А́йдов; born April 10, 1982) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays for FC Volga Nizhny Novgorod.

name: Dmitry Belov
description: Dmitry Valeryevich Belov (Russian: Дми́трий Вале́рьевич Бело́в; born January 28, 1980) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC Volga Tver.

name: Dmitry Burlak
description: Dmitry Borisovich Burlak (Russian: Дми́трий Бори́сович Бурла́к; born March 8, 1983) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played for FC Dynamo Kostroma.

name: Dmitry Chernukhin
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Chernukhin (Russian: Дми́трий Серге́евич Черну́хин; born November 17, 1988) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Zvezda Ryazan.

name: Dmitry Galanov
description: Dmitry Alexandrovich Galanov (Russian: Дмитрий Александрович Галанов; born January 30, 1994) is an association football midfielder from Russia who currently plays for FC Vityaz Podolsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Saturn-2 Moscow Oblast on April 21, 2011 in a game against FC Znamya Truda Orekhovo-Zuyevo.

name: Dmitry Garbuzov
description: Dmitry Nikolayevich Garbuzov (Russian: Дмитрий Николаевич Гарбузов; born May 24, 1985) is a professional association football player from Russia. Currently, he plays for FC Znamya Truda Orekhovo-Zuyevo.

name: Dmitry Goryachkin
description: Dmitry Borisovich Goryachkin (Russian: Дми́трий Бори́сович Горя́чкин; born January 17, 1988) is a Russian professional association football player. As of September 2009, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Zvezda Serpukhov. He is a brother of Sergei Goryachkin and a son of the president of FC Zvezda Serpukhov, Boris Goryachkin.

name: Dmitry Govorukhin
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Govorukhin (Russian: Дми́трий Серге́евич Говору́хин; born April 16, 1978) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC MITOS Novocherkassk.

name: Dmitry Ivchenko
description: Dmitry Alexeyevich Ivchenko (Russian: Дми́трий Алексе́евич И́вченко; born July 8, 1978) is a Russian professional association football player. He plays for FC Oryol.

name: Dmitry Klimanov
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Klimanov (Russian: Дми́трий Серге́евич Клима́нов; born July 18, 1982) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays for FC Nara-ShBFR Naro-Fominsk.

name: Dmitry Klimov
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Klimov (Russian: Дми́трий Серге́евич Кли́мов; born May 16, 1983) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played for FC Fakel Voronezh.

name: Dmitry Knyazhevich
description: Dmitry Knyazhevich (Russian: Дмитрий Максимович Княжевич, 21 June 1874 – 1918) was a Russian fencer. He competed in the individual foil and team épée events at the 1912 Summer Olympics.

name: Dmitry Krasilnikov
description: Dmitry Anatolyevich Krasilnikov (Russian: Дми́трий Анато́льевич Краси́льников; born May 7, 1979) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays for FC Volga Ulyanovsk.

name: Dmitry Kroyter
description: Dmitry Kroyter (born 18 February 1993) is an Israeli high jumper. He has been dubbed one of Israel's greatest sports talents, along with Gili Haimovitz and Yakov-Yan Toumarkin. He is coached by Anatoly Shafran at Maccabi Tel Aviv. Born in Siberia, Kroyter's family emigrated to Israeli in 1999. He became Israel's first ever Youth World Champion at the 2009 World Youth Championships in Athletics.

name: Dmitry Lapkes
description: Dmitry Lapkes (born 4 June 1976) is a Belarusian sabre fencer, who has competed at three Olympic games. His best result in the Olympic games is finishing 4th in Athens. He won a silver medal in the team sabre event at the 2011 World Fencing Championships.

name: Dmitry Larin
description: Dmitry Borisovich Larin (Russian: Дми́трий Бори́сович Ла́рин; born July 26, 1973) is a Russian professional association football player. In 2010, he played in the Russian First Division for FC Dynamo Bryansk.

name: Dmitry Lavlinsky
description: Dmitry Yevgenyevich Lavlinsky (Russian: Дмитрий Евгеньевич Лавлинский; born January 2, 1985) is a Russian professional association football player. He plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Syzran-2003 Syzran.

name: Dmitry Lokhonov
description: Dmitry Vitalyevich Lokhonov (Russian: Дмитрий Витальевич Лохонов; born 4 August 1990) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he is a free agent. He is a twin brother of Vladislav Lokhonov.

name: Dmitry Loshkaryov
description: Dmitry Gennadyevich Loshkaryov (Russian: Дми́трий Генна́дьевич Лошкарёв; born March 26, 1987) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played for FC Metallurg-Oskol Stary Oskol.

name: Dmitry Lushnikov
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Lushnikov (Russian: Дмитрий Сергеевич Лушников; born August 22, 1989) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays for FC Smena Komsomolsk-na-Amure.

name: Dmitry Malkov
description: Dmitry Vladimirovich Malkov (Russian: Дми́трий Влади́мирович Ма́лков; born October 27, 1978) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Spartak Kostroma.

name: Dmitry Milevsky
description: Dmitry Gennadyevich Milevsky (Russian: Дмитрий Геннадьевич Милевский; born June 28, 1991) is a Russian professional association football player. He is currently unattached.

name: Dmitry Milomayev
description: Dmitry Vladimirovich Milomayev (Russian: Дми́трий Влади́мирович Милома́ев; born July 23, 1989) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Spartak Tambov.

name: Dmitry Mizerovsky
description: Dmitry Vyacheslavovich Mizerovsky (Russian: Дмитрий Вячеславович Мизеровский; born April 4, 1991) is a Russian professional association football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC Tekstilshchik Ivanovo.

name: Dmitry Poloz
description: Dmitry Dmitriyevich Poloz (Russian: Дмитрий Дмитриевич Полоз; born July 12, 1991) is an association football forward from Russia who plays for FC Rostov.

name: Dmitry Sergeyevich Korolyov
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Korolyov (Russian: Дми́трий Серге́евич Королёв; born January 2, 1989) is a Russian professional association football player. In 2010, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Sportakademklub Moscow.

name: Dmitry Shepel
description: Dmitry Sergeyevich Shepel (Дмитрий Сергеевич Шепель) (born 8 August 1977, Leningrad) is a retired Russian speedskater. He becamethe World Junior Champion in 1998 in Roseville, Minnesota. The same year he set a junior world record on the 1,500 meters, skating that distance in 1:50,45 in Calgary. Shepel had his major success in 2001, when on the high-altitude ice rink of Baselga di Pinè in Italy he became European champion, breaking the hegemony of skaters from the Netherlands who otherwise won every event from 1992 to 2005. He participated at the Olympic Winter Games in 1998, 2002 and 2006. His most successful efforts were in 2002 in Salt Lake City, with a 4th place at the 5,000 meters and a 6th place at the 10,000 meters. </small> After this last distance on March 22, 2002, Shepel reached third place in the adelskalender, a ranking based on skaters' all-time personal records for the classic samalog distances, which position he held until January 2005.

name: Dmitry Sukhov
description: Dmitry Alexandrovich Sukhov (Russian: Дми́трий Алекса́ндрович Су́хов; born September 17, 1986) is a Russian professional association football player. In 2010, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Khimik Dzerzhinsk.

name: Dmitry Yuryevich Belyayev (born 1989)
description: Dmitry Yuryevich Belyayev (Russian: Дми́трий Ю́рьевич Беля́ев; born June 30, 1989) is a Russian professional association football player currently playing for FC Taganrog.

name: Dmytro Kolodin
description: Dmytro Kolodin (Ukrainian: Дмитро Колодін; born 12 April 1978) is a Ukrainian football midfielder who plays for FC Zhemchuzhyna Yalta.

name: Dmytro Leonov
description: Dmytro Leonov (Ukrainian: Дмитро Валерійович Леонов; born 6 November 1988 in Ukrainian SSR) is a professional Ukrainian football midfielder who currently plays for Ukrainian First League club FC Arsenal Bila Tserkva. Leonov is the product of the UOR Simferopol School System. He spent all his career as a player in different clubs of the Ukrainian First League and the Ukrainian Second League.

name: Dmytro Lytvynenko
description: Dmytro Lytvynenko (born 16 April 1987), is a Ukrainian futsal player who plays for Lokomotiv Kharkiv and the Ukraine national futsal team.

name: Dmytro Nazarenko
description: Dmytro Nazarenko (Ukrainian: Дмитро Миколайович Назаренко; born 14 September 1987) is a Ukrainian football defender who plays for FC Stal Alchevsk. Nazarenko was born in Donetsk and began playing professional football with FC Vorskla Poltava's second team. He would next spend 2.5 years with his hometown club FC Metalurh Donetsk, appearing in two Ukrainian Premier League and a few UEFA Cup matches. He moved on loan to Stal Alchevsk for the 2008–09 Ukrainian First League season, and then went to FC Banants of the Armenian Premier League for a short-term loan in 2009.

name: Dmytro Pryma
description: Dmytro Anatoliovych Pryma (Ukrainian: Дмитро Анатолійович Прима; born 13 March 1985 in Kiev, in the Ukrainian SSR of the Soviet Union) is a Ukrainian football striker currently playing for Ukrainian Second League club Stal Dniprodzerzhynsk.

name: Dmytro Skoblov
description: Dmytro Skoblov is a Ukrainian football striker for FC Illichivets Mariupol in the Ukrainian Premier League. He made his debut for main Illichivets time as substitution in second half in match against FC Krymteplytsia Molodizhne in Ukrainian First League in 3 August 2007.

name: Dmytro Sorokin
description: Dmytro Sorokin (born 14 July 1988), is a Ukrainian futsal player who plays for Lokomotiv Kharkiv and the Ukraine national futsal team.

name: Dmytro Zayko
description: Dmytro Mykolaiovych Zayko is a Ukrainian football striker currently playing for Ukrainian Second League club Kremin.

name: Dobrivoj Rusov
description: Dobrivoj Rusov (born 13 January 1993) is a Slovak football goalkeeper who currently plays for FC Spartak Trnava. He was appointed to A-team in July 2011 from youth teams.

name: Doc Daugherty
description: Harold Ray "Doc" Daugherty (born October 12, 1927) ia a retired American professional baseball player and manager, and high school football head coach. A shortstop in minor league baseball, he made one appearance as a pinch hitter in the Major Leagues for the Detroit Tigers in 1951. In it, he struck out against Billy Pierce of the Chicago White Sox on April 22. A native of Weirton, West Virginia, Daugherty attended Ohio State University, where he played football. After his baseball playing career ended, he became a teacher and coach in West Virginia and Ohio, and also managed the Short Season-Class A Duluth-Superior Dukes for the 1965 season.

name: Doc Gautreau
description: Walter Paul "Doc" Gautreau (July 26, 1901 – August 23, 1970) was an American professional baseball player, manager and scout. The native of Cambridge, Massachusetts, was a second baseman during his playing days. Also nicknamed "Punk," he stood a diminutive 5 feet 2 inches tall and weighed 129 pounds, and threw and batted right-handed. Gautreau attended The College of the Holy Cross in Worcester, Massachusetts, and the Crusaders went 92-8-1 during his tenure as the team's second baseman. He played his first year of professional baseball in 1925, making his debut in the Major Leagues that June as a member of the Philadelphia Athletics. After four games played and seven hitless at bats, his contract was sold to the Boston Braves of the National League in July. Gautreau's batting then picked up, as he hit .267 for the Braves that season, and won a job as a part-time player in 1926 and 1927. His tenure with the Braves was curtailed, however, when Boston obtained future Baseball Hall of Fame second baseman Rogers Hornsby for the 1928 campaign. Gautreau spent most of that season in the Class A Eastern League and made his final Major League appearance at the end of September. All told, he appeared in 261 games over four big-league seasons (1925–1928), and batted .257 with 207 hits and 40 stolen bases. After leaving the Majors, Gautreau became a regular with the Montreal Royals of the International League, playing with them for five seasons, including two as playing manager. After his career in uniform, he scouted for the Braves in both Boston and Milwaukee, as well as with the Los Angeles/California Angels. He died in Salt Lake City, Utah, at age 69.

name: Doc Kerr
description: John Jonas "Doc" Kerr (January 17, 1882 – January 9, 1937) was a Major League Baseball player who played for the Pittsburgh Rebels and the Baltimore Terrapins in 1914 and 1915.

name: Doc Leitner
description: George Aloysius Leitner (September 14, 1865 – May 18, 1937), was an American professional baseball player who played pitcher in the Major Leagues for the 1887 Indianapolis Hoosiers of the National League. He played college baseball at Fordham University and New York University.

name: Doc Martin (baseball)
description: Harold Winthrop Martin (1887–1935) was an American Major League Baseball pitcher. He played for the Philadelphia Athletics during the 1908, 1911 and 1912 seasons. He attended Tufts University.

name: Doc Oberlander
description: Hartman Louis Oberlander (1864–1922), was a Major League Baseball pitcher, who pitched in three games for the 1888 Cleveland Blues of the American Association. He played through 1891 in the minor leagues and went to school at Syracuse University.

name: Doc Ralston
description: Samuel Beryl "Doc" Ralston (August 3, 1885 – August 29, 1950) was an outfielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Washington Senators in 1910.

name: Doc Sechrist
description: Theodore O'Hara "Doc" Sechrist (1876–1950) was a professional baseball player. He was a pitcher who played for the New York Giants of the National League in one game, on April 28, 1899. He faced two batters and walked both of them. Because they did not score and he did not record an out, he has no official ERA from his appearance. In addition to his brief major league appearance, he played in the minor leagues from 1895 through 1904. He is buried in the Somerset City Cemetery, Somerset, Kentucky, with his wife, Gertrude.

name: Doc Waldbauer
description: Albert Charles "Doc" Waldbauer (February 22, 1892 – July 16, 1969) was a Major League Baseball pitcher who played for one season. He played for the Washington Senators for two games during the 1917 Washington Senators season.

name: Doc Wood
description: Charles Spencer "Doc" Wood (February 28, 1900 – November 3, 1974) was a professional baseball player. He appeared in three games in Major League Baseball for the Philadelphia Athletics in 1923 as a shortstop.

name: Doctor Mampuru
description: Doctor Mampuru is a South African football (soccer) right-back for Premier Soccer League club Mamelodi Sundowns.

name: Dod Brewster
description: George 'Dod' Brewster (born 7 May 1893, date of death unknown) was a Scottish former professional football centre-half who played for Aberdeen, Everton and Wolverhampton Wanderers.

name: Doddy Édouard
description: Doddy Édouard (born 17 June 1981) is a Mauritian footballer who currently plays as a striker for Faucon Flacq SC. He won one cap for the Mauritius national football team in 2004. Édouard previously played in Réunion for AS Marsouins.

name: Doe Boyland
description: Doe Boyland is a former Major League Baseball first baseman. Boyland was drafted in the second round of the 1976 Major League Baseball Draft by the Pittsburgh Pirates. He would play in 21 games with the team in 1978, 1979, and 1981. Boyland was later traded to the San Francisco Giants for Tom Griffin. He played at the collegiate level at the University of Wisconsin-Oshkosh.

name: Doke Schmidt
description: Doke Schmidt (born 7 April 1992) is a Dutch footballer who plays as a defender for SC Heerenveen in the Eredivisie.

name: Dolores Duffy
description: Dolores Duffy (December 25, 1934 – October 29, 2011) was an American sprinter. She competed in the Women's 200 metres event at the 1952 Summer Olympics. In her later life, she became an actress, which included a role in the television show Sex and the City.

name: Dolores Gallardo
description: Dolores Gallardo Núñez is a Spanish football goalkeeper, currently playing for Atlético Madrid in the Primera División. She previously played for Sevilla FC and Sporting Huelva. In 2010 she was named the best player in the U-17 European Championship and the best goalkeeper in the U-17 World Cup.

name: Dolores Pampin
description: Dolores Pampin (born 20 December 1973) is an Argentine fencer. She won a bronze medal in the team foil event at the 1995 Pan American Games. She also competed in the women's individual and team foil events at the 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Dolores Silva
description: Dolores Isabel Jacome Silva (born 7 August 1991) is a Portuguese international football player. She plays as a wide or central midfielder for Frauen Bundesliga club FCR 2001 Duisburg and the senior Portugal women's national team.

name: Dom DeCicco
description: Dominic John DeCicco (born September 11, 1988) is an American football linebacker for the Chicago Bears of the National Football League. He was signed by the Bears as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football at Pittsburgh.

name: Dom O'Donnell
description: Dom O'Donnell was a Gaelic Footballer from Tralee, County Kerry. He played Gaelic football with his local club John Mitchels, and was a member of the Kerry senior inter-county team during the 1960s. He won a Munster Championship medal in 1962 and 1964, that same year he also won an All Ireland Under 21 medal all has captain of the winning teams. At club level O'Donnell was part of the famed John Mitchels team of the late 1950s and 1960s, winning six Kerry Senior Football Championships (five in a row from 1959 to 1963 and again in 1966).

name: Dom Shipperley
description: Dom Shipperley is a rugby union footballer who plays professionally for the Queensland Reds in Super Rugby. His regular playing position is wing. He made his debut during the 2011 Super Rugby season against the Hurricanes. Shipperley was a member of the Australia under 20 team that competed in the 2011 IRB Junior World Championship. Dom Shipperley was also an OP1 recipient in 2008 at Nudgee College. An OP1 is the highest possible marks that can be achieved in the Queensland Certificate of Education. Shipperley spoke at his school saying, "Balance is that extra element that allows us to succeed when we might not have and to have fun and enjoy the journey that is school life," "I have found it is not the time you spend studying or doing homework but the quality of your effort and focus when you are sitting down. When you sit down to work make sure you are 100% focused on it. Avoid distractions and just do it."

name: Domagoj Pušić
description: Domagoj Pušić (born 24 October 1991) is a Croatian football midfielder, currently playing for NK Osijek in the Prva HNL.

name: Domenico Capello
description: Domenico Capello (born in 1888 in Turin; died in 1950 in Turin) was an Italian professional football player. He played in the first ever game of Italy national football team on 15 May 1910 against France.

name: Domenico D'Alberto
description: Domenico D'Alberto (born 1 February 1907 in Budapest) was a Hungarian professional football player. He also held Italian citizenship. He played for 3 seasons (50 games, 12 goals) in the Serie A for A.S. Roma and A.S. Lucchese Libertas 1905.

name: Domenico Maietta
description: Domenico Maietta (born 3 August 1982) is an Italian footballer who currently plays for Hellas Verona. Although included on Serie A rosters for Juventus and Perugia in the early 2000s, he currently has still not made a Serie A debut. He made his Serie B debut with Triestina in the 2002/2003 season.

name: Domenico Pace
description: Domenico Pace (born 9 July 1924) is an Italian fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1956 Summer Olympics.

name: Domenico Penzo
description: Domenico Penzo (born October 17, 1953 in Chioggia) is a retired Italian professional football player. He played 6 seasons (122 games, 27 goals) in the Serie A for A.S. Roma, Brescia Calcio, Hellas Verona F.C. , Juventus F.C. and S.S.C. Napoli. His best season was in 1982/83, when he scored 15 goals to become the second-best scorer in the Serie A, behind only Michel Platini who scored 16. After that season, he was bought by Juventus F.C. , but he didn't score as much for Juve. However, he achieved a rare feat of scoring 4 goals in the same game, in the first round game of the 1983–84 European Cup Winners' Cup against Lechia Gdańsk.

name: Domingo García (footballer)
description: Domingo García Heredia (born 1904 - date of death unknown) was a Peruvian football midfielder who played for Peru in the 1930 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Alianza Lima.

name: Domingo Mendy
description: Domingo Mendy (born 1870, date of death unknown) was a Uruguayan fencer. He competed in five events at the 1924 Summer Olympics.

name: Domingos Lopes
description: Domingos António Lopes (born 23 August 1912, date of death unknown) was a Portuguese footballer who played as forward. He was born in Mina de São Domingos.

name: Domingos Neves
description: Domingos das Neves (born unknown - deceased) was a Portuguese footballer who played as a forward.

name: Dominic Collins (swimmer)
description: Dominic Collins is an Australian Paralympic swimmer. At the 1996 Atlanta Games, he won a silver medal in the Men's 4x100 m Freestyle S7–10 event. He participated without winning any medals at the 2000 Sydney Games.

name: Dominic Longo
description: Dominic Longo (born 23 August 1970) is a retired Australian football (soccer) player. He was an Australian Institute of Sport scholarship holder. Longo played for the Australian national football team between 1993 and 1998.

name: Dominic McKinley
description: Dominic McKinley is an Irish retired sportsperson. He played hurling with his local club Loughgiel Shamrocks and was a member of the Antrim senior inter-county team in the 1980s and 1990s.

name: Dominic McMullan
description: Dominic McMullan is an Irish retired sportsperson. He played hurling with his local club Loughgiel Shamrocks and was a member of the Antrim senior inter-county team in the 1980s and 1990s.

name: Dominic Meier
description: Dominic Meier (born December 26, 1976) is a Swiss professional ice hockey defenceman. He is currently playing for the SC Bern of Switzerland's National League A.

name: Dominic Pürcher
description: Dominic Pürcher (born 24 June 1988 in Schladming) is an Austrian footballer who plays for Kapfenberger SV.

name: Dominic Picard
description: Dominic Picard (born June 22, 1982 in Sainte-Foy, Quebec) is a Canadian football centre for the Saskatchewan Roughriders of the Canadian Football League. He played CIS Football at Laval.

name: Dominic Rowe
description: Dominic Ryan Rowe (born 23 April 1993) is an English professional footballer who plays as a winger.

name: Dominic Ryan
description: Dominic Ryan (born 28 March 1990) is an Irish professional rugby union player for Lansdowne RFC and Leinster Rugby. He is a loose forward, playing primarily at openside flanker. Ryan made his senior debut for Leinster in the Celtic League in late 2009. He made his first appearance in the Heineken Cup against Saracens in January 2011, scoring two tries. Ryan was selected as part of the Ireland Wolfhounds squad to face Scotland A and England Saxons, his first call-up to senior international duty. In May 2011, he signed a new two-year contract with Leinster. Ryan had been out of action since October 2011 due to an ankle injury but has since returned to the squad, playing in Leinster's 16-13 last gasp win over Scarlets at the RDS on 17 February 2012 in the RaboDirect PRO12.

name: Dominic Wade
description: Dominic Wade (born April 12, 1990 in Largo, Maryland) is an undefeated professional boxer in the Super Middleweight division.

name: Dominic Williamson
description: Dominic Williamson (born 15 November 1975) is an English cricketer. Williamson is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born in Durham, County Durham. Williamson made his first-class debut for Leicestershire against the touring Indians in 1996. He played infrequently in first-class cricket for Leicestershire, making 8 further first-class appearances, the last of which came against Hampshire in the 2000 County Championship. In his 9 first-class matches, he scored 273 runs at an average of 30.33, with a high score of 47. With the ball, he took 14 wickets at an average of 37.78, with best figures of 3/19. It was though in List A cricket that Williamson was the prove to be more useful, making his debut for the county against Derbyshire in the 1996 Benson & Hedges Cup. He made 65 further List A appearances for Leicestershire, the last of which came against Yorkshire in the 1996 Norwich Union National League. In his 66 List A matches for the county, he scored 446 runs at an average of 13.11, with a high score of 39. With the ball, he took 79 wickets at an average of 21.29, with a best figures of 5/32. These figures, one of two five wicket hauls he took for Leicestershire, came against Sussex in the 1997 AXA Life League. In terms of wickets taken, the 1998 season was his most successful, with Williamson taking 33 wickets at an average of 18.84, with best figures of 5/37. Despite his success in the limited-overs format, Williamson left Leicestershire at the end of the 2000 season. In 2001 he joined Shropshire, making his debut for the county against the Worcestershire Cricket Board in the 2001 MCCA Knockout Trophy. He played Minor counties cricket for Shropshire in 2001 and 2002, making 6 Minor Counties Championship appearances and 4 MCCA Knockout Trophy appearances. He made 2 List A appearances while playing for Shropshire. The first of these came against Oxfordshire in the 2nd round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy, which was played in August 2001. In this match, he made his highest List A score of 49, before being dismissed by Luke List. With the ball, he bowled 4 wicket-less overs for the cost of 17 runs. The second of these came in the 3rd round of the same competition against Gloucestershire, which was played in May 2002. In this match, he scored 2 runs before being dismissed by Mike Smith, while with the ball he took the wicket of Mark Hardinges for the cost of 18 runs from 5 overs, with Gloucestershire winning by 7 wickets.

name: Dominic Yobe
description: Dominic Yobe (born 4 August 1986) is a Zambian footballer. His elder brother Donewell is also a professional footballer. Yobe represented Swedish Örgryte between 2004-2007 before signing with AC Oulu. He helped the team to win promotion to Veikkausliiga. On his first Veikkausliiga season in 2010, Dominic was named team captain. In November 2010 he signed a two-year contract with the reigning champions HJK. Yobe's contract was terminated in March 2011 after he was suspected of being involved in a match fixing scandal along with his brother and several other players. He was convicted to a seven-month suspended sentence for bribery.

name: Dominik Kohr
description: Dominik Kohr (born 31 January 1994) is a German footballer who plays as a midfielder for Bayer 04 Leverkusen in the Bundesliga. He came through Bayer Leverkusen's first team and made his Bundesliga debut in April 2012 a 1–0 win over 1899 Hoffenheim, as a substitute for André Schürrle.

name: Dominik Kramár
description: Dominik Kramár is a Slovakian professional ice hockey defenceman who played with HK SKP Poprad in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Dominik Nagy
description: Dominik Nagy (born 8 May 1995 in Bóly) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Pécsi Mecsek FC.

name: Dominik Picak
description: Dominik Picak (born 12 February 1992) is a Croatian football goalkeeper who plays for Lokomotiva Zagreb, on loan from Dinamo Zagreb.

name: Dominik Riečický
description: Dominik Riečický (born June 9, 1992) is a Slovakian ice hockey goaltender. He played with HC Košice of the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Dominik Schlumpf
description: Dominik Schlumpf (born March 3, 1991) is a Swiss professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for HC Lugano of Switzerland's National League A.

name: Dominika Luzarová
description: Dominika Luzarová (born 18 July 1982 in Přerov) is a former Czech tennis player. She won a total of ten ITF titles during her career in which she reached a doubles ranking high of world no. 180.

name: Dominique Da Silva
description: Dominique Da Silva (born 16 August 1989) is a Senegalese-Mauritanian footballer who plays as a forward for Al-Ahly. He spent time at the Académie de Football Nouakchott before joining CS Sfaxien in 2007. Four years later, he was transferred to Al-Ahly. He has been capped at international level by the Mauritania national team.

name: Dominique Harize
description: Dominique Harize, born 26 February 1956, was a rugby union player who was capped 9 times. He played with France Harize played as Wing for the Stade Toulousain. He was a member of the French team that won the Five Nations Championship in 1977 with the same fifteen players in all four matches and without conceding a try.

name: Dominique Lokoli
description: Dominique Lokoli (born 29 January 1952) is a former French footballer who played for Paris Saint-Germain F.C. , AS Nancy, AJ Auxerre and Stade de Reims.

name: Dominique Morrison
description: Dominique Morrison (born November 29, 1989) is an American professional basketball player. He was the 2012 Summit League player of the year and an Associated Press All-American in 2012. Morrison, a 6'6" forward from Raytown High School in Kansas City, Missouri, played collegiately at Oral Roberts. There he was a four-year starter for the Golden Eagles, leading the team in scoring for his final three years. He was also named first team all-conference for three consecutive years, and the Summit League player of the year as a senior. He was also named an honorable mention All-American by the Associated Press. For his career, Morrison scored 2,080 points. Morrison was part of the New Orleans Hornets' pre-season roster but did not make the final cut. Morrison then joined the Iowa Energy. In January 2013, he was waived by the Energy.

name: Dominique Robinson
description: Dominique M.J. Robinson (born March 1, 1982) is an American professional mixed martial arts (MMA) fighter. A professional MMA competitor since 2005, Robinson has made a name for himself fighting all over the United States, mainly on the West coast. Robinson has competed for organizations such as Tachi Palace Fights and Palace Fighting Championship. He holds notable victories over UFC veterans John Gunderson and Dave Kaplan.

name: Dominique Ross
description: Dominique Ross (born January 12, 1972 in Jacksonville, Florida) is a former professional American football running back in the National Football League. He attended Valdosta state. He would play with the Dallas Cowboys in 1995 and 1996.

name: Dominique Thibault
description: Dominique Thibault (born August 26, 1988) is an ice hockey player for the Montreal Stars and a former reality tv contestant.

name: Domonkos Ferjancsik
description: Domonkos Ferjancsik (born 7 September 1975) is a Hungarian fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 2000 and 2004 Summer Olympics. He won a silver and bronze medal at the 2003 World Fencing Championships and a gold medal at the 1998 World Fencing Championships.

name: Donát Laczkovich
description: Donát Laczkovich (born 19 April 1991) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Paks II in the Nemzeti Bajnokság II.

name: Don Bradley
description: Donald "Don" Bradley (11 September 1924 – 26 June 1997) was an English footballer who played for Mansfield Town as a left-back. Bradley, a native of Annesley in Nottinghamshire, began his career at West Bromwich Albion in 1945, but never made any league appearances for them. In 1949, he joined Mansfield Town, and made his debut on 20 August 1949 in a Division Three North match against Southport. Bradley is one of Mansfield's longest-serving players of all time, and during a 13-year spell at the club, he played a total of 413 matches for the Stags, scoring six goals. His last game for the club came on 23 October 1961 in a League Cup tie against Cardiff City at Ninian Park that Mansfield lost 2-1. He left Mansfield at the end of the 1961-62 season, and subsequently played a couple of seasons for non-league Ilkeston Town before retiring from playing the game. He did continue to work in football into his 60s working and amongst other roles worked as a boys football coach at Oldswinford Hospital School in the West Midlands. He died in June 1997, at the age of 72.

name: Don Campbell (ice hockey)
description: Donald William Campbell (born July 12, 1925 in Drumheller, Alberta) is a retired ice hockey center that played for the Chicago Black Hawks.

name: Don Eddy (baseball)
description: Donald Eugene Eddy (born October 26, 1946 in Mason City, Iowa) is a former Major League Baseball pitcher who played for the Chicago White Sox in 1970 and 1971. In Eddy's only plate appearance on September 30, 1971, he hit a double off Bill Parsons of the Milwaukee Brewers.

name: Don Erickson
description: Don Lee Erickson (December 13, 1931 – August 1, 2012) was a pitcher in Major League Baseball. He played for the Philadelphia Phillies in 1958.

name: Don Furness (rugby union)
description: Donald Charles "Don" Furness (11 April 1921– c. 1993) was a rugby union player who represented Australia. Furness, a hooker, was born in Clovelly, New South Wales and claimed 1 international rugby cap for Australia.

name: Don Hankins
description: Donald Wayne Hankins (February 9, 1902 – May 16, 1963) was a Major League Baseball pitcher who played for the Detroit Tigers in 1927.

name: Don Hendrickson
description: Donald William Hendrickson (July 14, 1913 – January 19, 1977) was an American professional baseball player and former Major League Baseball pitcher. He played two seasons with the Boston Braves (1945–1946).

name: Don Herndon
