description: Etienne Mermer (born 26 January 1977, Vanuatu) is a footballer from Vanuatu. He currently plays for Tafea Football Club and, from June 2010, has been the coach of the Vanuatu national side.

name: Etimoni Timuani
description: Etimoni (Reme) Timuani (born 14 August 1991 in Funafuti) is a Tuvaluan footballer who currently plays for Tofaga A.

name: Etrit Berisha
description: Etrit Berisha (born 10 March 1989 in Pristina) is a Kosovan Albanian footballer who plays for Kalmar FF in the Swedish Allsvenskan and the Albanian national team. He is a goalkeeper known for his athleticism and for his penalty taking ability.

name: Euclides Gomes Vaz
description: Euclides Gomes Vaz, aka Bébé (born 19 May 1983), is a Portuguese futsal player who plays for Benfica and the Portuguese national futsal team.

name: Eudes Dagoulou
description: Eudes Cratia Dagoulou Koziade (often erroneously reported as Eudes Dagoulou) is a Central African Republic professional football player. He plays for MC Oran in Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Eufemio Cabral
description: Eufemio Raúl Fernández Cabral (born 21 March 1955) is a Paraguayan football midfielder who played for Paraguay in the 1986 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Club Guaraní.

name: Euforia (wrestler)
description: Euforia (born December 5, 1974) is the ring name of a Mexican Luchador Enmascarado, or masked professional wrestler currently working for Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre (CMLL). Euforia's real name is not a matter of public record, as is often the case with masked wrestlers in Mexico where their private lives are kept a secret from the wrestling fans. Euforia is a part of a wrestling group called Los Guerreros del Infierno under the leadership of Último Guerrero, the group also includes Niebla Roja. He was formerly part of the groups Los Nuevo Infernales led by El Satánico and later Virus, followed by Los Cancerberos del Infierno with Virus, Raziel, Cancerbero and Pólvora, while also forming a tag team with Nosferatu.

name: Eugène Empeyta
description: Eugène Empeyta (12 September 1892 – 20 May 1951) was a Swiss fencer. He competed at the 1920, 1924 and 1928 Summer Olympics. He was also the President of the Fédération Internationale d'Escrime from 1929 to 1932.

name: Eugène Laermans
description: Eugène Laermans (born 8 May 1910, date of death unknown) was a Belgian fencer. He competed at the 1936 and 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Eugène Salami
description: Eugène Salami is a Nigerian footballer currently plays for Debreceni VSC in the Hungarian Borsodi Liga.

name: Eugen Sidorenco
description: Eugen Sidorenco (born 19 March 1989) in Moldova is a footballer who plays as a Forward, Attacking midfielder. He currently plays for F.C. Nazareth Illit in Liga Leumit and the Moldova national football team.

name: Eugene Butterworth
description: Eugene Butterworth (born 19 September 1984) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is tighthead prop. He represents the Griquas in the Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup having previously played for the Boland Cavaliers.

name: Eugene Clifford
description: Eugene Clifford (born January 29, 1988) is an American football safety who is currently a member of the Texas Revolution of the Indoor Football League. He was signed by the Baltimore Ravens as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football for Tennessee State University and Ohio State University.

name: Eugene Fadiora
description: Eugene Fadiora (born June 1, 1988 in Wolverhampton) is a British mixed martial artist, who fights at Welterweight and Middleweight.

name: Eugene Fomumbod
description: Eugéne Fomumbod is a Cameroonian football midfielders player who currently plays for BFC Siófok.

name: Eugene Melaniphy
description: Eugene "Ted" Michael Joseph Patrick Melaniphy (5 February 1912 – 3 June 1991) played as a footballer in the Football League in the 1930s. He was born in Westport, Ireland. He made his debut for Plymouth Argyle in the 1931-32 season, and played his last game for them in 1935-36, playing a total of 68 Football League Second Division games for them, and scoring an impressive 33 times. He scored a hat-trick for them on 7 October 1933 in a 4-1 victory over Bradford Park Avenue. He joined Cardiff City for the 1936-37 season and played 20 league matches for them, scoring 8 goals. After a short spell with Worcester City he joined Northampton Town for the 1939-40 season, but the season was abandoned due to the war after only a few games.

name: Eugene Sims
description: Eugene Sims (born March 16, 1986) is an American football player, who currently plays as a defensive end for the St. Louis Rams.

name: Eugeni Valderrama Domènech
description: Eugeni Valderrama Domènech (born 19 July 1994) is a Spanish footballer who plays for Gimnàstic in the Spanish second division, as a midfielder.

name: Eugenia Escudero
description: Eugenia Escudero Lavat (26 November 1914 – 18 January 2011) was a Mexican fencer. She competed in the women's individual foil event at the 1932 Summer Olympics. She married Hans Backhoff and had 5 children. Escudero died on 18 January 2011, at the age of 96.

name: Eugenia Mateianu
description: Eugenia Mateianu (born 8 April 1936) is a Romanian fencer. She competed in the women's team foil event at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Eugenio Calvarese
description: Eugenio Calvarese (born 19 May 1992 in Alba Adriatica) is an Italian footballer who plays as a defender for L'Aquila on loan from Serie B side Pescara.

name: Eugeniya Pashkova
description: Eugeniya Pashkova (born February 19, 1989) is a professional Russian tennis player. On June 7, 2010, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 402 whilst her best doubles ranking was 201 on August 3, 2009.

name: Euloge Ahodikpe
description: Euloge Daniel Ahodikpe (born 1 May 1983) is a naturalized Togolese footballer.

name: Euri Gonzalez
description: Euri Gonzalez is a Dominican boxer in the Welterweight division. He is most known for his fight with the Mexican Saul Alvarez.

name: Euros Lewis
description: Euros John Lewis (born 31 January 1942) is a former Welsh cricketer. Lewis was a left-handed batsman who bowled right-arm off break. He was born at Llanelli, Carmarthenshire.

name: Eury Pérez
description: Eury Eduardo Pérez (born May 30, 1990) is a professional baseball outfielder for the Washington Nationals of Major League Baseball. Pérez participated in the 2010 All-Star Futures Game. After the 2011 season, the Nationals added Pérez to their 40 man roster to protect him from the Rule 5 draft. He is regarded as a speedy outfielder with limited power and emerging hitting ability. In 2012, he broke out with the bat across multiple minor league levels, batting .314. His speed is also well discussed, as he stole 64 bases for Hagerstown in 2010 and 54 in 2012 for GCL, Harrisburg, Syracuse, and Washington.

name: Eusebia Riquelme
description: Eusebia Riquelme (born November 27, 1969) is a retired female track and field athlete from Cuba who competed in the sprint events during her career.

name: Eusebio Bejarano
description: Eusebio Bejarano Vilaro is a former Spanish footballer. He played for Atlético de Madrid between 1968 and 1979, winning the Spanish League in 1970, 1973, and 1976, the Spanish Cup in 1972 and 1976, and the Intercontinental Cup in 1975. He played in the 1974 European Cup Final, which Atlético lost.

name: Eusebio Díaz
description: Eusebio Díaz (1901–1959) was a Paraguayan football midfielder who played for Paraguay in the 1930 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Club Guaraní.

name: Eusebio de Almeida
description: Eusebio Hermenio Correia de Almeida or Eusebio (born June 9, 1985) is a football player. He is the current midfielder for the Timor-Leste national football team.

name: Eustacio Chamorro
description: Eustacio Chamorro was a Paraguayan football defender who played for Paraguay in the 1930 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Club Presidente Hayes.

name: Euzébio Neto
description: Euzébio Andrade Silva Neto, commonly known as Euzébio Neto (born October 20, 1990 in Gararu) is a Brazilian footballer currently playing for Desportivo Brasil.

name: Eva-Maria Ittner
description: Eva-Maria Ittner (born 21 September 1961) is a German fencer. She competed in the women's individual and team épée events at the 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Eva Fjellerup
description: Eva Fjellerup (born 30 April 1962) is a Danish fencer. She competed in the women's individual épée event at the 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Evald Tipner
description: Evald Tipner (13 March 1906 – 18 July 1947) was Estonian football, ice hockey and bandy player. He was capped 66 times for Estonian national football team, 7 times for bandy national team and once for ice hockey team. Tipner was also a good track and field athlete. Some sources report him as the first goalscorer in the history of World Cup preliminary competition, having scored what would be an own goal for Sweden against Estonia 7 minutes into the game, on 11 June 1933, in Stockholm. Some other sources consider this was not an own goal, and that it was actually scored by Swedish captain Knut Kroon.

name: Evaldas Razulis
description: Evaldas Razulis is a Lithuanian footballer who plays for FBK Kaunas as a striker.

name: Evan Barlow
description: Evan Barlow (born November 8, 1985) is a Canadian professional ice hockey forward. He currently plays with the San Antonio Rampage of the American Hockey League (AHL) on loan from the Reading Royals of the ECHL.

name: Evan Chevalier
description: Evan Chevalier (born May 13, 1992) is a French footballer, who plays as a midfielder for Gazélec Ajaccio, on loan from Bordeaux.

name: Evan Crawford (baseball)
description: Evan Shane Crawford (born September 2, 1986) is an American professional baseball pitcher with the Toronto Blue Jays of Major League Baseball.

name: Evan Jenkins (footballer)
description: Evan Thomas Jenkins (26 June 1906 – 1990) was a Welsh professional footballer who played as a winger.

name: Evan Newton
description: Evan Alexander Newton (born April 1, 1988 in Virginia Beach, Virginia) is an American soccer player who currently plays for San Jose Earthquakes in Major League Soccer.

name: Evan Rankin
description: Evan Rankin (born March 28, 1986) is an American professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing with the Rochester Americans of the AHL. Rankin played regularly for the Toledo Walleye of the ECHL between 2009 and 2011. On November 25, 2011, the Notre Dame product was signed by the Rochester Americans of the American Hockey League to a professional tryout contract. After contributing immediately to the offense, Rankin remained with the Americans for the duration of the 2011–12 season, signing his first AHL contract and scoring an impressive 29 points in 35 games. On July 3, 2012 it was announced that Rankin had been re-signed by the Americans to a one-year AHL contract extension.

name: Evan Richards
description: Evan Sloane Richards (23 January 1862 - 19 April 1931) was a Welsh international rugby union forward who played club rugby for Swansea, captaining the club through three seasons during the 1880s. Richards' father was Member of Parliament for Ceredigion, Evan Matthew Richards.

name: Evan Rodriguez
description: Evan Junior Rodriguez (born on September 21, 1988) is an American football fullback and tight end for the Chicago Bears of the National Football League. He played college football for Temple. Rodriguez is of Puerto Rican descent.

name: Evan Scribner
description: Evan Lee Scribner (July 19, 1985) is an American professional baseball pitcher for the Oakland Athletics of Major League Baseball.

name: Evan Stoflet
description: Evan Stoflet (born May 16, 1984) is an American professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the Bakersfield Condors in the ECHL.

name: Evan Taylor
description: Evan Taylor (born 25 January 1989 in Jamaica) is a Jamaican footballer who currently plays for Harbour View F.C. , on loan from Reno.

name: Evan Thomas (rugby league)
description: Evan Thomas was a Welsh professional rugby league footballer of the 1910s, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Salford, as a Hooker, or Loose forward/Lock, i.e. number 9, or 13.

name: Evan Watkins
description: Evan William Watkins (1882–1956) was a Welsh rugby footballer who played rugby union for Abertillery and Monmouthshire and rugby league professionally for Warrington. He also played cricket for Monmouthshire.

name: Evandro Silva Resende
description: Evandro Silva Resende (or simply Evandro, born May 10, 1986 in Brazil) is a Brazilian football striker who currently plays for Americano Futebol Clube.

name: Evangelos Skotidas
description: Evangelos Skotidas (born 1895) was a Greek fencer. He competed at the 1920 and 1924 Summer Olympics.

name: Evanildo Borges Barbosa Júnior
description: Evanildo Borges Barbosa Júnior, known as Juninho (born January 11, 1990 in Salvador, Bahia), is a left back who plays for Série A club Palmeiras.

name: Evans (baseball)
description: Evans was a Major League Baseball left fielder who played in one game for the New Haven Elm Citys on June 1, 1875. Evans, whose first name is unknown, collected two hits in four at bat, with a run batted in.

name: Evans Mensah
description: Evans Russ Mensah (born 29 July 1987) is a Ghanaian football player, who plays for Chanthaburi F.C. , a Thailand Division 1 League team in Thailand.

name: Evans Soligo
description: Evans Soligo (born 14 January 1979) is an Italian footballer who plays for Paganese Calcio 1926. He spent his entire career at Italian Serie B and Lega Pro.

name: Eveliina Sarapää
description: Eveliina Sarapää is a Finnish former football midfielder. She played for FC Honka and HJK Helsinki in the Naisten Liiga and Asker Fotball in the Norwegian Toppserien. She was a member of the Finnish national team, and played the 2005 European Championship.

name: Evelio González
description: Evelio González (born 11 October 1952) is a Cuban fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Evelio Hernández
description: Gregorio Evelio Hernández López (born December 24, 1931, at Guanabacoa, Cuba) is a retired professional baseball player, a right-handed pitcher who appeared in 18 games for the 1956–1957 Washington Senators of Major League Baseball. He stood 6 feet 1 inch tall and weighed 195 pounds . Hernández' professional career on the North American mainland spanned 11 seasons (1954–1958; 1961–1964; 1966–1967) and 370 games in U.S. and Mexican minor league baseball. His notable seasons included 1955, when he won 23 games and lost 15 while pitching in 55 games and 271 innings for the Hobbs Sports of the Class C Longhorn League, and the following year, 1956, when he won 18 and lost 4, compiling a stellar 2.86 earned run average, for the Charlotte Hornets of the Class A Sally League. That performance earned him a late-season call-up to the Senators, when he appeared in four games. Hernández split the next season between Charlotte, the Double-A Chattanooga Lookouts, and the Senators, for whom he worked in 14 more games. Altogether, his Major League record included one complete game, a 1–1 won-lost record (with an ERA of 4.45), 28 bases on balls and 24 strikeouts in 58⅔ innings.

name: Evelyn Halls
description: Evelyn Halls (born 18 August 1972) is an Australian fencer. She competed in the women's individual épée events at the 2000 and 2004 Summer Olympics.

name: Evelyn Hill
description: Evelyn Vernon Llewellyn Hill (18 April 1907 – 25 October 1953) played first-class cricket for Somerset from 1926 to 1929. He was born at Cyntwell, Cardiff, Wales and died at Weston-super-Mare, Somerset.

name: Evelyn Mayr
description: Evelyn Mayr (born 12 May 1989) is an Italian tennis player. The older sister of tennis player Julia Mayr, she is ranked, as of 22 March 2010, World No. 307 in singles and No. 355 in doubles.

name: Evelyn Vicchiarello
description: Evelyn Vicchiarello is an Italian football striker, currently playing for Calcio Chiasiellis in Serie A. As an Under-19 international she played the 2004 U-19 European Championship, and the following year she played her first game for the senior Italian national team. She was included in the squad for the 2009 European Championship, and subsequently took part in the 2011 World Cup qualifying.

name: Evelyne Schneider
description: Evelyne Schneider is an Austrian pair skater. With partner Wilhelm Bietak, she represented Austria at the 1968 Winter Olympics, where they placed 15th.

name: Evens Gravel
description: Evens Gravel (born 23 October 1970) is a Canadian fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1992 and 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Evert Brouwers
description: Evert Brouwers (born 17 June 1990) is a Dutch professional footballer who is currently without a club. He formerly played for AGOVV Apeldoorn.

name: Everton Lemos
description: Everton Alexandre Lemos known as Biton (born 11 May 1987) is a Brazilian footballer.

name: Everton Nogueira
description: Everton Nogueira (born December 12, 1959) is a former Brazilian football player.

name: Evgeny Khvostov
description: Evgeny Khvostov is a Russian professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for HC Yugra of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL).

name: Evgeny Kirillov
description: Evgeny Kirillov is a Russian professional tennis player. On July 26, 2010, he reached his highest ATP singles ranking of 206.

name: Evgeny Konobry
description: Evgeny Konobry (born August 17, 1985) is a Russian professional ice hockey goaltender who played for HC Spartak Moscow of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL) during the 2010-11 season.

name: Evgeny Palenga
description: Evgeny Palenga (born January 27, 1993) is a Russian professional ice hockey defenceman. He played with HC Spartak Moscow in the Kontinental Hockey League during the 2010–11 KHL season.

name: Evgeny Shalunov
description: Evgeny Shalunov (born 8 January 1992) is a Russian professional road and track bicycle racer who rides for UCI Continental Team Lokosphinx. Shalunov has competed as a professional since the middle of the 2011 season, having signed a stagiaire deal with Team RadioShack in July 2011. A winner of eight national events in 2011 with Lokomotiv-Urbycolan, Shalunov signed with the Lokosphinx team for the 2012 season. After finishing fourth in the La Roue Tourangelle held in France in March, Shalunov won his first UCI Europe Tour race in April 2012, by winning the Vuelta a La Rioja in Spain. Attacking around 30 km from the finish in La Rioja, Shalunov soloed to the finish line to win by 28 seconds ahead of Euskaltel-Euskadi's Pablo Urtasun and team-mate Mikhail Antonov.

name: Evgeny Shtaiger
description: Evgeny Shtaiger is a professional ice hockey player who currently plays the 2010–11 season in the Kontinental Hockey League with Metallurg Novokuznetsk.

name: Evgeny Zhdanov
description: Evgeny Zhdanov (born July 20, 1983) is a professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for HK Beibarys Atyrau of the Kazakhstani Championship.

name: Evral Trapp
description: Evral Trapp (born January 22, 1987) is a Belizean professional defender currently playing for Hopkins FC.

name: Evyatar Baruchyan
description: Evyatar Baruchyan is an Israeli footballer who currently plays for Beitar Jerusalem. His brother Aviram Baruchyan also plays in Beitar.

name: Ewan Davies
description: David Evans George "Ewan" Davies (23 June 1887 – 2 September 1979) was a Welsh international rugby union wing who won two caps for the Wales national rugby union team. He played club rugby for Cardiff RFC and London Welsh RFC and county rugby for Middlesex. Outside rugby he was a solicitor and successful businessman and owned a chain of cinemas.

name: Ewerton José Almeida Santos
description: Ewerton José Almeida Santos (born 23 March 1989) is a Brazilian footballer who plays for FC Anzhi Makhachkala as a central defender.

name: Eyad Abugharqud
description: Eyad Abugharqud is a Palestinian professional football (soccer) player currently playing for Hebron-based Shabab Al-Khaleel of the West Bank Premier League. He was the league's joint-top leading scorer in 2010–11 with Al-Am'ary scoring an impressive 20 goals in 22 league games. He received his first national team cap against Afghanistan on 3 July 2011.

name: Eyal Erlich
description: Eyal Erlich (born 1 January 1977) is a former professional tennis player from Israel.

name: Eynon Hawkins
description: Eynon Hawkins (birth registered July–September 1920 – 2001) is a Welsh professional rugby league footballer of the 1940s and '50s, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Salford, and Rochdale Hornets, as a Prop, i.e. number 8 or 10, during the era of contested scrums. His birth was registered in Bridgend district.

name: Eze Collins
description: Eze Collins (born 17 April 1985) is a Mozambique Professional footballer, who is currently playing for Delhi United in the I-league 2nd Division, India's 2nd division football league. Eze is a Forward (association football) but is also able to play anywhere in midfield. He was born in Lagos, Nigeria. He is highly experienced having already played in Nigeria, Belarus, Uzbekistan, Sri Lanka, Nepal, Bhutan and India. He is born to a Nigerian father and a Mozambican mother.

name: Ezra Lincoln
description: Ezra Perry Lincoln (November 17, 1868 – May 7, 1951) was a pitcher in Major League Baseball who played for the Cleveland Spiders and Syracuse Stars during the 1890 season. He continued to play in the minors through 1899, in the New England League.

name: Fábio Emanuel Moreira Silva
description: Fábio Emanuel Moreira Silva (born 5 April 1985) is a Cape Verdean international footballer who plays professionally for Metalurh Zaporizhya, as a midfielder.

name: Fábio Francisco Barros da Trindade
description: Fábio Francisco Barros da Trindade or simply Paulista (born April 28, 1988 in Paulista), is a Brazilian Striker. He currently plays for Santa Cruz.

name: Fábio Marques
description: Fábio Igor Ribeiro Marques (born 25 December 1990 in Vila Nova de Famalicão) is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Clube Oriental Lisboa as a defender.

name: Fábio Moura
description: Fábio Emanuel Rodrigues Moura is a Portuguese footballer who plays for C.D. Trofense as a forward.

name: Fábio Nunes Fernandes
description: Fábio Nunes Fernandes (born 15 January 1980) is a Brazilian football player.

name: Fábio Pereira de Azevedo
description: Fábio Pereira de Azevedo (born 1 January 1977), known simply as Fabinho, is a naturalized Togolese football striker, who currently plays for the Brazilian side Concórdia Futebol Clube. During his 4 years in the Salvadoran football, he won for Isidro Metapán the Clausura 2007. He scored the goal of the title, already in the extension.

name: Félicité Hamidouche
description: Félicité Tiziri Hamidouche (born 20 January 1990 in Pontoise) is a French football player who currently plays French club Paris Saint-Germain of the Division 1 Féminine. She is a former graduate of the women's section of the Clairefontaine academy and plays as a defender. Hamidouche is a former women's youth international for France having represented her nation at under-17 and under-19 level.

name: Félix Cortés
description: Félix Cortés (born 15 March 1989) is a Chilean football player that currently plays for Deportes La Serena.

name: Félix Galimi
description: Félix Galimi (1 January 1921 – 2 January 2005) was an Argentine fencer. He competed at the 1948, 1952 and 1964 Summer Olympics.

name: Félix Guerreiro
description: Félix Marques Guerreiro (born 5 August 1950) is a former Portuguese footballer who played as a forward.

name: Félix Prieto
description: Félix Jacinto Prieto Partido (born 24 May 1975) is a Spanish footballer who plays for CD El Campello as a forward.

name: Félix Quero
description: Félix Quero López is a Spanish footballer who plays for UD Logroñés as a forward.

name: Félix Salvador
description: Félix Martins Salvador (born 1 August 1932) is a former Portuguese footballer who played as forward.

name: Félix Tagawa
description: Félix Tagawa (born 23 March 1976) in Tahiti is a footballer who plays as a Striker. He currently plays for AS Dragon in the Tahiti Division Fédérale.

name: Férébory Doré
description: Férébory Doré is a Congolese football striker currently playing for Angers SCO. He made his debut with the team in the 2009-10 season, playing in six matches and scoring once.

name: F.A. Marple
description: F.A. Marple was a footballer who played for Burslem Port Vale in the 1890s.

name: F. Stuart Wilkins
description: F. Stuart "Stu" Wilkins (born c. 1928, Canton, Ohio) is a former American football player, lawyer, and businessman. He played at the guard position for the University of Michigan football team from 1945 to 1948 and was a starter on the Wolverines undefeated teams in 1947 and 1948. He practiced law for more than 50 years in Canton, Ohio. He was one of the leaders behind the establishment of the Pro Football Hall of Fame in Canton, serving on the steering committee that prepared the presentation to the NFL, and serving for more than 40 years on its board of trustees. He also served as the chairman of the board of the American Automobile Association from 1989 to 1991.

name: Faan Fourie
description: Stefanis Jakobus "Faan" Fourie (born 10 December 1982) is a South African cricketer who played two matches for Boland during the 2010–11 season. He is a right-handed batsman and right-arm medium-fast bowler.

name: Fabián Bordagaray
description: Fabián Bordagaray (born 15 February 1987) is an Argentine football forward who plays for San Lorenzo on loan from Argentinos Juniors.

name: Fabián Castillo
description: Fabián Andrés Castillo Sánchez (born June 17, 1992 in Cali) is a Colombian footballer who currently plays for FC Dallas in Major League Soccer.

name: Fabián Moyano
description: Fabián Gustavo Moyano Batres (born 2 January 1986) is an Argentine footballer who currently plays for Primera B side San Luis Quillota as goalkeeper.

name: Fabián Saavedra
description: Fabián Saavedra Muñoz (born 27 January 1992) is a Chilean footballer who plays for the Chilean Primera División side Unión Española as a Striker.

name: Fabián Slančík
description: Fabián Slančík (born 22 September 1991 in Veľký Krtíš) is a Slovak football forward who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FK Dukla Banská Bystrica.

name: Fabián Vázquez
description: Fabián Vázquez (born 1943) is a Mexican equestrian. He was born in Zimapán, Hidalgo. He won a bronze medal in team eventing at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow.

name: Fabian Heimpel
description: Fabian Heimpel (born 21 August 1990) is a German international rugby union player, playing for the University of Cape Town RFC and the German national rugby union team. He made his debut for Germany against Portugal on 27 February 2010. Heimpel has also played for the Germany's 7's side in the past, like at the 2009 Hannover Sevens. Heimpel was top scorer of the Rugby-Bundesliga in 2009-10 with 225 points. At the end of the 2010-11 season, Heimpel, together with his friend Florian Wehrspann, moved to South Africa for a year, to join University of Cape Town RFC, a team the former German international Bodo Sieber used to play for, but opted to return to Germany early. Fabian Heimpel was one of four German rugby players, together with Mustafa Güngör, Raphael Pyrasch and Bastian Himmer, who were promised by the DRV that they could join the Sportkompanie of the Bundeswehr, a special sports unit within the German Army. This was however not the case, with no places available in the unit for male rugby players until 2012. This let to great resentment by the players torwards the DRV and its then-chairman Claus-Peter Bach because all four had turned down other options in favour of the promised place in the Sportkompanie. Heimpel subsequently opted out of military service altogether and chose civilian service instead.

name: Fabian Joseph (footballer)
description: Fabian Joseph (born 12 February 1985) is an international soccer player from Saint Lucia, who plays as a defender.

name: Fabian Kling
description: Fabian Kling (born July 24, 1987) is a German footballer who currently plays for San Antonio Scorpions in the North American Soccer League.

name: Fabian Koch
description: Fabian Koch (born 24 June 1989) is an Austrian footballer who plays for Austria Wien.

name: Fabian Schär
description: Fabian Schär (born 20 December 1991 in Wil) is a Swiss professional footballer currently playing for FC Basel. He is right footed. He was selected to play in the Swiss football team at the 2012 Summer Olympics.

name: Fabien Lewis
description: Fabien "Fari" Lewis is a Trinidadian-born American, professional footballer who is currently playing for Kaya FC in the United Football League.

name: Fabijan Komljenović
description: Fabijan Komljenović (born 16 January 1968) is a former Croatian football player. He made his international debut against Slovenia at Murska Sobota on 19 June 1991, where he scored the winning goal (0-1). This was his single appearance for the Croatia national football team. While playing for Rijeka, he was nicknamed the Caniggia from Kantrida due to his style of play and physical appearance.

name: Fabio Albarelli
description: Fabio Albarelli (1943–1995) was an Italian competitive sailor and Olympic medalist.

name: Fabio Alves
description: For the player born 1986 also called Fabinho, see Fábio da Silva Alves. Fábio Alves Macedo (born 16 March 1985 in Ariquemes) known as Fabinho, is a Brazilian footballer who plays for A-League club Sydney FC.

name: Fabio Ayres
description: Fabio Ayres (born 1 January 1991 in Guarulhos) is a Brazilian footballer who plays for Perugia, on loan from Udinese.

name: Fabio Cassanelli
description: Fabio Cassanelli is an Italian Table football player. He is a multiple world champion. Partnering with Francesco Bonanno, he has won the gold medal for Disabled Doubles category at the ITSF World Championship (Nantes) in 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012 and it's a titleholder of the World CUP 2013.

name: Fabio Catacchini
description: Fabio Catacchini (born 19 January 1984) is an Italian footballer who plays for Serie B club Frosinone.

name: Fabio Concas
description: Fabio Concas (born 17 November 1986) is an Italian footballer who plays for Carpi.

name: Fabio Cusaro
description: Fabio Cusaro (born 20 November 1984 in Novara) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Tritium in Lega Pro Prima Divisione, Italian football's third tier, on loan from Serie B side, Cesena. He joined Foligno on a six-month loan deal and will return to Cesena on 30 June 2011.

name: Fabio Giordano
description: Fabio Marco Giordano (born 6 February 1983) is an Italian footballer who plays for Sarego on loan from Cittadella.

name: Fabio Gurgel
description: Fábio Duca Gurgel do Amaral is an 8 time Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu World champion. He has been practicing Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu (BJJ) since the age of 13. He received his black belt at the age of 19 from Romero "Jacaré" Cavalcanti. Along with Cavalcanti he is co-founder of the Alliance Jiu Jitsu Team. He is the teacher of BJJ and ADCC World Champion Marcelo Garcia. He is President of the Brazil based Professional League of Jiu- Jitsu

name: Fabio Lauria
description: Fabio Lauria (born 30 August 1986) is an Italian footballer who plays for Venezia.

name: Fabio Lebran
description: Fabio Lebran (born 12 January 1987) is an Italian footballer who plays for Italian Serie A club Parma.

name: Fabio Paratici
description: Fabio Paratici (born July 13, 1972 in Borgonovo Val Tidone) is an Italian former football player, currently working in the role of Sporting Director for Italian club Juventus.

name: Fabio Souza dos Santos
description: Fabio Souza dos Santos or simply Fabinho (born September 7, 1983 in Recife) is a forward player from Brazil.

name: Fabio Valsesia
description: Fabio Valsesia (born April 26, 1981 in Borgomanero) is a retired professional Italian. He played in the Serie B for A.C. Monza Brianza 1912.

name: Fabio Visone
description: Fabio Visone (born 26 February 1983 in Naples) is an Italian football player. He currently plays for U.S. Foggia as a midfielder.

name: Fabio da Silva Lopes
description: Fabio da Silva Lopes, commonly known as Fabio da Silva (born 9 January 1986), is a Portuguese rugby union football player. He plays as a Scrum-half. He made his club debut in France where he played for Lyon from 2005 till 2008 where he signed for Villeurbanne for a season before moving to Saint-Étienne for 2 seasons. He currently plays for Bourgoin as of 2011 and has played 25 games for them scoring 4 tries.

name: Fabrício Manini
description: Fabrício Manini aka Fabricio (born October 8, 1980 in Água Boa, Mato Grosso) is a Brazilian footballer who plays central back. He currently plays for Fortaleza.

name: Fabrício dos Santos Messias
description: Fabrício dos Santos Messias or simply Fabrício (born 28 March 1990) is a Brazilian football player who is currently playing for Segunda Liga side Portimonense.

name: Fabrice Estebanez
description: Fabrice Estebanez (born December 26, 1981 in Carcassonne), is a French (former)rugby league player and now rugby union player. He is a utility back and is able to play center and flyhalf. He has played for his CA Brive before joining Racing Metro 92.

name: Fabrice Guérit
description: Fabrice Guérit is a former professional footballer who played as a central defender. He played one Division 2 match in the 1992-93 season.

name: Fabrice Landreau
description: Fabrice Landreau (born August 1, 1968 in Angoulême), is a French rugby union player. He has played for his club, Stade Français. Fabrice Landreau began playing Rugby at SC Angoulême. He moved for FC Grenoble coached by Jacques Fouroux. After many injuries he moved to Neath RFC and one year later Bristol Rugby. He played for Stade Français which he won two Top 14 He earned his only cap for the France national team on November 4, 2000 against the Australia. After ending his player career, he joined Fabien Galthié for Coaching Forwards.

name: Fabrice Martin
description: Fabrice Martin (born 11 September 1986) is a French professional tennis player. He competes mainly on the ATP Challenger Tour and ITF Futures, both in singles and doubles. He reached his highest ATP singles ranking, No. 259 on 12 September 2011, and his highest ATP doubles ranking, No. 202, on 26 September 2011.

name: Fabrice Pauline
description: Fabrice Pauline (born December 5, 1982 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for Curepipe Starlight SC in the Mauritian Premier League and for the Mauritius national football team as a midfielder. He is featured on the Mauritian national team in the official 2010 FIFA World Cup video game.

name: Fabrice Piemontesi
description: Fabrice Piemontesi (born 16 August 1983) is an Italian professional road bicycle racer.

name: Fabrice Pithia
description: Fabrice Pithia (born May 7, 1987 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for Curepipe Starlight SC in the Mauritian Premier League and for the Mauritius national football team as a midfielder.

name: Fabricio Andre Pires
description: Fabricio Andre Pires (born January 29, 1982) is a former Brazilian football player.

name: Fabricio Lenci
description: Fabricio Lenci (born February 24, 1984 in San Nicolás de los Arroyos, Argentina) is an Argentine footballer currently playing for Crucero del Norte of the Primera B Nacional in Argentina. Lenci also has a double nationality, the second one being Italian.

name: Fabricio Monteiro
description: Fabricio Monteiro is a mixed martial artist from Brazil. He has a professional MMA record of 18–9. Monteiro has a second degree black belt in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu which he was awarded by Adilson Lima and has won numerous BJJ competitions and tournaments including the Absolute Section of the Pan American Championship (Jiu Jitsu) in 2000. He is a member of the Evolve MMA fight team and is based in Singapore. Monteiro made his professional MMA debut in 2004, winning by TKO and went on to win his next 10 fights. In 2006 he made his debut for Deep, winning by submission and he won all of his first three fights for the Japanese promotion. His first loss for Deep came at the hands of Satoru Kitaoka who submitted him in the second round of their fight which was a qualifier for the Pride Lightweight Grand Prix. In 2009 Monteiro retired from professional MMA competition because he was not earning enough money to train full-time.

name: Fabrizio Anzalone
description: Fabrizio Anzalone (born 24 July 1978) is an Italian footballer who plays for Lega Pro Prima Divisione team Carrarese. He had played over 140 games in Serie C1 and over 110 games in Serie C2. He only briefly played in Serie B in 2006–07 season.

name: Fabrizio Di Bella
description: Fabrizio Di Bella (born March 2, 1988 in Rome) is an Italian professional football player. Currently, he plays for S.S. Barletta Calcio on loan from A.S. Livorno Calcio. He made his Livorno debut on September 18, 2010, in a 0-0 draw at home to Portogruaro.

name: Fabrizio Garattoni
description: Fabrizio Garattoni is a former Italian figure skater and four-time national champion from 1993-96. He competed in several European and World Championships.

name: Faby Apache
description: Fabiola Balbuena Torres (born December 26, 1980) is a Mexican Luchadora, or female professional wrestler best known under the ring name Faby Apache (sometimes written as "Fabi Apache"). Between 2005 and 2009 she was involved in a long running storyline that revolved around her relationship with Billy Boy, her real life husband as well as her father Gran Apache, sister Mari Apache and even saw Billy Boy and Faby Apache's son Marvin play a part in it. She won the 2008 Reina de Reinas tournament and has held the AAA World Mixed Tag Team Championship three times.

name: Fachry Husaini
description: Fachry Husaini (born 27 July 1965 in Lhokseumawe) is an Indonesian football manager who previously manages the Indonesia Super League club Bontang FC. He is a former player of the Indonesian national team.

name: Fachtna Collins
description: Fachtna Collins is an Irish sportsperson. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Ilen Rovers and was a member of the Cork senior inter-county team in the 1990s and 2000s.

name: Facundo Píriz
description: Facundo Julián Píriz González, commonly known as Facundo Píriz, is a Uruguayan football player who plays as a Defensive midfielder for Terek Grozny.

name: Facundo Pereyra
description: Facundo Abel Pereyra (born 3 September 1987) is an Argentine footballer who currently plays in the Primera B Nacional side Gimnasia y Esgrima La Plata.

name: Fadel Jilal
description: Fadel Jilal (born 4 March 1964) is a Moroccan football midfielder who played for Morocco in the 1986 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Wydad Casablanca.

name: Fadel Settara
description: Fadel Settara (born May 18, 1975) is an Algerian football player. He has played for Algeria national team.

name: Fadhil Salim
description: Fadhil Salim (born 24 January 1983) is a Singaporean goalkeeper and currently plays for S. League club Hougang United FC. Fadhil started playing for Gombak United FC in 2009. In 2010, he joined Hougang United FC. Fadhil was nominated by the club for the YEO'S People's Choice Award 2010 for the 2010 S. League season.

name: Fadime Suna
description: Fadime Suna (born October 25, 1986 in Eskişehir) is a Turkish female middle distance and long distance runner. She is a member of the Beşiktaş J.K. Athletics Team in Istanbul. Fadime Suna began her athletics career following an unsuccessful start in basketball in the primary school. She says she is thankful to her teacher, who draw her attention to running. She won the gold medal in the 10,000 m event at the 2011 Summer Universiade held in Shenzen, China.

name: Faed Arsène
description: Faed Arsène (born 21 June 1985) is a Malagasy international footballer who plays in Belgium for Royal Mouscron-Péruwelz, as a striker.

name: Fahad Al Ansari
description: Fahad Ebrahim Al Ansari is a Kuwaiti footballer who is a Midfielder for the Kuwaiti Premier League club Al Qadsia.

name: Fahad Al Shammari
description: Fahad Sattam Al Shammari is a Qatari footballer who is a midfielder for Al Gharafa. He is the brother of Saad Al-Shammari, the former captain of the Qatar national team.

name: Fahad Awadh
description: Fahad Awadh is a Kuwaiti footballer who is a defender for the Kuwaiti Premier League club Al Kuwait.

name: Fahad Hadeed
description: Fahad Salim Hadid Obaid Ghraib, commonly known as Fahad Hadeed, is an Emirati footballer. who plays as a Midfielder for Al Wasl FC and the UAE national under-20 football team. Fahad used to play for Al Sharjah SC since his youth years. He was released on a free transfer following a dispute with the club, he has then signed a new contract with Al Wasl FC in December 2011.

name: Fahad Khalfan
description: Fahad Khalfan Al Bloushi (born 23 March 1992) is a Qatari footballer who is a striker for Al-Sailiya. He has also played for the Qatar national team.

name: Fahprakorb Rakkiatgym
description: Fahprakorb Rakkiatgym born is a professional boxer from Thailand. He was a former World Boxing Federation Champion.

name: Fahrudin Đurđević
description: His surname in Macedonian can also be transliterated as Ǵurǵeviḱ, and in Serbian is written as Ђурђевић in Cyrillic, or Đurđević/Djurdjević in Latin script. Fahrudin Gjurgjević is a current Macedonian football player of who plays in Spartak Subotica. He had previously played in the Macedonian First League with Makedonija GP and Vardar. He moved to Serbia in summer 2011 to sign with SuperLiga club FK Spartak Zlatibor Voda. He can play either as forward or any side winger. He has been a regular member of the Macedonian U-19 national team. On August 2011 he has been called for the Macedonian U-19 national team to play a friendly match against Cyprus U21 on September 6.

name: Fahrul Razi Kamaruddin
description: Fahrul Razi Bin Kamaruddin (born 12 April 1986) is a Malaysian Footballer.

name: Fain Skinner
description: Fain Skinner (born February 21, 1985 in Live Oak, Florida) is an American stock car racing driver. Winner of the 1999 World Karting Association National Championship, he races part-time in the NASCAR Nationwide Series and the ARCA Racing Series.

name: Fairoz Hasan
description: Fairoz Hasan (born 22 November 1988) is a Singaporean footballer, who plays Forward for S. League, Gombak United.

name: Faisal Al Badri
description: Faisal Saleh Al-Badri (born 4 June 1990 in Libya) is a Libyan footballer who plays for Al-Ahly Benghazi as a midfielder. He is a member of Libya national football team, played at 2012 Africa Cup of Nations. He is a reserve player.

name: Faisal Sakhizada
description: Faisal Safa Sakhizada (born 15 June 1990) is an Afghan association footballer who currently plays for Dandenong Thunder SC, football club from Afghanistan. He is also a player in Afghanistan national football team, and he has 12 caps. He wears jersey number 4 and his position on the field is centre back defender. He played in World Cup 2010 qualifiers,[1 1] and 2014 FIFA World Cup Qualification. One of the most best preformed Afghan player has been to many countries to expand his career, and is planning on continuing his dream career as a football player.

name: Faizal Zainal
description: Faizal Zainal (born 12 February 1974) is a retired Malaysian international footballer. His twin brother, Khairil Zainal was also a footballer. Their younger brother, Abdul Halim Zainal is currently a footballer with Negeri Sembilan FA, where the twins formerly played for.

name: Fan Qunxiao
description: Fan Qunxiao (Chinese: 樊群霄, born 18 September 1987) is a professional Chinese footballer who plays as a central defender for Chongqing F.C. in the China League One division.

name: Fan Xiaodong
description: Fan Xiaodong is a Chinese footballer who currently plays for Hangzhou Greentown F.C. as a midfielder in the Chinese Super League.

name: Fanndís Friðriksdóttir
description: Fanndís Friðriksdóttir (born 9 May 1990) is an Icelandic football player who plays as a midfielder. Fanndís is currently part of Iceland women's national team and competed in UEFA Women's Euro 2009. Fanndís comes from Vestmannaeyjar but plays in Kópavogur for Breiðablik. Fanndís scored her 1st goal for the Icelandic national team in a 1-0 win against China in Algarve Cup 2012.

name: Fannie Desforges
description: Fannie Desforges is a Canadian athlete from Fournier, Ontario. She is the first Canadian woman to win a competition in the Red Bull Crashed Ice competition. In addition, she has competed for the Ottawa Gee Gees women's ice hockey program in Canadian Interuniversity Sport, while competing for Team Canada at the 2011 Street and Ball Hockey World Championships in Bratislava, Slovakia.

name: Fanny Vágó
description: Fanny Vágó (born 23 July 1991 in Szeged) is a Hungarian football striker, currently playing for MTK Hungária FC in Hungary's Noi NB I. She has also played in Germany's Regionalliga for TSV Crailsheim and Iceland's Úrvalsdeild for Throttur. She is a member of the Hungarian national team.

name: Fanouris Goundoulakis
description: Fanouris Goundoulakis (Greek: Φανούρης Γουνδουλάκης; born 13 July 1983) is a Greek football player currently playing for Panionios in the Greek Super League.

name: Fantasma de la Quebrada
description: Edmundo Ibaes Salas (date of birth unknown) is a Mexican luchador, or professional wrestler, best known under the ring name Fantasma de la Quebrada (Spanish for "the Ghost of the Broken"). Ibaes is no the first wrestler to use the name, the original Fantasma de la Quebrada was active from the 1960s until the 1970s and was a good friend of Ibaes father and he gave Ibaes permission to use the name as well.

name: Faouzi Ghoulam
description: Faouzi Ghoulam (born 1 February 1991 in Saint-Priest-en-Jarez) is an Algerian footballer who plays for AS Saint-Étienne in Ligue 1.

name: Faqir Hussain
description: Faqir Hussain, is a retired Pakistani professional footballer.

name: Farès Benabderahmane
description: Farès Benabderahmane (born August 11, 1987 in Sidi Aïssa) is an Algerian football player. He currently plays for ES Sétif in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Farès Boudemagh
description: Farès Boudemagh (born 8 June 1982 in Algiers) is an Algerian professional footballer. He currently plays as a defender for the Algerian Ligue 2 club Olympique de Médéa.

name: Farahia Teuiria
description: Farahia Teuiria (born 29 August 1972) in Tahiti is a footballer who plays as a Midfielder. He previously played for AS Vaiete. He currently plays for AS Tiaré in the Tahiti Division Fédérale and the Tahiti national football team.

name: Fardin Abedini
description: Fardin Abedidni is an Iranian football defender, who currently plays for Iran's Premier Football League Tractor Sazi usually as a midfielder.

name: Farid El-Ashmawi
description: Farid El-Ashmawi is an Egyptian fencer. He competed in the team foil events at the 1960 and 1964 Summer Olympics. At the 1960 Games, he represented the United Arab Republic.

name: Farid El Alagui
description: Farid El Alagui (born 10 February 1985) is a professional footballer who currently plays as a striker for Football League One club Brentford.

name: Farid Mellouli
description: Farid Mellouli (born July 7, 1984 in Sétif) is an Algerian football player. He currently plays for ASO Chlef in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Farid Villaume
description: Farid Villaume (born February 10, 1975), is a French Muay Thai kickboxer, having won world titles in different boxes fists feet.

name: Farid Zerroukhat
description: Farid Zerroukhat is an Algerian professional footballer. He currently plays as a midfielder for the Algerian Ligue 2 club Olympique de Médéa.

name: Farkhad Gystarov
description: Farkhad Raufovich Gystarov (Russian: Фархад Рауфович Гыстаров; born November 21, 1994) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Kavkaztransgaz-2005 Ryzdvyany.

name: Farouk Chafaï
description: Farouk Chafaï (born June 23, 1990 in Algiers) is an Algerian professional footballer. He is currently playing for USM Alger in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Farrukh Choriev
description: Farrukh Choriev (born 27 July 1984) is an Tajikistan player, who currently plays for Regar-TadAZ Tursunzoda.

name: Farrukh Dustov
description: Farrukh Dustov (born May 22, 1986) is an Uzbek tennis player playing on the ITF Futures Tour and ATP Challenger Tour. On April 30, 2007, he reached his highest ATP singles ranking of 173. He is coached by Manuel Gasbarri.

name: Faruk Namdar
description: Faruk Namdar is a former professional Turkish footballer. Namdar made 104 appearances in the Turkish Süper Lig and 12 appearances in the German 2. Fußball-Bundesliga during his playing career.

name: Fasal Shahid
description: Fasal Hassan Shahid (born 4 March 1986) is an English cricketer. Shahid is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born in Birmingham, Warwickshire. Shahid made his only List A appearance for the Marylebone Cricket Club against Bangladesh A. In this match he took a single wicket, that of Shakib Al Hasan, for the cost of 33 runs from 7 overs. With the bat he scored 2 runs before being dismissed LBW by Rubel Hossain. He made his debut for Herefordshire in the 2009 MCCA Knockout Trophy against Wiltshire. Shahid currently plays Minor counties cricket for Herefordshire. He has previously played Second XI cricket for the Worcestershire Second XI.

name: Fata Salkunič
description: Fata Salkunič is a currently unattached Slovenian football midfielder, currently playing for USV Jena in the German Bundesliga. She previously played for ZNK Maribor and Krka Novo Mesto in the Slovenian League, Hamburger SV in the Bundesliga and FC Basel in the Swiss Nationalliga A. She is a member of the Slovenian national team.

name: Fatah Masoud
description: Fatah Masoud (born on 24 September 1989) is a Libyan futsal goalkeeper. Masoud played for the Libya national futsal team at the 2008 FIFA Futsal World Cup.

name: Fatah Nsaief
description: Abdul-Fatah Nsaief Jassim (born 2 February 1951) is an Iraqi football goalkeeper who played for Iraq in the 1986 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Al-Jaish.

name: Fathi Al-Khoga
description: Fathi Al-Khoga (born on 8 May 1984) is a Libyan futsal player. Al-Khoga played for the Libya national futsal team at the 2008 FIFA Futsal World Cup.

name: Fathi Jabir
description: Fathi Jabir (born 29 December 1980) is a Yemeni football striker and Club Al-Tilal، Yemen's top scorer the season: 1998/99

name: Fatih Atık
description: Fatih Atik is a French-Turkish professional footballer. He currently plays for the French Ligue 2 side Guingamp. He plays as a midfielder. He is a Turkish and a French citizen.

name: Fatih Baydar
description: Fatih Baydar (born November 25, 1983) is a Turkish weightlifter competing in the –85 kg division. At the 2012 European Championships held in Antalya, Turkey, he became silver medalist.

name: Fatih Egedik
description: Fatih Egedik (born 2 May 1982) is a Turkish professional footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Altay Izmir. Egedik was also a youth international.

name: Fatih Keleş
description: Fatih Keleş (born on November 27, 1989 in Trabzon, Turkey) is a European champion Turkish amateur boxer competing in the lightweight division. He is a member of the Kocaeli BB Kağıt S.K. in Izmit. He is coached by Nazmi Dalkıran.

name: Fatih Kocamis

He had season ending Tommy John surgery on March 28 and is expected to miss the entire 2013 season.

name: Fernando Saavedra
description: Fernando Antonio Saavedra Valencia is an a Chilean football defender and his currently playing for San Felipe. Between 2006 and 2007 he played for Quilmes of the Primera División Argentina.

name: Fernando Salas
description: Noel Fernando Salas (born May 30, 1985) is a Major League Baseball pitcher for the St. Louis Cardinals.

name: Fernando Sanjurjo
description: Fernando Sanjurjo (born 9 July 1982 in San Martín) is an Argentine football midfielder currently playing in Aurora.

name: Fernando Santis
description: Augusto Fernando Santís Ahumada (born 10 January 1958) is a Chilean former footballer.

name: Fernando Saraceni
description: Fernando Saraceni (19 January 1891 – 1956) was an Italian footballer. His brother Luigi Saraceni was also a footballer and played as a defender for SS Lazio in 1920s. Fernando began his football career in 1907 and spent all his career playing for SS Lazio. He played first in forward role and since 1921 in full back role. He was also team captain from 1919 to 1923. In 1915 he served the Italian Army during the World War I. He retired from football in 1924; later he held management roles for SS Lazio. He died in 1956.

name: Fernando Telles Ribeiro
description: Fernando Telles Ribeiro is a male diver from Brazil. He joined the Brazilian national diving squad at the age of 18, and competed at the Melbourne Olympics in 1956 and the Rome Olympics in 1960. Ribeiro also won the South American Diving Championships four times, and competed in the Pan-American Games. He continues to compete in 'Masters' diving competitions,having obtained the title of World Masters' Champion at the Nike Olympic Games in Portland USA in 1998 and Champion of the North American Open Masters in Oxford, USA in 2000.

name: Fernando Trejo
description: Fernando Trejo (born July 5, 1974) is a Mexican professional boxer in the Lightweight division and former WBC FECARBOX Super Featherweight champion, a title he never lost. He is rated as the 28th best Mexican Lightweight in the world.

name: Fernando Uribe
description: Fernando Uribe Himcapie (born 1 January 1988) is a Colombian footballer who plays as a striker for Atlético Nacional.

name: Fernando Zunzunegui
description: Fernando Zunzunegui Rodríguez is a retired Spanish footballer, who played as a defender.

name: Fernando de Castro Gonçalves
description: Fernando de Castro Gonçalves (born 27 January 1941) is a Brazilian former footballer who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Fernando de la Peña
description: Fernando de la Peña (born 22 August 1959) is a Spanish fencer. He competed in the épée events at the 1988, 1992 and 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Ferris Jennings
description: Ferris Gordon Jennings (November 10, 1913 – December 22, 1995) was an American football, baseball and basketball player. He played college football at the quarterback and safety positions for the University of Michigan in 1934 and 1936. He was the starting quarterback for the 1934 Michigan Wolverines football team. Jennings also played for the Michigan Wolverines men's basketball and Michigan Wolverines baseball teams between 1935 and 1937.

name: Ferry Aman Saragih
description: Ferry Aman Saragih (FAS) (born 12 June 1987) is an Indonesian national football player who currently plays for Pro Duta. His position is midfielder.

name: Fiachra Lynch
description: Fiachra Lynch is an Irish sportsperson. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Valley Rovers and has been a member of the Cork senior inter-county team since 2009. Before joining the senior team he enjoyed much success at underage level. He won a Munster Minor Championship in 2005. He then joined the Cork Under 21 team in 2006 where he won a Munster Championship medal; he also played in the All Ireland Final that year but Cork lost out to Mayo. In 2007 Cork retained their Munster Championship and went one better from the year before and beat Laois to give Lynch an All Ireland Under 21 medal. He also played with the Cork junior team. He won a Munster Championship medal with them in 2007 and later added an All Ireland medal. At club level he helped Valley Rovers win a County Intermediate Championship.

name: Fidel Luña
description: Fidel Luña was a Mexican fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1948.

name: Fidel Maldonado
description: Fidel Maldonado (born July 23, 1991 in Albuquerque, New Mexico) is an undefeated Mexican-American professional boxer and the current WBC Youth World Lightweight Champion.

name: Fidel Mondragón
description: Fidel Eduardo Mondragón Palomo (born February 24, 1981 in Jiquilisco) is a Salvadoran footballer who currently plays for Isidro Metapán in the Salvadoran Premier League.

name: Fidel Muñoz
description: Fidel Alexander Monterrosa Muñoz is a professional Colombian boxer in the Light Welterweight division and is the former Colombian National Lightweight champion.

name: Fifita Moala
description: Fifita Moala (born 30 August 1980), was a Tongan rugby league footballer of the 2000s. He played for the Melbourne Storm from 2000-04. In 2000, Moala played for the Tonga national rugby league team in the 2000 Rugby League World Cup.

name: Fikrejesus Amahazion
description: Fikrejesus (Fikre) Amahazion is a professional football (soccer) player currently playing for GKS Gornik Jaworzno. Amahazion is a technically skilled, physically strong, and versatile midfielder, able to play several positions. Most often, Amahazion is utilized as a central-midfielder or deep-lying playmaker where his reading of the game, precise distribution, and individual skills control the tempo of the match.

name: Fikret Kırcan
description: Fikret Kırcan (born December 25, 1919) is a Turkish former footballer. Born in Istanbul, he took up football at the age of ten and joined Fenerbahçe S.K. in 1934 as a member of their junior team, remaining there through 1956. During this time the squad was champion (1935 and 1944) and runner-up (1940 and 1947) of the Amatör Futbol Şampiyonası twice, six time-champion (1937, 1940, 1943, 1945, 1946, and 1950) and twice runner-up (1944 and 1947) of the Milli Küme Şampiyonası, three-time winner (1945, 1946, and 1950) and once runner-up (1944) of the Chancellor Cup, seven-time victor (1935-1937, 1944, 1947, 1948, 1953) and ten-time runner up (1934, 1938-1941, 1943, 1945-1946, 1950, and 1956) in the Istanbul Football League, and four-time winner of (1934, 1938, 1939, and 1945) and twice-runner up for (1942 and 1944) the Istanbul Shield and its successor the Istanbul Futbol Kupası. He served as Fenerbahçe team captain from 1951 through 1956 and was capped 12 times with the Turkish national team, thrice as captain, and attended the football tournament at the 1948 Summer Olympics, where his nation made it to the quarter-finals before being eliminated by eventual silver medalists Yugoslavia. Kırcan married at the age of 19 and attended law school for a short period, but was unable to keep up with his academic commitments and chose to continue his football career instead. Following his retirement he served in various administrative and executive capacities with Fenerbahçe S.K. , including a stint as Technical Director during the 1968-1969 season.

name: Filip Čech
description: Filip Čech (born Havířov, June 25, 1980) is a Czech professional ice hockey player. He played with HC Zlín in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season.

name: Filip Šimka
description: Filip Šimka (born February 18, 1986) is a Slovakian professional ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing in the Polish Hockey Superleague. He had previously played in the Slovak Extraliga with MHC Martin and HK Nitra.

name: Filip Škvorc
description: Filip Škvorc (born 22 July 1991 in Hohenems) is a Croatian football striker. After having his contract with Varaždin terminated due to unpaid wages in June 2011, Škvorc signed a five-year contract with Dinamo Zagreb and was loaned to Lokomotiva.

name: Filip Arsenijević
description: Filip Arsenijević (born 2 September 1983) is a Serbian footballer who plays for FK Jagodina in the Serbian SuperLiga. He previously played for OFK Beograd and FK Javor Ivanjica in the Serbian SuperLiga. Between 2009 and 2011 he has been in Greece playing with Panthrakikos in the Greek Super League. In 30 August 2011 he returned to Serbia and signed a one-year deal with top league club FK Jagodina. In 2012 signed a deal with the Kazakhstan Premier League team FC Shakhter Karagandy.

name: Filip Björk
description: Filip Björk (born October 1, 1986) is a Swedish professional ice hockey defenceman who played with HK SKP Poprad in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Filip Horanský
description: Filip Horanský (born January 7, 1993) and known professionally as Filip Horansky, is a tennis player from Slovakia. Filip, with partner Jiří Veselý, won the 2011 Boys Doubles Australian Open. He is coached by Miloslav Grolmus.

name: Filip Ivanow
description: Filip Ivanow (Belarusian: Філіп Иваноў; Russian: Филипп Иванов; born 21 July 1990) is a Belarusian professional football player who is currently playing for Vitebsk.

name: Filip Janković
description: Filip Janković is a Serbian footballer, currently playing for Red Star Belgrade.

name: Filip Kostić
description: Filip Kostić (Serbian Cyrillic: Филип Костић; born 1 November 1992) is a Serbian footballer who plays for who plays for Eredivisie club FC Groningen. He most frequently plays on left wing for his club.

name: Filip Mladenović
description: Filip Mladenović is a Serbian football defender playing for Red Star Belgrade. He entered into Borac senior team in the 2010–11 season, making 18 league appearances that season. He plays as left-back. He is also member of the Serbia national under-21 football team. 25 November 2011 confirmed that the first day of the winter transfer window to sign a contract with Red Star Belgrade.

name: Filip Novák (footballer)
description: Filip Novák (born 26 June 1990) is a professional Czech left-footed football player who currently plays for FK Baumit Jablonec and represents his country at youth level under 21 years old.

name: Filip Olsson
description: Filip Olsson (born January 28, 1991) is a Swedish ice hockey defenceman currently playing in Mörrums IK of the Division 1. Olsson has also played in Sweden's national junior team, both U18 and U19, and in AIK's elite team in Elitserien. His youth team is Flemingsbergs IK.

name: Filip Ozobić
description: Filip Ozobić is a Croatian midfielder, currently playing for HNK Hajduk Split on loan from Spartak Moscow and the Croatia national under-21 football team. He made his professional debut in the Russian Premier League on 28 November 2010 for Spartak Moscow.

name: Filip Peliwo
description: Filip Peliwo (born January 30, 1994) is a Canadian professional tennis player. Peliwo became the first Canadian male and second Canadian ever to win a Grand Slam in singles at any level with his 2012 Wimbledon boys' title win. This was Canada's second Grand Slam title in two days, one day after Eugenie Bouchard's. With the victory, Peliwo reached the No. 1 combined junior world ranking in July 2012, the first time a Canadian has been top ranked. He won his second straight junior Grand Slam title at the 2012 US Open. Peliwo was also runner-up in the boys singles events at the 2012 Australian Open and French Open.

name: Filip Racko
description: Filip Racko (born July 20, 1985) is a Czech footballer who is currently a free agent.

name: Filip Serečin
description: Filip Serečin (born 4 October 1989 in Košice) is a Slovak football striker who currently plays for the Corgoň Liga club MFK Ružomberok.

name: Filip Stojković
description: Filip Stojković is a Serbian footballer, currently playing for Serbian First League team Čukarički, on loan from Red Star Belgrade.

name: Filip Surovka
description: Filip Surovka is a Slovakian professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Filip Valenčič
description: Filip Valenčič (born 7 January 1992) is a football forward from Slovenia. His current club is Olimpija Ljubljana.

name: Filipe Daniel Mendes Barros
description: Filipe Daniel Mendes Barros (born 17 April 1992 in Paredes), commonly known as Pipo, is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Akritas Chlorakas in the Cypriot Second Division, as a forward.

name: Filipe Leão
description: Filipe Joaquim Gonçalves Andrade Ponce de Leão (born 13 November 1983 in Lisbon) is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Atlético Clube de Portugal as a goalkeeper.

name: Filipe Miguel Neves Ferreira
description: Filipe Miguel Neves Ferreira (born 27 September 1990 in Lisbon) is a Portuguese footballer who plays for C.F. Os Belenenses, as a midfielder.

name: Filipe Nzanza
description: Filipe Nzanza (born April 21, 1970) is an Angolan football player. He has played for Angola national team.

name: Filipp Snikhovskiy
description: Filipp Igorevich Snikhovskiy (Russian: Филипп Игоревич Сниховский; born July 13, 1991) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Istra.

name: Filipp Toluzakov
description: Filipp Toluzakov (born January 10, 1989) is a Russian professional ice hockey player. He played with HC Spartak Moscow in the Kontinental Hockey League during the 2010–11 KHL season.

name: Filippo Boniperti
description: Filippo Boniperti (born September 27, 1991 in Turin) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Parma.

name: Filippo Dal Moro
description: Filippo Dal Moro (born August 11, 1970 in Treviso) is a retired Italian professional football player. He played 2 seasons in the Serie A for A.S. Roma (12 games). He also played for Roma in the UEFA Cup in the 1998/99 season.

name: Filippo Forò
description: Filippo Forò (born 22 December 1987) is an Italian footballer who plays for Italian Serie B club Vicenza.

name: Filippo Fracaro
description: Filippo Fracaro (born 11 March 1992) is an Italian footballer who plays for Bassano.

name: Filippo Lombardi
description: Filippo Lombardi (born 22 April 1990 in Ancona) is an Italian goalkeeper who currently plays for Bologna in Serie A.

name: Filippo Petterini
description: Filippo Petterini (born 14 November 1980 in Foligno) is an Italian footballer who currently plays as a defender for Barletta in the Lega Pro Prima Divisione.

name: Filippo Spitoni
description: Filippo Spitoni (born April 17, 1984 in Fabriano) is an Italian professional football player, who currently plays for AC Pavia.

name: Filippo Tanaglia
description: Filippo Tanaglia (born 26 May 1990) is an Italian footballer who plays for Alessandria, on loan from Chievo.

name: Filippo Tasso
description: Filippo Tasso (born August 26, 1940 in Milan) is a retired Italian professional football player. His only season in the Serie A was his debut, 1958/59 one, when he played 3 games and scored 2 games for A.S. Roma. He also played for Roma in the 1958–60 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup and scored 2 goals in their first round matchup against the German club Hannover 96.

name: Fillipe Soutto
description: Fillipe Soutto Mayor Nogueira Ferreira, better known as Fillipe Soutto, is a Brazilian soccer midfielder, one of several players revealed in the basic categories of Atlético Mineiro. He currently plays for Vasco da Gama.

name: Finbarr Cullen
description: Finbarr Cullen was a Gaelic footballer from County Offaly, Ireland. He played with the Offaly intercounty team from 1991 to 200?. He was part of the Offaly team that won the Leinster Senior Football Championship in 1997 and the National Football League in 1998. He was also a noted hurler winning Leinster and All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championships in 1989. He played at club level with Edenderry winning Offaly Senior Football Championships in 1995, 1997, 1999 and 2001.

name: Finbarr Delaney
description: Finbarr Delaney is an Irish former sportsperson. He played hurling with his local club Blackrock and was a member of the Cork senior inter-county team for one season in 1989.

name: Finbarr Gantley
description: Finbarr Gantley is an Irish former sportsperson. He played hurling with his local club Beagh and was a member of the Galway senior inter-county team in the 1970s and 1980s.

name: Findlay Weir
description: Findlay Weir (born April 18, 1889 in Glasgow–died July 9, 1918) was a professional footballer who played for clubs including Maryhill, Sheffield Wednesday and Tottenham Hotspur.

name: Fintan Goold
description: Fintan Goold is an Irish sportsperson. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Macroom and has been a member of the Cork senior inter-county team since 2005.

name: Fintan Gould
description: Fintan Gould is an Irish sportsperson. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Macroom and has been a member of the Cork senior inter-county team since 2005.

name: Fiodor Cernych
description: Fiodor Černych (Russian: Фёдор Черных; born 21 May 1991) is a Lithuanian professional football player currently playing for Dnepr Mogilev.

name: Fiona McIntosh (fencer)
description: Fiona McIntosh (born 24 June 1960) is a Scottish writer and retired fencer. McIntosh was born in Edinburgh, Scotland and educated at Fitzwilliam College, Cambridge. During her fencing career, she was British champion four times, she won the Commonwealth Fencing Championships in 1990, collected a total of 12 Commonwealth medals and competed in the 1984, 1988, 1992 and 1996 Summer Olympics, reaching the finals in Barcelona 1992. More recently, she has written articles for magazines and worked with photographer Shaen Adey to produce books such as Seven Days in Mauritius and Table Mountain Activity Guide, both published by Struik, an imprint of Random House, in 2004.

name: Fiona Roberts
description: Fiona Roberts is a former association football player who represented New Zealand at international level. Roberts made her Football Ferns début in a 0-3 loss to Ghana on 26 August 1994, and made just one further appearance, in a 0-1 loss to Russia 2 days later.

name: Fionbarr Farrell
description: Fionbarr Farrell (born 3 March 1945) is an Irish fencer. He competed in five events at the 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Fiorenzo Marini
description: Fiorenzo Marini (14 March 1914 – 25 January 1991) was an Italian fencer. He won a silver medal in the team épée event at the 1948 Summer Olympics and a gold in the same event at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Fitim Kasapi
description: Fetim Kasapi (born 19 May 1983) is a Serbian-born football midfielder played for FK Čelik Nikšić in the Montenegrin First League.

name: Flávio Alex Valêncio
description: Flávio Alex Valêncio (better known just as Flavinho; born 27 July 1983) is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays for Neftchi Baku PFC in the Azerbaijan Premier League. He formerly played for the Brazilian club Grêmio Barueri in the Campeonato Paulista and the Campeonato Brasileiro Série A.

name: Flávio Boaventura
description: Flavio de Souza Boaventura, the Flavio Boaventura born in the Feira de Santana is a centre back who plays in the ABC Futebol Clube.

name: Flávio Ferreira
description: Flávio Nunes Ferreira (born 19 October 1991 in Nogueira do Cravo, Oliveira do Hospital) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays for Académica de Coimbra as a central defender or defensive midfielder.

name: Flávio Sérgio Viana
description: Flavio Sergio Viana known as Schumacher (born in São Paulo, August 31, 1975) is a Brazilian futsal player. He was elected as the 2008 World's Best Futsal Player. His nickname is a reference to German football goalkeeper Harald Schumacher.

name: Flame Delhi
description: Lee William "Flame" Delhi (November 5, 1892 – May 9, 1966) was a pitcher in Major League Baseball. He played one game for the Chicago White Sox in 1912. Delhi was the first Arizona-born player to appear in the major leagues.

name: Flavia Schwarz
description: Flavia Schwarz (born 11 July 1986) is a Swiss former football midfielder who played for FC Zürich and FFC Zuchwil 05 in the Nationalliga A. She currently serves as FC Zürich second team's assistant coach. She was a member of the Swiss national team, and previously she played the 2005 U-19 Euro and the 2006 U-20 World Cup.

name: Flavio Caicedo
description: Flavio Caicedo (born 29 February 1988) is an Ecuadorian international footballer who plays for El Nacional, as a midfielder.

name: Flavio Elias Cordeiro
description: Flavio Elias Cordeiro (born April 23, 1975) is a Brazilian football player.

name: Flavio Rogerio
description: Flávio Rogério, also known as Flávio (born December 22, 1976 in Siqueira Campos is a Brazilian naturalized Mexican footballer playing for Puebla of the Primera División de México.

name: Flemming Vögg
description: Flemming Vögg (12 September 1914 – 21 February 1991) was a Danish fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Fleurette Campeau
description: Fleurette Campeau (born 10 January 1941) is a Canadian fencer. She competed in the women's team foil event at the 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Fleury Sullivan
description: Florence P. Sullivan (1862 in East St. Louis, Illinois – February 15, 1897 in Fort Worth, Texas), was a professional baseball player who played pitcher in the Major Leagues in 1882. He would play for the Pittsburgh Alleghenys.

name: Flip van der Merwe
description: Flip van der Merwe (born 3 June 1985 in Potchefstroom) is a South African rugby union footballer who plays in the lock position. In June 2010 he was selected to represent the South African national team, the Springboks, in the 12 June test against France. In 2009, van der Merwe was recruited by the successful Super 14 team the Blue Bulls. Prior to joining the Blue Bulls, van der Merwe played his rugby for the Cheetahs. His father Flippie won six caps for South Africa from 1981 to 1989.

name: Florence Dadson
description: Florence Dadson (born 23 April 1992 in Cape Coast) is a Ghanaian female footballer, who currently plays for the Robert Morris University in Chicago Illinois, United States.

name: Florence Haring
description: Florence Haring (born 2 October 1985) is a French professional tennis player. As of June 26, 2006, she reached her highest single rankings of World number 213.

name: Florencia Molinero
description: Florencia Molinero (born November 28, 1988) is a professional Argentine tennis player. Her highest WTA singles ranking is 179, which she reached on August 13, 2012. Her career high in doubles is 179, which she reached on April 26, 2010. She is currently coached by Leonardo Alonso.

name: Florencia Quiñones
description: María Florencia Quiñones is an Argentine football midfielder, currently playing for FC Barcelona in Spain's Primera División. She previously played for San Lorenzo de Almagro in the Argentine league. She is a member of the Argentine national team, taking part in the 2007 World Cup and the 2008 Summer Olympics.

name: Florent Bessemans
description: Florent Bessemans (born 2 January 1940) is a Belgian fencer. He competed in the individual foil and épée events at the 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Florian Hartherz
description: Florian Hartherz is a footballer who plays as a defender for Werder Bremen in the Bundesliga.

name: Florian Jozefzoon
description: Florian Jozefzoon (born 9 February 1991) is a Dutch professional footballer who plays as a striker for RKC Waalwijk, in the Dutch Eredivisie

name: Florian Raspentino
description: Florian Raspentino (born June 6, 1989) is a French football player. He currently plays for Stade Brestois 29 on loan from Olympique de Marseille in Ligue 1.

name: Florian Thauvin
description: Florian Thauvin (born 26 January 1993 in Orléans) is a French footballer who plays for French club Bastia in Ligue 1. He plays as an attacking midfielder and is a France youth international having earned caps at under-18 level. Thauvin previously played for Grenoble and made his professional debut on 11 March 2011 in a 1–1 league draw with Vannes. Following the liquidation of Grenoble after the season, which saw the club relegated to the Championnat de France amateur 2, Thauvin departed the club and signed his first professional contract with Bastia. On 28 October 2012; scored his first goals against Bordeaux and Bastia won the match 3-1. On 29 January 2013, Thauvin signed a four and a half year deal with Ligue 1 club Lille, putting an end to media speculation of a switch to English giants Arsenal. The transfer fee was reported to be around 3.5 million euros. Thauvin would remain with Bastia until the end of the 2012-13 campaign.

name: Florian Vachon
description: Florian Vachon (born 2 January 1985) is a French professional road bicycle racer who rides for UCI Professional Continental Team Bretagne-Séché Environnement. Born in Montluçon, Vachon has competed as a professional since 2008, competing for Roubaix-Lille Métropole prior to moving to Bretagne-Schuller for the 2010 season.

name: Florin Lupeică
description: Florin Lupeică (born 6 March 1973) is a Romanian fencer. He competed in the sabre events at the 1992, 1996 and 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: Florin Niță
description: Florin Constantin Niță (born 3 July 1987, Bucureşti) is a Romanian footballer currently under contract with Liga I side Concordia Chiajna. First match Liga I was against Sportul Studențesc.

name: Floyd Wedderburn
description: Floyd E. Wedderburn (born May 5, 1976 in Kingston, Jamaica) is a former professional American football player who played guard for three seasons for the Seattle Seahawks. Floyd attended Upper Darby High School, where he lettered in football, basketball, and track and field (shot put and discus). Floyd went on to play football for Joe Paterno at Penn State University.

name: Floyd Wooldridge
description: Floyd Lewis Wooldridge (August 15, 1928 – May 14, 2008) was an American professional baseball player. A right-handed pitcher, he appeared in 18 Major League Baseball games for the 1955 St. Louis Cardinals. The native of Jerico Springs, Missouri, was measured during his playing days at 6 feet 1 inch tall and 185 pounds . Wooldridge started eight games during his MLB career. Both of his victories were complete-game efforts. On June 23, he defeated the Philadelphia Phillies 7–1 at Busch Stadium, scattering seven hits and issuing two bases on balls. On July 3, he defeated the Chicago Cubs 8–2 at Wrigley Field, giving up only five hits, walking three and striking out five. In 57⅔ major league innings, Wooldridge allowed 64 hits and 31 earned runs, walking 27 and striking out 14. During his minor league career (1950–53; 1955–57) he appeared in 193 games and posted a 59–62 won/lost record.

name: Fodé Camara
description: Fodé Camara (born 9 December 1973) is a Guinea international football player. Camara began his professional career in Belgium with Sint-Niklase. He played for several other Belgian clubs, including Waregem and Kortrijk. He scored a goal for Kortrijk as they achieved their biggest margin of victory over his-former club Waregem on 25 January 1998. Camara made several appearances for the Guinea national football team, including appearances at the 1994 and 1998 African Cup of Nations finals. He played for Guinea at the 1989 FIFA U-17 World Championship. In 2012 Camara return to Indonesia for managed his former club Bontang FC.

name: Fofana (footballer)
description: Fofana (born April 3, 1982) is an Angolan football player. He has played for Angola national team.

name: Fong Pak Lun
description: Fong Pak Lun (Chinese: 方柏倫, born 14 April 1993) is a Hong Kong Chinese football striker currently playing for Yokohama FC Hong Kong in the 2012-13 Hong Kong First Division League season.

name: Fons Pelser
