He played three more seasons with Bedfordshire, retiring from all cricket after the 1969 season.

name: Ian Dick
description: Ian Robinson Dick (30 August 1926 – 5 September 2012) was an Australian cricketer and field hockey player who played one first-class match for Western Australia in 1950 and also captained Australia in the hockey tournament at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne. Born in Boulder, Western Australia, Dick was the brother of Alexander Dick (who also played cricket for Western Australia) and David Dick (who was the school captain of Wesley College in 1936 and also played hockey for Western Australia). The brothers' uncle, Billy Dick, captained Carlton to the 1914 VFL premiership. Having worked as a pharmacist outside of sport, Dick died in September 2012.

name: Ian Evans (cricketer)
description: Ian James Evans (born 30 March 1982) is an English cricketer. Evans is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He was born in Oxford, Oxfordshire. Evans made his debut for Oxfordshire in the 2001 Minor Counties Championship against Wales Minor Counties. Evans played Minor counties cricket for Oxfordshire from 2001 to 2004, which included 11 Minor Counties Championship matches. He made his List A debut against Huntingdonshire in the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. He played 2 further List A matches, against the Nottinghamshire Cricket Board in the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2001 and against Shropshire in the 2nd round which was also played in 2001. In his 3 List A matches he scored 21 runs at a batting average of 7.00, with a high score of 18. With the ball he took a single wicket for the cost of 36 runs. His twin brother, Philip, has also played Minor counties and List A cricket for Oxfordshire.

name: Ian Fantham
description: Ian James Fantham (born 13 October 1964) is a former English cricketer. Fantham was a left-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Hemel Hempstead, Hertfordshire. Fantham played 2 Minor Counties Championship matches and 1 MCCA Knockout Trophy match for Hertfordshire from 1993 to 1995. He later joined Bedfordshire in the 1996 Minor Counties Championship against Staffordshire. Fantham played Minor counties cricket for Bedfordshire from 1996 to 2000, which included 18 Minor Counties Championship matches and 9 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his List A debut for Bedfordshire against Glamorgan in the 1998 NatWest Trophy. He played 2 further List A matches, against Huntingdonshire in the 1999 NatWest Trophy, and Northumberland in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. In his 3 matches, he scored 32 runs at an average of 16.00, with a high score of 32. With the ball he failed to take a wicket, bowling 27 overs without success.

name: Ian Fitzpatrick
description: Ian Matthew Fitzpatrick (born 22 September 1980) in Manchester, England, is a retired English professional footballer who played as a striker for Halifax Town and Shrewsbury Town in the Football League. F.A. National School Graduate, E.S.F. A, England U15-U18 (18 Caps). Ian appeared on the T. V Show The World at Their Feet in 1996 which charted the trials and tribulations of players going through the F. A National School selection process. He is the younger brother of former Hartlepool United midfielder Lee Fitzpatrick. Ian now co-owns the international soccer academy, World at Your Feet (www. wayfsoccer. com), which aims to provide children of all ages and ability with academy style coaching and pathway opportunities into professional clubs.

name: Ian Foster (rugby union)
description: Ian Foster is the assistant coach of the All Blacks and a former rugby union player. He was the coach of the Waikato Chiefs from 2004 to 2011. During his playing career he made 148 appearances for Waikato, a union record. He also played 28 games for the Chiefs.

name: Ian Gemmell
description: Ian James Gemmell (born 6 April 1953) is a former English cricketer. Gemmell was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm fast-medium. He was born in Ashton-under-Lyne, Lancashire. Gemmell made his debut for Cheshire in the 1978 Minor Counties Championship against the Somerset Second XI. Gemmell played Minor counties cricket for Cheshire from 1978 to 1983, including 48 Minor Counties Championship matches and two MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1964, he made his List A debut for Minor Counties North in the 1979 Benson and Hedges Cup, playing two matches against Middlesex and Yorkshire. He later represented the Minor Counties cricket team in the 1981 and 1982 competitions, playing five matches for the team. His debut in List A cricket for Cheshire did not come until the 1981 NatWest Trophy when Cheshire played Hampshire. He played two further List A matches for Cheshire, in 1982 against Middlesex and in 1983 against Kent. In total he ten List A matches, scoring 59 runs at a batting average of 7.37, with a high score of 20*. With the ball he took 7 wickets at a bowling average of 45.71, with best figures of 2/58.

name: Ian Gibbons (footballer)
description: Ian Kenneth Gibbons (born 8 February 1970) is a former English footballer who played in the Football League for Stoke City.

name: Ian Gildart
description: Ian Gildart (born Tuesday 14 October 1969) is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1980s and '90s, playing at club level for Wigan, Wakefield Trinity, and Oldham Bears, as a Second-row, i.e. number 11 or 12, and assisting at Wigan St Patricks ARLFC.

name: Ian Gillespie
description: Ian Gillespie (born 3 November 1976) is a former English cricketer. Gillespie was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm fast-medium. He was born in Shrewsbury, Shropshire. Gillespie made his debut for Shropshire in the 2002 Minor Counties Championship against Herefordshire. He made a further Minor Counties Championship appearance in 2002, against Oxfordshire. He made his only List A appearance in 2002, against Buckinghamshire in the 2nd of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In this match, he bowled 4 wicket-less overs, while with the bat he ended the Shropshire innings 26 not out. The following season he made his only MCCA Knockout Trophy appearance, against Devon.

name: Ian Hodgson
description: Kenneth Ian Hodgson (born 24 February 1960) is a South African born former English cricketer. Hodgson was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Port Elizabeth, Cape Province. Hodgson made his debut for Buckinghamshire in the 1980 Minor Counties Championship against Hertfordshire. Hodgson played Minor counties cricket for Buckinghamshire from 1980 to 1987, which included 39 Minor Counties Championship matches and 6 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. His first-class debut came for Cambridge University in 1981 against Essex. He played a further 26 first-class matches for the University, the last of which came against Oxford University in 1983. As an all-rounder, Hodgson scored 633 runs at an average of 25.32, with a high score of exactly 50, which came against Lancashire in 1982. With the ball, he took 55 wickets at 38.05 a piece, with best figures of 8/68. His best figures came against Glamorgan in 1982, with Hodgson taking his only five wicket haul in Glamorgans' first-innings, while in their second-innings he took 2 wickets, therefore not only giving him his only five wicket haul, but also his only ten wicket haul in a match. While attending Cambridge University, Hodgson made his List A debut for Combined Universities against Kent in the 1981 Benson & Hedges Cup. He played List A cricket for the team on 5 further occasions spread over the 1982 Benson & Hedges Cup and 1983 Benson & Hedges Cup. He scored 60 runs for Combined Universities at an average of 12, while making a high score of 41. While with the ball, Hodgson took 7 wickets for the team at an average of 25.71, with best figures of 3/30. While undertaking his studies at Cambridge University, Hodgson still managed to play for Buckinghamshire. He made his first List A appearance for the county in the 1984 NatWest Trophy against Lancashire. He played 4 further List A matches for the county, the last coming against Kent in the 1988 NatWest Trophy. His 5 appearances in limited-overs cricket for Buckinghamshire yielded him 51 runs at an average of 10.20, with a high score of 24. He bowled a total of 24 overs for Buckinghamshire, though without taking a wicket. His playing time with Buckinghamshire finished at the end of the 1987 season.

name: Ian Hughes (rugby league)
description: Ian Hughes (born 13 March 1972) is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1990s and 2000s, playing at club level for Sheffield Eagles, Wakefield Trinity, Hull Kingston Rovers, and Keighley Cougars, as a Second-row.

name: Ian Lawrence (cricketer)
description: Ian Seth Lawrence (born 11 April 1963) is a former English cricketer. Lawrence is a left-handed batsman. He was born in Ely, Cambridgeshire. Lawrence made his debut for Cambridgeshire in the 1985 Minor Counties Championship against Norfolk. He played for Cambridgeshire in Minor counties cricket from 1985 to 1991. He made his List A debut for the county against Yorkshire in the 1986 NatWest Trophy and played a further three List A matches to 1989, with the last coming against Worcestershire in the 1989 competition. In four List A matches he scored 78 runs at a batting average of 19.50, including a high score of 74 against Worcestershire in 1989.

name: Ian MacDonald (footballer)
description: Ian MacDonald (born 30 August 1953) is a Scottish former professional footballer who played as a central defender, making over 300 career appearances.

name: Ian Macowat
description: Ian S. Macowat (born 19 November 1965 in Oxford) is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League as a defender.

name: Ian Madigan
description: Ian Madigan (born 21 March 1989) is an Irish professional rugby union player for Blackrock College and Leinster Rugby. His primary position is at fly-half, although he can also play at full-back.

name: Ian McAllister (footballer)
description: Ian McAllister (born 8 February 1960) is a Scottish former professional footballer who spent his entire professional career with Ayr United, making 405 appearances in the Scottish Football League.

name: Ian McLoughlin
description: Ian Michael Mcloughlin is an Irish footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for MK Dons.

name: Ian McMahon
description: Ian McMahon, is an English footballer who played as a midfielder in the Football League. He is also the author of a book detailing the 1998–99 Doncaster Rovers F.C. Season called "The Only Way is Up". McMahon is married to Elise and has two children, Connor and Nolan. He is currently working as CEO of the Hong Kong Rugby Football Union.

name: Ian McShane (footballer)
description: Ian McShane (born 20 December 1992) is a Scottish professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Queen of the South.

name: Ian Moutray
description: Ian Edmund Joseph Moutray (born 2 July 1936) was a rugby union player who represented Australia. Moutray, an inside centre, was born in Ryde, New South Wales and claimed 3 international rugby caps for Australia. He was educated at Fort Street Boys High School and graduated from Sydney University. He played club rugby for Drummoyne in an era when it was a leading club.

name: Ian Patterson
description: Ian Daniel Patterson (born 4 April 1973) is an English former professional footballer who played as a central defender. Born in Chatham, Kent, Patterson started his career at Sunderland before moving to Burnley on a free transfer at the start of the 1993–94 season. He debuted against Bristol Rovers in September 1993, but did not make another appearance for the first team. He moved to Wigan Athletic in March 1994, making four appearances before being released at the end of the season.

name: Ian Pendlebury
description: Ian Pendlebury (born 3 September 1983) is an English former footballer who played as a defender for Wigan Athletic, Leigh RMI and Hyde United. Pendlebury made his debut for Wigan in 2001, making four league appearances for the club before being released in March 2003.

name: Ian Potter (rugby league)
description: Ian Potter is an English professional rugby league footballer of the 1970s and '80s, playing at representative level for Great Britain, and England and at club level for Warrington, Leigh (twice), and Wigan, as a Second-row, or Loose forward/Lock, i.e. number 11 or 12, or 13.

name: Ian Prior (rugby)
description: Ian Prior (born 21 August 1990) is an Australian rugby union player who plays for the Brumbies in Super Rugby. His playing position is scrum-half. He made his Super Rugby debut for the Reds against the Lions in Johannesburg during the 2011 Super Rugby season. He made the move from Brisbane to Canberra prior to the start of the 2012 Super Rugby season.

name: Ian Rowland (footballer)
description: Ian Rowland (born 4 March 1941) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the St Kilda Football Club in the Victorian Football League (VFL). Rowland played for the Saints from 1960 until 1966 and was St Kilda Football Club's leading goalkicker in 1961. He played in St Kilda's 1965 Grand Final side which was defeated by 35 points.

name: Ian Saltmarsh
description: Ian John Lindsay Saltmarsh (28 July 1901 – 1970) was an English cricketer. Saltmarsh's batting and bowling styles are unknown. He was born in Chester, Cheshire. Educated at Clifton College where he represented the College cricket team, Saltmarsh later made his Minor Counties Championship debut for Devon against the Surrey Second XI. From 1923 to 1924, he represented the county in 6 Championship matches, the last of which came against Cornwall. At some point beyond this, Saltmarsh moved to British Ceylon, where in the 1930/31 season he played his only first-class match for Dr J Rockwood's Europeans XI v Maharaj Kumar of Vizianagram's XI. In the teams first-innings he scored a 2 runs before being dismissed by Ghulam Mohammad. In their second-innings he was dismissed for a duck by Herbert Sutcliffe. He died in Redruth, Cornwall in 1970.

name: Ian Schultz
description: Ian Schultz (born February 4, 1990) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing with the Montreal Canadiens of the National Hockey League (NHL). Schultz was selected by the St. Louis Blues in the 3rd round (87th overall) of the 2008 NHL Entry Draft. He is the younger brother Jeff Schultz.

name: Ian Scott (footballer)
description: Ian Scott (born 20 September 1967) is a former footballer who played in the Football League for Bury, Crewe Alexandra, Manchester City and Stoke City.

name: Ian Stokes (cricketer)
description: Ian William Edward Stokes (born 22 February 1964) is a former English cricketer. Stokes was a left-handed batsman. He was born in Solihull, Warwickshire. Stokes made his debut for Staffordshire in the 1997 MCCA Knockout Trophy against Buckinghamshire. Stokes played Minor counties cricket for Staffordshire from 1997 to 1998, which included 6 Minor Counties Championship matches and 4 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1997, he made his List A debut against Nottinghamshire in the NatWest Trophy. He played a further List A match against Leicestershire in the 1998 NatWest Trophy. In his 2 List A matches, he scored 22 runs at an average of 11.00, with a high score of 18.

name: Ian Sturmer
description: Ian Sturmer (born 23 August 1991) is an English cricketer. Sturmer is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born in Chiddingly, Sussex. While studying for his degree in Information Management and Business Studies at Loughborough University, Sturmer made his first-class debut for Loughborough MCCU against Kent in 2011. In this match, he bowled 7 wicket-less overs in Kent's only innings of the match. With the bat, Sturmer scored 2 not out in Loughborough's first-innings, while in their second he was dismissed for 5 runs by Adam Riley.

name: Ian Tansley
description: Ian Joseph Tansley (born 22 January 1962) is a former English cricketer. Tansley was a right-handed batsman. He was born in Stockport, Cheshire. Tansley made his debut for Cheshire in the 1983 Minor Counties Championship against Buckinghamshire. Tansley played Minor counties cricket for Cheshire from 1983 to 1990, including 47 Minor Counties Championship matches and 20 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1985, he made his List A debut against Yorkshire in the NatWest Trophy. He played two further List A matches for Cheshire, against Glamorgan in the 1987 NatWest Trophy and Northamptonshire, which Cheshire famously won by 1 wicket, in the 1988 NatWest Trophy. In his three List A matches, he scored 35 runs at a batting average of 11.66, with a high score of 18. He also played Second XI cricket for the Warwickshire Second XI and the Derbyshire Second XI.

name: Ian Wishart (cricketer)
description: Ian Alexander Wishart (born 25 December 1948) is a former English cricketer. Wishart was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium-fast. He was born at Greenside, County Durham. Wishart made his debut for Durham against Cumberland in the 1971 Minor Counties Championship. He played minor counties cricket for Durham from 1971 to 1980, making a total of nineteen appearances for the county, the last of which came against Shropshire. In 1979, he made a single List A appearance for Minor Counties North against Kent at Lindum Sports Club Ground, Lincoln, in the 1979 Benson & Hedges Cup, He was dismissed for a duck in the match by Derek Underwood, while with the ball he bowled seven wicketless overs, with Kent winning by 9 wickets.

name: Ibra Sekajja
description: Ibra Sekajja (born 31 October 1992) is an English-Ugandan professional footballer who plays as a striker for Crystal Palace.

name: Ibrahim Abdel Hamidu Sharli
description: Ibrahim Abdel Hamidu Sharli (date of birth and death unknown) was an Egyptian football defender who played for Egypt in the 1934 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Al-Olympi Alexandria.

name: Ibrahim Al-Helwah
description: Ibrahim Al-Helwah (born 18 August 1972) is a Saudi Arabian football goalkeeper who played for Saudi Arabia in the 1994 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Al-Riyadh.

name: Ibrahim Al-Rumaihi
description: Ibrahim Saeed Al-Rumaihi is an Qatar football Forward who played for Qatar in the 1984 Asian Cup.

name: Ibrahim Al-Zawahreh
description: Ibrahim Farhan Al-Zawahreh (born in 1989) is a Jordanian footballer who is an attacking defender for Al-Faisaly (Amman). He is a member of the Jordan national football team.

name: Ibrahim El-Shayeb
description: Ibrahim El-Shayeb (born on April 26, 1984) is an Egyptian football midfielder who plays for El-Ittihad and he is currently the team captain.

name: Ibrahim Elsamni
description: Ibrahim Elsamni is an Egyptian former footballer who played at both professional and international levels.

name: Ibrahim Salim Saad
description: Ibrahim Salim Saad (born in 1972) is an Iraqi international football goalkeeper.

name: Ibrahim Sissoko
description: Ibrahim Sissoko (born 29 November 1991) is an Ivorian international footballer who plays as a forward for Panathinaikos in the Greek Superleague, on loan from VfL Wolfsburg.

name: Ibrahima Sory Souare
description: Ibrahima Sory Souaré (born 14 July 1982 in Conakry) is a Guinean football midfielder who, as of 2009 is playing for Greece side Kerkyra F.C.. He was a member of the Guinea squad for the 2006 African Nations Cup where the team were eliminated in the quarter-finals.

name: Ibrahima Tandia
description: Ibrahima Tandia (born 12 July 1993 in Longjumeau) is a French football player who plays for French club Caen in Ligue 1. He plays as either an attacking midfielder and began his career playing for local amateur clubs in Paris before joining professional club Sochaux in 2006. After five years with the club, Tandia joined Caen on a three-year deal, despite interest from English clubs Newcastle United and Chelsea. He was assigned the number 26 shirt and made his professional debut on 28 August 2011 appearing as a substitute in a 3–2 defeat to Rennes. At international level, Tandia is a France youth international having represented his nation at under-16 and under-17 level.

name: Ichizo Nakata
description: Ichizo Nakata (中田 一三, born 19 April 1973) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Ico Migliore
description: Lodovico Migliore, nicknamed Ico, (born December 27, 1956) is an Italian ex professional ice hockey player, businessman, chairman of Hockey Milano Rossoblu. His Hockey Team will participate in KHL Championship from the season 2012-2013.

name: Idálio Alexandre Ferreira
description: Idálio Alexandre Ferreira Espírito Santo (born 20 April 1983) is a Portuguese footballer who plays as a striker. He is simply known as Xano.

name: Idalmis Bonne
description: Idalmis Bonne Rousseaux (born February 2, 1971) is a retired female sprinter from Cuba.

name: Idan Baruch
description: Idan Baruch (born 11 January 1990 in Petah Tikva) is an Israeli-Romanian football goalkeeper currently playing for FC Unirea Slobozia.

name: Iddi Alkhag
description: Iddi Leif Deleuran Alkhag is a Danish footballer of Tanzania descent who plays in Denmark for FC Djursland. He has previously played for Esbjerg fB, Silkeborg IF, FC Fredericia, and BK Frem in Denmark, as well as Icelandic club HK. He has played 14 games and scored on goal for the Denmark national under-21 football team.

name: Ido Levy
description: Ido Levy is an Israeli footballer currently playing for Maccabi Netanya.

name: Idris Towill
description: Idris Arthur Towill (12 November 1909 – September 1988) was a professional rugby league footballer of the 1930s, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Huddersfield, and Keighley as a Centre, or Stand-off/Five-eighth, i.e. number 3 or 4, or 6. He was born in Bridgend district.

name: Idriss Saadi
description: Idriss Saadi is a French football player of Algerian descent who currently plays for French club Gazélec Ajaccio in Ligue 2, on loan from Saint-Étienne. He operates primarily in the lead striker role. Saadi is a French youth international and has represented his country at under-16, under-17, and under-18 level. Though, he is currently playing on the club's Championnat de France amateur team, Saadi made his professional debut on 28 August 2010 in a league match against Lens in a 3–1 victory.

name: Idwal Davies
description: David Idwal Davies (10 November 1915 – 7 July 1990) was a Welsh dual-code international rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1930s and '40s, playing representative level rugby union (RU) for Wales, and at club level for Swansea RFC, as a Centre, i.e. number 12 or 13, and playing representative level rugby league (RL) for Wales, and at club level for Leeds, as a Centre, i.e. number 3 or 4. Davies was born in Llanelli district He died in Llanelli, aged 74.

name: Idwal Fisher
description: Idwal Fisher (3 February 1935 — 5 January 2012) was a rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1960s, playing club level rugby union (RU) for Swansea RFC, in the Back row, and playing representative level rugby league (RL) for Wales, and at club level for both Warrington and Bradford, as a Second-row, i.e. number 11 or 12. Fisher was born in Swansea district.

name: Ifeoma Dieke
description: Ifeoma Nnenna Dieke (born 25 February 1981) is an American–born, Scottish football defender, currently playing for Vittsjö GIK of the Swedish Damallsvenskan. Since 2004, she has appeared on 90 occasions for the Scotland women's national football team. Dieke was born in Amherst, Massachusetts to Nigerian parents, moving to Cumbernauld in Scotland when she was three years old. Dieke and fellow Scot Kim Little were the only non–English players selected in the Great Britain squad for the 2012 London Olympics.

name: Ignace Moleka
description: Nzoko Ignace “Iggy” Moleka is a retired Zaire football (soccer) midfielder who played professionally in the United States and Japan. In 1991, Moleka received a sholarship to play soccer at Florida International University. He left FIU at the end of the season. In 1993, he played for Topaz Haiti, a selection of top players from the Haitian league, in the Miami Copa Latina. In 1994, he played for the Haitian Internationals. He also played for the Florida Stars in the USISL. In 1994, Moleka returned to FIU to finish his collegiate career. In 1996, he was selected as a First Team All American while the Golden Panthers finished runner-up in the NCAA Men's Division I Soccer Championship. In 1997, Moleka moved to Japan where he played for Albirex Niigata in the third division Hokushin'etsu. Moleka and his team mates won promotion to the second division Japanese Football League for the 1998 season. In the fall of 1999, Moleka returned to the United States where he played for the amateur Orlando Soccer Locker. Moleka signed with the Atlanta Silverbacks for the 1999 USL A-League season. He retired from playing in 2002, but remained with the Silverbacks where he has held a variety of positions including youth coach.

name: Ignacio Beristáin
description: Ignacio "Nacho" Beristáin is a Mexican trainer in the sport of boxing. Beristain is a member of the Boxing Hall of Fame and is considered one of the greatest trainers in the history of boxing.

name: Ignacio Don
description: Ignacio Óscar Don Núñez (born 28 February 1982) is an Argentine footballer that currently plays for Paraguayan Primera División club Nacional as goalkeeper. Don began his career at Paraguayan club Nacional in January 2005, aged 22. After two season in that club, in 2007, he moved to Chilean Primera División team Huachipato, directed by his countrymen Antonio Zaracho during that season, because he replaced to Arturo Salah in the bench, because he was signed by Chilean powerhouse Universidad de Chile. He had a six-months spell in Chile, playing 17 league games, but Don finished as the second-choice goalkeeper Cristián Torralbo. After an unnoticed pass at Huachipato, he returned to Nacional for the 2008 season, team in where the following season, Don played the 2009 Copa Libertadores, his first international tournament, because the club's successful season. The following season, he won the Primera División title and again won the same title in the 2011 season.

name: Ignacio Esparza
description: Ignacio Esparza Lozano is a Mexican professional boxer in the Cruiserweight division. He's the former Mexican National and WBA Fedebol Cruiserweight Champion.

name: Ignacio Goldstein
description: Ignacio Goldstein was a Chilean fencer. He competed in the individual sabre and épée events at the 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Ignacio González Barón
description: Jorge Ignacio González Barón, is a Uruguayan footballer.

name: Ignacio González King
description: Ignacio González King (born 28 March 1980) is a former professional tennis player from Argentina.

name: Ignacio Hirigoyen
description: Ignacio Hirigoyen (born 23 January 1976) is a former professional tennis player from Argentina.

name: Ignacio Posada
description: Ignacio Posada (born 3 March 1935) is a Colombian fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil and individual sabre events at the 1964 Summer Olympics.

name: Ignacio Salcedo
description: Ignacio María Salcedo Sánchez is a former Spanish footballer. He played for Atlético de Madrid between 1969 and 1977, winning the Spanish League in 1970, 1973, and 1976, the Spanish Cup in 1972 and 1976, and the Intercontinental Cup in 1975. He played in the 1974 European Cup Final, which Atlético lost.

name: Ignacio Zabal
description: Ignacio 'Nacho' Zabal Almazán (born 14 February 1987 in Alfaro, La Rioja) is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for SD Huesca as a goalkeeper.

name: Ignat Damyanov
description: Ignat Damyanov (Bulgarian: Игнат Дамянов; born 13 July 1987) is a Bulgarian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Spartak Varna.

name: Ignat Dishliev
description: Ignat Dishliev is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays as a defender for Beroe Stara Zagora.

name: Ignatius Dias
description: Ignatius Dias is an Indian football Midfielder who played for India in the 1984 Asian Cup. He also played for Salgaocar.

name: Ignaz Puschnik
description: Ignaz Puschnik (born 5 February 1934) is an Austrian football midfielder who played for Austria in the 1958 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Kapfenberger SV.

name: Igor Šemrinec
description: Igor Šemrinec (born 22 November 1987 in Bojnice) is a Slovak football goalkeeper who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FK AS Trenčín.

name: Igor Andreyushkin
description: Igor Pavlovich Andreyushkin (Russian: Игорь Павлович Андреюшкин; born May 26, 1989) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Dnepr Smolensk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Dnepr Smolensk on April 22, 2012 in a game against FC Volochanin-Ratmir Vyshny Volochyok.

name: Igor Bondarenko
description: Igor Mikhailovich Bondarenko (Russian: Игорь Михайлович Бондаренко; born January 8, 1986) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Yakutiya Yakutsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Yakutiya Yakutsk on May 15, 2011 in a game against FC Mostovik-Primorye Ussuriysk.

name: Igor Borisovich Kachmazov
description: Igor Borisovich Kachmazov (Russian: Игорь Борисович Качмазов; born August 30, 1968) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet First League in 1986 for FC Spartak Ordzhonikidze. He played 1 game in the UEFA Cup 1993–94 for FC Spartak Vladikavkaz.

name: Igor Boyarov
description: Igor Yuryevich Boyarov (Russian: Игорь Юрьевич Бояров; born July 31, 1991) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Vityaz Podolsk.

name: Igor Bredikhin
description: Igor Valeryevich Bredikhin (Russian: Игорь Валерьевич Бредихин; born March 11, 1984) is a Russian professional football player. In 2011, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Nosta Novotroitsk.

name: Igor Cheminava
description: Igor Revdikovich Cheminava (Russian: Игорь Ревдикович Чеминава born 23 March 1991) is a Russian football defender of Georgian descent who currently plays for Zenit. He made his debut for the main Zenit squad on March 13, 2011 in a Russian Premier League game against FC Terek Grozny.

name: Igor Degtyaryov
description: Igor Vladimirovich Degtyaryov (Russian: Игорь Владимирович Дегтярёв; born August 22, 1976) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 1993 for FC Gazovik Orenburg.

name: Igor Držík
description: Igor Držík (born 10 April 1982 in Ilava) is a Slovak football player who currently plays for ŠK SFM Senec.

name: Igor Dragunov
description: Igor Aleksandrovich Dragunov (Russian: Игорь Александрович Драгунов; born April 6, 1991) is a Russian football defender who currently plays for FC Pskov-747 Pskov. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Pskov-747 Pskov on September 8, 2011 in a game against FC Lokomotiv-2 Moscow.

name: Igor Gongalsky
description: Igor Gongalsky (born November 5, 1986) is a Ukrainian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing with the Rochester Americans of the American Hockey League (AHL). On November 27, 2010, the Portland Pirates of the American Hockey League signed Gongalsky to a professional tryout agreement, and he was resigned by the Pirates on January 23, 2011.

name: Igor Gorbatenko
description: Igor Nikolayevich Gorbatenko (Russian: Игорь Николаевич Горбатенко; born February 13, 1989 in Belgorod) is a Russian professional footballer. He last played for FC Spartak Moscow. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 2006 for FC Krylia Sovetov-SOK Dimitrovgrad.

name: Igor Ignatushkin
description: Igor Ignatushkin (born April 7, 1984) is a Russian professional ice hockey center who currently plays for Atlant Mytishchi of the Kontinental Hockey League. He was selected by Washington Capitals in the 8th round (242nd overall) of the 2002 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Igor Jovićević
description: Igor Jovićević (born 30 November 1973 in Zagreb) is a Croatian former football player of Montenegrin descent. After being labeled as the new Zvonimir Boban while playing in the youth team of the most successful Croatian club, NK Dinamo Zagreb, with only 17 years, he signed, in summer of 1991 a contract with Real Madrid. His transfer cost was one million dollars, however, the contact was based on the fact that the Merengues, in case of lining him in the first team, would have to pay a total of five million, being that the probable cause of having him playing in the B squad. He had the privilege there of being trained by world class experts, like Rafa Benitez, among others, and he had to opportunity of playing along some youngsters that would become worldwide stars, like Raúl, Guti, Juan Esnáider or Urzaiz. But there was another unquestionable fact that made his career shine much less than initially expected, a heavy injury that he had while playing against Ukraine with the Croatian national team. After having a one year pause, he returned to Croatia to play with another club from the capital of the now independent Croatia, NK Zagreb. But, he was not the same any more. From then on, he would have an exotic career, playing with J. League Division 1 club Yokohama F. Marinos, Brazilian Guarani Futebol Clube and a short spell in France with FC Metz before moving to China to play with Shenyang Dongjin, a discrete passage in Ukraine with Karpaty Lviv before definitely finishing his career in China, again, with a new knee ligaments injury, aged 32. After retiring, he returned to Spain, this time to Marbella where he owns a bar. His father Čedomir "Čedo" Jovićević is from Cetinje, Montenegro (also a former Dinamo Zagreb player) while his mother is from Zagreb.

name: Igor Jurković
description: Igor Jurković (born 15 July 1985) is a Croatian heavyweight kickboxer fighting out of Poreč, Croatia. He was 6 times Croatian national champion 2004, 2005, 2006 in Thai boxing, and kickboxing champion 2005 in full contact, 2005 and 2006 in low kick rules, and also was sparring partner of Mirko Cro Cop. He has fought in K-1 and he is under contract with Glory World Series.

name: Igor Khaymanov
description: Igor Anatolyevich Khaymanov (Russian: Игорь Анатольевич Хайманов; born March 26, 1994) is a Russian football midfielder, who plays for FC Alania Vladikavkaz. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Alania-d Vladikavkaz on April 26, 2012 in a game against FC FAYUR Beslan.

name: Igor Khokhlov
description: Igor Dmitriyevich Khokhlov (Russian: Игорь Дмитриевич Хохлов; born December 14, 1993) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Premier League for FC Dynamo Moscow. He is the son of former Russian international Dmitri Khokhlov.

name: Igor Kireyev
description: Igor Olegovich Kireyev (Russian: Игорь Олегович Киреев; born February 17, 1992 in Zheleznogorsk) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Rostov. He made his Russian Premier League debut on March 14, 2010 for FC Spartak Moscow in a game against FC Dynamo Moscow.

name: Igor Kislov
description: Igor Kislov is a former Ukrainian footballer.

name: Igor Klejch
description: Igor Klejch (born 28 March 1964) is a retired footballer who played as a midfielder for clubs in Czechoslovakia and Greece.

name: Igor Klitsov
description: Igor Vladimirovich Klitsov (Russian: Игорь Владимирович Клицов; born July 7, 1986) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Avangard Podolsk in the Russian Second Division.

name: Igor Klyuchnikov
description: Igor Kluchnikov(born 7 January 1983) is a Russian rugby union player who play for VVA-Podmoskovye Monino and is part of the Russian squad for the 2011 Rugby World Cup in New Zealand. He is a tall, strong back who can play as both full back and winger. He gained his 50th cap in Russia's World Cup opener against USA on 15 September 2011.

name: Igor Korobeynikov
description: Igor Gennadyevich Korobeynikov (Russian: Игорь Геннадьевич Коробейников; born November 18, 1987) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Sibiryak Bratsk in the Russian Second Division.

name: Igor Kotora
description: Igor Kotora (born 13 July 1989 in Nitra) is a Slovak football defender who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FC Nitra.

name: Igor Kuznechenkov
description: Igor Kuznechenkov (Russian: Игорь Кузнеченков; born January 3, 1966) is a retired Russian professional footballer.

name: Igor Lambarschi
description: Igor Lambarschi (Russian: Игорь Анатольевич Ламбарский; born November 26, 1992 in Edineț) is a Moldovan-born Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Krasnodar. He made his Russian Premier League debut for FC Krasnodar on 5 March 2012 in a game against FC Rostov.

name: Igor Lavrentyev
description: Igor Aleksandrovich Lavrentyev (Russian: Игорь Александрович Лаврентьев; born February 4, 1989) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Zvezda Ryazan.

name: Igor Lichnovsky
description: Igor Lichnovsky Osorio (born 7th March 1994) is a Chilean footballer that currently plays for Primera División club Universidad de Chile and the national U-20 team as centre back. Lichnovsky also holds a Austrian passport due to his ancestry.

name: Igor Maslennikov (footballer)
description: Igor Sergeyevich Maslennikov (Russian: Игорь Сергеевич Масленников; born 5 February 1991) is a Russian professional football player. He plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Energiya Volzhsky. He is a twin brother of Aleksei Maslennikov.

name: Igor Maystrenko
description: Igor Yuryevich Maystrenko (Russian: Игорь Юрьевич Майстренко; born July 26, 1992) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Akademiya Togliatti in the Russian Second Division.

name: Igor Melyakov
description: Igor Melyakov (born December 23, 1976) is a Russian professional ice hockey forward. He was selected by Los Angeles Kings in the 6th round (137th overall) of the 1995 NHL Entry Draft. Melyakov played 1993-2008 in the Russian Superleague.

name: Igor Mijović
description: Igor Mijović : Игор Мијовић; born 11 July 1985 in Belgrade is a Serbian footballer, who currently plays for Red Star Belgrade.

name: Igor Miović
description: Igor Miović is a Serbian football defender who plays for Hong Kong First Division League club Sun Pegasus. He previously played with FK Smederevo, FK Železničar Smederevo and INON Požarevac.

name: Igor Mirčeta
description: Igor Mirčeta is a Serbian footballer who plays for Platanias in the Greek Superleague as a midfielder . Mirčeta began his professional career with FK Obilić and FK Radnički Pirot. He joined Zalaegerszegi TE in 2008, where he played with the reserve team in the NB II. He moved to Kalamata F.C. in the Greek Beta Ethniki in January 2009. He joined Kastoria F.C. in the Gamma Ethniki for the 2009–10 season. He scored his first league goal for Kastoria on 7 October 2009.

name: Igor Mordvinov
description: Igor Vladimirovich Mordvinov (Russian: Игорь Владимирович Мордвинов; born June 21, 1972) is a Russian professional footballer. In 2008, he played for an Amateur Football League side FC Dynamo Kostroma. He made his professional debut in the Russian Third Division in 1994 for FC Torpedo Pavlovo. He played 2 games and scored 1 goal in the UEFA Intertoto Cup 1997 for FC Lokomotiv Nizhny Novgorod.

name: Igor Muzychko
description: Igor Nikolayevich Muzychko (Russian: Игорь Николаевич Музычко; born August 1, 1987) is a Russian football defender, who currently plays for FC Chita. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Chita on June 8, 2011 in a game against FC Radian-Baikal Irkutsk.

name: Igor Nedorezov
description: Igor Olegovich Nedorezov (Russian: Игорь Олегович Недорезов; born June 27, 1981) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Metallurg-Kuzbass Novokuznetsk. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2000 for FC Zenit St. Petersburg. He played 7 games in the UEFA Intertoto Cup 2000 for FC Zenit St. Petersburg.

name: Igor Okhrimenko
description: Igor Nikolayevich Okhrimenko (Russian: Игорь Николаевич Охрименко; born October 28, 1981) is a Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Okean Nakhodka.

name: Igor Osredkar
description: Igor Osredkar (born 28 June 1986), is a Slovenian futsal player who plays for FC Litija and the Slovenian national futsal team.

name: Igor Ozhiganov
description: Igor Ozhiganov (born October 13, 1992) is a Russian professional ice hockey defenceman. During the 2010–11 KHL season, Ozhiganov played two games with HC CSKA Moscow in the Kontinental Hockey League.

name: Igor Palachyov
description: Igor Vitalyevich Palachyov (Russian: Игорь Витальевич Палачёв; born October 9, 1973) is a retired Russian professional footballer. In 2003 he moved from FC KAMAZ to FC Dynamo Saint Petersburg.

name: Igor Pestretsov
description: Igor Pestretsov (Russian: Игорь Пестрецов; born January 9, 1963) is a retired Russian professional footballer.

name: Igor Petrović
description: Igor Petrović is a Serbian footballer currently playing for Serbian club FK Napredak Kruševac. He usually plays as right midfielder. In Serbian SuperLiga season 2009-10 he played 23 matches (1.928 minutes on the pitch) and got 2 yellow cards.

name: Igor Piskunov
description: Igor Viktorovich Piskunov (Russian: Игорь Викторович Пискунов; born March 5, 1989) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Taganrog in the Russian Second Division.

name: Igor Popović
description: Igor Popović is a Serbian football player, currently is Free Agent. He had played previously with Serbian SuperLiga club FK Spartak Subotica.

name: Igor Povalyayev
description: Igor Stanislavovich Povalyayev is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet Top League in 1979 for FC Pakhtakor Tashkent. He played 3 games in the European Cup 1988–89 for FC Spartak Moscow.

name: Igor Reshetnev
description: Igor Yuryevich Reshetnev (Russian: Игорь Юрьевич Решетнев; born June 18, 1990) is a Russian football midfielder who last played for FC Karelia Petrozavodsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Karelia Petrozavodsk on April 18, 2011 in a game against FC Petrotrest St. Petersburg.

name: Igor Romanenko
description: Igor Aleksandrovich Romanenko (Russian: Игорь Александрович Романенко; born June 2, 1983) is a Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Bataysk-2007.

name: Igor Romanov
description: Igor Mikhailovich Romanov (Russian: Игорь Михайлович Романов; born May 5, 1986) is a Russian football midfielder who currently plays for FC Syzran-2003 Syzran. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Dynamo Izhevsk in 2003.

name: Igor Sergeyevich Kaleshin
description: Igor Sergeyevich Kaleshin (Russian: Игорь Сергеевич Калешин; born May 29, 1983) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Volgar-Gazprom Astrakhan.

name: Igor Shapovalov
description: Igor Valeryevich Shapovalov (Russian: Игорь Валерьевич Шаповалов; born February 5, 1985) is a Russian professional football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC Sibiryak Bratsk. He played for the main squad of FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk in the Russian Cup and the Russian Premier League Cup.

name: Igor Shestakov
description: Igor Sergeyevich Shestakov (Russian: Игорь Сергеевич Шестаков; born December 31, 1984 in Moscow) is a Russian professional footballer. He last played for FC Khimki. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 2004 for FC Gazovik Orenburg. He played two games for the main FC Saturn-RenTV Ramenskoye squad in the Russian Premier League Cup.

name: Igor Sinyutin
description: Igor Sinyutin (also romanized as Siniutin or Sinioutine); born January 3, 1974 in Samara, Russian SFSR) is a Russian figure skater. He is the 1995 Grand Prix International St. Gervais silver medalist and 1996 Nebelhorn Trophy bronze medalist. Sinyutin presently coaches at Club Hielo in Jaca, Spain. Sinyutin started skating in 1980 in Kuibyshev, Russia with first coach Lyubov Zgirova. In 1986, he moved to a different sport club, "Kriliya Sovetov", and started working with coach Galina Belyashova Galina and choreographer Tatiana Mihalkina.

name: Igor Sirotinin
description: Igor Olegovich Sirotinin (Russian: Игорь Олегович Сиротинин; born 20 January 1991) is a Russian professional footballer. He plays for FC Biolog-Novokubansk Progress.

name: Igor Sjunin
description: Igor Sjunin (born 4 December 1990) is an Estonian triple jumper.

name: Igor Stamenovski
description: Igor Stamenovski (born 16 June 1980 in Delčevo) is a retired Macedonian professional footballer. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2001 for FC Spartak Moscow.

name: Igor Stojanov
description: Igor Stojanov is a Macedonian football player, currently playing for FK Bregalnica Štip.

name: Igor Sukenník
description: Igor Súkenník (born 25 October 1989) is a Slovak football player who currently plays for FK Viktoria Žižkov.

name: Igor Usminskiy
description: Igor Vladimirovich Usminskiy (Russian: Игорь Владимирович Усминский; born April 23, 1977 in Grozny) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for Terek Grozny. He made his professional debut in the Russian Premier League in 1996 for FC Zhemchuzhina Sochi.

name: Igor Valetov
description: Igor Valetov (Russian: Игорь Анатольевич Валетов; born 1 February 1946) is a Soviet fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team épée event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Igor Yekimov
description: Igor Aleksandrovich Yekimov (Russian: Игорь Александрович Екимов; born May 30, 1993) is a Russian football striker who currently plays for FC Irtysh Omsk. name: Ihor Kirienko

Malysh is the product of the Kovel-Volyn Sportive School System. He spent large part of his career as a player in different clubs of the Ukrainian First League and the Ukrainian Premier League and abroad.

Melnyk is the product of the Lviv Oblast Sportive School System. He spent large part of his career as a player in different clubs of the Ukrainian First League and the Ukrainian Premier League.

name: Ihor Ozarkiv

Ozarkiv is the product of the Karpaty Lviv Youth School System. He made his debut for FC Karpaty entering as a second-half substitute against FC Volyn Lutsk on 1 October 2011 in Ukrainian Premier League. He also played for Ukrainian national football teams in different age representations.

name: Iiro Tarkki
description: Iiro Tarkki (born July 1, 1985) is a Finnish professional ice hockey goaltender who currently plays for Salavat Yulaev Ufa of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL). Iiro is the younger brother of goaltender Tuomas Tarkki.

name: Ijah Anderson
description: Ijah Massai Anderson (born 30 December 1975) is a footballer who plays as a defender. Anderson played in The Football League for Brentford, Wycombe Wanderers, Bristol Rovers and Swansea City. He also had a spell in non-League football with Conference South club Lewes. He made his debut in The Football League for Brentford, in the 1–1 away draw against Bury on 17 August 1996 in a Second Division. In November 2005, Anderson tested positive for taking cocaine and was banned for six-months, although he pleaded his innocence claiming his drink was spiked. Steve King signed Anderson for Conference South club Lewes, in August 2006. However, he was released less than a month later after just four appearances for Lewes.

name: Ike Danning
description: Isaac "Ike" Danning (January 20, 1905 - March 30, 1983) was an American Major League Baseball catcher who played for the St. Louis Browns in 1928. His brother, Harry Danning, played for the New York Giants from 1933 to 1942.

name: Ike Kamp
description: Alphonse Francis Kamp (September 5, 1900 – February 25, 1955) is a former Major League Baseball pitcher. He played two seasons with the Boston Braves from 1924 to 1925.

name: Ike Rockenfield
description: Isaac Broc Rockenfield (November 3, 1876 – February 21, 1927) was a second baseman in Major League Baseball. He played for the St. Louis Browns.

name: Ike Samuels
description: Samuel Earl Samuels (1874–1964) was a third baseman for the St. Louis Browns of the National League in 1895.

name: Ike Udeh
description: Ike Udeh is a retired Nigerian football (soccer) striker who played one season in Major League Soccer and one in the USISL. Udeh played on both the Nigerian U-17 and U-21 teams before moving to the United States to attend Alabama A&M. On February 1, 1997, the Kansas City Wizards selected Udeh in the second round (seventeenth overall) of the 1997 MLS College Draft. The Wizards waived him on June 17, 1997. In July, He signed with the Carolina Dynamo. but an automobile accident left him severely injured. and he spent nine months in rehabilitation during which he earned his masters degree from Alabama A&M. In May 1998, he joined the Jacksonville Cyclones of the USISL. Udeh has an extensive resume of coaching high school soccer teams in Alabama.

name: Ikpefua Osas Marvelous
description: Ikpefua Osas Marvelous (born 20 October 1986 in Warri) is Nigeria footballer who currently plays for Persepam Madura United.

description: Ilyes Sidhoum (born August 10, 1989 in Nedroma) is an Algerian football player. He is currently playing as a right back for WA Tlemcen in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Imants Terrauds
description: Imants Terrauds (born 26 July 1936) is an Australian fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1964 Summer Olympics.

name: Imanuel Wanggai
description: Imanuel Wanggai (born February 23, 1988) is an Indonesian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Persipura Jayapura. In 2009, he also playing futsal for Mutiara Hitam in Indonesian Futsal League. His cousin, Patrich Wanggai and Izaac Johanes Wanggai, is also a football player.

name: Imarjoe Miller
description: Imarjoe Miller is a former American amateur boxer and current professional boxer in the Light Welterweight division. Miller, a late-comer to the sport, went from juvenile delinquency to becoming a pro boxer. He is currently trained by Troy Bodean (boxing) at the wildcard boxing gym Roach.

name: Imraan Mohammad
description: Imraan Mohammad (born 31 December 1976) is an English cricketer. Mohammad is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He was born at Solihull, Warwickshire. Mohammad made his first-class debut for Cambridge University against Middlesex in 1997. From 1997 to 1999, he represented the University in 15 first-class matches, the last of which came against Oxford University. During this period, he also played a single first-class match for British Universities against the touring New Zealanders. It was while representing the University that he made his debut for Cornwall in the Minor Counties Championship against Wales Minor Counties in 1998. From 1998 to 1999, he represented the county in 9 Championship matches, the last of which came against Devon. During the 1999/00 Pakistan cricket season, Mohammad made his debut for Pakistan Customs against Hyderabad. It was during this season that he made his debut in List A cricket when Pakistan Customs played Karachi Whites. In the following English cricket season, he made his first-class debut for Gloucestershire in the County Championship against Sussex. During the 2000 season he played 4 first-class matches for the county, the last of which came against Worcestershire. During the 2000 season, he also represented the Gloucestershire Cricket Board in List A cricket. His debut for the Board came against the Nottinghamshire Cricket Board in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. His second and final List A match for the Board came in the same competition against the Derbyshire Cricket Board. It was in his 3 List A matches that he scored 55 runs at a batting average of 18.33, with a single half century high score of 53. In the field he took 3 catches, while with the ball he took a single wicket at a bowling average of 38.00, with best figures of 1/38. For the 2001/02 Pakistani season, he once more represented Pakistan Customs. During this season he represented the team in 5 first-class matches, the last of which came against Pakistan International Airlines. During the same season, he also represented Hyderabad in first-class cricket. He made his debut for the team against Bahawalpur and played for the team in 3 further matches, with his final first-class appearance coming against Gujranwala. In his combined total of 35 first-class matches, he scored 1,701 runs at an average of 34.71, with 6 half centuries and 4 centuries. His highest score in first-class cricket was a double century score of 210*. In the field he took 12 catches, while with the ball he took 4 wickets an average of 68.25, with best figures of 1/26. He currently plays club cricket for Hampstead Cricket Club in the Middlesex County Cricket League.

name: Imran Jamshed
description: Imran Jamshed (born 31 December 1973) is a former Pakistani born English cricketer. Jamshed was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Sialkot, Punjab. Jameshed represented the Worcestershire Cricket Board in 3 List A matches. His first came against Dorset in the 1st round of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2002. His final 2 List A matches came against the Sussex Cricket Board and Worcestershire in the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 3 List A matches, he took 10 wickets at a bowling average of 12.40, with a single five wicket haul which gave him best figures of 5/36.

name: Imran Sahib
description: Imran Shahib is a former Singapore international football player who plays for Tampines Rovers.

name: Imran Shah (cricketer)
description: Imran Hussain Shah (born 8 September 1978) is a former English cricketer. Shah was a right-handed batsman who bowls slow left-arm orthodox. He was born in Newcastle, Northumberland and educated at King's School, Tynemouth, before attending the University of Northumbria. Shah made his debut for Northumberland in the 1998 MCCA Knockout Trophy against the Durham Cricket Board. Shah played Minor counties cricket for Northumberland from 1998 to 2003, which included 11 Minor Counties Championship matches and 6 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1999, he made his List A debut against Ireland in the NatWest Trophy. In this match he took his only List A wicket, that of Andrew Patterson for the cost of 64 runs. He made a further appearance against Shropshire in the 1st round of the 2004 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2003. He also played Second XI cricket for the Durham Second XI.

name: Imre Tiitsu
description: Imre Tiitsu (born June 18, 1980) is an Estonian ice sledge hockey player. He was part of the Estonian sledge hockey team at the 2002 Winter Paralympics in Salt Lake City, USA. He had an amputation of both legs after an accident.

name: Inés Ferrer Suárez
description: Inés Ferrer Suárez (born June 1, 1990) is a professional Spanish tennis player. On July 11, 2011, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 336 whilst her best doubles ranking was 219 on July 4, 2011.

name: Indira Ilić
description: Indira Ilić is a Serbian football defender, currently playing for Iowa Western Community College in Council Bluffs, Iowa. She previously played for Mašinac Niš. She is a member of the Serbian national team.

name: Indrit Hithi
description: Indrit Hithi (born 5 February 1990) is an Albanian association footballer who plays for Albanian First Division side Luftëtari Gjirokastër, as a defender. Hithi previously played for Partizani Tirana and KF Laçi. He has also represented his country at under-17, under-19 and under-21 level.

name: Indy Khabra
description: Indy Khabra is a Canadian soccer player who currently plays as a midfielder for Khalsa Sporting Club.

name: Ines Müller (figure skater)
description: Ines Müller is a former German pair skater who competed with Ingo Steuer. They placed 7th at two European Championships. Müller quit after the 1990–1991 season.

name: Inge Heiremans
description: Inge Heiremans is a Belgian football striker currently playing for Lierse SK in the Belgian First Division. She has also played for Rapide Wezemaal and K. Sint-Truidense VV (BFD), Lindenwood Lions and Jacksonville Dolphins, Hafnarfjarðar, Tampa Bay Extreme and VfL Wolfsburg. She first played the European Cup in 2006 with Rapide Wezemaal. She is a member of the Belgian national team.

name: Inger Klint
description: Inger Klint (20 November 1890 – 7 January 1967) was a Danish fencer. She competed at the 1928 and 1932 Summer Olympics.

name: Ingo Porges
description: Ingo Porges (born 22 August 1938) is a German former footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a midfielder.

name: Ingrid Sander
description: Íngrid Sander (born 12 March 1937) is a Venezuelan fencer. She competed in the women's individual and team foil events at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Ingrid Wells
description: Ingrid Wells (born March 29, 1989) is an American professional soccer player from Upper Montclair, New Jersey. Nicknamed "the Little General", Ingrid was a midfielder for the Georgetown University women's soccer team, and currently plays on the United States U-23 women's national soccer team and Washington Spirit.

name: Ingvar Gärd
description: Gustaf Ingvar Bertil Gärd (6 October 1921 – 31 August 2006) was a Swedish football midfielder who played for Sweden in the 1950 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Malmö FF.

name: Ingvar Rydell
description: Gustav Ingvar Rydell (born 7 May 1922) is a Swedish football forward who played for Sweden in the 1950 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Malmö FF and won a bronze medal at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Intharat Apinyakool
description: Intharat Apinyakool is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Thai Premier League side Esan United. He played for Thailand at the 1999 FIFA U-17 World Championship in New Zealand and the 2005 FIFA Beach Soccer World Cup in Brazil.

name: Ioachim Moldoveanu
description: Constantin Ioachim Moldoveanu (1910-31 July 1981) was a Romanian football forward who played for Romania in the 1938 FIFA World Cup. He also played for FC Rapid București.

name: Ioan Cunningham
description: Ioan Cunningham (Born January 1, 1983) is a Welsh rugby union coach, for Scarlets.

name: Ioanna Chatziioannou
description: Ioanna Chatziioannou (Ιωάννα Χατζηιωάννου; born October 22, 1973 in Georgia) is a retired female weightlifter from Greece. She became an Olympic medalist during the 2000 Summer Olympics when she won the bronze medal in the women's – 63 kg class.

name: Ioannis Chadjivasilis
description: Ioannis Chadjivasilis is a Cypriot footballer who plays as a forward and tends to play as a second striker who currently plays for Aris Limassol. He is highly regarded for his dribbling skills. He is considered one of the most promising young players in Cyprus at the moment.

name: Ioannis Stefas
description: Ioannis Stefas (Greek: Γιάννης Στέφας; 28 October 1948 – 17 July 2010) was a Greek professional footballer who played as a goalkeeper for a number of clubs including PAOK and Korinthos. Stefas began his career with local club Korinthos. He played in the Greek first division with PAOK from 1972 to 1975, before returning to Korinthos where he finished his career.

name: Ion Al-Ioani
description: Ion Al-Ioani (born 7 May 1983), is a Romanian futsal player who plays for Győri ETO Futsal Club and the Romanian national futsal team.

name: Ion Rudeanu
description: Ion Rudeanu was a Romanian fencer. He competed in the team foil and épée events at the 1928 Summer Olympics.

name: Ion Teodorescu
description: Ion Teodorescu (born Bucharest, 27 July 1976) is a Romanian rugby union footballer. He plays as a wing. He played in France for SU Agen and in Romania for Contor Arad. Teodorescu had 39 caps for Romania, from 2001 to 2007, scoring 13 tries, 65 points in aggregate. He played four matches at the 2003 Rugby World Cup, scoring a try. He was selected for the 2007 Rugby World Cup but was never used. Teodorescu has been absent from his national team since then.

name: Ionuţ Florea
description: Ionuţ Florea (born 7 September 1980), is a Romanian futsal player who plays for Dava Deva and the Romanian national futsal team.

name: Ionuț Șerban
description: Ionuţ Şerban (born 7 August 1995, Ploiești) is a Romanian professional football player, who currently plays for Sportul Studenţesc in the Romanian Liga I.

name: Ionuț Moldovan
description: Ionuţ "Ion" Moldovan (born 17 January 1978) is a former professional tennis player from Romania.

name: Iorwerth Evans
description: Iorwerth Evans Evans (born 23 May 1906 Trelewis — died 18 September 1985 in Bedford) was a rugby union footballer of the 1930s, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Bedford Athletic RFC, Bedford RFC, and London Welsh RFC, as a Hooker, i.e. number 2.

name: Iorwerth Jones
description: Iorwerth Jones (born 3 April 1903 in Loughor — died 31 August 1983 in Penclawdd) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1920s, playing representative level rugby union (RU) for Wales, and at club level for Llanelli RFC, as a Number Eight, and playing club level rugby league (RL) for Leeds. He was a great man and a great grandfather.

name: Iosif Czako
description: Iosif Czako (born 11 June 1906, date of death unknown) was a Romanian football Defender.

name: Iosif Solomonov
description: Iosif Viktorovich Solomonov (Russian: Иосиф Викторович Соломонов; born 6 June 1986) is a Russian professional footballer, currently playing for FK Jūrmala-VV in the Latvian Higher League.

name: Ippei Watanabe
description: Ippei Watanabe (渡辺 一平, born 28 September 1969) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Ira Hillary
description: Ira Hillary is a former professional American football player who played wide receiver for four seasons for the Cincinnati Bengals and Minnesota Vikings.

name: Ira Matthews
description: Ira Richard Matthews, III (born August 23, 1957 in Rockford, Illinois) is a former professional American football player who played kick returner and punt returner for three seasons for the Oakland Raiders. Matthews stood 5"8' and weighed 175 lbs which made it difficult to catch him. Matthews was named to the NFL 1979 All-Pro Team as a return man during his rookie season. On October 25, 1979, Matthews set a Monday Night Football record for kick-off returns with a 104-yard return against the San Diego Chargers. Matthews was a member of the Oakland Raiders Super Bowl XV championship team. During his three seasons with the Raiders he helped lead his team to win the 1980 Wild Card, 1981 AFC West Conference Championship, and Super Bowl XV. His career ended at the end of his 1981 season due to injuries, only playing for three seasons total. Matthews was drafted by the Raiders in the sixth round of the 1979 NFL Draft. He played collegiate football at the University of Wisconsin, where he led the nation in punt returns in 1978, averaging 16.9 yards per punt return, including three for touchdowns. He is widely considered one of the greatest returners of the Oakland franchise.

name: Ira Townsend
description: Ira Dance "Pat" Townsend (January 9, 1894 – July 21, 1965) was a Major League Baseball pitcher. He played two seasons with the Boston Braves from 1920 to 1921.

name: Iraia Iturregi
description: Iraia Iturregi Sustatxa is a Spanish football midfielder, currently playing for Athletic Bilbao in Spain's Primera División She has also played in United States's NCAA for Florida State Seminoles. She has been a member of the Spanish national team. Previously she scored the winner in the final of the 2004 Under-19 European Championship, Spain's first triumph in women's football. Iturregi was the team's captain and top scorer joint with Jade Boho. Two months later she played her first match with the senior national team, against Norway in the 2005 European Championship qualifying.

name: Irakli Chargaziya
description: Irakli Guramovich Chargaziya (Russian: Ираклий Гурамович Чаргазия; born December 29, 1991) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Spartak Tambov. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Spartak Tambov on August 29, 2011 in a game against FC Zenit Penza. His brother Georgi Chargaziya is also a footballer.

name: Irakli Dzaria
description: Irakli Dzaria (born 1 December 1988) is a Georgian footballer currently under contract for Georgian side FC Dinamo Tbilisi.

name: Irakli Kobalia
description: Irakli Kobalia (born 13 March 1992) is an Georgian association football player, who is currently playing for FC Baia Zugdidi in the Umaglesi Liga. He plays as a Striker.

name: Irakli Kvekveskiri
description: Irakli Kvekveskiri (born 12 March 1990) is a Georgian football player who currently plays for Pécsi Mecsek FC.

name: Irakli Liluashvili
description: Irakli Liluashvili (born 13 October 1984) is a Georgian footballer who recently played for 1. liga club FK Bodva. He played for Nitra in the 2008 UEFA Intertoto Cup.

name: Irakli Logua
description: Irakli Genovich Logua (Russian: Ираклий Генович Логуа; born July 29, 1991) is a Russian professional football player. He plays for Flora Tallinn in Estonian Meistriliiga. He made his Russian Premier League debut on July 24, 2010 for FC Dynamo Moscow in a game against FC Rubin Kazan.

name: Irakli Shekiladze
description: Irakli Shekiladze (born 17 September 1992) is Georgian football player. He is a striker and currently plays for Empoli in Italy.

name: Iran Cassius
description: Iran Cassius (born 3 January 1985) is an international football player from Saint Lucia, who plays as a goalkeeper.

name: Irbin Guerrero
description: Irvin Alberto Guerrero Hylton (born 26 April 1984) in Honduras is a footballer who currently plays as a defender for Vida in the Liga Nacional de Fútbol de Honduras.

name: Irek Faskhiyev
description: Irek Zakariyevich Faskhiyev is a Russian professional footballer. In 2009, he played for Russian Second Division Zone Ural-Povolzhye side FC Volga Ulyanovsk, where he plays as a defender.

name: Irek Ganiyev
description: Irek Kutdusovich Ganiyev (Russian: Ирек Кутдусович Ганиев; born January 16, 1986) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Gazovik Orenburg.

name: Irena Martínková
description: Irena Martínková is a Czech football Midfielder, currently playing for KIF Örebro DFF in the Damallsvenskan. She is a member of the Czech national team. Irena is the older twin of Czech footballer Lucie Martínková.

name: Irene Forbes
description: Irene Forbes (born 3 April 1949) is a Cuban fencer. She competed in the women's team foil event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Irene Fuhrmann
description: Lena Fuhrmann is a former football player. She played mostly for USC Landhaus Wien, and was a member of the Austrian national team. She currently serves as the coach of the Austrian Under-19 national team.

name: Irene Paredes
description: Irene Paredes is a Spanish athlete and footballer. She currently plays as a defender for Athletic Bilbao in Spain's Primera División. She played her first minutes for the Spanish national team in November 2011 against Romania.

name: Iresh Saxena
description: Iresh Saxena (born 14 March 1984 in Faridabad, Haryana) is a Bengal cricketer who made his debut against Madhya Pradesh against Bengal at Gwalior, Nov 10–13, 2008. He was signed on Indian Premier League for Kolkata Knight Riders.

name: Irina Kuzmina
description: Irina Kuzmina (born 16 January 1986 in Riga) is a retired Latvian tennis player. Kuzmina won two singles and eight doubles titles on the ITF tour during her career. On 13 October 2008, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 307. On 13 July 2009, she peaked at world number 193 in the doubles rankings. Kuzmina has a 19–13 record for Latvia in Fed Cup competition.

name: Irina Saratovtseva
description: Irina Saratovtseva is a Kazakhstani football goalkeeper who currently plays for Energiya Voronezh in the Russian women's football championship. She has also played for Zvezda Perm, where she was Nadezhda Baranova's reserve, and Sporting Huelva in Spain for half a season. In her first season in Zvezda the team won the league and reached the UEFA Women's Cup final. She has also won four Kazakhstani leagues with Alma-KTZ, her first team.

name: Irina Ushakova
description: Irina Ushakova (born 29 September 1954) is a Soviet fencer. She won a silver medal in the women's team foil event at the 1980 Summer Olympics.

name: Iris Sihvonen
description: Iris Hellin Sihvonen (married Jokinen, born 22 April 1940 at Liperi, Finland) is a former Finnish speedskater. She represented Finland at the Olympic Winter Games of 1960 in Squaw Valley, Placer County, California and made seven consecutive appearances at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women between 1955 and 1961. She became Finnish champion in 1956 and 1961 and skated at first with Valkeakosken Haka and later with Valkeakosken Koskenpojat.

name: Iris Zimmermann
description: Iris Zimmermann (born January 6, 1981) is an American fencer. She competed in the women's individual and team foil events at the 2000 Summer Olympics and she won a bronze medal at the 1999 World Fencing Championships. Her sister is Felicia Zimmermann, an Olympic fencer for the United States in 1996 and 2000. In 2009, the sisters purchased the Rochester Fencing Club in Rochester, New York. Zimmerman married strongman Kevin Nowack on June 19, 2010, at the Rochester Museum and Science Center.

name: Irma Sánchez
description: Irma Sánchez is a Mexican boxer in the Light Flyweight division and she is the current WBC Silver Female Light Flyweight Champion.

name: Irune Murua
description: Irune Murua is a Spanish football forward, currently playing for Athletic Bilbao in Spain's Primera División. She was a member of the Spanish team that won the 2004 Under-19 European Championship, where she scored two goals in the two first matches against Switzerland and Finland. She is the daughter of former footballer Andoni Murua.

name: Irv Bartling
description: Henry Irving Bartling (1914–1973) was an American Major League Baseball infielder. He played for the Philadelphia Athletics during the 1938 season. Bartling attended Michigan State University.

name: Irv Carlson
description: Irv Carlson was a player in the National Football League. He played with the Kenosha Maroons.

name: Irv Hach
description: Irvin William Hach (1873–1936) was a Major League Baseball second baseman and third baseman. He played for the 1897 Louisville Colonels.

name: Irv Jeffries
description: Irvine Franklin Jeffries (September 10, 1905 – June 8, 1982) was an infielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Chicago White Sox and Philadelphia Phillies.

name: Irvin Gernon
description: Irvin Gernon (born 30 December 1962) is an English former football defender who played for Ipswich Town, Gillingham, Reading and Northampton Town.

name: Irving Berry
description: Irving Berry is a featherweight boxer from Panama and is the second ranked featherweight for the WBA championship.

name: Irving Ormiston
description: Irving William Leonard Ormiston (19 June 1895 – c. 1969) was a rugby union player who represented Australia. Ormiston, a flanker, was born in Cowra, New South Wales and claimed a total of 3 international rugby caps for Australia.

name: Irvino English
description: Irvino English (born 23 October 1977) is a Jamaican international footballer who plays for Waterhouse, as a midfielder.

name: Iryna Dvoskina
description: Iryna Dvoskina is a Ukraine-born Australian athletics coach who works with Paralympic athletes.

name: Iryna Vasylyuk
description: Irina Vasylyuk is a Ukrainian football defender, currently playing for Mordovochka Saransk in the Russian Championship. She previously played for several sides in the Ukrainian League including Metalist Kharkiv with whom she played the 2004-05 UEFA Women's Cup, Energiya Voronezh in Russia and Medyk Konin in the Polish Ekstraliga. She is a member of the Ukrainian national team since 2008, and took part in the 2009 European Championship.

name: Iryna Zvarych
description: Iryna Zvarych is an international Ukrainian football goalkeeper playing in FCF Juvisy. She has won three Leagues and five national Cups with Rossiyanka, where she's currently the team's first choice goalkeeper. She can also play as a field player, and while playing for Energiya Voronezh she scored a hat trick over KFF Shkiponjat in the 2005 UEFA Women's Cup. Zvarych took part in the UEFA Women's Euro 2009 as Nadezhda Baranova's reserve. With Ukraine eliminated she was a starting player in the final group stage game against Finland, but she had to be replaced five minutes before half time following a collision with Laura Kalmari.

name: Isaac Chilemba
description: Isaac Chilemba (born 17 May 1987) is a Malawian professional boxer competing in the light heavyweight division. He is the former IBO world champion at super middleweight and former WBC International champion at light heavyweight. He has also held the African Boxing Union titles at both weights. Moreover, Isaac has been featured in the top ten in Ring Magazine's ratings for light heavyweights.

name: Isaac Cofie
description: Isaac Cofie (born September 20, 1991) is a Ghanaian professional footballer who is currently playing for Serie A club Chievo.

name: Isaac Harrison
description: Isaac Marshall Harrison (8 June 1880 – 25 February 1909) was an English cricketer. Harrison's batting style is unknown. He was born at Calverton, Nottinghamshire. Harrison made his first-class debut for Nottinghamshire against Middlesex at Lord's in the 1901 County Championship. He made six further first-class appearances in that season for the county, the last of which came against Lancashire at Old Trafford. In his seven first-class appearances for the county, he scored a total of 143 runs at an average of 14.30, with a high score of 33. He died at the village of his birth on 25 February 1909, following ill-health which had led him to give up playing cricket.

name: Isaac Ingram
description: Isaac Ingram (14 May 1855 – 19 November 1947) was an English cricketer. Ingram was a right-handed batsman who fielded as a wicket-keeper. He was born at Leigh, Kent. Ingram made his first-class debut for Kent against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1878. He made eleven further first-class appearances for the county, the last of which came against Nottinghamshire in 1879. In his twelve first-class matches, he scored 112 runs at an average of 5.89, with a high score of 25. Behind the stumps he took 8 catches and made 7 stumpings. He died at the village of his birth on 19 November 1947.

name: Isaac Kissi
description: Isaac Kissi (born May 14, 1987 in Brong-Ahafo) is a Ghanaian footballer currently playing for Rochester Rhinos in the American third division USL Pro.

name: Isaac Koné
description: Isaac Koné (born 3 January 1991) is an Ivorian footballer who plays for French club Étoile Fréjus Saint-Raphaël as a central defender.

name: Isaac Lea (footballer)
description: Isaac George Lea (17 February 1911 – 24 October 1972) was an English professional footballer who made 65 appearances in the Football League playing for Birmingham and Millwall. He played as a wing half. Lea was born in Donnington Wood, Shropshire. He began his football career with Oswestry Town and Oakengates Town before joining Birmingham of the Football League First Division in 1932. He made his debut on 8 October 1932 in a 2–1 win at home to Sheffield Wednesday, but was unable to dislodge England international right-half Lew Stoker from the starting eleven, and made only 28 appearances in all competitions in four-and-a-half years with the club. He joined Millwall at the end of the 1936–37 season, and contributed to their winning the Third Division South title the following season. He made guest appearances for Wrexham and for Wellington Town during the Second World War, and retired from football in 1943. He died in Dawley, Shropshire, in 1972 at the age of 61.

name: Isaac Thelin
description: Isaac Kiese Thelin (born 24 June 1992) is a Swedish footballer who plays for IFK Norrköping as a forward.

name: Isaac Vallie-Flagg
description: Isaac Vallie-Flagg (born April 8, 1978) is an American mixed martial artist currently competing in the lightweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship.

name: Isaak "Tjaak" Pattiwael
description: Isaak "Tjaak" Pattiwael (23 February 1914 – 16 March 1987) was an Indonesian football forward who played for the Dutch East Indies in the 1938 FIFA World Cup. He also played for VV Jong Ambon Batavia.

name: Isabella Shinikova
description: Isabella Shinikova (born October 25, 1991) is a professional Bulgarian tennis player. On April 02, 2012, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 289 whilst her best doubles ranking was 242 on July 23, 2012.

name: Isabella Tobias
description: Isabella Tobias (born August 23, 1991 in New York City, United States) is an American ice dancer who competes with Deividas Stagniūnas for Lithuania.

name: Isabelle Boéri-Bégard
description: Isabelle Boéri-Bégard (born 7 July 1960) is a French fencer. She won a gold medal in the women's team foil event at the 1980 Summer Olympics.

name: Isabelle Gauthier
description: Isabelle Gauthier (born 2 April 1980) is a Canadian ice skater, and as of 2011, one of the Dancing on Ice professional skaters.

name: Isabelle Olsson
description: Isabelle M. Olsson is a Swedish figure skater. Her mother, Susanne, and sister Angelica, are also involved in skating.

name: Isabelle Pedersen
description: Isabelle Pedersen (born January 27, 1992) is a Norwegian hurdling athlete. At the 2010 World Junior Championships in Athletics, she won a gold medal in the 100 m hurdles.

name: Isaia Rasila
description: Isaia Rasila (29 April 1969 – 9 October 2010) was a Fijian rugby union player, who was capped for Fiji on 34 occasions, five as team captain. He played in two Rugby World Cups.

name: Isaiah Frey
description: Isaiah Demetryst Frey (born April 6, 1990) is an American football cornerback for the Chicago Bears of the National Football League.

name: Isaiah Greenhouse
description: Isaiah Greenhouse (born July 15, 1987) is an American football linebacker and fullback who is currently a free agent. He was signed by the Houston Texans as an undrafted free agent in 2010. He played college football at Northwestern State.

name: Isaiah Pead
description: Isaiah D'Vaughn Pead (born December 14, 1989) is an American football running back for the St. Louis Rams of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Cincinnati. He was considered one of the top running back prospects for the 2012 NFL Draft.

name: Isaiah Smithurst
description: Isaiah Smithurst (6 November 1920 – 26 January 1982) was an English cricketer. Smithurst was a left-handed batsman who bowled slow left-arm orthodox. He was born in Eastwood, Nottinghamshire. Smithurst made a single first-class appearance for Nottinghamshire against Gloucestershire in 1946 County Championship.
