During his only first-class match, he scored 1 run and was dismissed for a duck in Nottinghamshire's first innings, leaving him a batting average of 0.50. He died at Giltbrook, Nottinghamshire on 26 January 1982.

name: Isak Ahrling
description: Isak Ahrling (born March 23, 1992) is a Swedish professional ice hockey player. He played with Modo Hockey in the Elitserien during the 2010–11 Elitserien season.

name: Isamu Matsuura
description: Isamu Matsuura is a football player for Shonan Bellmare in Japan's J. League.

name: Ishan Debnath
description: Ishan Debnath (born June 7, 1991) is an Indian footballer who currently plays for Prayag United in the I-League.

name: Ishmail Kamara
description: Foday Ishmail Kamara is a football (soccer) player currently playing for Football League Two club Barnet. He has gained five international caps for Sierra Leone.

name: Isiah Williams (basketball)
description: Isiah Williams is an American college basketball player for Utah Valley University. Williams was the Great West Conference player of the year in 2011 and UVU's first division I All-American in basketball. Williams, a 6'1" guard from Farragut High School in Chicago, Illinois, played two years of junior college ball at the College of Eastern Utah, where he led the Golden Eagles to a third place finish in the 2010 NJCAA Men's Division I Basketball Championship. He then moved to Utah Valley University to play for Dick Hunsaker and complete his four-year degree. In his junior season of 2010–11, Williams averaged 17.4 points and 1.8 assists per game as he led the Wolverines to an 11–1 finish and a Great West Conference regular-season championship. Williams was named first team All-Conference and Conference player of the year. At the conclusion of the season, Williams was named an Associated Press honorable mention All-American, making him the first player in school history to receive such an honor. In 2011–12, Williams was chosen to repeat as the preseason GWC player of the year by a vote of the league's coaches.

name: Isidor Sekseri
description: Isidor Sekseri (born 19 November 1986 in Rrethi i Mirditës) is an Albanian footballer who currently plays as a midfielder for Albanian champions Dinamo Tirana in the Albanian Superliga. His main position is in the centre of midfield but he can play in more advanced roles as well.

name: Isidro González
description: Isidro González (born October 15, 1907, date of death unknown) was a Spanish fencer. He competed in the individual sabre event at the 1928 Summer Olympics.

name: Isidro Gutiérrez
description: José Isidro Gutiérrez Vásquez (born 21 October 1989), is a Salvadoran footballer who currently plays as a midfielder for Águila in the Salvadoran Premier League.

name: Isitolo Maka
description: Isitolo Maka (born 25 May 1975) is a former rugby union footballer for the All Blacks playing as a number 8 and making four appearances, all in 1998. Maka was the coach of the Tonga squad at the 2011 Rugby World Cup. {{#invoke:citation/CS1|citation |CitationClass=web }}

name: Islam Feruz
description: Islam Feruz (born 10 September 1995) is a Scottish footballer who plays for English Premier League club Chelsea. He spent most of his youth career with Scottish Premier League team Celtic, but later moved to Chelsea in September 2011 after rejecting a professional contract with the Scottish club. A naturalised citizen of Scotland, Feruz declared in 2009 that he would play for the Scotland national football team, and has represented the country at several youth levels.

name: Islam Magdy
description: Islam Magdy (born 1990 in Zagazig) is an Egyptian footballer who last played as a midfielder for Svetkavitsa in the Bulgarian A PFG. He was released in November,2011.

name: Islam Saber
description: Islam Saber (born May 30, 1990) is an Egyptian football player who plays as a Striker for the Egyptian team Arab Contractors.

name: Islam Shamshiev
description: Islam Shamshiev, born 1 March 1991, is a Kyrgyzstani footballer who is a midfield player of Dordoi Bishkek.

name: Islam Tsuroyev
description: Islam Zyaudinovich Tsuroyev (Russian: Ислам Зяудинович Цуроев; born April 23, 1989) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Angusht Nazran. He made his professional debut in the Russian First Division in 2006 for FC Angusht Nazran.

name: Islem Chikhi
description: Islem Chikhi (born 18 May 1985 in Blida) is an Algerian professional football player who currently plays as a forward for Algerian Ligue 2 club Olympique de Médéa.

name: Islom Tukhtakhodjaev
description: Islom Tukhtahujaev (born 30 October 1989) is an Uzbek footballer who plays as a defender for Lokomotiv Tashkent. Islom is an Uzbek youth international, having represented his country at every level from Under-19 to Under-20. He was also capped for the senior national team.

name: Ismaél Díaz
description: José Ismaél Díaz (died 1976) was a Salvadoran footballer.

name: Ismaïl Mansouri
description: Ismaïl Mansouri (born March 12, 1988 in Blida) is an Algerian football player. He currently plays for USM Alger in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Isma Alif Mohd Salim
description: Isma Alif Bin Mohd Salim (born on February 22, 1987) is a Malaysian footballer. His preferred position is as a midfielder, and specially as a left winger.

name: Ismael D'Angelo Herrera
description: Ismael D'Angelo Herrera (born 3 October 1991) is an association footballer from American Samoa. Herrera can play either as a midfielder or as a forward and currently plays for domestic club PanSa East FC. Ismael has also represented his country at U20 level and at the 2011 Pacific Games.

name: Ismael Londt
description: Ismael Londt (born 14 November 1986) is a Surinamese-Dutch kickboxer, current SuperKombat Super Heavyweight Champion and 2012 K-1 World Grand Prix Final Runner-Up.

name: Ismail Al Hammadi
description: Ismail Al Hammadi (born July 1, 1988) is a footballer from the United Arab Emirates (UAE). He currently plays for Al-Ahli Football Club - Dubai.

name: Ismail Faruqi Asha'ri
description: Ismail Faruqi is a Malaysian footballer currently playing for Terengganu FA in Malaysia Super League. He plays as a central midfielder and sometimes attacking midfielder for the squad. He made his debut for Malaysia national football team in the 2014 FIFA World Cup qualifying match against Singapore on 23 July 2011. {{#invoke: Navbox | navbox }}

name: Isoa Logavatu
description: Isoa Tuinaceva Logavatu (born 1925 at Nadi, Fiji; died 1991 in Fiji) was a Fijian cricketer. Logavatu made his first-class debut for Fiji in 1948 against Auckland during Fiji's 1947/48 tour of New Zealand. During the tour he played five first-class matches, with his final first-class match coming against Auckland. In his 5 first-class matches for Fiji he scored 73 runs at a batting average of 12.16, with a high score of 48. With the ball he took 16 wickets at a bowling average of 30.00, with best figures of 4/46. Logavatu took 3 catches in the field. Logavatu also represented Fiji in 26 non first-class matches from 1948 to 1962, with his final match for Fiji coming against Taranaki during their 1961/62 tour of New Zealand. Logavatu died in Fiji in 1991.

name: Isobel Bishop
description: Isobel Bishop (born 8 September 1991) is an Australian water polo player. She has earned water polo scholarships from the South Australia Institute of Sport and the Australian Institute of Sport. She plays for the Adelaide Jets in the National Water Polo League. She is a member of the Australia women's national water polo team and won a gold medal at the 2011 Canada Cup and another gold at the 2011 FINA Junior World Championships. She is trying to solidify a spot on the team in order to represent the country at the 2012 Summer Olympics.

name: Isobel Christiansen
description: Isobel "Izzy" Christiansen is an English football midfielder currently playing for Birmingham City in the FA WSL. She has played the Champions League with Everton LFC. As a junior international she won the 2009 U-19 European Championship and a silver in the following year's edition, and played the 2008 U-17 and 2010 U-20 World Cups.

name: Israel Cohen
description: Israel Cohen is a former Israeli footballer who in 2002 while playing for Hapoel Haifa was suspected of Match fixing. He now plays amateur basketball with Hapoel Modi'in in Liga Bet (the 5th tier).

name: Israel Correa
description: Isarel Correa Beltran is a Mexican professional boxer in the Lightweight division. Guzmán was trained by Eduardo Garcia and is the former California State Lightweight Champion.

name: Israel Fogel
description: Israel Fogel (born 2 April 1949) is a retired Israeli footballer.

name: Israel Garcia
description: Israel Carlos Garcia (born May 12, 1970 in San Juan, Puerto Rico) is a Heavyweight boxer from Puerto Rico.

name: Israel Hajaj
description: Israel Hajaj is a retired Israeli footballer who is known for being the legendary captain of Maccabi Netanya in the late 1970s.

name: Israel Jiménez
description: Israel Sabdi Jiménez Nañez (August 13, 1989) is a Mexican footballer who plays for the Liga MX club Tigres de la UANL. A right back, Jiménez is a regular player for the Mexico national football team.

name: Israel Silva Matos de Souza
description: Israel Silva Matos de Souza (born 24 June 1981 in São Paulo, Brazil) is a Guatemalan football player who plays for Xelajú MC.

name: Israel Tordoya
description: Israel Jonathan Tordoya Isidro (born 21 February 1980) is a Peruvian footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder. He currently plays for Cobresol FBC.

name: Issa Al-Mohammadi
description: Issa Al-Mohammadi is a Qatarian football Defender who played for Qatar in the 1984 Asian Cup.

name: Issa Al-Sabah
description: Issa Al-Sabah (born on 1987) is a Jordanian footballer, of Palestinian origin, who is a forward for Al-Wahdat.

name: Issa Cissokho (footballer)
description: Issa Cissokho (born 23 February 1985 in Paris) is a French-born Senegalese football player who currently plays as a right back for Nantes in Ligue 2. He is the older brother of Valencia CF and French international defender Aly Cissokho. Cissokho began his career playing for Louhans-Cuiseaux and made his professional debut with the club at the age of 17 in the 2002–03 Championnat National season. After the season, he signed with Guingamp and spent his entire career at the club playing on its reserve team. After two years playing for amateurs clubs Orléans and Blois, respectively, Cissokho joined Carquefou in the Championnat de France amateur 2, the fifth level of French football. In his first season at the club, he helped the team achieve promotion to the Championnat de France amateur. After another season with Carquefou, in June 2010, Cissokho signed an amateur contract with professional club Nantes. After spending the majority of the 2010–11 season playing on the club's reserve team, in April 2011, Cissokho was called up to the senior team and made his club debut on 15 April in a league match against Dijon. In the following match, he scored his first professional goal in a 2–2 draw with Nîmes.

name: Issac Booth
description: Isaac Ramoun Booth is a retired American professional football player who played three seasons in the National Football League with the Cleveland Browns and Baltimore Ravens. Booth was drafted by the Browns in the fifth round of the 1994 NFL Draft and played defensive back for the Browns for the 1994 and 1995 seasons, earning one start in each of his first two seasons. After the 1995 season the original Cleveland Browns relocated to Baltimore, Maryland and became the Baltimore Ravens. Booth played his final season with the Ravens playing in 11 games and earning a career high three starts. Booth retired from football after the 1996 season. During his brief career, Booth played in 36 games, earning five starts, 55 tackles, two interceptions and one forced fumble.

name: Issac Monks
description: Issac Monks was an English footballer who played for Derby County.

name: Issaga Diallo
description: Issaga Diallo (born 26 January 1987) is a French footballer who plays for Servette FC in the Swiss Super League.

name: Issam Mahrous
description: Essam Mahrous is a Syrian football Defender who played for Syria in the 1984 Asian Cup.

name: Issei Yoshimi
description: Issei Yoshimi (born June 16, 1982) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Issiaka Eliassou
description: Issiaka Eliassou (born 12 August 1985) is a Malian football player currently playing for the Egyptian Premier League side Smouha Sporting Club as a right back. He is a member of Mali national football team.

name: Issouf Campaoré
description: Issouf Campaoré (born 12 April 1988 in Agnibilékrou in Côte d'Ivoire) is a Burkinabé international football defender playing with FK Banat Zrenjanin in Serbian First League. Formed at l’Ecole de Formation Yeo Martial (EFYM) in Côte d'Ivoire he played with Ivorian A.S.C. Ouragahio. He had trials with Olympique de Marseille and short spells with R.E. Virton and FC Metz before moving to Serbia in 2008 where after playing initially one season with lower leagues club FK Fruškogorac he signed with FK Banat Zrenjanin. He preferably plays as left-back although he can also play as left-winger. Despite being born in Côte d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast) and having made part of the Côte d'Ivoire cadetes national team, he has chousen to represent Burkina Faso national team since 2008.

name: Issoufou Boubacar Garba
description: Issoufou Boubacar Garba (born 2 February 1990) is a Nigerien footballer who plays for Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1 side ES Hammam-Sousse as a midfielder. He plays national football for his country.

name: István Básti
description: István Básti (born 19 September 1944 in Salgótarján) is a Hungarian footballer. He was born in Salgótarján in Nógrád County. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City, where the won a gold medal with the Hungarian team.

name: István Halász
description: István Halász (born 12 October 1951) is a Hungarian football midfielder who played for Hungary in the 1978 FIFA World Cup. He also played for FC Tatabánya.

name: István Kovács (footballer born 1992)
description: István Kovács (born 27 March 1992 in Szombathely) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Videoton. He is a midfielder who began his career at Haladas, where he played very well during the first half of the 2011/2012 season. His impressive performances earned him a move to Hungarian giants Videoton in January 2012. So far he hasn't been able to fight himself into the starting 11 but if he keeps going no doubt he could be a star in the future.

name: István Ladóczki
description: István Ladóczki (born 11 January 1986 in Budapest) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for USC Mank.

name: István Ludánszki
description: István Ludánszki (born 27 July 1987 in Debrecen) is a Hungarian Football (soccer) defender. He currently plays for Balmazújvárosi FC.

name: István Mészáros (footballer)
description: István Mészáros (born 3 March 1980 in Szekszárd) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Paksi SE.

name: István Marton
description: István Marton (born 15 November 1944) is a Hungarian Olympic fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: István Nagy (footballer born 1986)
description: István Nagy (born 16 May 1986 in Dunaújváros) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Paksi SE.

name: István Osztrics
description: István Osztrics (born 25 December 1949) is a Hungarian fencer. He won a gold medal in the team épée event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: István Sipeki
description: István Sipeki (born 17 February 1979 in Eger) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Paksi SE.

name: István Szekér
description: István Szekér (born 25 December 1970 in Várpalota) is a Hungarian football player.

name: István Szelei
description: István Szelei (born 7 December 1960) is a Hungarian fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team foil event at the 1988 Summer Olympics.

name: Istvan Kulcsar
description: Istvan Kulcsar (born 13 September 1936) is a Swiss fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Ita Vaea
description: Ita Vaea (born 9 February 1989) is a Tongan rugby union player who plays for the Brumbies in Super Rugby. His playing position is openside flanker. He made his Brumbies debut during the 2011 Super Rugby season against the Sharks in Canberra. Vaea attended Nelson College from 2006 to 2007.

name: Itan Chavira
description: Itan Daniel Chavira is a former American minor league ice hockey forward currently playing for the USA National Inline Team and the Ripon Savage of American Inline Hockey League.

name: Itzhak Vissoker
description: Itzhak Vissoker (born 18 September 1944) is an Israeli former international footballer who competed at the 1970 FIFA World Cup, as well as at the 1976 Summer Olympics. Vissoker played in 40 official games for the Israeli national side. Vissoker played club football for Hapoel Petah Tikva and Maccabi Netanya.

name: Iulian Arhire
description: Iulian Arhire (born 17 March 1976 in Galaţi) is a Romanian professional footballer player who played as a midfielder.

name: Iulian Bursuc
description: Iulian Bursuc (born 23 September 1976) is a retired Moldovan professional football player. He latest played for Dacia Chişinău. He retired from the game immediately after he punched a referee in 2009.

name: Iulian Dumitraș
description: Iulian Dumitraş (born Suceava, 22 June 1982) is a Romanian rugby union player. He plays as a fly-half and as a fullback. Dumitraş played in France for Tarbes Pyrénées Rugby, Section Paloise (2005/06-2007/08) SC Albi 2008/09 and now plays for FC Lourdes(Rugby). He has 23 caps for Romania, since his debut in 2002, with 7 tries, 4 conversions and 1 penalty scored, 46 points in aggregate. The Romanian player was present at the 2007 Rugby World Cup finals, playing in all the four games.

name: Iuri Gabiskiria
description: Iuri Gabiskiria (Georgian: იური გაბისკირია; born 1 September 1968 in Bakuriani) is a retired Georgian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet Second League in 1988 for FC Torpedo Kutaisi. He played 2 games in the UEFA Cup 2006–07 for FC Ameri Tbilisi.

name: Iuri Osip'ovi
description: Iuri Osip'ovi (born 16 March 1937) is a Soviet Olympic fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil events at the 1956 Summer Olympics.

name: Iván Arturo Torres
description: Ivan Arturo Torres (born 27 February 1991 in Asunción) is a Paraguayan football medfield who currently plays for Cerro Porteño.

name: Iván Candela
description: Iván Menéndez Candela is a Spanish footballer who plays for Real Oviedo in the Spanish third division, as a left defender.

name: Iván Endara
description: Iván Endara is an Ecuadorian professional tennis player.

name: Iván García (diver)
description: Iván Alejandro García Navarro (born 25 October 1993 in Guadalajara) is a Mexican diver. He is nicknamed "Pollo" ("Chicken"). He won two gold medals in the 2011 Pan-American Games. At the 2012 Summer Olympics in London García won the silver medal in the synchronized 10 metre platform diving, with his partner Germán Sánchez.

name: Iván Garrido
description: Iván Garrido (born June 2, 1981, Colombia) is a Colombian footballer. He is currently under contract with Atlético Huila.

name: Iván Menczel
description: Iván Menczel (14 December 1941 – 26 November 2011) was a Hungarian football midfielder and Olympic champion. Menczel won the Olympic Games title in Mexico City in 1968, and in addition he was member of the Hungarian team which participated at the 1962 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Salgótarjáni BTC.

name: Iván Morales
description: José Iván Morales Elvira is an undefeated Mexican professional boxer in the Bantamweight division. He's the younger brother of both Diego Morales a former WBO Champion and of Boxing Legend Erik Morales.

name: Iván Moreno Dellano
description: José Iván Moreno Dellano is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for SD Ponferradina in Segunda División, as a midfielder.

name: Iván Peñaranda
description: Iván Peñaranda Llauradó (born 6 March 1981) is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a forward. After signing a contract with A.C. Milan at the age of 18, his career never developed, as he played for mostly in the lower leagues of his country – which included spells in amateur football – and abroad. In Spain, he played in four different categories, but never in La Liga.

name: Iván Piris
description: Iván Rodrigo Piris (born 10 March 1989) is a Paraguayan football right-footed defender who plays for Serie A club Roma, on loan from Deportivo Maldonado.

name: Iván Popoca
description: Rey Iván Popoca is a Mexican professional boxer in the Light Welterweight division.

name: Iván Pozo
description: Iván Pozo is a Spanish professional boxer. Pozo is a former EBU European Flyweight champion and former WBO Inter-Continental Flyweight champion. He currently fights at bantamweight and defended his WBC Mundo Hispano title by defeating Adonis Rivas by unanimous decision on March 4, 2011.

name: Iván Ramírez
description: Iván Ramírez is an undefeated Mexican professional boxer in the Middleweight division.

name: Iván Trevejo
description: Iván Trevejo (born 9 November 1971) is a Cuban fencer. He won a silver medal in the individual épée event at the 1996 Summer Olympics and a bronze in the team event at the 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: Iván Vargas
description: Iván Vargas (born 5 June 1991) is a Paraguayan football left midfielder. He currently plays for Club Rubio Ñu.

name: Iva Landeka
description: Iva Landeka is a Bosnian-born Croatian football midfielder currently playing for USV Jena in the German Bundesliga. She previously played for Dinamo Maksimir in the Croatian 1st Division, FC Kärnten in the Austrian Frauenliga and Unia Racibórz in the Polish Ekstraliga, also playing the Champions League with Dinamo and Unia. She is a member of the Croatian national team since 2005. Her brother Davor and her cousin Josip are also footballers, currently playing respectively for Grasshopper Zürich and Carl Zeiss Jena.

name: Iva Mocová
description: Iva Mocová is an international Czech football striker playing for Sparta Prague. She has been a member of the Czech national team since 2003. That same year she first played the UEFA Women's Cup with Slavia Prague. Mocová scored two goals in the 2011 World Cup qualifying. She subsequently scored the Czech Republic's first goal in the 2013 Euro qualifying in a 1-1 tie against Austria.

name: Ivan, Viscount d'Oyley
description: Ivan, Viscount d'Oyley, born Alastair Ivan Ladislaus Lucidus Evans, (2 February 1880 – 26 May 1904) was an American who competed for France at the Olympics in fencing. He competed in the individual épée event at the 1900 Summer Olympics. He inherited the title of Viscount from his father, an American dentist, Dr. John Henry Evans. Dr. Evans worked on Pope Leo XIII, who gave him the title of the Marquis d'Oyley. Viscount d'Oyley killed himself from a self-inflicted gunshot.

name: Ivan Ďatelinka
description: Ivan Ďatelinka (born March 6, 1983) is a Slovak professional ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing with HC Slovan Bratislava of the Kontinental Hockey League.

name: Ivan Žugčić
description: Ivan Žugčić (born 22 May 1958) is a retired Croatian football defender.

name: Ivan Asyutin
description: Ivan Nikolayevich Asyutin (Russian: Иван Николаевич Асютин; born January 17, 1989) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Fakel Voronezh. He played for the main squad of FC Fakel Voronezh in the Russian Cup.

name: Ivan Baraban
description: Ivan Baraban (born 21 January 1988 in Vinkovci) is a Croatian football player, currently playing for RNK Split in the Prva HNL.

name: Ivan Bartoš
description: Ivan Bartoš (born 25 April 1977) is a Slovak football striker who currently plays for TUS Gross St. Florian.

name: Ivan Božović
description: Ivan Božović is a Serbian footballer. He currently plays for FK Smederevo .

name: Ivan Bobylev
description: Ivan Andreyevich Bobylev (Russian: Иван Андреевич Бобылев; born March 7, 1991) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Torpedo Vladimir.

name: Ivan Brondi de Carvalho
description: Ivan Brondi de Carvalho (born 7 October 1941) is a Brazilian former footballer.

name: Ivan Brown (Canadian football)
description: Ivan Brown (born July 18, 1985 in Regina, Saskatchewan) is a professional Canadian football defensive end for the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted by the Alouettes in the fourth round of the 2009 CFL Draft. He has also been a member of the Hamilton Tiger-Cats. He played CIS football for the Saskatchewan Huskies.

name: Ivan Bukenya
description: Ivan Bukenya (born 1 November 1991) is a Ugandan professional footballer who plays in the Iraqi Premier League.

name: Ivan Cacchioli
description: Ivan Cacchioli is an Italian football player who is currently playing for Pavia on loan from Parma.

name: Ivan Castiglia
description: Ivan Castiglia (born January 6, 1988 in Cosenza) is an Italian footballer who plays for Serie B club Reggina. Castiglia returned to Reggina from Cittadella in the winter transfer season.

name: Ivan Cvjetković
description: Ivan Cvjetković (born 2 January 1960) is a retired Croatian international football player.

name: Ivan Danshin
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Danshin (Russian: Иван Александрович Даньшин; born April 20, 1982) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 1999 for PFC CSKA-2 Moscow.

name: Ivan Dechev
description: Ivan Dechev (Bulgarian: Иван Дечев is a Bulgarian footballer who plays for Slavia Sofia.

name: Ivan Dineen
description: Ivan Dineen (born 5 July 1987 in Ireland) is an Irish rugby union player for Munster in the Pro 12. He plays as a Centre or Wing.

name: Ivan Dornič
description: Ivan Dornič is a Slovakian professional ice hockey player in Slovakia recently with MHC Martin of the Slovak Extraliga. He was selected by the New York Rangers in the 6th round (176th overall) of the 2003 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Ivan Dupasquier
description: Ivan Dupasquier (born 23 November 1961) is a former professional tennis player from Switzerland.

name: Ivan Dyagolchenko
description: Ivan Alekseyevich Dyagolchenko (Russian: Иван Алексеевич Дьягольченко; born November 2, 1980) is a Russian professional footballer. In 2011, he played for FC Sokol Saratov.

name: Ivan Dzenisevich
description: Ivan Dzenisevich (Belarusian: Іван Дзенісевіч; Russian: Иван Денисевич; born 9 November 1984) is a Belarusian professional footballer. As of 2012, he plays for Neman Grodno.

name: Ivan Franjic
description: Ivan Franjic (born 10 September 1987) is an Australian football (soccer) player of Croatian descent currently playing for A-League club Brisbane Roar.

name: Ivan Goranov
description: Ivan Goranov (Bulgarian: Иван Горанов; born on 10 June 1992) is a Bulgarian footballer currently playing as a winger for Beroe Stara Zagora.

name: Ivan Goryunov
description: Ivan Andreyevich Goryunov (Russian: Иван Андреевич Горюнов; born May 28, 1988) is a Russian professional football player. He plays for FC Dynamo Barnaul.

name: Ivan Grésèque
description: Ivan Grésèque is a French rugby league former player, coach and manager who represented his country. His son, Maxime, has also represented France at halfback.

name: Ivan Grinyuk
description: Ivan Nikolayevich Grinyuk (Russian: Иван Николаевич Гринюк; born April 25, 1979) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC MITOS Novocherkassk.

name: Ivan Hladík
description: Ivan Hladík (born 30 January 1993 in Myjava) is a Slovak football defender who currently plays for FK Senica.

name: Ivan Jakov Džoni
description: Ivan Jakov Džoni (born 25 July 1994 in Split) is a Croatian football forward, currently playing for HNK Hajduk Split.

name: Ivan Jerković
description: Ivan Jerković (born 13 January 1979) is a Croatian professional footballer who last played in Singapore for Brunei DPMM, as a midfielder.

name: Ivan Kalchuk
description: Ivan Sergeyevich Kalchuk (Russian: Иван Сергеевич Кальчук; born May 8, 1991) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Sever Murmansk.

name: Ivan Kemnitz
description: Ivan Kemnitz (born 14 April 1943) is a Danish fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivan Khlyntsev
description: Ivan Khlyntsev is a Russian professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for HC Yugra of the Kontinental Hockey League (KHL).

name: Ivan Khomutov
description: Ivan Khomutov (born March 11, 1985) is a Russian professional ice hockey forward. He is currently playing with Kompanion-Naftogaz Kyiv of the Ukrainian Professional Hockey League (PHL). He was selected by New Jersey Devils in the 8th round (242nd overall) of the 2002 NHL Entry Draft. Prior to returning to Russian to join the KHL for the 2008–09 KHL season, Khomutov had played 201 games in the American Hockey League with the Albany River Rats and Lowell Devils.

name: Ivan Khristov
description: Ivan Mariyanov Khristov (Russian: Иван Мариянов Христов; born July 6, 1992) is a Russian professional football player of Bulgarian descent, who last played for FC Gubkin.

name: Ivan Klyukin
description: Ivan Vasilyevich Klyukin (Russian: Иван Васильевич Клюкин; born June 5, 1986) is a Russian football midfielder who currently plays for FC Gornyak Uchaly. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Metallurg Lipetsk in 2006.

name: Ivan Knezović
description: Ivan Knezović (born 25 September 1982) is a Croatian football defender who currently plays for Domžale in the Slovenian PrvaLiga.

name: Ivan Kocjančić
description: Ivan Kocjančić is a former Croatian football player. Born in Rijeka, he played for HNK Rijeka during his entire career, collecting close to 500 caps. He played as a defender and captained his club when it won promotion to the Yugoslav First League in 1974. Following the end of his career he remained active with Rijeka, coaching in the youth programme. He managed one of Rijeka games as an interim manager in 1996.

name: Ivan Kolosov
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Kolosov (Russian: Иван Александрович Колосов; born May 6, 1984) is a Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Astrakhan.

name: Ivan Kolpakov
description: Ivan Leonidovich Kolpakov (Russian: Иван Леонидович Колпаков; born April 26, 1993) is a Russian football striker who currently plays for FC Slavyansky Slavyansk-na-Kubani. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Slavyansky Slavyansk-na-Kubani on April 17, 2011 in a game against FC Olimpia Gelendzhik.

name: Ivan Komarov
description: Ivan Komarov (Russian: Иван Комаров; born 19 June 1921) is a Soviet fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivan Korbankolev
description: Ivan Korbankolev (born on 20 June 1987) is a Bulgarian footballer currently playing as a striker for Yeledzhik Ihtiman.

name: Ivan Korobkov
description: Ivan Mikhailovich Korobkov (Russian: Иван Михайлович Коробков; born March 18, 1988) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Volochanin-Ratmir Vyshny Volochyok in the Russian Second Division.

name: Ivan Kotora
description: Ivan Kotora (born 27 June 1991 in Levice) is a Slovak football midfielder who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club MFK Ružomberok.

name: Ivan Kurdanin
description: Ivan Yuryevich Kurdanin (Russian: Иван Юрьевич Курданин; born March 24, 1984) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Gubkin. He played for the main squad of FC Amkar Perm in the Russian Cup.

name: Ivan Kurpishev
description: Ivan Borisovich Kurpishev (born 2 March 1969) is a Russian powerlifter.

name: Ivan Kusakin
description: Ivan Valeriyevich Kusakin (Russian: Иван Валериевич Кусакин; born October 18, 1991) is a Russian football defender, who currently plays for FC KUZBASS Kemerovo. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC KUZBASS Kemerovo on August 21, 2011 in a game against FC Chita.

name: Ivan Lendrić
description: Ivan Lendrić (born 8 August 1991) is a Croatian football player currently playing for Zulte Waregem in the Belgian Pro League.

name: Ivan Loseto
description: Ivan Loseto (born 23 February 1988) is an Italian footballer. He is the son of former footballer Giovanni Loseto.

name: Ivan Lozenkov
description: Ivan Sergeyevich Lozenkov (Russian: Иван Сергеевич Лозенков; born April 14, 1984) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Arsenal Tula. He played for the main squad of FC Zenit St. Petersburg in the Russian Premier League Cup. In October 2009, he received a contusion when a fan threw a firecracker at him from the stands. Early in 2009, he played for the farm club of FC Zenit St. Petersburg called FC Smena-Zenit St. Petersburg and was the team's captain. Zenit fans considered him transferring to the rival Dynamo St. Petersburg team as betrayal.

name: Ivan Lukyanov
description: Ivan Ananyevich Lukyanov (Russian: Иван Ананьевич Лукьянов; born 27 December 1990) is a Russian football striker, who currently plays for FC KAMAZ Naberezhnye Chelny. He made his professional debut for FC KAMAZ Naberezhnye Chelny on April 4, 2011 in a Russian First Division game against FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok.

name: Ivan Manayenko
description: Ivan Manayenko (Russian: Иван Ильич Манаенко; 1919–1985) was a Soviet fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivan Marconi
description: Ivan Marconi (born 25 October 1989) is an Italian footballer who plays for Seconda Divisione club Savona.

name: Ivan Markelov
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Markelov (Russian: Иван Александрович Маркелов; born April 17, 1988) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Karelia Petrozavodsk.

name: Ivan Mekikov
description: Ivan Mekikov (Bulgarian: Иван Мекиков; born 29 May 1982) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays as a midfielder for Vidima-Rakovski.

name: Ivan Merli Sala
description: Ivan Merli Sala (born 8 February 1989) is an Italian footballer who plays for Italian fourth division club Lecco.

name: Ivan Milosavljević
description: Ivan Milosavljević is a Serbian football defender who plays for Rudar Kostolac.

name: Ivan Močinić
description: Ivan Močinić is a Croatian football player currently playing for HNK Rijeka in Croatia's Prva HNL. Born in Rijeka, in his first professional season he collected 13 caps and scored his first goal for Rijeka in the last round of 2011-12 Prva HNL. He has also had 8 caps for Croatia's Under-19 side, including 3 games at the 2012 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship. He is regarded as one of Rijeka's greatest prospects.

name: Ivan Mršić
description: Ivan Mršić, also known as John Mrsic and Big J, (born August 1, 1949) is a retired professional footballer. Born in Teslić, SR Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia, he began his career in 1963, with local club FK Proleter Teslić. He was picked up by bigger club FK Borac Banja Luka the next season. He turned down an offer from Croatian Giants HNK Hajduk Split and went on to play with many Yugoslav clubs including three first division clubs NK Olimpija Ljubljana, FK Radnički 1923, and Yugoslav power house FK Partizan Belgrade although he never got to make any league appearance for them. He finished his European career with Macedonian club FK Pelister before coming and playing professional in the United States for Fort Lauderdale Strikers in 1978. After a season he went on to play for ASL`s Columbus Magic In 1981, Mršić signed with the Cleveland Force of the Major Indoor Soccer League. He then moved to Canada where he spent a season with the amateur Serbian White Eagles before finishing his career with Toronto Croatia.

name: Ivan Nagaev
description: Ivan Nagaev (Russian: Иван Нагаев; born 3 July 1990) is an Uzbekistani professional footballer who currently plays for Lokomotiv Tashkent. He plays as a forward.

name: Ivan Nagibin
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Nagibin (Russian: Иван Александрович Нагибин; born March 21, 1986) is a Russian professional football player. He plays for FC Tom Tomsk.

name: Ivan Novović
description: Ivan Novović (born 26 April 1989) is a Montenegrin professional footballer playing for FK Zeta.

name: Ivan Olegovich Yakovlev
description: Ivan Olegovich Yakovlev (Russian: Иван Олегович Яковлев; born January 27, 1993) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Radian-Baikal Irkutsk.

name: Ivan Ondruška
description: Ivan Ondruška (born 12 September 1967) is a former Slovak football goalkeeper who recently played for the Slovak 2. liga club MŠK Rimavská Sobota.

name: Ivan Ordets
description: Ivan Ordets is a Ukrainian football defender who plays on loan for team of FC Illichivets Mariupol in the Ukrainian Premier League. Ordets is the member of different Ukrainian national youth football teams. He also is member of Ukraine national under-19 football team last time and scored 1 goal in match against Sweden national under-19 football team on 9 October 2010.

name: Ivan Ostojić
description: Ivan Ostojić (Serbian Cyrillic: Иван Остојић; born 26 June 1989 in Pančevo) is a Serbian football defender who currently plays for the Corgoň Liga club MFK Košice.

name: Ivan Paunović
description: Ivan Paunović is a Serbian football midfielder. He signed his first contract in 2003 with FK Smederevo playing back then in the First League of Serbia and Montenegro. Still young and after not getting any chance to play in the league during that year, he decided to continue his career in lower league clubs such as FK Sloga Požega, FK Vujić Voda and FK Sloboda Užice. In summer 2006 he moved to FK Mladi Radnik and after a good first half of the season, he spent the next six months on loan with FK Voždovac playing then in the 2006–07 Serbian SuperLiga. Unfortunately FK Voždovac ended the seasons relegated, but Paunović impressed and the club signed him and he will end up playing two more seasons with them. In 2009 he moved to FK Srem Sremska Mitrovica and after six months Romanian Liga I club FC Universitatea Craiova signed him. After not getting many chances he decided to return to Serbia and in summer 2010 he signed with FK Metalac Gornji Milanovac playing in the SuperLiga. In winter break of 2010-11 he was loaned to FK Novi Pazar to help the club to reach its ambitions to end the season promoted to the SuperLiga for its first time.

name: Ivan Pazemov
description: Ivan Vladimirovich Pazemov (Russian: Иван Владимирович Паземов; born July 23, 1973) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Russian Premier League in 1992 for FC Torpedo Moscow.

name: Ivan Pešić
description: Ivan Pešić (Serbian Cyrillic: Иван Пешић, born 7 July 1989) is a Serbian football midfielder playing for FK Mladost Lučani in the Serbian First League.

name: Ivan Penkin
description: Ivan Mikhailovich Penkin (Russian: Иван Михайлович Пенкин; born September 11, 1986) is a Russian football midfielder who currently plays for FC Irtysh Omsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Chkalovets Novosibirsk in 2006.

name: Ivan Perfilyev
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Perfilyev (Russian: Иван Александрович Перфильев; born September 6, 1988) is a Russian professional football player who last played in 2010 for FC Khimik Dzerzhinsk.

name: Ivan Petryak
description: Ivan Petryak is a professional Ukrainian football midfielder who plays for Zorya Luhansk in the Ukrainian Premier League. He made his debut for main Zorya team as substitution in second half in match against Shakhtar Donetsk in Ukrainian Premier League in 2 October 2011.

name: Ivan Piccoli
description: Ivan Piccoli (born April 3, 1981 in Fano) is an Italian professional footballer who plays for Fano. In January 2008 he was loaned to Ancona. He was signed outright in June. After Ancona was expelled from professional league, he joined Fano on 6 December 2010.

name: Ivan Podolyak
description: Ivan Olegovich Podolyak (Russian: Иван Олегович Подоляк; born October 4, 1990) is a Russian professional association football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Avangard Kursk.

name: Ivan Quintans
description: Ivan Quintans (born 15 October 1989) is a Liechtensteiner footballer who currently plays for FC Balzers.

name: Ivan Redkach
description: Ivan Redkach is an undefeated Ukrainian professional boxer in the Lightweight division.

name: Ivan Reitmayer
description: Ivan Reitmayer is a Slovakian professional ice hockey defenceman who played with HK SKP Poprad in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Ivan Reyzvikh
description: Ivan Yuryevich Reyzvikh (Russian: Иван Юрьевич Рейзвих; born December 21, 1981) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Volga Tver.

name: Ivan Rybakov
description: Ivan Olegovich Rybakov (Russian: Иван Олегович Рыбаков; born December 14, 1986) is a Russian football midfielder, who last played for FC Syzran-2003 Syzran. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Syzran-2003 Syzran on May 30, 2011 in a game against FC Ufa.

name: Ivan Sablya
description: Ivan Nikolayevich Sablya (Russian: Иван Николаевич Сабля; born November 15, 1982) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Dynamo Kostroma in the Russian Second Division.

name: Ivan Semenets
description: Ivan Viktorovich Semenets (Russian: Иван Викторович Семенец; born October 1, 1981) is a Russian professional footballer. In 2009, he played for FC Fakel-Voronezh Voronezh. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2001 for FC Fakel Voronezh.

name: Ivan Semyonov
description: Ivan Vladimirovich Semyonov (Russian: Иван Владимирович Семёнов; born July 9, 1988) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Ufa.

name: Ivan Sergeyev
description: Ivan Sergeyev is a professional tennis player.

name: Ivan Shamarin
description: Ivan Sergeyevich Shamarin (Russian: Иван Сергеевич Шамарин; born March 7, 1992) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Rubin-2 Kazan.

name: Ivan Shpakov
description: Ivan Vladimirovich Shpakov (Russian: Иван Владимирович Шпаков; born June 8, 1986 in Kingisepp) is a Russian professional footballer. He plays for FC Metallurg-Kuzbass Novokuznetsk. He made his professional debut in the Russian Second Division in 2002 for FC Mostransgaz Gazoprovod. He played 3 games in the UEFA Cup 2005–06 qualification rounds for FC Krylia Sovetov Samara. In June 2009 he was signed by FK Ventspils. In August 2010 he left the team, becoming a free agent after a very successful season with the club.

name: Ivan Shtefko
description: Ivan Yuryevich Shtefko (Russian: Иван Юрьевич Штефко; born November 26, 1986) is a Russian professional football player. In 2011, he played for FC Zenit-Izhevsk Izhevsk.

name: Ivan Shyshkin
description: Ivan Shyshkin born 16 September 1983 in Magdeburg, GDR,, is a Ukrainian football midfielder currently playing for PFC Sevastopol.

name: Ivan Skerlev
description: Ivan Skerlev (Bulgarian: Иван Скерлев; born 28 January 1986 in Haskovo) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays for Haskovo as a defender.

name: Ivan Snezhko
description: Ivan Aleksandrovich Snezhko (Russian: Иван Александрович Снежко; born March 24, 1988) is a Russian professional football player. In 2010, he played for FC Zelenograd in the Russian Second Division.

name: Ivan Stoyanov (footballer born 1949)
description: Ivan Georgiev Stoyanov (Bulgarian: Ивaн Гeopгйeв Cтoянoв; born 20 January 1949) is a Bulgarian former football midfielder who played for Bulgaria in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Levski Sofia.

name: Ivan Tasić
description: Ivan Tasić (born 8 May 1979) is a footballer who plays as a midfielder for Kavala.

name: Ivan Temnikov
description: Ivan Viktorovich Temnikov (Russian: Иван Викторович Темников; born 28 January 1989) is a Russian footballer currently playing for FC Rubin Kazan of Russia. He primarily plays as a right defender. He made his professional debut in the Russian Premier League in 2007 for FC Saturn Moscow Oblast.

name: Ivan Trushkin
description: Ivan Sergeyevich Trushkin (Russian: Иван Сергеевич Трушкин; born June 2, 1985) is a Russian professional football player. He last played in the Russian Second Division for FC Zvezda Ryazan.

name: Ivan Tsankov
description: Ivan Tsankov (born 26 March 1984) is a Bulgarian football player, who last played for Nesebar as a midfielder.

name: Ivan Tsvetkov
description: Ivan Petkov Tsvetkov (Bulgarian: Иван Цветков; born 31 August 1979 in Blagoevgrad) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays as a forward for Botev Plovdiv.

name: Ivan Ustinov
description: Ivan Vitalyevich Ustinov (Russian: Иван Витальевич Устинов; born July 17, 1994) is a Russian football midfielder who currently plays for FC Dynamo Kirov. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Saturn-2 Moscow Oblast on April 30, 2011 in a game against FC Dynamo Kostroma.

name: Ivan Vinkov
description: Ivan Vinkov Bulgaria) is a Bulgarian football midfielder who plays for Slavia Sofia.

name: Ivan Vinnikov
description: Ivan Vinnikov (Russian: Иван Винников; born May 28, 1964) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet Second League in 1988 for FC Torpedo Naberezhnye Chelny. He played 5 games and scored 1 goal in the UEFA Intertoto Cup 1996 for FC KAMAZ-Chally Naberezhnye Chelny.

name: Ivan Vladimirovich Bakulin
description: Ivan Vladimirovich Bakulin (Russian: Иван Владимирович Бакулин; born April 16, 1986) is a Russian professional football player. In 2009, he played in the Russian Second Division for FC Istra. He played for the main squad of FC Moscow in the Russian Cup.

name: Ivan Vodanovich
description: Ivan Vodanovich (born 8 April 1930 in Wanganui, New Zealand—died 2 September 1995, Wellington, New Zealand) was a New Zealand Rugby union player and coach. He played three tests for the All Blacks in 1955, the New Zealand national rugby union team's 384th cap. Vodanovich was All Blacks coach from 1969 to 1971. As then coach and chief selector of the New Zealand team, he gained some notoriety for warning that the first test of the British Lions 1971 tour of New Zealand could be "another Passchendaele" for the Lions if they continued to play negative rugby as they had in a preliminary match against Canterbury. The Lions went on to record a rare series win 2-1.

name: Ivan Volobuiev
description: Ivan Nikolayevich Volobuiev (Russian: Иван Николаевич Волобуев; born 5 January 1991 in Moscow) is a Russian ice dancer. He currently competes with partner Valeria Starygina.

name: Ivan Vyacheslavovich Belyayev
description: Ivan Vyacheslavovich Belyayev (Russian: Иван Вячеславович Беляев; born May 26, 1986) is a Russian professional football player who is currently a free agent.

name: Ivan Yershov (footballer)
description: Ivan Ivanovich Yershov (Russian: Иван Иванович Ершов; born May 22, 1979) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Arsenal Tula. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2001 for FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk. He played 2 games in the UEFA Cup 2001–02 with FC Chernomorets Novorossiysk.

name: Ivan Yevgenyevich Novoseltsev
description: Ivan Yevgenyevich Novoseltsev (Russian: Иван Евгеньевич Новосельцев; born August 25, 1991) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Torpedo Moscow in the Russian First Division.

name: Ivan Zafirov
description: Ivan Georgiev Zafirov (Bulgarian: Ивaн Гeopгйeв Цафиpoв) (born 30 December 1947) is a former Bulgarian football defender. After short spells at Sliven, it was with CSKA Sofia that he found his spiritual home in the 1970s. Zafirov, a right-back, played 340 times for the Reds, scoring 8 goals. Nine Bulgarian championships and five Bulgarian Cups tell the tale of how successful Zafirov was. Zafirov was on Bulgaria's roster for the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He represented the Lions 50 times, scoring once. Zafirov won a silver medal at the 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivan Zavaliy
description: Ivan Viktorovich Zavaliy (Russian: Иван Викторович Завалий; born September 18, 1984) is a Russian professional footballer. Currently, he plays for FC Biolog-Novokubansk Progress. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2004 for FC Rubin Kazan.

name: Ivana Andrés
description: Ivana Andrés Sanz is a Spanish football defender currently playing for Valencia CF in the Spanish 1st Division. She is currently an under-19 international. As an under-17 international she won the 2010 and 2011 U-17 European Championships and a bronze in the 2010 U-17 World Cup.

name: Ivana Bojdová
description: Ivana Bojdová is a Slovak midfielder currently playing for Unia Racibórz in the Polish Ekstraliga. She previously played for Slovan Duslo Šaľa in the Slovak First League. She has played the Champions League with both teams. She is a member of the Slovak national team since 2001.

name: Ivana Ivanović
description: Ivana Ivanović is a Serbian football midfielder, currently playing for SFK Sarajevo in the Bosnian League. She has played the Champions League with Mašinac Niš and Sarajevo. She has been a member of the Serbian national team.

name: Ivana Rudelic
description: Ivana Rudelic is a German footballer of Croatian descent, who plays as a striker for Bayern Munich in the Bundesliga. As a junior international, she won the 2008 U-17 and 2011 U-19 European Championships plus a bronze in the 2008 U-17 World Cup.

name: Ivann Espag
description: Ivann Espag (born 8 September 1987) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is prop. He represents the Griquas in the Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup. Espag previously played for the Blue Bulls and Boland Cavaliers.

name: Ivar Eriksson
description: Ivar Eriksson (born 25 December 1909, death in 1938) http://de. wikipedia. org/Ivar_Eriksson was a Swedish football defender who played for Sweden in the 1938 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Sandvikens IF.

name: Ivar Schjøtt
description: Ivar Schjøtt (born 28 December 1955) is a Norwegian fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivar Tingdahl
description: Ivar Tingdahl (21 December 1893 – 9 February 1962) was a Swedish fencer. He competed at the 1928 and 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivaylo Danchev
description: Ivaylo Danchev Pavlov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Данчев Павлов) (born 31 March 1984 in Vratsa) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Botev Vratsa as a forward.

name: Ivaylo Dimitrov (footballer born 1989)
description: Ivaylo Dimitrov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Димитров; born 26 March 1989) is a Bulgarian footballer who currently plays for Dobrudzha Dobrich as a winger. Dimitrov was educated in CSKA Sofia's youth academy.

name: Ivaylo Georgiev (footballer born 1942)
description: Ivaylo Georgiev (born 1942) is a Bulgarian footballer. He was born in Montana. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City, where he won a silver medal with the Bulgarian team.

name: Ivaylo Gerdzhikov
description: Ivaylo Gerdzhikov (born 12 June 1991 in Plovdiv) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Lokomotiv Plovdiv as a midfielder.

name: Ivaylo Ivanikov
description: Ivaylo Ivanikov (born 17 May 1971) is a Bulgarian footballer who currently plays for Pirin Blagoevgrad as a goalkeeper

name: Ivaylo Ivanov
description: Ivaylo Ivanov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Иванов; born 8 December 1974) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Slavia Sofia as a goalkeeper.

name: Ivaylo Radentsov
description: Ivaylo Ichkov Radentsov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Раденцов; born 29 May 1983 in Pleven) is a Bulgarian football player, who currently plays for Spartak Pleven as a midfielder.

name: Ivaylo Sokolov
description: Ivaylo Sokolov (born 15 September 1984) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays for Nesebar as a defender.

name: Ivaylo Stoyanov
description: Ivaylo Stoyanov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Стоянов; born 13 July 1990) is a Bulgarian footballer who currently plays for Minyor Pernik as a midfielder.

name: Ivaylo Yanachkov
description: Ivaylo Yanachkov (Bulgarian: Ивайло Яначков; born 31 August 1986) is a Bulgarian football goalkeeper who currently plays for Botev Vratsa.

name: Ivaylo Zafirov
description: Ivaylo Zafirov (born 16 April 1992) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Kaliakra Kavarna as a forward. Zafirov's father Adalbert Zafirov is a former football player and current manager of Kaliakra.

name: Ivelin Kostov
description: Ivelin Kostov (born 29 January 1986) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for Kaliakra Kavarna as a midfielder.

name: Iveta Dudová
description: Iveta Dudová is a Czech former football striker who played for Compex Otrokovice in the Czech First Division. She was a member of the Czech national team for eight years.

name: Iveta Mazáčová
description: Iveta Mazáčová (born 15 December 1986) is a Czech athlete who specialises in the sprint disciplines 60 m, 100 m and 200 metres. At the 2006 European Athletics Championships, Mazáčová finished seventh in her 200 m heat for a 25th place overall result. In 2011, for the third year in succession, Mazáčová won the gold medal at the Czech Indoor Championships in the 60 metres, securing a personal best time of 7.37 seconds.

name: Ivette López
description: Ivette López (born July 12, 1990) is a professional Mexican tennis player. On December 17, 2007, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 1046 whilst her best doubles ranking was 500 on August 29, 2011.

name: Ivey Shiver
description: Ivey Merwin Shiver (January 22, 1907 – August 31, 1972) was an outfielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Detroit Tigers and Cincinnati Reds.

name: Ivica Cokolic
description: Ivica Cokolic is a Croatian footballer who plays for Vietnamese club TDC Binh Duong in the Vietnam First Division.

name: Ivica Gligorovski
description: Ivica Gligorovski (born 15 April 1981) is a Macedonian football player who currently is coaching in his own youth academy. Gligorovski has twice been the top scorer of the First Macedonian Football League, scoring 15 goals during the 2007–08 and 14 goals during the 2008–09 season, with FK Milano Kumanovo. Gligorovski has made several appearances for the Macedonia national football team, making his debut as a second half substitute in a friendly against Croatia on 9 February 2003.

name: Ivica Senzen
description: Ivan "Ivica" Senzen (born 4 May 1951 in Sisak) ia a former Croatian footballer. After beginning his career at his hometown club Metalac Sisak, Senzen was picked up by Dinamo Zagreb in 1970. Senzen spent the next nine years playing for the club, and had appeared in a total of 447 matches and scored 103 goals for the club (206 appearances and 29 goals in the Yugoslav First League), in a generation that featured other notable players such as Drago Vabec, Zlatko Kranjčar, and Velimir Zajec. In 1979 he moved to Germany where he spent three seasons playing for 1860 Munich, and scored 8 goals in 82 appearances for the German side. He then moved on to Austria Klagenfurt, where he played between 1982 and 1986, before returning to Croatia and spending two years with Jugokeramika (today known as Inter Zaprešić) and then two years with Radnik Velika Gorica, before retiring in 1990. After retiring from active football, Senzen turned to managing and coaching. He first worked at Radnik's youth academy for a year, before taking over as club's manager and winning promotion to Prva HNL in 1991. Between 1991 and 1999 he managed several Croatian clubs, before coming to Dinamo Zagreb in 1999 as assistant manager to Ilija Lončarević. Dinamo won the championship title that season, and Senzen stayed at the club working at Dinamo's academy. He currently works as a coach of the youngest age group at the Dinamo academy, the Zagići II (under-8 team) and occasionally does scouting for the club, bringing in youth players to Dinamo.

name: Ivo Jan (ice hockey b. 1942)
description: Ivo Jan is a retired Slovenian professional ice hockey player. He played for HK Acroni Jesenice in the Yugoslav Ice Hockey League. Jan played for the Yugoslavia national ice hockey team at the IIHF World Championships, and the Winter Olympics in 1964, 1968, and 1972. His son Ivo Jan was also an ice hockey player.

name: Ivo Jukić
description: Ivo Jukić (born 13 April 1986), is a Croatian futsal player who plays for MNK Split Brodosplit Inženjering and the Croatia national futsal team.

name: Ivo Kotaška
description: Ivo Kotaška (born 26 January 1980) is a Czech professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for Ciarko PKS Bank KH Sanok in the PLH. He has played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga. Kotaška previously played for IHC Písek, HC Znojemští Orli, HC Olomouc and HK Tábor.

name: Ivo Prskalo
description: Ivo Prskalo (born 2 January 1948 in Čapljina former Yugoslavia, died 2 September 2010 in Sydney Australia) was an Australian international association footballer who played for Marconi Fairfield in the National Soccer League.

name: Ivonne Witteveen
description: Ivonne Witteveen (born 22 January 1944) is a Dutch Antillean fencer. She competed in the women's individual foil event at the 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Ivor Bennett
description: Ivor Bennett (16 June 1913 — 16 June 2003) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1930s. Bennett was born in Aberkenfig. At representative level he played rugby union (RU) for Wales, and at club level for Aberavon RFC, playing at Prop, i.e. number 1 or 3, and at club level played rugby league (RL) for Warrington. He died in Neath aged 90.

name: Ivor Jones (footballer born 1899)
description: Ivor Jones (31 July 1899 – 24 November 1974) was a Welsh international footballer who played professionally as a winger.

name: Ivor Lingard
description: Ivor Lingard (birth registered January→March 1942 in Lower Agbrigg district, Wakefield) is an English professional rugby league footballer of the 1960s and '70s, playing at club level for Featherstone Rovers, and Parramatta Eels, as a Stand-off/Five-eighth, or Scrum-half/Halfback, i.e. number 6, or 7.

name: Ivor Seemley
description: Ivor John Seemley (born 30 June 1929) is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League, as a left back.

name: Iya Gavrilova
description: Iya Gavrilova is a hockey player who competes for Russia women's national ice hockey team. She represented Russia in women's ice hockey in the 2006 and 2010 Winter Olympics. Gavrilova has also competed in the NCAA with the Minnesota Duluth Bulldogs and in the Western Women's Hockey League with the Minnesota Whitecaps. She also played for Tornado Moscow Region in 2006-2007 and 2008-2010 seasons. She is currently enrolled at the University of Calgary where she helped lead the Calgary Dinos women's ice hockey team to a CIS championship in her first season.

name: Izaac Johanes Wanggai
description: Izaac Johanes Wanggai or just Izaac Wanggai is an Indonesian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Indonesian football club Persidafon Dafonsoro. His younger brother, Patrich Wanggai, and his cousin, Imanuel Wanggai, is also a football player.

name: Izak van der Westhuizen
description: Izak van der Westhuizen (born 23 January 1986) is a South African rugby union footballer. He plays as a lock for Edinburgh in the Pro 12. He formerly played for the Cheetahs in both Super Rugby and the Currie Cup.

name: Izatullah Dawlatzai
description: Izatullah Dawlatzai (born 10 May 1991) is an Afghan cricketer. He is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium-fast. He currently represents the Afghanistan national cricket team. Dawlatzai started representing Afghanistan in age group cricket, which culminated in the Afghanistan Under-19 cricket team qualifying for the 2010 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup in New Zealand, for the first time in their history. Dawlatzai represented the team in all their matches during the tournament. His debut for the senior team came in a first-class match against Kenya in the 2009-10 ICC Intercontinental Cup. In that match he took his maiden first-class wicket, that of Collins Obuya. Following the first-class match, he made his One Day International debut against Kenya in the 2nd ODI. In what was also his maiden List-A match, he took the wickets of Seren Waters and Collins Obuya for the cost of 37 runs.

name: Izet Redžepagić
description: Izet Redžepagić (1955 – 2007) was a professional football forward who played in the former Yugoslavia and Turkey.

name: Izudin Dervic
description: Izudin Daði Dervić (born 22 February 1963) is a retired Icelandic international footballer of Bosnian origin who played for Selfoss, FH, KR, Leiftur, Þróttur R. and Valur. Dervic is currently managing Leiknir from Fáskrúðsfjörður.

name: Izumi Iimura
description: Izumi Iimura (born 2 December 1980) is a former Japanese cricketer who played three Women's One Day International cricket matches for Japan national women's cricket team in 2003.

name: Izumi Yokokawa
description: Izumi Yokokawa (born February 25, 1963) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Izunna Uzochukwu
description: Izunna Arnest Uzochukwu (born 11 April 1990) is a Nigerian professional football midfielder, who currently plays for the Danish Superliga side FC Midtjylland.

name: Izzaq Faris Ramlan
description: Izzaq Faris Ramlan, is a Malaysian footballer who currently playing for Harimau Muda A as a Striker. He was called up by Malaysia 2009 coach K. Rajagobal for their friendly match in Turkey in 2010. Izzaq faris also participate Harimau Muda in Slovakia and after several good matches with Harimau Muda he was called up for the Malaysian team which participated in the 2010 Asian Games. In November 2010, Izzaq was called up to the Malaysia national squad by coach K. Rajagopal for the 2010 AFF Suzuki Cup. Malaysia won the 2010 AFF Suzuki Cup title for the first time in their history. He is Harimau Muda A top scorer in 2011 Malaysia Super League with 9 goal from 16 appearances.

name: Ján Čirik
description: Ján Čirik (born 30 December 1982) is a Slovak football defender who currently plays for FK Slovan Duslo Šaľa. His former club was the Corgoň Liga club FC Nitra.

name: Ján Fröhlich

name: Ján Marcin

name: Ján Mucha (footballer born 1978)
description: Ján Mucha (20 June 1978 in Bojnice) is a Slovak football goalkeeper who currently plays for the Slovak 3. liga club TJ Baník Ružiná.

name: Ján Zolna
description: Ján Zolna (born 27 February 1978) is a Slovak football player who currently plays for Wakefield F.C..

name: Jéhan Le Roy
description: Jéhan Le Roy (1923–1992) was a French equestrian. He won a bronze medal in team eventing at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome, together with Guy Lefrant and Jack le Goff.

name: Jérémie Romand
description: Jeremie Romand (born February 28, 1988) is an ice hockey player who played for France at the 2011 IIHF World Championship.

name: Jérémy Faug-Porret
description: Jérémy Faug-Porret (born 4 February 1987) is a French football defender. He currently plays for Bulgarian A PFG side Chernomorets Burgas. Jérémy has previously played for Chambéry, Vauban Strasbourg and Strasbourg B.

name: Jérémy Hélan
description: Jérémy Hélan (born 9 May 1992) is a French footballer playing as a winger for Sheffield Wednesday on loan from Manchester City.

name: Jérémy Labor
description: Jérémy Labor (born 19 March 1992 in Pontoise) is a French football player who plays for Monégasque club Monaco in Ligue 2. He plays as a left back, but can also be utilized as a central defender. Labor is a France youth international having represented his nation at under-18 and under-19 level. He was a member of the Monaco under-19 team that won the 2010–11 edition of the Coupe Gambardella and made his professional debut on 19 November 2011 in a Coupe de France match against Alès. A week later, he made his league debut in a 2–0 defeat to Nantes.

name: Jérémy Serwy
description: Jérémy Serwy (born 4 June 1991) is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for White Star Woluwe on loan from S.V. Zulte Waregem in the Belgian Pro League.

description: Jérôme Bigard (born 16 February 1985) is a Luxembourger international footballer who plays club football for FC UNA Strassen, as a defender.

name: Jérôme Cintas
description: Jérôme Cintas (born 11 April 1971) is a French former professional footballer who played as a defender.

name: Jérôme Foulon
description: Jérôme Foulon is a former professional footballer, who last played for Championnat de France amateur 2 side AC Cambrai. He played as a right-back.

name: Jérôme Roussillon
description: Jérôme Roussillon (born 6 January 1993 in Sarcelles) is a French football player who plays for French club Sochaux in Ligue 1. He plays as a left back. Roussillon is a France youth international having represented his nation at under-18 level. He made his professional debut on 2 May 2012 in a league match against Ajaccio appearing as a substitute.

name: Jérôme Schneider
description: Jérôme Schneider (born 4 November 1981) is a Swiss footballer who plays for Servette FC in the Swiss Super League.

name: Jérôme Sykora
description: Jérôme Sykora (born April 14, 1971) is a former professional footballer who played as a goalkeeper.

name: Jóbson

description: József Hátszeghy (13 January 1904 – 18 January 1988) was a Hungarian fencer. He competed at the 1936 and 1948 Summer Olympics.

Bundesliga for KFC Uerdingen 05 on May 25, 1997 when he came on as a half-time substitute for René Schmidt in a game against 1. FSV Mainz 05. He was sent off later in that game.

name: Jørgen Hammer
description: Jørgen Hammer (born 2 April 1991) is a Norwegian association football player who currently plays for Stabæk. He spent his youth career in Hosle IL and Bærum SK before joining Stabæk Fotball at junior level. He signed a professional contract in August 2010, lasting throughout the year. Already two days later he made his first-team debut, at home against Lillestrøm SK.

name: Jørgen Thorup
description: Jørgen Thorup (born 7 May 1950) is a Danish fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1972 Summer Olympics.

name: Jørgen W. Hansen

name: Júlio César Rocha Costa

name: Júlio César Zabotto
description: Júlio César Zabotto (born 16 February 1983), known as Júlio César, is a Brazilian footballer.

name: Júlio César da Cruz Coimbra
description: Júlio César da Cruz Coimbra known as Júlio César (born 10 October 1980) is a Brazilian footballer.

name: Július Schubert
description: Július Schubert (12 December 1922 – 4 May 1949) was a Slovak football player. He played twice for the Czechoslovakia national football team and played club football for ŠK Slovan Bratislava and Torino.

name: Júnior César Moreira da Cunha
description: Júnior César Moreira da Cunha, the Juninho is a striker who plays for Atlético Goianiense.

name: Jústinus Hansen
description: Jústinus Hansen (born 14 May 1985) is an Faroese international footballer who plays club football for Spjelkavik ILin Norwegian 3rd division, as a midfielder. He played for NSÍ Runavík from 2002 to 2011 and B68 Toftir from 2011 to 2012.

name: Jürgen Bucher
description: Jürgen Bucher (born 22 March 1957) is a retired German footballer. Bucher made a total of 95 2. Fußball-Bundesliga appearances for 1. FC Nürnberg, MTV Ingolstadt and Tennis Borussia Berlin.

name: Jürgen Gredig
description: Jürgen Gredig (born 19 January 1966 in West Berlin) is a retired German football defender.

name: Jürgen Nolte
description: Jürgen Nolte (born 19 November 1959) is a German fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events for West Germany at the 1984 and 1988 Summer Olympics and for Germany at the 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: Jānis Vinters
description: Jānis Vinters (born 19 December 1971) is a Latvian rally racing motorcycle rider and farmer. He has competed several times in Dakar Rally. In 2004 and 2005 he withdrew to injuries. In 2006 he finished in 10th place but year later he won tho stages and ranked 6th. As of 2012 this was his last participation at Dakar Rally.

name: Jūlija Vansoviča
description: Jūlija Vansoviča (born 24 August 1975) is a Latvian fencer. She competed in the women's individual épée event at the 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: J'Marcus Webb
description: J'Marcus Webb (born August 8, 1988) is an American football offensive tackle for the Chicago Bears of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Bears in the seventh round of the 2010 NFL Draft. He played college football at West Texas A&M.

name: J'Michael Deane
description: J'Micheal Deane (born May 4, 1986 in Hinton, Alberta) is a professional Canadian football offensive lineman for the Calgary Stampeders of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted 21st overall by the Stampeders in the 2010 CFL Draft and signed a contract with the team on May 10, 2011 after finishing his college eligibility. He played college football for the Michigan State Spartans.

name: J-Mee Samuels
description: J-Mee Samuels (born May 20, 1987) is an American sprinter who specializes in the 100 meters. He participated for the United States at the 2007 World Championships in Athletics, running in the 100 meters and 4 × 100 metres relay. Samuels attended Mount Tabor High School in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, where he became the National High School record holder for 100 meters in 10.08 seconds at the Russell Blunt East Coast Invitational, matching the American Junior Record set by 2004 Olympic gold medalist Justin Gatlin in 2001. He also ran a 200 meter dash time of 20.32, which was the sixth-fastest ever by a U.S. prep athlete. Samuels was named to USA Today's All-USA track team in 2005. He currently attends the University of Arkansas and has been a three-time All-American selection. Samuels improved his 100 m personal record to 10.03 seconds in August 2010, finishing third at the Spitzenleichtathletik meet in Nottwil, Switzerland, behind Nesta Carter and Walter Dix.

name: J.P. Bekasiak
description: J.P. Bekasiak is a Canadian football defensive tackle for the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted with the fourth overall pick in the 2007 CFL Draft by the Hamilton Tiger-Cats. He played college Football with the Toledo Rockets.

name: J.P. Dalton
description: J.P. Dalton is a Gaelic footballer from County Wicklow, Ireland. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Kiltegan and has been a member of the Wicklow senior panel since 2005.

name: J.T. Putney
description: J.T. Putney (October 5, 1928 - April 11, 2001) was a former NASCAR Grand National Series race car driver who would accomplish 16 finishes in the "top five" in addition to 49 finishes in the "top ten. " Herman Beam would become one of Putney's employers; guiding him to a seventh-place finish at the end of the 1965 NASCAR Grand National Cup Series.

name: J. B. Thompson
description: James Bogne "J. B. " Thompson (1829 – 18 July 1877) was one of the creators of the original laws of Australian rules football, one of the founders and the inaugural secretary of the Melbourne Football Club, a cricketer for both Victoria and the Melbourne Cricket Club (MCC), and a journalist for Melbourne newspaper, The Argus.

name: J. C. Bailey
description: Joseph Carl Bailey, Jr. (August 23, 1983 – August 30, 2010) was an American professional wrestler, better known by his ring name J. C. Bailey. He wrestled for numerous American-based professional wrestling promotions including Combat Zone Wrestling, IWA Mid-South, and IWA East Coast.

name: J. C. Banks
description: Jimmy "J. C. " Banks (born August 24, 1989 in Milwaukee, Wisconsin) is an American soccer player.

name: J. C. Hartman
description: J C Hartman is a former Major League Baseball shortstop. He played parts of two seasons, 1962 and 1963, for the Houston Colt .45s. Hartman also played for the Kansas City Monarchs in 1955, when they were a barnstorming team.

name: J. C. Sherritt
description: J. C. Sherritt (born May 2, 1988 in Truckee, California) is a Canadian football linebacker for the Edmonton Eskimos. Sherritt played his college football at Eastern Washington and was the 2010 recipient of the Buck Buchanan Award.

name: J. D. Martinez
description: Julio Daniel "J. D. " Martinez (born August 21, 1987) is an American professional baseball outfielder with the Houston Astros of Major League Baseball (MLB).

name: J. D. Quinn
description: James "J. D. " Quinn is an American football guard who is currently a free agent. He was signed by the Miami Dolphins as an undrafted free agent in 2009, but was later released during training camp. He played college football at Montana.

name: J. J. Hoover
description: James Allen Hoover (born August 13, 1987) is an American professional baseball pitcher for the Cincinnati Reds of Major League Baseball.

name: J. J. Jones
description: John Eddie "J. J. " Jones (April 16, 1952 – July 9, 2009) was an American football quarterback in the National Football League. He was signed by the New York Jets as an undrafted free agent in 1975. He played college football at Fisk. Jones died in a house fire in 2009.

name: J. James (Northamptonshire cricketer)
description: J. James (full name and dates of birth and death unknown) was an English cricketer. James' batting and bowling styles are also not known. What is known about James is that he played two first-class matches for Northamptonshire in the 1906 County Championship, playing against Nottinghamshire and Warwickshire. In these two matches, he scored just two runs, while with the ball he took two wickets at an average of 62.50, with best figures of 1/14.

name: J. P. Anderson
description: J. P. Anderson (born April 27, 1992) is a Canadian ice hockey goaltender currently playing for the Sarnia Sting of the Ontario Hockey League (OHL). He was signed as an undrafted free agent by the San Jose Sharks of the National Hockey League after a strong performance in the 2010 Young Stars Tournament.

name: J. P. Testwuide
description: Jon Paul "J.P. " Testwuide (born November 5, 1984) is an American professional Ice Hockey Defenseman currently playing for the Missouri Mavericks of the Central Hockey League. On August 2, 2011, the Chicago Wolves announced that they had signed Testwuide for the 2011–12 AHL season. On November 7, 2011, the Wolves assigned Testwuide to the Missouri Mavericks, the team's Central Hockey League affiliate. On November 14, 2011, Testwuide was recalled by the Wolves. On December 3, 2011, Testwuide was assigned by the Wolves to the Mavericks for a second time. On December 6, 2011, Testwuide was recalled by the Wolves from the Mavericks again. On March 5, 2012, Testwuide was loaned by the Wolves to the Abbotsford Heat, also of the American Hockey League. Per remarks made by J.P. 's brother, fellow professional Hockey player Mike Testwuide, which were published in a November 26, 2012 blog post on the website of the newspaper The Saratogian, J.P. had retired from professional Hockey. On January 25, 2013, Testwuide came out of retirement and signed with the Missouri Mavericks of the Central Hockey League for third stint with the team.

name: J. R. Boone
description: J. R. Boone (July 29, 1925 – January 21, 2012) was a professional American football player who played halfback for six seasons for the Chicago Bears, the San Francisco 49ers, and the Green Bay Packers. He was born in Clinton, Oklahoma. Boone was drafted by the Chicago Bears in the 22nd round of the 1948 NFL Draft, which was held on December 19, 1947. He was a star athlete player for the University of Tulsa, and earned nine letters, and graduated in physical education and social science. A captain of the University of Tulsa football team, Boone was also a star athlete in basketball, track, baseball. He was a versatile athlete, with plenty of speed that complemented his abilities, and often he was a back, safety, punt and kick returner. He was also drafted by the New York Yankees baseball organization. Boone was traded to the San Francisco 49ers in 1952, and then to the Green Bay Packers in 1953. Boone's six-year pro career statistics included 497 rushing yards in 130 carries and five touchdowns in 63 games. He also had sure hands, which caught sixty-nine pass receptions for 1,251 yards, eight touchdowns (18.1 average per catch), and returned seventy-two punt returns for 725 yards (10.1 average).

name: J. R. Sweezy
description: J.R. Sweezy (born April 8, 1989) is an American football offensive guard for the Seattle Seahawks. He was selected in the seventh round, 225th overall, by the Seahawks in the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at NC State.

name: J. T. Bruett
description: Joseph Timothy Bruett is a former professional baseball outfielder. He played parts of two seasons in Major League Baseball for the Minnesota Twins in 1992-93. Bruett played at the collegiate level at the University of Minnesota. He was drafted in the eleventh round of the 1988 Major League Baseball Draft by the Twins.

name: J. T. Noone
description: Joseph "J. T. " Noone (born July 17, 1988 in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania) is an American soccer player currently playing for VSI Tampa Bay FC in the USL Professional Division.

name: J. T. Wyman
description: James Thomas Wyman (born February 27, 1986 in Edina, Minnesota) is an American professional ice hockey right winger for the Tampa Bay Lightning organization of the National Hockey League. Wyman was drafted in the fourth round, 100th overall, by the Montreal Canadiens in the 2004 NHL Entry Draft. July 1, 2011, Wyman was signed as an unrestricted free agent by the Tampa Bay Lightning On December 20, 2011, as a member of the Lighting, Wyman scored his first NHL goal against Carey Price of the Montreal Canadiens, the team that drafted him. On June 15, 2012, Wyman was re-signed by the Lightning to a one-year extension.

name: JC Janse van Rensburg
description: JC Janse van Rensburg (born 9 January 1986) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is loosehead prop. He represents the Lions in Super Rugby and the Golden Lions in the Currie Cup. In 2013, he signed a two-year deal with French team Bayonne.

name: JC Kritzinger
description: JC Kritzinger (born 4 December 1987) is a former South African rugby union footballer. He represented Western Province and Stormers between 2008 and 2011, but was released by Western Province at the end of 2012 following a succession of serious injuries to pursue full-time studies.

name: JC Roos
description: JC Roos (born 12 September 1990) is a South African rugby union footballer. He plays mostly as a fly-half. He represents the Pumas in the Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup having previously played for the Blue Bulls.

name: JT Southern
description: JT Southern (born 1964) is a retired American professional wrestler. Though he achieved most notoriety during his 1992 feud with Van Hammer in World Championship Wrestling, Southern also competed for Verne Gagne's American Wrestling Association, Continental Wrestling Association (CWA) in Memphis, Tennessee, and in UWF International in Japan.

name: JaMychal Green
