description: Jari Sailio is a Finnish professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for Espoo Blues of the SM-liiga.

name: Jarius Wynn
description: Jarius Jessereel Wynn (born August 29, 1986) is an American football defensive end for the San Diego Chargers of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Green Bay Packers in the sixth round of the 2009 NFL Draft and played for the Tennessee Titans during the 2012 season. He played college football at Georgia.

name: Jarkko Immonen (ice hockey b. 1984)
description: There is also a Jarkko Immonen (ice hockey b. 1982) who was drafted by Toronto Maple Leafs in the 2002 NHL Entry Draft as 8th round pick, 254th overall. Jarkko Antero Immonen {{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=Jarkko Antero Immonen. jpg|size=230px|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}} Born (1984-01-18) January 18, 1984 (age 29) Kouvola, Finland Height 5 ft 11 in Weight 198 lb Position Forward Shoots Left SM-liiga teamFormer teams PelicansBluesSaiPa NHL Draft 110th overall, 2002Dallas Stars Playing career 2003–present Jarkko Antero Immonen (born January 18, 1984) is a Finnish professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for Lahti Pelicans of the SM-liiga. He was selected by the Dallas Stars in the 4th round (110th overall) of the 2002 NHL Entry Draft. Midway through the 2010–11 season, on January 28, 2011, Immonen transferred from his first SM-lliga club, the Espoo Blues, to the Pelicans and signed an addition one-year contract. In the following 2011–12 season, Immonen enjoyed his most successful season win the SM-liiga since 2008, scoring 32 points in 59 games to help the Pelicans reach the finals. On May 3, 2012, he was re-signed to a two-year extension with the Pelicans.

name: Jarkko Värttö
description: Jarkko Värttö (born 24 February 1989) is a Finnish football player currently playing for IFK Mariehamn.

name: Jarmo Jokila
description: Jarmo Jokila (born February 13, 1986) is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally for HC Banská Bystrica in the Slovak Extraliga. He also used to play for SaiPa of SM-liiga.

name: Jarmo Matikainen
description: Jarmo Matikainen (born 21 February 1960) is a Finnish football player and coach, who currently manages the Wales women's national football team. Matikainen made over 400 league and cup appearances in a long playing career which included a season at First division (second tier of Finnish competition) with KontU in 1988. He scored nine league goals in 1987 and 12 league goals in 1990 for Helsingin Ponnistus . Matikainen later player–coached Vuosaaren Viikingit from the fourth division to the second division (third level of Finnish league football). Matikainen also managed his first club Helsingin Ponnistus before taking a job with the Football Association of Finland in 1999. Matikainen successfully coached the Finland U–17 and U–19 teams and was assistant coach of the senior team which reached the UEFA Women's Euro 2005 semi-final. In August 2010 it was announced that Matikainen was to take over as Wales' first ever full-time head of national teams on 4 October 2010. As well as overseeing the senior team's UEFA Women's Euro 2013 qualifying campaign, Matikainen assumed direct responsibility for the U–17 and U–19 teams. The holder of a UEFA Pro Licence, Matikainen was also tasked by the Football Association of Wales with helping to develop an overall strategy for women's football in Wales.

name: Jarnell Stokes
description: Jarnell Stokes (born January 7, 1994) is an American college basketball player, currently a sophomore at the University of Tennessee. He was one of the top rated high school players in the class of 2012.

name: Jarno Koskiranta
description: Jarno Koskiranta is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for Tappara of the SM-liiga.

name: Jarno Molenberghs
description: Jarno Molenberghs (born December 12, 1989) is a Belgian football player who currently plays for K.V.C. Westerlo.

name: Jarno Tuunainen
description: Jarno Tuunainen (born 5 November 1977) is a Finnish footballer who currently plays for MyPa in Finnish Veikkausliiga.

name: Jarod Palmer
description: Jarod James Palmer (born February 10, 1986) is an American professional ice hockey forward currently playing with the Minnesota Wild of the National Hockey League. He is a native of Fridley, Minnesota, and an alum of the USNTDP, where he played for two seasons. Palmer was a member of the silver medal-winning U.S. squad at the World Under-18 Championship in 2004. After graduating from high school, he spent two seasons in the USHL with the Tri-City Storm. Palmer then completed four years of collegiate hockey at Miami University in Oxford, Ohio. He made his NHL debut with the Wild on December 17, 2011.

name: Jarosław Kisiel
description: Jarosław Kisiel (born 22 May 1964) is a Polish fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: Jaroslav Dittrich
description: Jaroslav Dittrich (born 8 March 1982 in Prague, Czech Republic) is a Czech football player who has made more than 40 appearances in the Gambrinus Liga, the top Czech football league.

name: Jaroslav Jágr
description: Jaroslav Jágr (born February 9, 1984) is a Czech professional ice hockey goaltender. He played with HC České Budějovice in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season.

name: Jaroslav Kasík
description: Jaroslav Kasík is a Czech professional ice hockey defenceman who played with HK SKP Poprad in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season.

name: Jaroslav Kmiť
description: Jaroslav Kmiť is a Slovakian professional ice hockey player who played with HK SKP Poprad in the Slovak Extraliga during the 2010–11 season. In January 2012 he joined the Danish club AaB Ice hockey

name: Jaroslav Kostelný
description: Jaroslav Kostelný (born 19 April 1985 in Banská Bystrica) is a Slovak football defender who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club MFK Ružomberok.

name: Jaroslav Markovič
description: Jaroslav Markovič (born May 22, 1985) is a Slovakian professional ice hockey player currently playing with HC Pardubice in the Czech Extraliga.

name: Jaroslav Mihálik
description: Jaroslav Mihalík (born 27 July 1994 in Spišská Nová Ves) is a Slovak football striker who currently plays for the Corgoň Liga club MŠK Žilina.

name: Jaroslav Starý
description: Jaroslav Starý was a Czech fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Jaroslav Zelený
description: Jaroslav Zelený (born 20 August 1992) is a Czech football player who currently plays for FC Hradec Králové.

name: Jaroslava Lorencová
description: Jaroslava Lorencová is a Czech football goalkeeper, currently playing for Sparta Prague in the Czech First Division. She previously played for 1. FC Brno. She is a member of the Czech national team. She made her debut on 31 May 2009 in a match against Poland.

name: Jarrad Ross
description: Jarrad Ross' is an Australian football (soccer) player who currently plays for the A-League club Newcastle Jets. He is also a twin. On 9 January 2008 he made his senior debut for the Jets against Adelaide United.

name: Jarred Seymour
description: Jarred Seymour (born 22 February 1990) is an Australian ice hockey player currently playing for the Cornell University in the American Collegiate Hockey Association.

name: Jarret Lukin
description: Jarret Lukin (born January 24, 1984) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing with the Allen Americans in the Central Hockey League. On August 14, 2008, the Florida Everblades traded Lukin to the Dayton Bombers, along with Steve Czech, Mike McLean, and future considerations, in exchange for Yannick Tifu.

name: Jarret Zukiwsky
description: Jarret Zukiwsky (born December 7, 1972) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey player. During a professional career that spanned seven seasons and five different leagues, Zukiwsky played 200 regular season games scoring 77 goals and 153 points while racking up 747 minutes in penalties.

name: Jarrett Lee
description: Calen Jarrett Lee (born June 2, 1989) is an American football quarterback. Jarrett attended Louisiana State University where he was the starting quarterback for eight games in 2008, one game in 2009, and nine games in 2011. Lee was signed as an undrafted free agent by the San Diego Chargers on April 29, 2012, but was waived on August 31, 2012.

name: Jarriel King
description: Jarriel King (born February 27, 1987) is an American football offensive tackle who is currently a free agent. He played for the Seattle Seahawks of the NFL previously. King played college football at South Carolina. He was cut from the Seahawks in March 2012 after the team learned of his arrest for sexual assault in South Carolina. According to the alleged victim, she "repeatedly told [King and another man] to stop."

name: Jarron Gilbert
description: Jarron Gilbert (born September 30, 1986) is an American football defensive end for the Buffalo Bills of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Chicago Bears in the third round of the 2009 NFL Draft. He played college football at San Jose State. Gilbert has also been a member of the New York Jets.

name: Jarvis Jenkins
description: Jarvis Jenkins (born April 24, 1988) is an American football defensive end for the Washington Redskins of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted by the Redskins with the 41st pick in the 2011 NFL Draft. He played college football at Clemson University.

name: Jasem Sadeghi
description: Jasem Sadeghi (born March 30, 1986) is an Iranian football player, who currently plays for Esteghlal Ahvaz of the IPL

name: Jaslee Hatta
description: Jaslee Hatta is a Singapore international football player who plays for Balestier Khalsa.

name: Jasmin Šćuk
description: Jasmin Šćuk (born 14 July 1990 in Jablanica) is a Bosnian football midfielder. He currently plays for FK Mlada Boleslav in the Czech Gambrinus Liga. Šćuk was part of the youth team of FK Mlada Boleslav before breaking into the first team in November 2010.

name: Jasmin Krejc
description: Jasmin Krejc is an Austrian football goalkeeper, currently playing for ASV Spratzern in the ÖFB-Frauenliga. She is a member of the Austrian national team.

name: Jasmin Pllana
description: Jasmin Pllana (born 6 January 1989) is an Austrian professional association football player currently playing for SKU Amstetten. He plays as a defender.

name: Jasmina Tinjić
description: Jasmina Tinjić is a professional Bosnian tennis player playing in the ITF Women's Circuit. On July 4, 2011, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 257. On August 8, 2011, she also reached her highest WTA doubles ranking of 521. She is coached by Jusuf Tinjić.

name: Jason Akeson
description: Jason Akeson (born June 3, 1990) is a Canadian professional ice hockey right winger currently playing for the Adirondack Phantoms of the American Hockey League (AHL).

name: Jason Anderson (cricketer)
description: Jason Anderson (born 17 February 1979) is a Bermudian cricketer. Anderson is a right-handed batsman who fields as a wicket-keeper. He was born in Bermuda. Anderson made his debut for Bermuda in a List A match in the 2011 World Cricket League Division Two against Papua New Guinea. He made four further List A matches in the competition, the last of which came against Uganda. Anderson scored a total of 176 runs in the tournament, which came at an average of 44.00, with a high score of 106 not out. This score was made against Hong Kong. He was selected as part of Bermuda's squad for the World Twenty20 Qualifier.

name: Jason Arakgi
description: Jason Arakgi (born May 12, 1985) is a Canadian football Linebacker for the BC Lions of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted in the 3rd round of the 2008 CFL Draft by the BC Lions. He played college football at McMaster. Arakgi was born in Montreal, Quebec, and grew up in Oakville, Ontario. He is the son of CFL receiver Nick Arakgi.

name: Jason Bailey
description: Jason Bailey (born June 4, 1987) is a retired Canadian professional ice hockey player who most recently played for the Binghamton Senators of the AHL.

name: Jason Baitieri
description: Jason Baitieri is a French-Australian professional rugby league footballer for the Catalans Dragons of Super League. A France international representative forward, he previously played for the Sydney Roosters of the National Rugby League.

name: Jason Banton
description: Jason Steve Banton (born 15 December 1992) is an English footballer who plays as a winger for Plymouth Argyle on loan from Crystal Palace. Born in Tottenham, he made his debut in the Football League in 2011. In an interview with LFC TV, Banton described himself as a left-winger, saying that "I'm right-footed but I like to play on the left and cut in."

name: Jason Barnes
description: Jason Barnes (born April 11, 1984 in San Jose, California) is a professional Canadian football wide receiver for the Toronto Argonauts of the Canadian Football League. He was originally signed by the Central Valley Coyotes as a street free agent in 2007. He then played for three seasons with the Edmonton Eskimos. He played college football for the Sacramento State Hornets.

name: Jason Barrett
description: Jason Barrett (born March 27, 1976 in South London) is a Jamaican-British actor, script writer and mixed martial artist, currently working for UCMMA.

name: Jason Beckett
description: Jason Beckett (born July 23, 1980) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for the Nottingham Panthers of the British Elite Ice Hockey League (EIHL). He was drafted by the Philadelphia Flyers in the 2nd round (42nd overall) of the 1998 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Jason Behrendorff
description: Jason Paul Behrendorff (born 20 April 1990) is an Australian cricketer, currently listed with Western Australia and the Perth Scorchers in Australian domestic cricket. Although born in New South Wales, Behrendorff grew up in Canberra, and played representative cricket for the Australian Capital Territory at both junior and senior and levels, going on to represent the Prime Minister's XI. A left-arm fast bowler, he transferred to Western Australia for the 2009–10 season, and made his debut at state level the following season, playing several matches due to injuries to other fast bowlers. Behrendorff played more regularly for Western Australia over the following seasons, and also made his debut for the Perth Scorchers during the 2012–13 season of the Big Bash League.

name: Jason Boltus
description: Jason Boltus (born August 21, 1986) is a professional American football quarterback for the Utah Blaze of the Arena Football League (AFL). He previously played for the Hamilton Tiger-Cats of the Canadian Football League. Boltus was signed as a street free agent by the Tiger-Cats in 2009. He played Division III college football for the Hartwick Hawks, where he was also the team's punter. His younger brother Jeremy, a 2011 United States Military Academy graduate, plays lacrosse for the Charlotte Hounds of Major League Lacrosse.

name: Jason Bowles
description: Jason Bowles (born November 24, 1982 in Ontario, California), is an American stock car racing driver and the 2009 K&N Pro Series West series champion. He currently competes in the NASCAR Nationwide Series.

name: Jason Boyce
description: Jason Boyce is a retired American soccer forward who played professionally in Major League Soccer and the USL A-League.

name: Jason Brilz
description: Jason Brilz (born July 7, 1975) is an American mixed martial artist. He formerly fought for the Ultimate Fighting Championship in the light heavyweight division.

name: Jason Brookins
description: Jason Arnaz Brookins (born January 5, 1976 in Mexico, Missouri) is a former professional American football running back who played one season for the Baltimore Ravens of the National Football League. He played college football at Lane College in Jackson, Tennessee.

name: Jason Broyles
description: Jason Broyles is an American former professional wrestler. He is best known for his stint in Extreme Championship Wrestling under the ring name EZ Money. He also wrestled for World Championship Wrestling in its final month of operation under the ring name Jason Jett.

name: Jason Chorak
description: Jason Chorak (September 23, 1974, Vashon, Washington) is an All-American American football linebacker. In 1996 he won the Washington Huskies' season award for the defensive L. Wait Rising Lineman Of Year, Pacific-12 Conference's Defensive Player of the Year and College Football All-America Team. He was selected in the 1998 NFL Draft by St. Louis Rams (Compensatory pick). In 1998 he played for 4th AFC South league team Indianapolis Colts and for XFL team Chicago Enforcers. Chorak is of Croat origin. His parents are Croatian immigrants.

name: Jason Christie
description: Jason Christie (born April 25, 1969) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey player. He is currently the head coach of the Ontario Reign of the ECHL. He was previously the head coach of the Bloomington PrairieThunder in the Central Hockey League (CHL).

name: Jason Coleman
description: Jason Coleman (born 21 August 1974) is a former Australian cricketer. Coleman was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Sydney, New South Wales. Coleman made his List-A debut for Huntingdonshire against Oxfordshire 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. He played 2 further List-A matches for the county. These were against the Surrey Cricket Board in the same competition and the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was played in 2001. In his 3 List-A matches, he scored 46 runs at a batting average of 46 and a high score of 26. With the ball he took 3 wickets at a bowling average of 35.33, with best figures of 1/26. In 2003, Coleman joined Cambridgeshire, where he made his Minor Counties Championship debut for the county against Cumberland. From 2003 to 2004, he represented the county in 6 Minor Counties Championship matches, with his final appearance for the county coming against Bedfordshire.

name: Jason Colwick
description: Jason Colwick (born 25 January 1988 in San Marcos, Texas) is a two-time NCAA champion American pole vaulter. His personal best vault is 5.72 metres, achieved in April 2009 in Austin, Texas. He attended and competed for Rice University in Houston, Texas.

name: Jason Cousins
description: Jason Cousins (born 4 October 1970) is an English former footballer. His eleven years with Wycombe Wanderers from 1991 to 2002 have made him a legend at the club.

name: Jason DeSantis
description: Jason DeSantis (born March 9, 1986) is an American professional ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing with the Hamilton Bulldogs of the American Hockey League whilst under contract to the Montreal Canadiens of the National Hockey League.

name: Jason Dellaero
description: Jason Christopher Dellaero (born December 17, 1976) was a shortstop in Major League Baseball. He played for the Chicago White Sox in 1999.

name: Jason Donnelly
description: Jason Donnelly is a New Zealand former rugby league player who played professionally and represented his country. His position of preference was on the wing.

name: Jason Ebanks
description: Jason Ebanks (born 19 December 1988) is a Caymanian footballer who plays as a midfielder. He has represented the Cayman Islands during a World Cup qualifying match in 2008.

name: Jason English
description: Jason English (born February 17, 1986 in Mobile, Alabama) is a professional American and Canadian football wide receiver who is currently a member of the Colorado Ice. He was signed by the Jacksonville Jaguars as an undrafted free agent in 2009. He played college football for the Tuskegee Golden Tigers. On June 29, 2009, English was signed by the Toronto Argonauts of the Canadian Football League and assigned to their practice roster but was released by the team on July 20, 2009.

name: Jason Ferguson (snooker player)
description: Jason Ferguson is a former professional snooker player. He reached the World Snooker Championship on three occasions, and was for four seasons ranked in the world's top 32 players, reaching a peak position of #28. In 1998 Ferguson was elected to the board of the World Professional Billiards and Snooker Association (WPBSA), and became chairman of the organisation in 2001. After retiring as a professional player and leaving his position on the WPBSA, he served as the mayor of Ollerton and Boughton between 2009 and 2010. In July 2010 Ferguson was re-elected as chairman of the WPBSA.

name: Jason Ferris
description: Jason Ferris (born 6 July 1976) is an Australian former professional rugby league footballer who played for six different clubs between 1996 and 2005. He played at either halfback or five-eighth. He made his debut in 1996 for the Canberra Raiders in the round 3 match against Parramatta. In November 2009, Ferris was assaulted by two men at Glen Innes and required corrective facial surgery after the attack. In 2010 Ferris was sentenced to at least 13 months in jail after he was convicted of stealing $7,500 from his former employers, the Criterion Hotel in Gundagai, in October 2009. He was also charged with three separate driving offences. A mid-range drink driving offence as well as two offences of driving with a disqualified license. On appeal, he had his sentence downgraded.

name: Jason Finch
description: Jason Michael Finch (born 27 September 1969) is an English cricketer. Finch is a right-handed batsman, although his bowling style is unknown. He also occasionally played as a wicketkeeper. He was born at Hastings, Sussex. Finch represented the Sussex Cricket Board in 3 List A matches. These came against the Essex Cricket Board and Wales Minor Counties in the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2001. His final List A appearance came against the Worcestershire Cricket Board in the 2nd round of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2002. In his 3 List A matches, he scored 60 runs at a batting average of 30.00, with a high score of 26. With the ball he took a single wicket at a bowling average of 22.00, with best figures of 1/22. He currently plays club cricket for Hastings and St Leonards Priory Cricket Club in the Sussex Cricket League.

name: Jason Floros
description: Jason Scott Floros is an Australian cricketer. He currently plays for Queensland in the Sheffield Shield and Ryobi One Day Cup, and for the Sydney Thunder in the Big Bash League.

name: Jason Flowers
description: Jason "Collie" Flowers is a professional rugby league footballer, and current coach, playing at representative level for Scotland, and at club level for Castleford Tigers, Halifax, and Salford City Reds, primarily as a Fullback but also at Wing, Centre, or Second-row. Flowers is currently Jamie Benn's assistant coach for the National Conference League (NCL) Eagles.

name: Jason Geathers
description: Jason Geathers (born August 4, 1980 in Delray Beach, Florida) is a wide receiver who is currently a member of the Orlando Predators of the Arena Football League. He played his collegiate football with the Miami Hurricanes. Prior to joining the Riders, he played with the San Jose SaberCats of the Arena Football League. He was released by the Riders on June 24, 2009.

name: Jason Goodall
description: Jason Goodall (born 23 January 1967) is a former professional tennis player from the United Kingdom.

name: Jason Green
description: David Jason Green (born June 5, 1975) is a former Major League Baseball pitcher who played for the Houston Astros in 2000.

name: Jason Gregoire
description: Jason Gregoire (born February 24, 1989) is a Canadian ice hockey left wing. Gregoire developed his skills as a youth playing for the Winnipeg Blues. He joined the Lincoln Stars in 2006 and played there for two years. He was selected by the New York Islanders in the 3rd round (76th overall) of the 2007 NHL Entry Draft. Gregoire played for the University of North Dakota in the WCHA until the end of his Junior Year in 2011. After playing for the Fighting Sioux for three years, Gregoire signed a two-way contract with the Winnipeg Jets.

name: Jason Hardy
description: Jason Paul Hardy (born 14 December 1969) is a retired English professional association footballer who played as a defender. He started his career with Burnley, making his professional debut in the 0–1 defeat to Aldershot on 21 March 1987.

name: Jason Harmon
description: Jason Harmon (born January 27, 1987) is a wide receiver in professional football who is currently a member of the Lakeland Raiders of the Ultimate Indoor Football League. He played college football at Florida Atlantic.

name: Jason Harris-Wright
description: Jason Harris-Wright (born 19 September 1988) is an Irish rugby union player for Connacht Rugby. Harris-Wright's choice of position is at hooker. Harris-Wright attended Presentation College, Bray and Blackrock College. Harris-Wright earned 7 caps for Leinster Schools and 5 for the Leinster under-20 team. Harris-Wright has played 5 times for the Ireland under-19's and 10 times for the Ireland under-20's. Harris-Wright has also represented Leinster A 4 times in the British and Irish Cup. He signed for Bristol Rugby on 8 November 2011. In May 2012 he joined Connacht Rugby ahead of the 2012/12 season after Bristol failed to win promotion back to the Aviva Premiership.

name: Jason Harrison
description: Jason Christian Harrison (born 15 January 1972) is an English cricketer. Harrison is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He was born in Amersham, Buckinghamshire. Having made his debut in county cricket for Buckinghamshire, who he played for in both the Minor Counties Championship and the MCCA Knockout Trophy, Harrison made his first-class debut for Middlesex in a first-class match against Cambridge University in 1994. He played 9 further first-class matches for Middlesex, the last coming against Warwickshire in the 1996 County Championship. In his 10 first-class matches for Middlesex, he scored 298 runs at a batting average of 19.86, with a high score of 46*. It was for Middlesex that he made his List A debut for, against Leicestershire in the 1994 AXA Equity & Law League. He played 4 further List A matches for Middlesex, up to 1996. After being released by Middlesex, Harrison played a further two seasons for Buckinghamshire, in which time he made his List A debut for the county against Surrey in the 1998 NatWest Trophy. The season following that he joined Lincolnshire for the 1999 season. He played Minor counties cricket for Lincolnshire from 1999 to 2002. Harrison also appeared in the List A cricket for Lincolnshire, making 8 appearances in that format for the county, the last coming against Glamorgan in the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 8 appearances for the county, he scored 164 runs at an average of 20.50, with a single half century high score of 71. This came against Suffolk in the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. He rejoined Buckinghamshire in 2003, who he continues to play Minor counties cricket for to this day. Upon his return to his native county, he also played a final List A match, against Lancashire in the 2005 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his career he played a total of 15 List A matches, scoring 239 runs at an average of 19.91, with a high score of 71. With the ball he took 3 wickets at a bowling average of 67.66, with best figures of 1/3.

name: Jason Herrick
description: Jason Herrick (born October 5, 1987 in Elmhurst, Illinois) is a retired American soccer player.

name: Jason Hotchkin
description: Jason Hotchkin (born June 5, 1978 in Kalamazoo, Michigan) is an American soccer player, currently playing for Harrisburg City Islanders in the USL Professional Division.

name: Jason Kelce
description: Jason D. Kelce (born November 5, 1987) is an American football center for the Philadelphia Eagles of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Eagles in the sixth round of the 2011 NFL Draft. He played college football at Cincinnati.

name: Jason Krizan
description: Jason William Krizan (born June 28, 1989) is an American baseball outfielder in the minor league system of the Detroit Tigers of Major League Baseball. Prior to being drafted by the Tigers, he played college baseball at Dallas Baptist University, where Krizan was named a First-Team All-American in his senior season.

name: Jason Kutney
description: Jason Kutney (born September 5, 1981 in Freehold Borough, New Jersey) is an American soccer player who currently plays for Pittsburgh Riverhounds in the USL Professional Division.

name: Jason Layman
description: Jason Layman (born July 29, 1973) is a former American football offensive lineman in the National Football League. He was drafted by the Houston Oilers in the second round of the 1996 NFL Draft. He played college football at Tennessee. In 1999, the Titans made it to Super Bowl XXXIV in which Layman appeared as a substitute, however they lost to the Kurt Warner-led St. Louis Rams.

name: Jason Lidden
description: Jason Lidden (born 24 April 1969) is a former Australian professional rugby league footballer for the Western Suburbs Magpies, Penrith Panthers and Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs.

name: Jason Maniecki
description: Zbigniew "Jason" Maniecki is a former defensive tackle in the National Football League. He was drafted in the fifth round of the 1996 NFL Draft by the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and played three seasons with the team.

name: Jason Marcano
description: Jason Marcano (born 30 December 1983) is an international soccer player from Trinidad and Tobago who plays professionally for San Juan Jabloteh as a forward. Jason was born to parents Maria John and Steve Marcano the only boy with five female siblings. He started his football career at the age of 10 while attending arima west government primary school, he later went on to play for the under 20 team and the Trinidad and Tobago under 23 Olympic team in 2003. Jason is married, has one son and lives with his family in Arima.

name: Jason Marshall (rugby union)
description: Jason Marshall is a Canadian rugby union player. His position is tighthead prop, and he has played 12 tests for the Canadian national team. Marshall currently plays for Stade Aurillacois Cantal Auvergne in the Rugby Pro D2. Marshall had previously played rugby in the British Columbia Premiership with Capilano RFC and James Bay Athletic Association as well as with the BC Bears in the Canadian Rugby Championship. Marshall originally had aspirations of becoming a professional football player as he played as a quarterback with Simon Fraser University and eventually tried out for the Edmonton Eskimos of the Canadian Football League. After being cut from the Eskimos Marshall focused on rugby eventually making the Canadian national senior team in 2008. Marshall competed for Canada at the 2011 Rugby World Cup starting at tighthead prop in all four of Canada's pool matches.

name: Jason Massie
description: Jason Massie (born September 13, 1984 in Liverpool) is an English footballer who currently plays for GPS Portland Phoenix in the USL Premier Development League.

name: Jason Medeiros
description: Jason Medeiros (born August 22, 1989 in Hamilton, Ontario) is a Canadian football offensive lineman for the Hamilton Tiger-Cats of the Canadian Football League. He was signed as an undrafted free agent on May 30, 2012. After the 2011 CIS season, he was ranked as the tenth best player in the Canadian Football League’s Amateur Scouting Bureau January rankings for players eligible in the 2012 CFL Draft, and seventh by players in Canadian Interuniversity Sport. He is a graduate of St. Thomas More Catholic Secondary School in Hamilton and played CIS football with the McMaster Marauders and was a part of their 2011 Vanier Cup championship. Medieros was named a CIS All-Canadian in 2012.

name: Jason Nugent
description: Jason Nugent (born May 18, 1982 in Scarborough, Ontario) is a Canadian football defensive back who is currently a free agent. He most recently played for the Calgary Stampeders of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted by the Edmonton Eskimos in the second round of the 2006 CFL Draft. He played college football at Rutgers.

name: Jason Palmada
description: Jason Palmada (born 25 February 1969) is a New Zealand former rugby league footballer.

name: Jason Price (ice hockey)
description: Jason Price (born February 8, 1985) is an American professional ice hockey player who is currently playing with the Augusta Riverhawks in the Southern Professional Hockey League.

name: Jason Prior
description: Jason Christopher Prior (born 20 December 1988) is an English footballer who plays as a striker for Conference National side Dartford on loan from League Two club AFC Wimbledon. He has previously played for non-league sides AFC Newbury, Moneyfields and Bognor Regis Town. He made his full Football League debut for AFC Wimbledon on 28 January 2012.

name: Jason Rutledge
description: Jason Rutledge (born 15 December 1977) is a New Zealand rugby union player who plays provincial rugby for Southland, and is in the Super Rugby team the Highlanders. Rutledge made his debut for the Highlanders in 2004, but after playing two games that season, did not return to the Highlanders until the 2009 season. He came on as a substitution for David Hall in the season opener against the Brumbies, scoring a try minutes from full time which briefly put the Highlanders in the lead.

name: Jason Sabio
description: Jason Abbott Abantao Sabio (born 30 June 1986) is a Filipino international soccer player who plays for Kaya as a center back or a right back but is more comfortable at central defense because of his leap, speed and communication skills. A native of the Philippines, he moved to the United States at a young age where he eventually settled in Huntsville, Alabama. There he took up the sport of soccer, playing in high school and in college where he also obtained a bachelor's degree in biochemistry graduating cum laude. He is currently in law school at the University of Alabama and is also a player and coach of their club soccer team. An aspiring lawyer, he will pursue playing professional soccer if he cannot get offers from Baker, Donelson, Bearman, Caldwell & Berkowitz or Maynard Cooper Gale law firms.

name: Jason Seacole
description: Jason Seacole (born 10 April 1960) is a former English footballer who played for Oxford United and Wycombe Wanderers. During his spell at Oxford, he became the youngest player to play in the league for the club, aged just 16 years and 149 days. He is also the club's youngest scorer in the league.

name: Jason Shoemark
description: Jason Shoemark is a professional rugby union player who serves as a centre for the Exeter Chiefs in the Aviva Premiership.

name: Jason Slowey
description: Jason Slowey (born January 27, 1989) is an American football offensive lineman signed to the Oakland Raiders' practice squad. He was drafted by the San Francisco 49ers in the sixth round of the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at Western Oregon University. Slowey drew little attention heading into the 2012 NFL Draft until Western Oregon's pro day in March. A left tackle in college, he was projected to move inside to guard in the NFL. On October 23, 2012, Slowey was signed by the Raiders.

name: Jason Smart
description: Jason Smart is an Australian Paralympic athlete. He won a gold medal at the 1988 Seoul Games in the Men's 4x100 m Relay A2A4-7 event.

name: Jason Soloman
description: Jason Rafael Soloman (born 6 October 1970) is a retired English professional footballer who played as a defender. Soloman made over 100 league appearances for a number of clubs between 1990 and 1997, before playing non-league football.

name: Jason Suttle
description: Jason Suttle is a former defensive back in the National Football League. He played two seasons with the Denver Broncos before being a member of the San Francisco 49ers during his final season.

name: Jason Walton
description: Jason Walton (born 13 June 1990) is an English rugby league player. Walton plays for Batley in the Co-operative Championship. He was previously with Salford playing five matches from the bench in the Super League. Jason Walton's usual position is centre, although he is also used in the second row. Walton appeared for England Under-17s against the Australian Institute of Sport in 2007.

name: Jason Weaver (cricketer)
description: Jason Richard Weaver (born 11 Auguat 1968) is a former English cricketer. Weaver was a right-handed batsman who fielded as a wicket-keeper. He was born in Wellington, Cumberland. Weaver made his debut for Shropshire in the 1989 Minor Counties Championship against Wiltshire. Weaver played Minor counties cricket for Shropshire from 1989 to 1991, which included 11 Minor Counties Championship appearances and a single MCCA Knockout Trophy match. He made his List A debut against Derbyshire in the 1990 NatWest Trophy. In this match, he was dismissed for a duck by Ole Mortensen. He made a further List A appearance against Leicestershire in the 1991 NatWest Trophy. He scored 6 runs in this match, before being dismissed by Craig Wilkinson.

name: Jason Werner
description: Jason Michael Werner (born September 17, 1986) is a former American football linebacker who used to play for the Purdue University football team beginning in 2005 and declared eligible for play through the 2010 season. He was a team co-captain for the 2009 season. He was named Indianapolis Star Indiana Mr. Football 2004 while attending the Roncalli High School where he was a player on the Indiana 4A state championship teams in 2002, 2003, and 2004. His senior year he was also named as an Indianapolis Star Marion County Male Co-Athlete of the Year.

name: Jason Woodward
description: Jason Christopher Woodward. He moved to Australia in early 2013 and joined the Rebels for the 2013 Super Rugby season. There was speculation, pre-season, he would be full back if Kurtley Beale moved to fly-half.

name: Jason Zucker
description: Jason Zucker (born January 16, 1992) is an American ice hockey player currently playing for the Minnesota Wild. Zucker participated in the 2010 World Juniors for Team USA and won the gold medal. He was also a member of Team USA's bronze medal winning team at the 2011 World Juniors. Zucker is Jewish, was born in Newport Beach, California, and was raised in Las Vegas, Nevada. He attended Pioneer High School in Ann Arbor, Michigan. Playing for the University of Denver in 2010–11, he was the WCHA Rookie of the Year, and was also named to the WCHA All-Rookie Team and 2nd All-Star Team. Zucker signed his entry-level contract with the Wild on March 27, 2012, and made his NHL Debut in a victory against the Florida Panthers on March 29, 2012. He scored his first NHL goal against Petr Mrazek on February 17, 2013 in a Wild win over the Detroit Red Wings.

name: Jasse Ikonen
description: Jasse Ikonen is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who currently plays for KalPa of the SM-liiga.

name: Jasur Hasanov
description: Jasur Orziqulovich Hasanov is a footballer from Uzbekistan currently playing for Emirati club Emirates Club. He usually plays as left midfielder. Hasanov is a regular starter for the Uzbekistan national football team.

name: Jauna Murmu
description: Jauna Murmu is an Indian woman Sprint runner and Hurdler from Odisha who specializes in 400 metres and 400 metres hurdles. She belongs to Mayurbhanj District of Odisha. She has received coaching from Arun Kumar Das and Subash Chandra Dasmohapatra.

name: Javad Asghari Moghaddam
description: Javad Asghari Moghaddam, born 12 August 1979 in Tonekabon, Mazandran, Iran is an Iranian futsal player. He is a member of Dabiri Tabriz and the Iran national futsal team.

name: Javad Ghorab
description: Javad Ghorab is an Iranian football Midfielder who played for Iran in the 1972 Summer Olympics . He also played for Taj SC.

name: Javad Maheri
description: Javad Maheri (born December 10, 1983) is an Iranian footballer who plays for Sepahan in the Iran Pro League. He currently plays as the loan for Mes Rafsanjan football club.

name: Javarris James
description: Javarris James (born September 18, 1987) is an American football running back for the Arizona Cardinals of the National Football League (NFL). He was signed by the Indianapolis Colts as an undrafted free agent in 2010. He played college football at the University of Miami. He has also been a member of the New England Patriots and Washington Redskins. He is the younger cousin of NFL running back Edgerrin James, who also played college football in Miami and later for the Colts.

name: Javed Ahmadi
description: Javed Ahmadi (born 2 January 1992) is an Afghan cricketer. He is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He currently represents the Afghanistan national cricket team. Ahmadi started representing Afghanistan in age group cricket, which culminated in the Afghanistan Under-19 cricket team qualifying for the 2010 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup in New Zealand, for the first time in their history. Ahmadi proceeded to represent Afghanistan during the trounament. His debut for the senior team came against Scotland in a warm-up match for the 2010 ICC World Cricket League Division One. During this tournament he made his debut in List-A cricket and also his debut in One Day International cricket against Scotland. He played one further ODI during the tournament, which came against hosts the Netherlands. To date he has played 2 further ODI's, both of which came against Scotland during Afghanistan's tour of Scotland in 2010. In his 4 ODI's to date, he has scored 31 runs at a batting average of 10.33, with a high score of 25. Meanwhile, in the field he has taken 2 catches. His debut first-class match came against Kenya in the 2009-10 ICC Intercontinental Cup. During the match he made scores of 11 and 55, his maiden first-class half century. Ahmadi's favourite player is the Australian Michael Clarke, although he likens his own batting style to that of Michael Vaughan.

name: Javed Mohammed
description: Javed Mohammed (born April 17, 1989) is a Trinidadian footballer who currently plays in the TT Pro League with T&TEC SC.

name: Javeria Khan
description: Javeria Khan(born 14 May 1988) is a female Pakistani cricketer from Karachi, Sindh. She is played in Pakistan national women's cricket team as All-rounder. She also played the ICC Women's World Cup 2009. She played International level as well as Domestic level.

name: Javi Barral
description: Javier 'Javi' Barral García (born 30 September 1981 in Madrid) is a Spanish footballer who plays for CD Guadalajara as a left defender.

name: Javi Flores
description: Javier 'Javi' Flores Santacruz (born 9 February 1986 in Córdoba, Andalusia) is a Spanish footballer who plays for Elche CF as an attacking midfielder.

name: Javid Imamverdiyev
description: Javid Imamverdiyev (Azerbaijani: Cavid İmamverdiyev; born 1 August 1990 in Shamkir), Azerbaijani footballer playing currently for Neftchi Baku. He is also a member of the Azerbaijan national football team.

name: Javid James
description: Javid James (born April 17, 1986 in New Orleans, Louisiana) is a professional American and Canadian football wide receiver who is currently a free agent. He was signed by the Montreal Alouettes as a street free agent in 2008. He played college football for the UCF Knights.

name: Javier Ballesteros
description: Javier 'Javi' Ballesteros Tomás is a Spanish footballer who plays for CD Guijuelo as a striker.

name: Javier Cárdenas
description: Javier Cárdenas Martínez (born 8 December 1952) is a Mexican football midfielder who played for Mexico in the 1978 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Deportivo Toluca.

name: Javier Capelli
description: Javier Capelli is an Argentine footballer currently playing for Rangers of the Chilean Primera División as defender.

name: Javier Chila
description: Bernardo Javier Chila Ayovi (born July 14, 1984) is an Ecuadorian footballer who plays for El Nacional in Serie A de Ecuador.

name: Javier Cortés
description: Javier Cortés Granados (born July 20, 1989) is a professional footballer. He currently plays as a Forward for the Pumas de la UNAM in the Mexican First Division.

name: Javier Gallo
description: Javier Gallo González is a Mexican professional boxer in the Bantamweight division.

name: Javier Guédez
description: Javier Antonio Guédez Sánchez (born October 15, 1982) is a male judoka from Venezuela. He won the bronze medal in the extra lightweight division (– 60 kg) at the 2007 Pan American Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. He represented his native country at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, PR China.

name: Javier Guarino
description: Javier Guarino (born April 16, 1986 in Salto) is a Uruguayan footballer who currently plays for Real Esppor Club as a striker.

name: Javier Jiménez Camarero
description: Javier 'Javi' Jiménez Camarero is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for Real Murcia as a goalkeeper.

name: Javier Manquillo
description: Javier 'Javi' Manquillo Gaitán (born 5 May 1994) is a Spanish footballer who plays for Atlético Madrid B as a right defender.

name: Javier Moises Hernandez
description: Javier Moisés Hernández Posada is a Salvadoran football midfielder who currently plays for C.D. Vista Hermosa in the Salvadoran Premier League.

name: Javier Roca
description: Javier Leopoldo Roca Sepúlveda (born on August 9, 1977 in Santiago) is a Chilean footballer that currently plays for Persis Solo in the Liga Indonesia Premier Division (LPIS).

name: Javier Salazar
description: Javier Bohuzlav Salazar Tejada (born 11 March 1982) is a Peruvian footballer who plays as a centre back. He currently plays for José Gálvez FBC.

name: Javier Smith
description: Javier Smith (born 21 March 1987) in the British Virgin Islands is a footballer who plays as a Defender. He currently plays for British Virgin Islands Championship club Virgin Gorda Ballstars and the British Virgin Islands national football team.

name: Javille Brooks
description: Javille Brooks (born 21 September 1984) in Anguilla is a footballer who plays as a forward. He currently plays for the Anguilla national football team.

name: Javy Guerra
description: Luis Javier Guerra (born October 31, 1985) is a pitcher in Major League Baseball for the Los Angeles Dodgers.

name: Jay Aston (rugby league)
description: Jay Aston is an rugby league footballer who represented Papua New Guinea at the 2008 World Cup. He plays professionally at club level with the Melbourne Storm, but has yet to make his first-grade football debut. Aston's favoured position is hooker, but he can also cover the second row. Aston made his International debt against Australia in the 2008 World Cup, coming off the substitutes bench in the Pool A 46-6 loss at Dairy Farmers Stadium, Townsville, Queensland. Prior to being signed by the Storm, Aston played for Norths Devils in the Queensland Cup. Following playing for the Devils, he was selected to represent East Queensland at the Queensland Carnival. In 2008, he spent a year in the Toyota Cup with Melbourne Under 20's.

name: Jay Cascalenda
description: Jay Cascalenda (born July 10, 1985) is an American professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the Bakersfield Condors in the ECHL.

name: Jay Handlan
description: Jay Handlan College Washington & Lee Conference Southern Sport Basketball Position Forward Height precision_format| 1.8796 | 2}} m Nationality American Born (1928-02-02)February 2, 1928Wheeling, West Virginia Died January 10, 2013(2013-01-10) (aged 84) High school Triadelphia(Wheeling, West Virginia) Awards Helms Foundation All-America (1951) 3× Honorable Mention All-America 2× All-Southern Conference 4× All-Virginia 4× Top 16 scorer nationally Second all-time W&L scorer (2,002 points) John Bernard "Jay" Handlan (February 2, 1928 – January 10, 2013) was an American former college basketball star at Washington and Lee University in Lexington, Virginia from 1948 to 1952. He was born in Wheeling, West Virginia. A 6 ft 2 in forward, Handlan is best known for being a prolific scorer and for setting the still–standing National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) record for field goal attempts in a game with 71.

name: Jay Johnson (baseball)
description: Jay Robert Johnson (born December 21, 1989) is a Canadian professional baseball pitcher in minor league baseball organization of the Philadelphia Phillies of Major League Baseball. Prior to beginning his professional career, he played college baseball at Texas Tech University. He has also competed for the Canadian national baseball team.

name: Jay Lee Harris
description: Jay Lee Harris is an English professional footballer who plays for the Chicago Mustangs of the Professional Arena Soccer League.

name: Jay MacDowell
description: Jay MacDowell is a former professional American football player who played wide receiver for six seasons for the Philadelphia Eagles. {{#invoke: Navbox | navbox }} {{#invoke: Navbox | navbox }}

name: Jay Pettibone
description: Harry Jonathan Pettibone (born June 21, 1957 in Mount Clemens, Michigan) is former Major League Baseball pitcher. Pettibone played for the Minnesota Twins in 1983. He batted and threw right-handed. He was drafted by the Texas Rangers in the 25th round of the 1979 amateur draft.

name: Jay Rhodemyre
description: Jay Rhodemyre (died June 7, 1968) is a former center in the National Football League. He was drafted by the Green Bay Packers in the seventh round of the 1948 NFL Draft and would play four seasons with the team.

name: Jay Ross (American football)
description: Jay Randall Ross (born October 3, 1987) is an American football defensive tackle for the Buffalo Bills of the National Football League. He was signed as an undrafted free agent by the New Orleans Saints in 2010. He played college football at East Carolina University.

name: Jay Schlueter
description: Jay D Schlueter (July 31, 1949 – May 13, 2010) was an outfielder who played in Major League Baseball during the 1971 season. Listed at 6 ft 0 in, 182 lb. , he batted and threw right-handed. Born in Phoenix, Arizona, Schlueter was a second round selection in the 1967 MLB Draft by the Houston Astros. He spent part of five seasons in the minor leagues before joining the big club in the 1971 midseason. Unfortunately, he formed part of a very congested Astros outfield that included César Cedeño, César Gerónimo, Jimmy Wynn and Bob Watson, among others. Schlueter went 1-for-3 and scored one run in seven games, but never returned to the majors. After that, he went to the minors for four more seasons. In a nine-year minors career, he posted a .209 average with 48 home runs and 128 runs batted in in 863 games. Following his playing career, Schlueter became a dedicated coach and supporter of all youth and high school sports in Scottsdale, Arizona, and Chaparral, New Mexico. He later worked as a commercial real estate broker. Schlueter died in his homeland of Scottdale at the age of 60.

name: Jay Timo
description: Jay Timo (born 16 October 1982) is a Tuvaluan footballer who played for Nauti FC in 2007.

name: Jaya Teguh Angga
description: Jaya Teguh Angga Warsito is an Indonesian footballer who currently playing for Arema Indonesia in the Indonesian Premier League. His natural position is striker. he is also playing for the Indonesia national football team.

name: Jayde Herrick
description: Jayde Matthew Herrick (born 16 January 1985) is an Australian cricketer who plays for Victoria in Australian domestic cricket. He is a right-arm fast-medium bowler and a right-hand batsman. In November 2010 Herrick made his First-class cricket debut for Wellington in a New Zealand domestic match and then the following month played for Victoria in a match against England. He impressed, making 40 runs from just 19 balls in the second innings and by taking the wickets of Eoin Morgan and Paul Collingwood. Herrick made a remarkable Sheffield Shield debut for Victoria in March 2011. Playing against South Australia, he claimed match bowling figures of 6/115 from 36 overs. Batting at number 11, he was also part of a crucial 85-run partnership with Steve Gilmour. In that partnership, Herrick contributed 43 from 55 balls. He recently signed with the Melbourne Renegades in the newly formed Big Bash League for the 2011/12 season.

name: Jayden Levitt
description: Jayden Ross Levitt (born 23 June 1986) is a South African born English cricketer. Levitt is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break. He was born in Johannesburg, Transvaal Province. Levitt made his debut in Minor counties cricket for Wiltshire against Cheshire in the 2007 Minor Counties Championship. To date, he has made sixteen Minor Counties Championship and eight MCCA Knockout Trophy appearances for the county. In 2011, he joined the Unicorns to play in the Clydesdale Bank 40. He made his List A debut for the team against Gloucestershire and followed this up with two further appearances against Somerset and Glamorgan. In his three matches he scored 65 runs at an average of 21.66, with a high score of 33.

name: Jaymon Crabb
description: Jaymon Crabb (born 6 March 1978) is a former professional tennis player from Australia. He is the brother of Jaxon Crabb, who played for the West Coast Eagles and Port Adelaide in the Australian Football League.

name: Jayson Rego
description: Jayson Rego is an American rugby league player for the Ipswich Jets in the Queensland Cup. He has previously played College Football for the Hawaii Warriors football team as a runningback. He is a United States national rugby league team international. Also selected to the 2011 All-American 7's team. His position is fullback and wing.

name: Jayson Vemoa
description: Jayson "Supercharge" Vemoa a former Muay Thai World Champion from New Zealand leading a successful coaching career in Japan as the Head Kickboxing Coach at the Ichigeki Academy in Tokyo for the IKO1 (Matsui) Kyokushin Organization, preparing Kyokushin kaikan for K-1 and other world wide professional Martial Art events. The list of people he has trained includes Jonah Lomu, Hidetoshi Nakata, Noriyuki Higashiyama, Ray Sefo, Glaube Feitosa, Aleksandr Pitchkounov, Jordan Tai, Doug Viney, Ewerton Teixeira, Mark Hunt

name: Je-Vaughn Watson
description: Je-Vaughn Watson (born 22 October 1983 in Saint Catherine Parish) is a Jamaican footballer who currently plays for the FC Dallas in Major League Soccer.

name: Jeaffreson Vennor Brewer
description: Jeaffreson Brewer (1853–1924) was a rugby union international who represented England in 1875.

name: Jean-Baptiste Gobelet
description: Jean-Baptiste Gobelet (born 13 March 1983) is a French rugby union footballer. He currently plays for Stade Français in the Top 14. His usual position is on the wing but he can also play at centre. He previously played for Biarritz Olympique, whilst there he won two Top 14 titles.

name: Jean-Baptiste Maquet
description: Jean-Baptiste Maquet (born 6 February 1922) is a Belgian fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-Baptiste Perlant
description: Jean-Baptiste Perlant (born 22 February 1977) is a former professional tennis player from France. Perlant made his Grand Slam debut in the 1998 French Open. He lost his opening match to Spaniard Jose Imaz-Ruiz in five sets. At the US Open later that year, he defeated world number 38 Jason Stoltenberg, who had previously reached the semi-finals of Wimbledon. In the second round he met seventh seed Alex Corretja and again lost a five set match. His only doubles appearance at Grand Slam level was in the 1997 French Open, where he partnered Jean-François Bachelot. The pair had the misfortune of having to face the number one seeds in the opening round, Todd Woodbridge and Mark Woodforde. They won just three games in the match.

name: Jean-Blaise Evéquoz
description: Jean-Blaise Evéquoz (born 27 November 1953) is a Swiss fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team épée event at the 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-Charles Seneca
description: Jean-Charles Seneca (born 23 October 1945) is a Monégasque fencer. He competed in the individual épée event at the 1972 Summer Olympics. He was also Monaco's flag bearer during the Opening Ceremony.

name: Jean-Charles Skarbowsky
description: Jean-Charles Skarbowsky (born March 10, 1975) is a French former kickboxer and 3-times European Muay Thai champion. Skarbowsky has been one of the best farangs who have fought in Thailand.

name: Jean-Christophe Faurel
description: Jean-Christophe Faurel (born 6 March 1981) is a former professional tennis player from France.

name: Jean-Christophe Lourde
description: Jean-Christophe Lourde is a French footballer of Mauritian descent who currently plays for French CFA side AFC Compiègne.

name: Jean-Claude Bozga
description: Jean-Claude Adrimer Bozga (born 1 June 1984, Galati) is an Romanian footballer who is currently playing for Vestsjælland. He is a Congolese born and established in Romania.

name: Jean-Claude Garneau
description: Jean-Claude Garneau is a retired Canadian ice hockey forward who played 17 games in the WHA for the for the Quebec Nordiques during the 1974–75 WHA season.

name: Jean-Claude Sawyer
description: Jean-Claude Sawyer (born August 12, 1986) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the Cincinnati Cyclones in the ECHL. He was selected by the Minnesota Wild in the 5th round (161st overall) of the 2004 NHL Entry Draft. On July 2, 2007, he was signed as a free agent by the Chicago Blackhawks.

name: Jean-Eudes Maurice
description: Jean-Eudes Maurice (born 21 June 1986) is a French-born Haitian footballer who plays for French club Le Mans on loan from Paris Saint-Germain.

name: Jean-François Di Martino
description: Jean-François Di Martino (born 2 March 1967) is a French fencer. He won a silver medal in the team épée event at the 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-François Dumoulin
description: Jean-François Dumoulin (born May 5, 1976 in Trois-Rivières, Quebec, Canada) is a Canadian race car driver who drives in the Rolex Sports Car Series and drove one NASCAR Nationwide Series race at Montreal and finished 7th.

name: Jean-François Montauriol
description: Jean-François Montauriol (born 21 March 1983) in Toulouse, France is a Franco-Italian rugby union player. His preferred position is in the Back Row although he can also play equally well in the Second Row. He currently plays for Rugby Rovigo in the National Championship of Excellence. He began his career at his hometown club Stade Toulousain but was never a regular first-XV player. He moved to Venezia before the start of the 2008-09 season, where his performances were rewarded with a call-up to the Italy squad for the match against England in the 2009 Six Nations Championship. He came on as a replacement for the final 4 minutes of the game at Twickenham, winning his first cap. He was also selected on Italy's 2009 summer tour to Australia and New Zealand. He won his second cap against Australia in Melbourne on this tour.

name: Jean-François Tournon
description: Jean-François Tournon (6 August 1905 – 12 April 1986) was a French fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team sabre event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-Jacques Kilama
description: Jean-Jacques Kilama, or simply Kilama, (born October 13, 1985, in Cameroon) is a Cameroonian defender. He is currently playing for Sunray Cave JC Sun Hei in the Hong Kong First Division League.

name: Jean-Jacques N'Domba
description: Jean-Jacques N'Domba is a former professional footballer who played as a midfielder.

name: Jean-Joseph Renaud
description: Jean-Joseph Renaud (16 January 1873 – 8 December 1953) was a French fencer. He competed at the 1900 and 1908 Summer Olympics. He was also a prolific journalist, author and playwright whose books La Defense dans la Rue (Self Defence in the Street - 1912) and L'escrime (fencing - 1911) are recognised as an important contribution to early 20th century literature on those subjects. He was a proponent of the field of honor, saying: "From every point of view dueling is beneficent. " He refereed many duels (including ones involving Clemenceau and Leon Blum) and fought at least 15 himself (being a fencing master, all but 4 were fought with pistols; he was victorious in all of them).

name: Jean-Louis Montero
description: Jean-Louis Montero (born 28 April 1971) is a French former professional footballer who played as a right back.

name: Jean-Luc Escayol
description: Jean-Luc Escayol is a footballer currently playing for Division d'Honneur club Port-la-Nouvelle. He plays as a defensive midfielder.

name: Jean-Luc Lambourde
description: Jean-Luc Lambourde (born 10 April 1980) is a French football player who currently plays for Amical Club on the island of Guadeloupe in the Guadeloupe Division d'Honneur. He plays as a Defender and began his football career playing for amateur club Avion in 2002. After spending three seasons with the club, Lambourde ventured to his native homeland joining his current club, where he currently remains. In his second season with the club, he won the Coupe de Guadeloupe. Lambourde is also a member of the Guadeloupe national football team. He is one of a few players in the team to have participated in all three of the team's appearances as the CONCACAF Gold Cup.

name: Jean-Luc Rougé
description: Jean-Luc Rougé is a French judoka.

name: Jean-Manuel Thetis
description: Jean-Manuel Thetis is a French footballer who played 116 matches and scored 4 goals in Ligue 1 in the 1989-1997 period and played 22 matches and scored 2 goals for Marseille in Ligue 2 in the 1994-1995 season. Thetis then went on to have a 3 year spell at Ipswich Town. At Ipswich he scored important winners in two 1-0 league victories against Tranmere Rovers and West Bromwich Albion (a game in which he later got sent off). He also scored once for Ipswich in the League Cup against Luton Town. He then had two brief loan spells at Wolverhampton Wanderers and Sheffield United respectively in 2000 and 2001.

name: Jean-Marc Chouinard
description: Jean-Marc Chouinard (born 6 November 1963) is a Canadian fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at four consecutive Olympic Games from 1984 to 1996.

name: Jean-Marc Doussain
description: Jean-Marc Doussain (born 12 February 1991) is a French rugby union fly half. He plays club rugby for Stade Toulousain and has appeared for the French national U20 side. He made his debut for France with 5 minutes left of the 2011 Rugby World Cup Final, becoming the first player ever to make his Test debut in a Rugby World Cup Final. Doussain was born in Sainte-Croix-Volvestre and played for Saint-Girons rugby club before signing for Toulouse in 2007, at the age of 17. {{#invoke:citation/CS1|citation |CitationClass=news }} His father, Jean Doussain, was also a rugby player, having played at scrum-half for Stade Saint-Gaudinois in the 1980s. Doussain made his first full appearance for Toulouse on 28 November 2009, against Montauban. His current contract commits him to Toulouse until the end of the 2014 season. {{#invoke:citation/CS1|citation |CitationClass=news }}

name: Jean-Marc Garcia
description: Jean-Marc Garcia is a Francen rugby league player who represented his country in the 1995 and 2000 World Cups.

name: Jean-Marie Banos
description: Jean-Marie Banos (born 10 February 1962) is a Canadian fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at four consecutive Olympic Games between 1988 and 1996. His brother, Jean-Paul Banos, also fenced for Canada at four Olympic Games. He is married to Caitlin Bilodeaux, who fenced for the United States at the 1988 and 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-Michel Aguirre
description: Jean-Michel Aguirre (born Tostat, November 2, 1951) is a former French rugby union player. He played as a Scrum-half and Fullback. Aguirre played for Stade Bagnérais. He started his career as a Scrum-half but his usual positions became Fullback. Jean-Michel Aguirre earned his first national cap on November 27, 1971 against the Australia at Colombes.

name: Jean-Michel Fontaine
description: Jean-Michel Fontaine (born August 28, 1988 in Réunion) is a French forward currently playing for Fleetwood Town.

name: Jean-Nicolas Carrière

He was drafted in the third round with the 21st overall pick in the 2008 CFL Draft by the Toronto Argonauts and played the 2008 CFL season for them. On July 9, 2009, Carrière was released by the Argonauts. Carrière played CIS Football for the McGill Redmen.

name: Jean-Noël Ferrari
description: Jean-Noël Ferrari (born 7 June 1974) is a French fencer. He won a gold medal in team foil at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Athens, together with Lionel Plumenail, Brice Guyart and Patrice Lhotellier.

name: Jean-Noël Laboiteuse
description: Jean-Noël Laboiteuse (born 12 January 1977) is a Mauritian former international footballer who played as a midfielder. He won nine caps and scored one goal for the Mauritius national football team between 2002 and 2007.

name: Jean-Pascal Barraque
description: Jean-Pascal Barraque (born April 24, 1991) is a French rugby union footballer. He plays for Biarritz Olympique. He is a utility back. His usual positions is fly-half, although he can play as a centre or Fullback.

name: Jean-Patrick Abouna
description: Jean-Patrick Abouna Ndzana (born 27 September 1990) is a Cameroonian international footballer who plays for Astres, as a full back.

name: Jean-Paul Olinger

name: Jean-Philippe Daurelle

name: Jean-Philippe Levasseur
description: Jean-Philippe Levasseur (born January 15, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey goaltender who is currently playing for the SG Cortina in Serie A, the top tier of professional ice hockey in Italy. He was selected by the Mighty Ducks of Anaheim in the 7th round (197th overall) of the 2005 NHL Entry Draft. During the 2010–11 AHL season he played for the Syracuse Crunch.

name: Jean-Pierre Garuet-Lempirou
description: Jean-Pierre Garuet-Lempirou (born June 15, 1953 in Lourdes) is a former French international rugby union player. He played as a prop for FC Lourdes. He earned his first cap with the French national team on 13 November 1983 against Australia at Clermont-Ferrand. Since then he was established as one of the elite props in world rugby. He was called for the 1987 Rugby World Cup, where France was runners-up to New Zealand.

name: Jean-Pierre Muller
description: Jean-Pierre Muller (29 August 1924 – 1 July 2008) was a French fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean-Pierre Vanek
description: Jean-Pierre Vanek (born 19 January 1969) is a Luxembourgian footballer. He retired from playing in 2002.

name: Jean-Reck Ah Fok
description: Jean-Reck Ah Fok (born 9 February 1983) is a Mauritian footballer who currently plays as a striker for PAS Mates. He won three caps for the Mauritius national football team in 2002.

name: Jean-Silvestre N'Keoua
description: Jean-Sylvestre N'Keoua (born 31 December 1979) is a football player from the Republic of the Congo. N'Keoua played for Africa Sports National in the CAF Champions League 2000. N'Keoua has made several appearances for the Republic of the Congo national football team, including qualifying matches for the 1998 and 2002 FIFA World Cup. He also played at the 2000 African Nations Cup.

name: Jean-Yves André
description: Jean-Yves André (born May 31, 1977 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for Cercle de Joachim in the Mauritian Premier League and for the Mauritius national football team as a midfielder. He is featured on the Mauritian national team in the official 2010 FIFA World Cup video game.

name: Jean-Yves Li Waut
description: Jean-Yves Li Waut (born 2 July 1978) in Tahiti is a footballer who plays as a Defender. He currently plays for AS Manu-Ura in the Tahiti Division Fédérale and the Tahiti national football team.

name: Jean Antoine
description: Jean Antoine is an American former professional wrestler. After debuting in 1961, she worked a series of mixed tag team matches with partner Terry Funk. In the early 1970s, she went to Japan to work for All Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling. While part of the company, she held the WWWA World Championship once and the WWWA World Tag Team Championship twice with partner Sandy Parker. Back in the United States, she wrestled in Oregon's first women's match in over 50 years in 1975.

name: Jean Barrientos
description: Jean Pierre Agustin Barrientos Díaz (born September 16, 1990 in Montevideo), commonly known as Jean Barrientos, is a Uruguayan footballer who plays as an attacking midfielder for Vitória S.C. in Portugal.

name: Jean Barthe
description: Jean Barthe (born July 22, 1932 in Lourdes), was a French rugby league and rugby union player.

name: Jean Bredenkamp
description: Jean Bredenkamp (born 12 January 1993) is a South African cricketer who currently plays for Boland. He is a right-handed batsman and right-arm medium-fast bowler. Bredenkamp made his first-class debut on 10 March 2011 against Gauteng.

name: Jean Brichaut
description: Jean Brichaut (born 29 July 1911 in Liège, Belgium; died 1962) was a Belgian footballer.

name: Jean Capdouze
description: Jean Capdouze was a French rugby union and rugby league footballer of the 1960s and 70s. He first played rugby union, representing his country in several test matches before switching to rugby league, playing for the Union Treiziste Catalane club and for France's national team in the 1968 and 1970 World Cups.

name: Jean Cerrottini
description: Jean Cerrottini (born 19 October 1938) is a Swiss fencer. He competed in the individual foil event at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Christian N'Kongue
description: Jean Christian Njoh N'Kongue (born March 7, 1983 in Obala) is an Cameroonian footballer currently under contract with CSM Râmnicu Vâlcea.

name: Jean Condom
description: Jean Condom (born August 15, 1960 in Saint-André-de-Seignanx) is a retired French international rugby union player. He played as a lock for Biarritz Olympique. He earned his first cap with the French national team on 31 October 1982 against Romania at Bucharest in 13-9 loss. He was called for the 1987 Rugby World Cup, where France was runners-up to New Zealand.

name: Jean Ducret
description: Jean Ducret (born 20 November 1887, date of death unknown) was a French international footballer. He played as a midfielder and played for five teams, most notably Olympique Lillois and Stade Français. Ducret was one of the national team's first-ever permanent captains having served in the role 13 times in 20 appearances from 1910–1914. Ducret also scored three goals for the team, which included his first-ever against Italy in a 6–2 defeat in May 1910.

name: Jean Fabre (rugby union)
description: Jean Fabre (born Rodez, 7 November 1935) is a former French rugby union player. He played as a flanker. He played for Stade Toulousain. He earned his first cap with the French national team on 11 November 1962 against Romania at Bucharset. In 1964 he became captain of French national team. After his player career he became president of Stade Toulousain during the 1980s.

name: Jean Fievez
description: Jean Fievez (born 30 November 1910, date of death unknown) was a Belgian footballer. He was born in Brussels.

name: Jean Gachassin
description: Jean Gachassin (born 23 December 1941) is a former French rugby union footballer from Bagnères-de-Bigorre, Hautes-Pyrénées. Now Gachassin is President of the Fédération Française de Tennis. He was a utility back. His usual positions was Wing but also at fly-half and centre and fullback and has represented France. He was a part of the French national team which won the 1968 Grand Slam in the Five Nations.

name: Jean Gagnon
description: Jean Gagnon (born November 25, 1956) is a Canadian-born former ice hockey player who played 20 seasons of professional hockey, including 6 seasons (1980–1986) with HC Fribourg-Gottéron in the Swiss National League A.

name: Jean Gilbert Bayaram
description: Jean Gilbert Bayaram (born July 7, 1974 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for Pamplemousses SC in the Mauritian Premier League and for the Mauritius national football team as a midfielder. He is featured on the Mauritian national team in the official 2010 FIFA World Cup video game.

name: Jean Hauert
description: Jean Hauert (born 30 October 1911) was a Swiss fencer. He competed at the 1936 and 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Heeremans
description: Jean Heeremans (31 January 1914 – 2 August 1970) was a Belgian fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Laroyenne
description: Jean Laroyenne (6 March 1930 – 13 February 2009) was a French fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team sabre event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Levavasseur
description: Jean Levavasseur (8 June 1924 – 10 February 1999) was a French fencer. He won a bronze medal in the team sabre event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Paul Boumsong
description: Jean Paul Casimir E. Boumsong or Jean Paul Boumsong or J.P. Boumsong (born on May 20, 1985) is a Cameroonian footballer who last played for Persiram Raja Ampat.

name: Jean Paul Ntsogo Boya
description: Jean Paul Ntsogo Boya (born September 23, 1984 in Yaoundé) is a Cameroonian footballer who plays for Slovakian side FK Dunajská Streda.

name: Jean Petit (Belgian footballer)
description: Jean Petit (25 February 1914 – 5 June 1944) was a Belgian footballer. He was(born in Liège . He played as a defender for Standard de Liège. He played four times for Belgium in 1938.

name: Jean Piero Pérez
description: Jean Piero Pérez is a Venezuelan professional boxer in the flyweight division and is the current interim World Boxing Association flyweight champion.

name: Jean Plumier
description: Jean Plumier (born 17 September 1909, date of death unknown) was a Belgian fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Jean Prunescu
description: Jean Prunescu (born 6 July 1989 in Bucharest) is a Romanian football player under contract with Steaua II Bucureşti. In the 2008–09 season, Prunescu played three games in Liga I while on loan to Gloria Buzău.

name: Jean Robert Yelou
description: Jean Robert Yelou (born 25 September 1983) in Vanuatu is a footballer who plays as a Midfielder. He previously played for Tafea F.C.. He currently plays for Amicale F.C. in the Vanuatu Premia Divisen and the Vanuatu national football team.

name: Jean Sayegh
description: Jean Sayegh (born June 28, 1981 in Lebanon) is a male water polo player from Canada. He was a member of the Canada men's national water polo team, that claimed the bronze medal at the 2007 Pan American Games in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Sayegh was also part of the Canadian team which placed 11th at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing. Playing as a forward Sayegh was named to the tournament all-star team at the Canadian Championships.

name: Jean Segura
description: Jean Carlos Enrique Segura (born March 17, 1990) is a Dominican professional baseball infielder for the Milwaukee Brewers of Major League Baseball.

name: Jean Stemmet
description: Jean Stemmet (born 6 June 1986) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is outside-centre. He represents the Griquas in the Currie Cup and Vodacom Cup. Stemmet previously played for both Western Province and the Sharks in the Vodacom Cup. He also played in the Varsity Cup for Maties.

name: Jean Tamini
description: Jean Tamini (9 December 1919 – 13 March 1993) was a Swiss football forward who played for Switzerland in the 1950 FIFA World Cup. He also played for FC Lyon, AS Saint-Étienne, and Servette FC.

name: Jean Tholix
description: Jean Tholix (born 6 February 1982 in Toamasina) is a Malagasy footballer. He currently plays for AS Adema.

name: Jean da Silva Duarte
description: Jean da Silva Duarte better known simply as Jean (born 1 September 1978) is a Brazilian professional football defender.

name: Jean de Bardel
description: Jean de Bardel was a Swiss fencer. He competed in the team foil event at the 1928 and 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Jeanine Sobek
description: Jeanine Sobek (born February 22, 1972) was a women's ice hockey player from Minnesota. In the NCAA, she competed for the Northeastern Huskies in Hockey East. During the 2000-01 NWHL season, she competed for the Brampton Thunder.

name: Jeanne Vidal
description: Jeanne Vidal was a French fencer. She competed in the women's individual foil event at the 1932 Summer Olympics.

name: Jeannette Bailey
description: Jeannette Bailey (born 9 April 1931) is a British fencer. She competed in the women's team foil event at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Jeannot Lamarque
description: Jeannot Lamarque (born January 4, 1982 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for Curepipe Starlight SC in the Mauritian Premier League and for the Mauritius national football team as a midfielder. He is featured on the Mauritian national team in the official 2010 FIFA World Cup video game.

name: Jeb Brovsky
description: John "Jeb" Brovsky (born December 3, 1988 in Lakewood, Colorado) is an American soccer player currently with Montreal Impact in Major League Soccer.

name: Jeci
description: Jecimauro José Borges known by his nickname Jeci (born April 22, 1980 in Guaratinguetá), is a Brazilian football defender. He currently plays for Kawasaki Frontale.

name: Jedd Ebanks
description: Donovan Jedd Ebanks (born 2 February 1988) is a Caymanian footballer who plays as a defender. He has represented the Cayman Islands during World Cup qualifying matches in 2008 and 2011

name: Jedd Gardner
description: Jedd Gardner is a Canadian football wide receiver for the Guelph Gryphons. He was drafted 28th overall by the Toronto Argonauts of the Canadian Football League in the 2011 CFL Draft and signed with the team on May 31, 2011. After being released following the 2011 training camp, Gardner returned to play out his final year at Guelph.

name: Jedd Gyorko
description: Jedd Lindon Gyorko is an American professional baseball player. He plays for the San Diego Padres of Major League Baseball. He is considered one of the best prospects in baseball. Gyorko attended University High School in Morgantown, West Virginia, where he was named one of the best baseball players in the state. He then enrolled at West Virginia University, and set numerous school records for the West Virginia Mountaineers. Gyorko won the 2010 Brooks Wallace Award as the best shortstop in NCAA Division I baseball. As a professional, Gyorko plays second base and third base.

name: Jeerawat Thongluae
description: Jeerawat Thongluae (Thai จีรวัฒน์ ทองลือ) is a Thai footballer. He plays for Thailand Division 1 League clubside Sisaket.

name: Jeferson Antonio Alves Dupin
description: Jeferson Antonio Alves Dupin (born October 19, 1972) is a former Brazilian football player.

name: Jeferson Paulo Rodrigues de Souza
description: Jeferson Paulo Rodrigues de Souza (born December 14, 1981), known simply as Mikimba or Jeferson, is a naturalized Togolese football midfielder, who plays for Comercial-MS in the Campeonato Sul-Mato-Grossense (Brazil).

name: Jeferson da Costa Silva
description: Jeferson da Costa Silva (born May 3, 1990 in Nova Iguaçu) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Vasco da Gama.

name: Jeff Adrien
