name: Jonathan Hamm
description: Jonathan Hamm {{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=|size=|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}}StatisticsReal name Jonathan HammNickname(s) Beauty SalonRated at 255 poundsHeight 6–7Nationality AmericanBorn October 14 1985Atlanta, GeorgiaStance OrthodoxBoxing recordTotal fights 42Wins 40Losses 2 Jonathan Hamm is a former standout amateur boxer,currently undefeated professional boxer, actor and a former professional football player. Hamm was the #1 Super-Heavyweight Amateur boxer in the United States in 2011 after winning the 2011 U.S. Nationals. Hamm was an alternate in the super-heavyweight division of the 2012 London Olympic Games for the U.S. Hamm earned Black College All-American, 1st Team All Conference, 1st Team All-Region and The Marion E. Jackson Defensive Player of the Year in 2006. Hamm is originally from Atlanta, Georgia but now lives and trains in Carson, California at the Rock Gym.

name: Jonathan Hartley
description: Jonathan Samuel Hartley (born 8 January 1960) is a former English cricketer. Hartley was a left-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Burnley, Lancashire. Hartley made his debut for Oxfordshire in the 1989 Minor Counties Championship against Buckinghamshire. Hartley played Minor counties cricket for Oxfordshire from 1989 to 1994, which included 43 Minor Counties Championship matches and 11 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his List A debut against Gloucestershire in the 1989 NatWest Trophy. He played 5 further List A matches, the last coming against Glamorgan in the 1993 NatWest Trophy. In his 6 List A matches, he scored 99 runs at a batting average of 19.80, with a high score of 46. With the ball he took 6 wickets at a bowling average of 33.66, with best figures of 2/48. He had previously played Second XI and Minor counties cricket for the Lancashire Second XI from 1979 to 1982, later playing for the Warwickshire Second XI in 1986.

name: Jonathan Himebauch
description: Jonathan Himebauch (born August 13, 1975, in Greenwich, Connecticut) is a former professional gridiron football offensive lineman in the Canadian Football League, XFL, and NFL Europe. Currently, he serves as the offensive coordinator for the Toronto Argonauts of the CFL. Jonathan Himebauch is currently an offensive line coach at Wake Forest University.

name: Jonathan Hood
description: Jonathan Hood (born December 23, 1985 in Mississauga, Ontario) is a professional Canadian football defensive back for the Toronto Argonauts of the Canadian Football League.

name: Jonathan Howard
description: Jonathan Howard is a footballer who played in The Football League for Chesterfield and Rotherham United and was part of the Chesterfield FC side which enjoyed a famous FA Cup run during the 1996-97 football campaign.

name: Jonathan Iilahti
description: Jonathan Iilahti is a Finnish professional ice hockey goaltender who currently plays for Espoo Blues of the SM-liiga. He belonged to the same Espoo Blues junior ice hockey program as current KalPa goaltender Mikko Koskinen and the up-and-coming Erno Suomalainen; becoming more than just a benchwarmer in European ice hockey. Iliahti would go on to be drafted 39th overall by the Vancouver Giants in the 2011 CHL Import Draft. However, he chose to remain in Finland.

name: Jonathan Johansson (ice hockey)
description: Jonathan Johansson (born June 30, 1991) is a Swedish professional ice hockey centre, currently playing for Mora IK of the HockeyAllsvenskan, the second highest-level league in Sweden.

name: Jonathan Justin
description: Jonathan Justin is a Mauritian-French footballer who is currently a free agent.

name: Jonathan Kodjia
description: Jonathan Kodjia (born 22 October 1989) is a striker currently playing for French club AS Cherbourg Football, on loan from Stade Reims.

name: Jonathan Lindsay
description: Jonathan Lindsay is a professional footballer currently playing for Stalybridge Celtic.

name: Jonathan Lucroy
description: Jonathan Charles Lucroy (born June 13, 1986) is a Major League Baseball catcher for the Milwaukee Brewers.

name: Jonathan Maicelo
description: Jonathan Maicelo Román (born October 1983) is a male professional boxer from Callao, Peru. On 2009-09-06 he became the first Peruvian boxer to ever enter World Ranking. He is now the holder of Latin American lightweight title. Silver medalist: Bolivarian Games (Ambato, ECUADOR 2001)/ Silver medalist: Pre-Panamerican Tournament (Tijuana, MEXICO 2003)/ Quarter Finalist: Panamerican Games (Santo Domingo, DOMINICAN REP. 2003)/ Semifinalist: Pre-Olympic Tournament (Rio de Janeiro, BRAZIL 2004)

name: Jonathan Malo
description: Jonathan Joseph Malo (born September 29, 1983) is a Canadian professional baseball shortstop. Malo currently plays for the Québec Capitales of the Canadian-American Association. Malo has also competed for the Canadian national baseball team.

name: Jonathan Martins Pereira
description: Jonathan Martins Pereira (born 30 January 1986 in Bayonne) is a French football defender who currently plays for En Avant de Guingamp.

name: Jonathan Massaquoi
description: Jonathan Massaquoi (born May 11, 1988) is an American football defensive end for the Atlanta Falcons of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Troy. He was considered one of the best linebacker prospects for the 2012 NFL Draft.

name: Jonathan Miles (cricketer)
description: Jonathan Samuel Miles (born 21 February 1986) is an English cricketer. Miles is a right-handed batsman who bowls left-arm medium pace. He was born at Sutton Coldfield, Warwickshire. Miles made his debut for Lincolnshire in the 2005 Minor Counties Championship against Cambridgeshire. He played Minor counties cricket for Lincolnshire from 2005 to 2007, making 14 Minor Counties Championship and six MCCA Knockout Trophy appearances. He joined the MCC Young Cricketers programme in 2008, and in that same season he made his List A debut for the Marylebone Cricket Club against Bangladesh A at The Racecourse, Durham. In Bangladesh A's innings, he took the wickets of Tamim Iqbal and Nazimuddin, finishing with figures of 2/44 from nine overs. The 2010 season saw Miles play for Norfolk, with him making four appearances for the county in that seasons Minor Counties Championship. In that same season he also signed for the Unicorns team which would take part in the 2010 Clydesdale Bank 40, a team formed of players without current full-time contracts with one of the regular first-class counties. He made his List A debut for the team against Sussex. Miles has made twelve further List A appearances for the team, the last of which came against Gloucestershire in the 2011 Clydesdale Bank 40. In his thirteen appearances for the Unicorns, he has taken a total of 10 wickets at an average of 53.10, with best figures of 3/49.

name: Jonathan Morley
description: Jonathan Bell Morley (29 January 1884 – 1957) was an English professional footballer who played as a winger.

name: Jonathan Newell
description: Jonathan James Newell (born 30 September 1978) is a former English cricketer. Newell was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm off break. He was born at Crawley, Sussex. Newell represented the Sussex Cricket Board in a single List A match against Hertfordshire in the 1999 NatWest Trophy. In 2005, he joined Buckinghamshire. He made his debut in the Minor Counties Championship against Staffordshire. From 2005 to 2007, he represented the county in 15 Championship matches, the last of which came against Hertfordshire. Newell also represented the county in the MCCA Knockout Trophy, where he played 3 matches for the county between 2005 and 2006 against Wiltshire, Cambridgeshire and Hertfordshire.

name: Jonathan O'Callaghan
description: Jonathan O'Callaghan is an Irish sportsperson. He plays hurling with his local club Castletownroche and was a member of the Cork senior inter-county team from 2004 until 2005. He missed the final of the 2004 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship because of a broken cheekbone.

name: Jonathan Pérez
description: Jonathan Pérez (born June 18, 1987 in Clamart) is a footballer, who currently plays for SO Chambéry Foot.

name: Jonathan Peña
description: Jonathan Peña (born December 22, 1973) is a Puerto Rican fencer. He competed in the individual épée event at the 2000 Summer Olympics.

name: Jonathan Perkins
description: Jonathan Roy Perkins (born 9 October 1976) is a former English cricketer. Perkins was a right-handed batsman. He was born at Reading, Berkshire. Perkins made his Minor Counties Championship debut for Berkshire in 1998 against Cheshire. From 1998 to 2005, he represented the county in 22 Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which came in the 2005 Championship when Berkshire played Oxfordshire. Perkins also played in the MCCA Knockout Trophy for Berkshire. His debut in that competition came in 2001 when Berkshire played Dorset. From 2001 to 2006, he represented the county in 10 Trophy matches, the last of which came when Berkshire played Dorset in the 2006 MCCA Knockout Trophy. Additionally, he also played List-A matches for Berkshire. His List-A debut for the county came against Lincolnshire in the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was played in 2001. From 2001 to 2005, he represented the county in 4 matches, with his final List-A match coming when Berkshire played Gloucestershire in 2005 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy at Sonning Lane, Reading. In his 4 matches, he scored 36 runs at a batting average of 9.00, with a high score of 22. In 2008, he represented Buckinghamshire in 3 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches against Lincolnshire, Cambridgeshire and Dorset.

name: Jonathan Rebolledo
description: Jonathan Eduardo Rebolledo Ardiles (born 22 October 1991) is a Chilean footballer that currently plays for Primera División club Deportes Iquique as a striker.

name: Jonathan Robertson
description: Jonathan Robertson (born 29 May 1991) is a Dutch professional footballer who plays for FC Oss. He formerly played two seasons for Almere City.

name: Jonathan Roy
description: Jonathan Roy (born January 5, 1980) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing in Switzerland with EHC Basel of the NLB.

name: Jonathan Ruffin
description: Jonathan Ruffin (born August 1, 1981) is an American football placekicker who the Arena Football League. He played college football for the University of Cincinnati, and was recognized as an All-American and the nation's best college placekicker. He was signed by the Pittsburgh Steelers as an undrafted free agent in 2003, and he has played professionally for the Berlin Thunder of NFL Europe. He is currently a free agent.

name: Jonathan Salt
description: Jonathan David Salt (born 6 January 1991) is an English cricketer. Salt is a right-handed batsman, but his bowling style is unknown. He was born in Chester, Cheshire and was educated at Poole Grammar School. While studying for his degree in Law at Durham University, Salt made his first-class debut for Durham MCCU against Yorkshire in 2011. In his only first-class match to date, Salt claimed a single wicket, that of Gary Ballance, for the cost of 93 runs in the match.

name: Jonathan Schoop
description: Jonathan Jesus Schoop (born October 16, 1991) is a Dutch baseball player and infielder in the Baltimore Orioles organization.

name: Jonathan Ship
description: Jonathan Andrew Ship (born 23 April 1981) is an English cricketer. Ship is a left-handed batsman. He was born at West Bromwich, Staffordshire. Ship represented the Warwickshire Cricket Board in a single List A match against Cumberland in the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2001 at St George's Road, Millom. In his only List A match, he scored 5 runs. He currently plays club cricket for Sutton Coldfield Cricket Club.

name: Jonathan Singleton (baseball)
description: Jonathan L. Singleton (born September 18, 1991) is a first baseman in the Houston Astros organization.

name: Jonathan St. Pierre
description: Jonathan St-Pierre was a professional Canadian football offensive lineman who is currently retired. He was drafted by the Saskatchewan Roughriders in the second round of the 2008 CFL Draft. St-Pierre played college football for the Illinois State Redbirds. He was traded to the Toronto Argonauts on January 6, 2010, for non-import wide receiver Obed Cétoute. On September 5, 2012, St-Pierre was released by the Toronto Argonauts. On September 25 he signed onto the practice roster of the Calgary Stampeders. St-Pierre retired from professional football on January 30, 2013.

name: Jonathan Tennenbaum
description: Jonathan "Jonny" Tennenbaum is an Argentine-Israeli professional association football player currently contracted to Hapoel Afula.

name: Jonathan Top
description: Jonathan Top (born January 26, 1993) is an American and Guatemalan soccer player who currently plays for FC Dallas in Major League Soccer.

name: Jonathan Toto
description: Jonathan Toto (born 30 March 1990) is a French footballer of Cameroonian heritage, who is a striker currently playing for Greek side Doxa Drama. Toto began his career in Cameroon with Canon Yaoundé before moving to Italy to sign for A.C. Legnano. After they were wound up, Toto moved to Scotland to sign as an amateur for Greenock Morton before being quickly released. He moved to Singapore with Etoile FC in 2011 and then to under-23 side Courts Young Lions.

name: Jonathan Trower
description: Jonathan Trower (born 12 June 1979) is an English cricketer. Trower is a right-handed batsman who bowls leg break. He was born in Sheffield, Yorkshire. Trower made his debut for Lincolnshire in the 2000 Minor Counties Championship against Cumberland. Trower played Minor counties cricket for Lincolnshire from 2000 to 2007, which included 41 Minor Counties Championship matches and 15 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his List A debut against Cheshire in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. He played 9 further List A matches for Lincolnshire, the last coming against Glamorgan in the 2004 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 10 matches, he scored 219 runs at an average of 24.33. He scored 2 half centuries, with a high score of 76 against Berkshire in the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. Leaving Lincolnshire at the end of the 2007 season, Trower has since gone on to play Minor counties cricket for Berkshire in 2008 and Norfolk in 2009.

name: Jonathan Vitale
description: Jonathan Vitale (born 11 March 1981 in Canton) is an American rugby union prop. He is a member of the United States national rugby union team and participated with the squad at the 2007 Rugby World Cup.

name: Jonathan Walford
description: Jonathan Edwin Peter Walford (born 24 January 1982) is an English cricketer. Walford is a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Hornchurch, Essex. Walford made his debut for Bedfordshire in the 2004 Minor Counties Championship against Staffordshire. Walford played Minor counties cricket for Bedfordshire from 2004 to 2009, which included 11 Minor Counties Championship matches and 11 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his only List A appearance against Sussex in the 2005 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In this match, he scored 27 runs before being dismissed by James Kirtley. He has also played Second XI cricket for the Essex, Kent, Nottinghamshire, Worcestershire and Leicestershire Second XI's.

name: Jonathan Waterhouse
description: Jonathan Arthur Waterhouse (born 11 April 1965) is a former English cricketer. Waterhouse was a right-handed batsman. He was born in Leek, Staffordshire. Waterhouse made his debut for Staffordshire in the 1985 Minor Counties Championship against Northumberland. Waterhouse played Minor counties cricket for Staffordshire from 1985 to 1997, which included 52 Minor Counties Championship matches and 4 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1988, he made his List A debut against Surrey in the NatWest Trophy. He played 2 further List A matches for Staffordshire, against Hampshire in the 1993 NatWest Trophy and Derbyshire in the 1996 NatWest Trophy. In his 3 matches, he scored 76 runs at an average of 25.33. He made a single half century, which came against Surrey, with Waterhouse making 52.

name: Jonathan Wilkinson
description: Jonathan Wilkinson was an English footballer who played in The Football League for Accrington.

name: Jonathan Wisniewski
description: Jonathan Wisniewski (born July 16, 1985 in Albi) is a French rugby union fly-half, currently playing for the Top 14 team Racing Métro.

name: Jonathan de León
description: Jonathan Horacio de León Ochoa (born June 22, 1987) is a Mexican footballer who plays for Queretaro F.C. in the Liga MX.

name: Jonathon Benn
description: Jonathon Andrew Benn (born 24 June 1967) is a former English cricketer. Benn was a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born in Rawtenstall, Lancashire. Benn made his debut for Northumberland in the 1989 MCCA Knockout Trophy against Lincolnshire. Benn played Minor counties cricket for Northumberland from 1989 to 2002, which included 43 Minor Counties Championship matches and 7 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his only List A appearance against Yorkshire in the 1992 NatWest Trophy. He opened the batting in this match, scoring a single run before being dismissed by Darren Gough.

name: Jonathon Charlesworth
description: Jonathon Charlesworth is an Australian field hockey player. He is a medical doctor. In field hockey, he plays in the midfield and wears a white headband. He played for the WA Thundersticks in the Australian Hockey League, winning a championship with the team in 2008. He joined the Kookaburras in 2009, where he was coached by his father Ric Charlesworth. He is trying to earn a spot on the national team that will represent Australia at the 2012 Summer Olympics.

name: Jonathon Harvey
description: Jonathon David Harvey (born 18 December 1969) is a former English cricketer. Harvey was a right-handed batsman who played primarily as a wicketkeeper. He was born at Burnley, Lancashire. Harvey made his debut in County Cricket for Durham in the 1991 Minor Counties Championship against Northumberland. He played one further Championship match for the county in that season against Norfolk. At the end of the 1991 season, Durham were elevated to first-class status and Harvey's services were no longer required. In 1992, he joined Hertfordshire, making his debut for the county in the Minor Counties Championship against Bedfordshire. From 1992 to 1993, he represented the county in 7 Championship matches, the last of which came against Cambridgeshire. In 1993, he represented the county in 2 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches against Bedfordshire and Staffordshire, as well as playing his debut List A match against Gloucestershire in the 1993 NatWest Trophy. Harvey later represented the Lancashire Cricket Board in 2 List A matches against the Netherlands in the 1999 NatWest Trophy and the Yorkshire Cricket Board in the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his total of 3 List A matches, he scored 39 runs at a batting average of 13.00, with a high score of 20. Behind the stumps he took 3 catches. His brother, Mark, played first-class cricket for Lancashire.

name: Jones Awuah
description: Jones Awuah (born 7 October 1983) is a Ghanaian association football player.

name: Jones Leandro
description: Jones Leandro Souza da Silva (born April 29, 1984) is a Brazilian footballer who plays as a forward for Nova Iguaçu.

name: Jong Il-Gwan
description: Jong Il-Gwan in North Korea is a footballer who plays as a Striker. He currently plays for Rimyongsu in the DPR Korea League and the North Korea national football team. On 24 November 2010 he was crowned AFC Youth Player of the Year. On 5 June 2012 numerous reports surfaced linking the player with a move to Newcastle United with later reports strongly linking him with FK Partizan and PSV Eindhoven.

name: Joni Töykkälä
description: Joni Töykkälä is a Finnish professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for HIFK of the SM-liiga.

name: Jonis Khoris
description: Jonis Khoris (born 15 March 1989) is an Italian footballer of Moroccan descent who plays for HinterReggio.

name: Jonne Virtanen
description: Jonne Virtanen is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who currently plays for JYP of the SM-liiga.

name: Jonny Godsmark
description: Jonathan "Jonny" Godsmark (born 3 September 1989) is an English footballer who currently plays for Ashington.

name: Jonny Hughes
description: Jonathan 'Jonny' Adam Hughes (born 12 September 1985) is an English cricketer. Hughes is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium-fast. He was born in Slough, Berkshire. Hughes made his debut for Buckinghamshire in the 2003 MCCA Knockout Trophy against Wiltshire. His next Minor counties appearance for Buckinghamshire didn't come until 2008, when he played a further Tropy match against Cambridgeshire. He played a single Minor Counties Championship match in 2008 against Norfolk. Hughes made his first-class debut for Loughborough UCCE against Somerset in 2007. He played a further five first-class fixtures spread over 2007 and 2008, the last coming against Worcestershire. In his six first-class matches he scored 149 runs at a batting average of 21.28, with a high score of 45. With the ball he took 7 wickets at a bowling average of 34.14, with best figures 3/33.

name: Jonny Lomax
description: Jonathan "Jonny" Lomax (born 4 September 1990) is a professional rugby league player who plays for St Helens in the engage Super League. A versatile player, Lomax is primarily a stand-off but is equally as comfortable at scrum-half, but featured more regularly on the wing in the early stages of his professional career. He signed for Saints from amateur club Orrell St James in 2007. In 2009 - his first season with the St Helens first team - he was handed the number 30 jersey, and made eight appearances, scoring three tries. In 2010, he was handed the number 24 jersey and in 2011, the number 20 jersey. Lomax has impressed at scrum-half with his committed displays and following the departure of Kyle Eastmond to Bath rugby union, wears the number 7 jersey in the 2012 season. Possessing an excellent combination of speed, footwork and skill he has proved to be a key attacking threat for the club. His ability in defense is also a notable attribute.

name: Jono Jenkins
description: Jono Jenkins is a rugby union footballer. He plays for the RC Narbonne in Pro D2 having previously represented the Waratahs. His regular playing position is openside flanker. Jenkins was educated at Saint Ignatius' College, Riverview in Sydney. He made his senior debut for the Force during the 2010 Super 14 season against the Reds.

name: Jonte Green
description: Jonte Green (born July 19, 1989) is an American football cornerback for the Detroit Lions of the National Football League (NFL). He was selected in the sixth round, 196th overall, by the Lions in the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at New Mexico State.

name: Joo Hyun-Jae
description: Joo Hyun-Jae (Hangul: 주현재; born 26 May 1989) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a defender for Incheon United in the K-League.

name: Joo Ki-Hwan
description: Joo Ki-Hwan is a South Korean footballer playing currently for PSPS Pekanbaru.

name: Joo Sung-Hwan
description: Joo Sung-Hwan (Hangul: 주성환; born 24 August 1990) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a striker for Chunnam Dragons in the K-League.

name: Jooce Suwarimbo
description: Jooce Suwarimbo (born 22 May 1942) is a former Indonesian tennis player. She is also sometimes referred to as Yoce or Jo Suwarimbo, or Tri Soewarimbo Yolanda. In 1961, she reached the finals in the doubles competition of the Indonesian Championships, partnered by Vonny Djoa. They lost to the Japanese pair of Akiko Fukui and Reoko Miyagi, 6-3 3-6 6-2. In April 1962, she and partner Mien Suhadi won the doubles competition of the Jakarta Raya Championships, beating Vonny Djoa and Liem in the final, 6-1 6-4. She lost the singles final to Suhadi, 4-6 7-5 7-5. Later in that year they reached the final of another Jakarta tournament, losing the final to the Australian pair of Faye Toyne and Val Wicks, 6-0 8-6. At the 1962 Asian Games in Jakarta, Suwarimbo won two medals: the bronze medal in the Women's Doubles with partner Suhadi, and the bronze medal in the Mixed Doubles with partner Sofiyan Mudjirat.

name: Joonas Hurri
description: Joonas Hurri (born March 31, 1991) is a Finnish professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for Pelicans of the SM-liiga.

name: Joonas Järvinen
description: Joonas Järvinen is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for TPS of the SM-liiga. He signed a contract as an unrestricted free agent with Nashville Predators for the 2012-13 season.

name: Joonas Kuusela
description: Joonas Kuusela is a Finnish professional ice hockey goaltender who currently plays for Pelicans of the SM-liiga.

name: Joonas Liimatainen
description: Joonas Liimatainen (born July 4, 1991) is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who played with Tappara in the SM-liiga during the 2010-11 season.

name: Joonas Pöntinen
description: Joonas Pöntinen (born 19 March 1990) is a Finnish football player currently playing for KuPS.

name: Joonas Vaino
description: Joonas Vaino is an Estonian professional basketball player. He is currently playing for Finnish club Namika Lahti at the power forward position.

name: Joop Kasteel
description: Joop Kasteel, also known as 'de zwarte parel' (the black pearl, born 27 August 1964, Amersfoort) is a former Dutch mixed martial artist. Kasteel made his mixed martial arts debut on 15 June 1996. He is a veteran of the RINGS promotion and as he has fought the majority of his fights for them. His trainers were, Chris Dolman, Hans Nijman and Michel van Halderen he also stated he trained with "Dirty" Bob Schrijber. As a former bodybuilder he went into the MMA world & became one of the most popular Dutch fighters noted for his power and physique, normally weighing in at around 265 lbs.

name: Joop Pelser
description: Joop Pelser (17 March 1892 – 27 July 1974) was a Dutch footballer who played for Ajax. His brothers Jan, Adriaan and Fons were also all footballers for Ajax, as was his son Harry. Another son, also named Jan, joined the Waffen-SS during World War II, and Pelser, his wife, and three sons all joined the Nationaal-Socialistische Beweging.

name: Joost Ebergen
description: Joost Ebergen (born 2 June 1990) is a Dutch footballer who currently plays for Dutch club FC Oss coming from N.E.C..

name: Jorbison Reis dos Santos
description: Jorbison Reis dos Santos, also known simply as Jorbison (born December 30, 1991 in Camaçari), is a Brazilian football left back. He came through the Flamengo youth system and has started playing the professional team in 2009, despite still playing in the youth team. He currently plays for Corinthians Alagoano.

name: Jordan Bendfeld
description: Jordan Bendfeld (born February 9, 1988) is a Canadian ice hockey defenceman.

name: Jordan Burrow
description: Jordan Burrow (born 12 September 1992) is an English footballer who plays as a forward for Morecambe in Football League Two.

name: Jordan Cameron
description: Jordan Cameron (born August 8, 1988) is an American football tight end for the Cleveland Browns of the National Football League. He played college football at the University of Southern California.

name: Jordan Clark
description: Jordan Clark (born 14 October 1990) is an English cricketer. Clark is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace and who occasionally fields as a wicket-keeper. He was born in Whitehaven, Cumbria and was educated at Sedbergh School. Clark made his debut for Cumberland in the 2007 Minor Counties Championship against Norfolk. The following season he played two further matches in that competition, against Buckinghamshire and Cumberland. Clark joined Lancashire's Academy in 2008; after two years in the Academy, he was given a scholarship with Lancashire in January 2010. Having represented the Lancashire Second XI in since 2008, Clark made his debut for Lancashire in Lancashire's last List A match in the 2010 Clydesdale Bank 40 against Worcestershire. He scored 32 runs before being dismissed by Jack Shantry. In the winter of 2010/11 Clark suffered a stress fracture to the back. At the start of the 2011 season, Clark's scholarship was renewed and in June he made his Twenty20 debut. He scored 19 runs from 11 balls as Lancashire tied with Derbyshire. In October Clark signed his first full-time professional contract with Lancashire.

name: Jordan Clark (footballer)
description: Jordan Clark (born 22 September 1993) is an English professional footballer who plays for Chesterfield, on loan from Barnsley, as a striker.

name: Jordan Cook
description: Jordan Alan Cook (born 20 March 1990) is an English professional footballer, who plays as a striker for Yeovil Town on loan from Charlton Athletic.

name: Jordan Copp
description: Jordan Lee Copp (born 29 September 1993) is an English footballer who plays as a midfielder for Truro City. Born in Saltash, he made one appearance for the first team of Plymouth Argyle in the League Cup in August 2011.

name: Jordan Davis
description: Jordan Davis (born January 21, 1983 in Salt Lake City, Utah) is an American soccer player.

name: Jordan Evans
description: Jordan Evans (born October 25, 1987 in Chester, Virginia) is an American soccer player who most recently played for Richmond Kickers in the USL Second Division.

name: Jordan Faucher
description: Sadek Jordan Faucher (born 6 November 1991 in Créteil) is a French football player of Algerian descent. He currently plays for Belgian Second Division club Antwerp

name: Jordan Garcia-Calvete
description: Jordan Garcia-Calvete (born 6 May 1992) is a Belgian-born Spanish footballer currently playing for De Graafschap in the Dutch Eredivisie, on loan from Belgian Pro League club R.S.C. Anderlecht. He plays as an attacking midfielder. Despite being born in Brussels, Garcia-Calvete holds a Spanish passport.

name: Jordan Gavin
description: Jordan Gavin (born 22 September 1982) is an Australian ice hockey and inline hockey player who plays for the Canberra Knights in the Australian Ice Hockey League. He is a member of the Australian national ice hockey team and Australian national inline hockey team.

name: Jordan Graye
description: Jordan Cameron Graye (born June 15, 1987 in Washington, D. C) is an American soccer player who currently plays for Carolina RailHawks in the North American Soccer League.

name: Jordan Hulls
description: Jordan Hulls (born April 16, 1990) is a senior basketball player for the Indiana Hoosiers men's basketball team at Indiana University. Hulls is considered one of the country's best shooters and uses extreme preparation, taking hundreds of shots each day, even on game days. His shot employs a quick and pure form with remarkably high accuracy.

name: Jordan Matechuk
description: Jordan Matechuk (born September 22, 1985 in Yorkton, Saskatchewan) is a professional Canadian football linebacker and long snapper for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers of the Canadian Football League. He played junior football for the Regina Thunder, Winnipeg Rifles and Victoria Rebels. He was signed by the Blue Bombers as an undrafted free agent in 2007. Matechuk was signed by the Hamilton Tiger-Cats in 2008 and was released before the 2011 season after spending three seasons with the club. On February 14, 2012, Matechuk once again signed with the Winnipeg Blue Bombers.

name: Jordan Mein
description: Jordan Mein (born October 10, 1989) is a Canadian mixed martial artist. He currently fights in the welterweight division of the Ultimate Fighting Championship.

name: Jordan Morrison
description: Jordan Morrison (born June 4, 1986) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the San Francisco Bulls in the ECHL. He was selected by the Pittsburgh Penguins in the 7th round (222nd overall) of the 2004 NHL Entry Draft. On August 7, 2012, Morrison signed for the Bulls after returning from a European season in Austria and Norway with EC KAC and Lillehammer IK respectively.

name: Jordan Mustoe
description: Jordan David Mustoe (born 28 January 1991) is an English football defender who plays for Carlisle United on loan from Wigan Athletic as a left back.

name: Jordan Nobbs
description: Jordan Nobbs (born 8 December 1992) is an English footballer who wears the number eight shirt for Arsenal Ladies. She is a combative, goalscoring central midfielder. She has represented the England women's national football team and youth and senior level. She is nicknamed Nobber by her England team–mates.

name: Jordan Pacheco
description: Jordan Patrick Pacheco (born January 30, 1986) is a right-handed Major League Baseball infielder and catcher for the Colorado Rockies. Prior to playing professionally, Pacheco attended La Cueva High School and then University of New Mexico, where he played from 2005 to 2007. In 2005, he hit .408 with 15 home runs and 52 RBI in 52 games, Freshman 2nd team All-America and Mountain West Conference All-Star honors. In 2005, he played with the Northwoods League La Crosse Loggers where he hit .287 with a team Leading 13 2B's. He played in 62 of the possible 64 games that summer. In 2006, he hit .351 with 11 stolen bases in 59 games with the University of New Mexico, once again earning a spot on the Mountain West Conference All-Star team. He also played for the Yarmouth-Dennis Red Sox of the Cape Cod League that year, hitting .190 in 42 games and posting a 1.35 ERA in four relief appearances. In 2007 he hit .397 in 55 games, once again being named a West Conference All-Star and earning Mountain West Conference Player of the Year honors. He was drafted in the ninth round of the 2007 amateur draft and began his professional career that season. Pacheco split his first professional season between the Casper Rockies and Tri-City Dust Devils, hitting a combined .287 with 64 hits in 62 games. In 2008, he played for the Dust Devils and hit .280 in 54 games. He hit .323 with 13 home runs, 79 RBI and 12 stolen bases for the Asheville Tourists in 2009 and was named a South Atlantic League All-Star as well as the South Atlantic League Most Valuable Player. In 2010, he played for the Modesto Nuts and Tulsa Drillers, hitting a combined .323 in 125 games, walking 60 times while striking out only 44 times. He was a California League All-Star that season. In 2011 he made his Major League debut with the Colorado Rockies on September 6 against the Arizona Diamondbacks. He went 2 for 4 with 2 RBI, although he did commit a throwing error.

name: Jordan Pugh
description: Jordan Alexander Pugh (born January 29, 1988) is an American football safety for the Washington Redskins of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Texas A&M University. He was selected in the sixth round of the 2010 NFL Draft by the Carolina Panthers.

name: Jordan Robinson
description: Jordan Robinson is an English football defender who plays for Billingham Synthonia. Previously a youth team player at Middlesbrough, he signed for Wigan in 2010, and made his first-team debut in an FA Cup match against Hull City on 8 January 2011. In September 2012, Robinson signed for Northern League side Billingham Synthonia, and made his debut on the 29 September against Shildon.

name: Jordan Rose
description: Jordan Rose (born 22 November 1989) is an English footballer who plays as a defender for Alfreton Town on loan from A.F.C. Telford United.

name: Jordan Ross
description: Jordan Ross is a professional rugby league footballer, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Keighley Cougars, Rochdale Hornets, and York City Knights, as a Second-row.

name: Jordan Schafer
description: Jordan James Schafer (born September 4, 1986) is a Major League Baseball center fielder for the Atlanta Braves.

name: Jordan Schmaltz
description: Jordan Schmaltz (born October 8, 1993) is an American ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing for the North Dakota Fighting Sioux men's ice hockey team which competes in NCAA's Division I in the Western Collegiate Hockey Association conference. Schmaltz came to the University of North Dakota after playing in the USHL with the Green Bay Gamblers where he won the 2012 Clark and Anderson Cups. He also received the honors of first team USHL. In 2011 he was traded to Green Bay from Sioux City where he was named to the 2010-11 USHL All-Rookie Team and also to the USHL First All-Star Team. Schmaltz was a member of the gold medal winning USA team at the 2010 World Junior A Challenge. Schmaltz was drafted 25th overall by the St. Louis Blues in the 2012 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Jordan Sisco
description: Jordan Christopher Sisco (born February 24, 1988) is a professional Canadian football wide receiver for the Saskatchewan Roughriders of the Canadian Football League.

name: Jordan Szwarz
description: Jordan Szwarz (born May 14, 1991) is a Canadian ice hockey player with the Portland Pirates of the American Hockey League. He was selected by the Phoenix Coyotes in the 4th round (97th overall) of the 2009 NHL Entry Draft. Szwarz Played for the Saginaw Spirit of the Ontario Hockey League from 2007-2011 and became the team’s third all-time leading scorer with 204 career OHL points. He made his professional debut with the San Antonio Rampage in the 2009-10 season.

name: Jordan Tait
description: Jordan Tait is a former professional footballer who played in The Football League for Darlington and Oldham Athletic. He also played in Scotland for Arbroath, Ross County, Ayr United, St Johnstone and his hometown club Berwick Rangers

name: Jordan Taylor
description: Jordan Taylor (born October 24, 1988) was a 3 time 2nd Team All-American right-handed pitcher for the Michigan Wolverines softball team from 2008-2011 and is currently on the U.S. Women's Futures national softball team.

name: Jordan Taylor (basketball)
description: Jordan Taylor (born September 30, 1989) is an American basketball player, currently playing for Virtus Roma of the Italian League.

name: Jordan Todman
description: Jordan Todman (born February 24, 1990) is an American football running back for the Jacksonville Jaguars of the National Football League. He played college football with the University of Connecticut Huskies. He finished his collegiate career third on the Huskies all-time rushing list before being drafted with the 183rd overall pick by the San Diego Chargers in the sixth round of the 2011 NFL Draft.

name: Jordan Veretout
description: Jordan Veretout (born 1 March 1993 in Ancenis) is a French footballer who plays for French club Nantes in Ligue 2. He plays as a midfielder. Veretout made his professional debut on 13 May 2011 in a league match against Sedan. He made his first start the following season in the team's opening match of the campaign; a 1–0 extra time win over Reims in the Coupe de la Ligue. Veretout is a France youth international having represented his nation at under-18 and under-19 level.

name: Jordan Webb
description: Jordan Webb (born 24 March 1988) is a Canadian professional soccer player who plays for S. League club Home United, as a winger.

name: Jordan Willis (footballer)
description: Jordan Kenneth Willis (born 24 August 1994) is an English football player. He is a defender who currently plays for Football League One team Coventry City.

name: Jordany Valdespin
description: Jordany V. Valdespin (born December 23, 1987) is a Major League Baseball Utility Player for the New York Mets.

name: Jordi Benet
description: Jordi Benet (born 15 July 1980) is an Andorran football player. He has played for Andorra national team.

name: Jordi Hoogstrate
description: Jordi Hoogstrate (born 2 June 1983) is a retired Dutch footballer who played as a midfielder. Hoogstrate started his career in 2001 with FC Groningen and was named a talented midfielder. He followed his former teammate Arjen Robben on a 3 million Euro transfer to PSV Eindhoven summer 2003. At PSV Hoogstrate suffered with serious knee injuries. He only played five matches for PSV. He was on loan at FC Emmen for two periods but suffered again with knee injuries. In 2008, when his contract in Eindhoven was expired, he rejoined FC Groningen and would start in the reserve squad. In July, in a match with Jong FC Groningen, he got seriously injured on his knee once again. He ended his career in March 2009 and started to coach in the FC Groningen youth academy. Hoogstrate also played for the Netherlands national under-21 football team.

name: Jordi Murphy
description: Jordi Murphy (born 22 April 1991) is Spanish born Irish rugby player, who plays as a flanker. He is registered to Lansdowne RFC and plays for provincial and Pro 12 League side Leinster.

name: Jordi Rubio
description: Jordi Rubio (born 1 November 1987) is an Andorran international footballer who plays for Santa Coloma, as a defender.

name: Jordi Tarrés (footballer)
description: Jordi Tarrés Páramo (alternately Jorge Tarrés Páramo, Chinese: 佐迪; born 16 March 1981 in Barcelona) is a Spanish footballer who plays for Kitchee SC in the Hong Kong First Division League, as a forward.

name: Jordie Benn
description: Jordie Benn (born July 26, 1987 in Victoria, British Columbia) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the Dallas Stars in the National Hockey League. He is the brother of Dallas Stars forward Jamie Benn. On January 3, 2012, Benn made his NHL debut against the Detroit Red Wings, playing alongside his younger brother Jamie. Both Benn brothers assisted on a goal by Loui Eriksson, which was the first career NHL point for Benn. On March 23, 2013, Benn scored his first career NHL goal against Semyon Varlamov of the Colorado Avalanche.

name: Jordy Croux
description: Jordy Croux (born 15 January 1994) is a Belgian footballer who currently plays as a defender for Racing Genk in the Belgian Pro League.

name: Jordy Mercer
description: Jordan "Jordy" J. Mercer (born August 27, 1986) is a professional baseball shortstop for the Pittsburgh Pirates of Major League Baseball (MLB). Prior to beginning his professional career, he played college baseball for Oklahoma State University. He has also competed for the United States national baseball team in international competition. Mercer bats and throws right-handed.

name: Jordy van Deelen
description: Jordy van Deelen (born 29 June 1993) is a Dutch footballer who currently plays as a defender for Dutch Eerste Divisie club Excelsior.

name: Jordy van de Kracht
description: Jordy van der Kracht (born 3 June 1990 in Rheden) is a Dutch footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for De Graafschap. As of February 2012, he has remained an unused substitute in major matches.

name: Jore Trompet
description: Jore Trompet (born 30 July 1992) is a Belgian footballer who currently plays for SC Lokeren.

name: Jorge Antonio Ortíz
description: Jorge Antonio Ortíz (born June 1, 1984 in Concepción) is a Bolivian football defender. He currently plays for Blooming in the Liga de Fútbol Profesional Boliviano.

name: Jorge Barbosa de Lima
description: Jorge Barbosa (born 6 August 1979) is an Brazilian footballer who plays as a forward for C.S. Herediano in the Costa Rican Primera División.

name: Jorge Bardou
description: Jorge Bardou is a male former tennis player from Spain. Bardou represented his native country in the singles competition at the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles. He was eliminated in the second round there by Jakob Hlasek. Bardou's highest ranking in singles was World No. 173, which he reached on May 9, 1985. His highest doubles ranking was World No. 104, which he reached on April 14, 1986.

name: Jorge Bartual
description: Jorge Bartual Medina (born 18 August 1971 in Valencia) is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a goalkeeper.

name: Jorge Berrio
description: Jorge Berrio is a former Argentine association football defender who played five seasons in the North American Soccer League. In 1979, Berrio signed with the Memphis Rogues of the North American Soccer League. In the fall of 1980, he moved to the Jacksonville Tea Men and played the 1980-1981 NASL indoor season followed by two outdoor NASL seasons. In 1983, the Tea Men moved to the second division American Soccer League, winning the title. He then played one NASL indoor season with the Tulsa Roughnecks in 1983-1984. In 1984, Berrio played one last season with the Tea Men, this time in the United Soccer League.

name: Jorge Britto
description: Jorge Britto is a Brazilian professional mixed martial artist and Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu black belt, practitioner and instructor. He holds a Bachelor's degree in Physical Education, and is currently the head Jiu-Jitsu instructor at Toronto BJJ.

name: Jorge Caetano Rubens
description: Jorge Caetano Rubens (born 19 June 1941) is a Brazilian former footballer who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Jorge Cazulo
description: Jorge "Piqui" Cazulo (born 14 February 1982) is an Uruguayan footballer who plays for Torneo Descentralizado club Sporting Cristal. He can play as a central or attacking midfielder.

name: Jorge Chula
description: Jorge Miguel Feijoca Chula is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Moreirense F.C. on loan from Sporting Clube de Portugal mainly as a right winger.

name: Jorge Eduardo Álvarez
description: Jorge Eduardo Álvarez Guerrero is a Chilean footballer who plays as Midfielder / Winger for Curicó in the Chilean Primera División B. He is commonly known as Koke Álvarez.

name: Jorge Eduardo Márquez
description: Jorge Eduardo Márquez (born 1 March 1990), known as Jorge, is a Mexican footballer who plays for Puebla F.C. in Mexico, mainly as a Striker. He started off his football career at Atlético Lagunero who play in the Mexican second division. He was invited by Puebla FC to pre season camp on June 3, 2011 where he earned a spot in the first club's squad.

name: Jorge Filipe Monteiro
description: Jorge Filipe Monteiro dos Santos Lourenço, known as Monteiro (born 15 August 1988 in Porto), is a Portuguese footballer who plays for AEL Limassol in the Cypriot First Division, as a winger.

name: Jorge Fitch
description: Jorge Fitch is a former Mexican Major League Baseball who played for the Mexican clubs Tigres, Pericos de Puebla and Broncos de Reynosa in a 10 year span where he played 1,670 games with 1,676 hits and .272 batting lifetime average. He also played in the Mexican Pacific League with the clubs from Hermosillo, Obregón and Navojoa during a 9 year span. He started his managerial career in 1972 with Broncos de Reynosa and would later manage the Tecolotes de Nuevo Laredo, Pericos de Puebla and Alacranes de Durango. He managed 8 years finishing with a record of 829-421 playing 5 playoff series and winning 2 championships with Tecolotes de Nuevo Laredo in 1977 and with Angeles negros in 1979

name: Jorge Francisco Casanova
description: Jorge Francisco Casanova Canchila (born July 6, 1984) is a Venezuelan soccer midfielder who plays for Deportivo Táchira.

name: Jorge Franco
description: Jorge Franco (17 September 1923 – 26 August 1989) was a Portuguese fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: Jorge Huamán
description: Jorge Huamán (born 11 April 1977 in Callao) is a Peruvian footballer who plays as a defender for Sport Boys in the Peruvian First Division.

name: Jorge Ibarra
description: Jorge José Ibarra Sánchez is a Mexican footballer who plays as a Midfielder for Estudiantes de Altamira of Mexico.

name: Jorge Lino Romero
description: Jorge Lino Romero Santa Cruz (born 23 September 1937) is a Paraguayan football forward who played for Paraguay in the 1958 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Club Sol de América.

name: Jorge Luis Gabrich
description: Jorge Luis Gabrich (born October 14, 1963) was an Argentinian professional footballer who played in the 1983 FIFA World Youth Championship and won second place in the tournament he also received the Bronze Boot award for his performance.

name: Jorge Luiz Frello
description: Jorge Luiz Frello Filho known as Jorginho (born 20 December 1991) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Hellas Verona. He made his Serie B debut with Hellas Verona in the 2011/2012 season.

name: Jorge Luiz de Amorim Silva
description: Jorge Luiz de Amorim Silva (born 5 September 1979) is a Brazilian football player.

name: Jorge Manuel Lopes Silva
description: Jorge Manuel Lopes da Silva (born 23 June 1959 in Lisbon) is a Portuguese retired footballer who played as a striker.

name: Jorge Martín de San Pablo
description: Jorge Juan Martín de San Pablo Sánchez de Rojas, simply Jorge, is a Spanish footballer who plays as a central defender.

name: Jorge Mendoza
description: Jorge Mendoza (born 15 May 1989) is an Paraguayan international footballer who plays for Guaraní, as a midfielder.

name: Jorge Molino
description: Jorge Molino Baena (born 4 March 1988 in Madrid) is a Spanish footballer who plays for CF Fuenlabrada mainly as a second striker.

name: Jorge Neves
description: Jorge Filipe Pereira Neves (born 17 September 1987 in Fátima) is a Portuguese footballer who plays for C.D. Fátima as a midfielder.

name: Jorge Ortí Gracia
description: Jorge Ortí Gracia is a Spanish footballer who plays for Real Zaragoza B as a forward.

name: Jorge Páez, Jr.
description: Jorge Páez, Jr. is a Mexican professional boxer in the Welterweight division. He is the current WBC Youth Intercontinental Welterweight Champion. His brother is Welterweight prospect Azriel Páez and his father is the former WBO, IBF Champion Jorge Páez.

name: Jorge Pardon
description: Jorge Hernesto Pardon García (March 4, 1905 - December 19, 1977) was a Peruvian footballer who played for Peru at the 1930 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Sporting Cristal.

name: Jorge Pereira da Silva
description: Jorge Pereira da Silva (born 4 December 1985) is a Brazilian football player who currently plays for Kecskeméti TE located in Hungary, club that competes on the well-known Nemzeti Bajnokság I. Known by his football name "Jorginho". His brother is Ueslei.

name: Jorge Ramírez
description: Jorge Ramirez (born 25 May 1986 in Montevideo) is a Uruguayan football striker. He currently plays for Isidro Metapan. Ramírez began his career in 2008, playing for Club Atlético Progreso before transferring to Club Nacional de Fútbol the following year. In 2010, he signed with the Bolivian side Oriente Petrolero for one year.

name: Jorge Reyes Oregón
description: Jorge Reyes Oregón is a Mexican footballer who currently plays for Tiburones Rojos de Veracruz in the Ascenso MX.

name: Jorge Rolando
description: Jorge Rolando (born 14 November 1906, date of death unknown) was a Uruguayan fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Jorge Roque
description: Jorge Roque Vargas (born April 29, 1950 in Ponce, Puerto Rico) is a former Major League Baseball center fielder. Roque played for the St. Louis Cardinals from 1970 to 1972 and the Montreal Expos in 1973.

name: Jorge Salinas (footballer)
description: Jorge Martín Salinas (born 6 May 1992) is a Paraguayan football midfielder who currently plays for the Ekstraklasa club Legia Warsaw. He previously played for AS Trenčín.

name: Jorge Sarria
description: Jorge Sarria was a Peruvian fencer. He competed in the individual sabre event at the 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: Jorge Schwager
description: Jorge Osvaldo Schwager Navarrete is a Chilean footballer who currently plays for the Unión La Calera in the Primera División Chilena.

name: Jorge Sebastian Nunez
description: Jorge Sebastian Nunez (born December 10, 1986) is a former Argentine football player.

name: Jorge Silva (boxer)
description: Jorge Silva is a Mexican professional boxer in the Welterweight division.

name: Jorge Soler
description: Jorge Soler (born February 25, 1992 in Havana, Cuba) is a Cuban baseball outfielder. Soler played for the Cuban national baseball team in international competition. He defected from Cuba in 2011, seeking a career in MLB. After establishing his residency in Haiti, Soler signed a nine-year contract with the Chicago Cubs.

name: Jorgen Rogers
description: Jorgen Rogers (born 11 October 1967) is a New Zealand former rugby football player who played rugby league for the Manly-Warringah Sea Eagles.

name: Jorginho James
description: Jorginho James (born 7 July 1994) is a Jamaican international footballer who plays for Kingston College, as a midfielder.

name: Joris Jehan
description: Joris Jehan (born September 9, 1989 in Vénissieux) is a French football, who currently plays for Mont's D'Or Azergues Chasselay.

name: Jorrick Calvin
description: Jorrick Raydell Calvin (born July 17, 1987) is an American football cornerback who is currently a member of the Chicago Rush of the Arena Football League. He was drafted by the Arizona Cardinals in the sixth round of the 2010 NFL Draft. He played college football at Troy. He has also been a member of the Philadelphia Eagles.

name: Jorronie McLean
description: Jorronie McLean (born 27 August 1994) is a Caymanian footballer. He has represented the Cayman Islands during a World Cup qualifying match in 2011, aged 17.

name: José-Thierry Goron
description: José-Thierry Goron (born 1 April 1977) in Martinique is a footballer who plays as a Forward. He currently plays for Rivière-Pilote in the Martinique Championnat National and the Martinique national football team.

name: José Ángel Bueno Ortega
description: José Ángel Bueno Ortega (born 7 February 1991) is a Spanish footballer who plays for Pobla de Mafumet in the Spanish fourth division, as an attacking midfielder.

name: José Adolfo Valencia
description: José Adolfo Valencia Arrechea (born December 18, 1991 in Bogotá, Colombia) is a Colombian footballer currently playing for Portland Timbers in Major League Soccer.

name: José Alberto Mendoza Posas
description: José Alberto Mendoza Posas (born 21 July 1989 in Olanchito, Yoro, Honduras) is a Honduran footballer who play as goalkeeper for Marathón in the Honduran national league.

name: José Alejandro Rodríguez
description: José Alejandro Rodríguez is a Mexican professional boxer. He competes in the Lightweight division.

name: José Alfredo Barrera
description: José Alfredo Barrera (born October 2, 1983 in Bellflower, California) is a Mexican American professional boxer in the Welterweight division.

name: José Altuve
description: José Carlos Altuve (born May 6, 1990) is a Venezuelan professional baseball second baseman for the Houston Astros of Major League Baseball. Altuve made his major league debut in July 2011. He is currently the shortest active player in Major League Baseball at 5 feet 5 inches . Altuve's short stature has inspired an unofficial unit of measure, with baseball broadcasters asking "how many Altuves" a home run has traveled.

name: José Antonio Collado Herrera
description: José Antonio Collado Herrera is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for Rayo Vallecano B in Segunda División B, as a striker.

name: José Antonio Llamas
description: José Antonio Llamas Martínez is a Spanish footballer who plays for SD Huesca in Segunda División, as a right defender.

name: José Antonio Rodríguez López
description: José Antonio Rodríguez López is a former Spanish footballer. He played for Atlético de Madrid between 1960 and 1964, winning the Spanish Cup in 1960, 1961, and 1963, and the European Cup Winners Cup in 1962.

name: José Antonio Vélez
description: José Antonio Vélez Jiménez (born 16 September 1983), aka Ñoño, is a Spanish footballer who plays for Gimnàstic de Tarragona, as a striker or left back. His brother, Fran Vélez, is also a footballer.

name: José Artur de Melo Júnior
description: José Artur de Melo Jr. known as Juninho (literally little Júnior) (born 7 March 1987) is a Brazilian footballer who plays for Guarani (MG). He also known as Júnior until 2008.

name: José Balbino da Silva
description: José Balbino da Silva (born 23 March 1896 - deceased) was a Portuguese footballer who played as a forward.

name: José Bandeira
description: José Bandeira (born 13 October 1961) is a Portuguese fencer. He competed at the 1988 and 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: José Bokung
description: José Bokung Alogo (born 31 December 1987 in Ebebiyín), also known as Colin, is an Equatoguinean amateur football defender. He currently plays for Deportivo Mongomo in the Equatoguinean Premier League.

name: José Bravo
description: José Domínguez Bravo (18 November 1916 – 1993) was a Spanish footballer born in Ceuta, 18 November 1916. He played as a left winger, the first team he played for was SD Ceuta. He then played for Levante, SD Ceuta again, and Real Murcia. In 1940 he joined FC Barcelona in which he played until the 1947-48 season, a total of 196 games, scoring 88 goals in all competitions. With the Blaugrana he won La Liga in 1945 and 1948, in addition to the Copa del Rey in 1942. When he left the club he moved to Gimnàstic de Tarragona and thereafter SD Ceuta, where he retired in 1951. He played one match for the Spanish national team against France in Seville on 15 March 1942. Spain won by four to zero. However this was the only time he would represent La furia roja.

name: José Carlos Martins Ferreira
description: José Carlos Martins Ferreira (born 2 August 1966 in Lisbon), known as José Carlos, is a Portuguese retired footballer who played as a right defender.

name: José Carlos dos Anjos Sávio
description: Savio Jose Carlos dos Anjos, better known as Zé Carlos (Criciúma, September 9, 1985), is a Brazilian footballer who acts as a goalkeeper. Currently playing for Paysandu.

name: José Casanova
description: José Casanova (died 8 December 1987) was a Peruvian international footballer who played as a midfielder. Casanova died in the 1987 Alianza Lima air disaster.

name: José Castro (fencer)
description: José Castro (born 14 March 1928) is a Portuguese fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1948 Summer Olympics.

name: José Cecena
description: José Isabel (Lugo) Cecena is a former Major League Baseball pitcher who played in 1988 with the Texas Rangers.

name: José Celaya
description: José Antonio Celaya (born November 3, 1981 in Salinas, California) is a Mexican American professional boxer in the Middleweight division and is the former WBO NABO Welterweight Champion.

name: José Cuero
description: José Cuero born in Bogotá, Colombia on March 30, 1990 is a football player, who plays for Millonarios in the Categoría Primera A, as a defender or midfield. Cuero is a product of the Millonarios youth system and played with the Millonarios first team since March, 2010.

name: José D'Andrea
description: José D'Andrea (born 26 November 1915) was an Argentine fencer. He competed at the 1948 and 1952 Summer Olympics.

name: José Duno
description: José Ricardo Duno (born 1977-03-19 in San Félix) is a Venezuelan football midfielder who made a total number of 12 appearances for the Venezuela national team between 1999 and 2000. He started his professional career at Nueva Cadiz Cumana.

name: José Eduardo da Silva Barbosa Alves
description: José Eduardo da Silva Barbosa Alves, known as José Eduardo, is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Akritas Chlorakas in the Cypriot Second Division, as a goalkeeper.

name: José Fernandes
description: José Fernandes (born 12 September 1934) is a Portuguese fencer. He competed in three events at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: José Fernando de Aguiar Jr.
description: José Fernando de Aguiar Júnior or simply Fernando (born November 17, 1991 in Porto Alegre), is a Brazilian defensive midfielder. He currently plays for Palmeiras.

name: José Ferreira
description: José Ferreira (born 7 May 1923) is a Portuguese fencer. He competed at the 1952 and 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: José Ferreira Pinto
description: José Fernando Ferreira Pinto (born 7 November 1939) is a former Portuguese footballer who played as a midfielder.

name: José Francisco Altur
description: José Francisco Altur (born 24 March 1968) is a former professional tennis player from Spain.

name: José Gavica
description: José Eduardo Gavica (born 8 January 1969) is a retired Ecuadorian football midfielder. He was a member of the Ecuador national football team for eleven years, and obtained a total number of 34 caps during his career.

name: José Gerardo Moreira Rocha Júnior
description: José Gerardo Rocha Moreira Junior, known as Junior Squads (Fortaleza, November 19, 1977) is a Brazilian footballer. Currently supports the Horizonte in the league of the state of Ceará, Campeonato Cearense.

name: José Germano de Sales
description: José Germano de Sales (25 March 1942 – 30 September 1998) was a Brazilian footballer.

name: José Gralha
description: José Maria Gralha (born 14 March 1905 - deceased) was a Portuguese footballer who played as forward.

name: José Guimarães (fencer)
description: José Guimarães (born 2 February 1965) is a Portuguese fencer. He competed in the individual foil event at the 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: José Hernández (tennis)
description: José Hernández (born March 13, 1990) is a professional male tennis player from the Dominican Republic. Hernández reached his highest individual ranking on the ATP Tour on January 28, 2013 when he became World number 556. Hernández is a member of the Dominican Republic Davis Cup team, having posted a 3–3 record in singles and a 2–0 record in doubles in seven ties played since 2006. Hernández has represented the Dominican Republic in multiple international competitions. Hernández partnered with countrywoman Chandra Capozzi in the mixed doubles competition at the 2010 Central American and Caribbean Games, winning the bronze medal. He also represented the Dominican Republic at the 2011 Pan American Games, though did not win any medals at the Games.

name: José Herrada
description: José Herrada Lopez (born 1 October 1985) is a Spanish professional road bicycle racer, who rides for UCI ProTeam Movistar Team. His brother Jesús is also a professional cyclist, and is a member of the Movistar Team, like his brother. Born in Mota del Cuervo, Herrada has been competing as a professional since the 2006 season, competing for the Viña Magna-Cropu, Contentpolis-Murcia and Caja Rural teams prior to joining the Movistar Team for the 2012 season. Herrada made his Grand Tour début at the 2012 Giro d'Italia; during the sixteenth stage, Herrada was part of the stage-long breakaway, and ended up finishing the stage in fifth place.

name: José Ilson dos Santos
description: José Ilson dos Santos (born 28 November 1975) is a Brazilian football player.

name: José Julián de la Fuente
description: José Julián de la Fuente (born 7 September 1903, date of death unknown) was a Uruguayan fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: José Julio Mendoza
description: José Julio Mendoza López is a professional Mexican boxer. He competes in the Lightweight division.

name: José Larduet
description: José Larduet Gómez (b. February 23, 1990 - Santiago de Cuba) is a Cuban amateur boxer best known for winning Light-Heavyweight Bronze at the 2009 World Amateur Boxing Championships. In November 2008 he won gold at the 2008 Youth World Amateur Boxing Championships. He added a Cuban Senior title in January 2009 (Playa Giron). At the 2009 World Amateur Boxing Championships he won Bronze after being edged by Russian favorite Artur Beterbiyev 6:10.

name: José Laverdecia
description: José Laverdecia (born 6 August 1960) is a Cuban fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1980 Summer Olympics.

name: José Loayza

name: José Luis Álvarez
description: José Luis Álvarez (born 22 January 1969) is a Spanish fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1992 Summer Olympics.

name: José Luis Jiménez
description: José Luis Jiménez Marín is a professional Chilean footballer who currently plays as a Forward for Universidad de Concepción.

name: José Luis Silva
description: José Luis Silva Araya is a Chilean footballer, who plays as midfielder for Kallithea.

name: José Luis Soto
description: José Luis Soto Quirós (13 September 1932 – 11 February 2006) was a Costa Rican football player, who played as a striker.

name: José Luis Vegar
description: José Luis Vegar Tebar is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a midfielder.

name: José Macotelo
description: José Macotelo (born July 12, 1985 in San José) is a Costa Rican footballer. He currently plays for Belén Siglo XXI.

name: José Manuel Brunet
description: José Manuel Brunet (born 2 May 1894) was an Argentine fencer. He competed in the individual sabre event at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: José Manuel Colmenero Crespo
description: José Manuel Colmenero Crespo, known as José Manuel, is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a right midfielder.

name: José Manuel Osório
description: José Manuel Osório is an undefeated Mexican professional boxer in the Super Featherweight division. Osório is promoted by current WBC Champion, Mexican Saúl Álvarez' company Canelo Promotions.

name: José Manuel Sánchez
description: José Manuel Sánchez Terrones is an undefeated Mexican professional boxer in the Flyweight division.

name: José Manuel Silva Oliveira
description: José Manuel Silva Oliveira (born 23 October 1990 in Braga), aka Zé Manuel, is a Portuguese footballer who plays for S.C. Braga B as a left winger.

name: José Manuel Velázquez

name: José Rodríguez (infielder)
description: José Rodríguez (February 23, 1894 – January 21, 1953), nicknamed "Joseíto" or "El Hombre Goma" in Spanish and "Joe" in English, was a Cuban infielder who played in Major League Baseball from 1916 to 1918 and in the Cuban League from 1914 to 1939. A defensive specialist, according to Roberto González Echevarría, Rodríguez "was considered the best defensive first baseman in Cuba" of his time. He was also a long-time manager in the Cuban League and managed for one season in the minors. He was inducted into the Cuban Baseball Hall of Fame in 1951. Rodríguez was born in Havana in 1894. His younger brother Oscar also became a baseball player and manager in the Cuban League and the minor leagues and joined José as a member of the Cuban Baseball Hall of Fame in 1960.

name: Joseph Birds
description: Joseph Birds (29 October 1887 – 28 April 1966) was an English professional footballer who played as a goalkeeper. Despite not being particularly tall for his position, he was described as extremely agile and a good shot-stopper. He started his career in non-league football with Macclesfield Town before moving to Football League Second Division side Stockport County in 1910. He played 15 league matches prior to the outbreak of the First World War. During the conflict, Birds played as a wartime guest for Manchester City. After the war, he made a further 22 league appearances for Stockport before moving to Third Division North outfit Nelson in the summer of 1922. Birds made his debut for Nelson on 26 August 1922 in the 2–6 defeat away to Bradford Park Avenue. The team conceded only 10 goals at home in the league all season as they achieved promotion to the Second Division in 1922–23. In a higher league, Birds found first team opportunities limited, playing four times at the start of the 1923–24 campaign before being replaced by former Portsmouth goalkeeper Harry Abbott. Birds left Nelson in the summer of 1924 and subsequently retired from professional football.

He kept cool and said the he would do his speaking in the ring. Joseph Kwadjo shocked the Australian boxing fraternity when he knocked out Jammie Pittman in the seventh round to capture the IBF Australasian super middleweight title at La Montage reception centre in Sydney, Australia. http://www. fijilive. com/sports/news/2010/04/09/14655. name: Joseph Marlow
description: Joseph Marlow (12 December 1854 – 8 June 1923) was an English cricketer who played 24 first class matches for Derbyshire between 1879 and 1886. Marlow was born at Bulwell, Nottinghamshire. In 1878 he played a match for Buxton against a touring Australia team, where he opened a 22-man batting line up scoring one and five, and took one wicket. He made his first class debut for Derbyshire in the 1879 season against Nottinghamshire in July, when he took three wickets. However he did not play for Derbyshire again until the 1883 season. In the 1883 season he played five matches for the county in which he took a respectable number of wickets, most notably against Sussex with 6 for 27 and another 4 to make a ten wicket match. His most successful season of 1884, saw him play twelve matches and take 34 wickets at 19.97. He took 5 for 43 against MCC, 5 for 31 against Kent which included a hatrick, 5 for 40 against Surrey and his career best of 7 for 46 against Yorkshire. He played four matches in the 1885 season and two in the 1886 season but did not show the same level of performance. A right-arm medium pace bowler, Marlow took 60 first class wickets at 20.61. His right-handed batting scored 317 runs in 45 first class innings at 7.92. Marlow umpired one match between his county and a touring Australian side in 1886. He also returned to Derbyshire for a non-first-class in 1890, struggling with both bat and ball. Marlow died at Bulwell at the age of 68.

name: Joseph Oosting

name: Joseph Paletta, Jr.

name: Joseph Plant
description: Hugh Joseph Plant (12 October 1907 – 30 August 1993) was an Australian first-class cricketer who represented Victoria in the Sheffield Shield during the 1930s. An Old Xaverian, Plant was initially an Australian rules footballer and played a senior match for Victorian Football League club Richmond in the 1925 VFL season. Richmond lost the fixture, which took place at the Melbourne Cricket Ground, to Melbourne by 39 points. He couldn't break into Richmond's team again and instead continued his football career at Coburg, where he played as a centre half back in their 1928 premiership side. When Plant made his first-class cricket debut in 1932, it was as a specialist off spinner. Playing against Tasmania at Launceston, Plant took career best figures of 6-43 as the island state collapsed from 2 for 128 to 171 all out. He then took perhaps the two biggest scalps of his career, Herbert Sutcliffe and Eddie Paynter, when Victoria played against the touring Marylebone Cricket Club at the MCG the following year. An all-rounder, Plant's batting peaked in the 1935/36 season when he made 395 runs at 39.50, including three of his four first-class half centuries. He put on a couple of notable performances early in the summer, starting with an innings of 64 against the Marylebone Cricket Club, who were touring Australia once more. Aside from reaching his then highest first-class score he also chipped in with a couple of wickets. His other memorable effort came against New South Wales at the MCG, where he scored 76 in his first innings and followed it up by having a hand in six dismissals when it was their opponent's turn to bat, two of them wickets and the other four catches. In 1936/37, his final season, Plant was a member of Victoria's Sheffield Shield winning team, having taken part in three matches during their campaign.

name: Joseph Pombo
description: Joseph Pombo is a rugby league player who currently plays for the Halswell Hornets in the Canterbury Rugby League. He is a Papua New Guinea international.

name: Joseph Rogers (Canadian football)
description: Joseph Rogers is a former all-star and award winning Canadian Football League wide receiver. After playing college football at Texas Southern Rogers had an all-star rookie season in 1996 with the Ottawa Rough Riders. His 73 catches, 1259 yards and 8 touchdowns won him the Frank M. Gibson Trophy as best rookie in the CFL East. Unfortunately, he never lived up to this fine performance over the next 3 seasons, playing for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers, Calgary Stampeders, Edmonton Eskimos and Winnipeg again, eventually retiring after 1999.

name: Joseph Shoosmith
description: Joseph Shoosmith (17 June 1859 – 9 April 1901) was an English cricketer. Shoosmith's batting and bowling styles are unknown. He was born at Kemp Town, Sussex. Shoosmith made a single first-class appearance for Sussex against Yorkshire at Bramall Lane, Sheffield in 1881. In Sussex's first-innings he was dismissed for 2 runs by Allen Hill. He took the wicket of Hill in Yorkshire's first-innings, finishing with figures of 1/23 from 16 overs. In Sussex's second-innings he ended unbeaten on 0, with Yorkshire going on to winning by 9 wickets. This was his only major appearance for Sussex. In 1881, he was shown in the Census as living with his parents at 2 Eastern Quadrant, Brighton. His father William was born at Lewes, Sussex and worked as a baker, muffin and crumpet maker. He was aged 46 in 1881. His mother Mary was born at Pembroke, Wales. He had four sisters, two of which were employed as teachers. He died at Brighton on 9 April 1901.

name: Joseph Thorley
description: Joseph James Thorley (7 Augusy 1894 – 26 December 1962) was an English cricketer. Thorley was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium. He was born in Fernham, Berkshire and he died in Marylebone, London.

name: Joseph Zerafa

name: Josephine Pucci

name: Josh Archibald (ice hockey)
description: Josh Archibald (born October 6, 1992) is a Canadian-born American ice hockey player. He is currently playing for the Nebraska–Omaha Mavericks men's ice hockey team which competes in NCAA's Division I in the Western Collegiate Hockey Association conference. Archibald was selected by the Pittsburgh Penguins in the 6th round (174th overall) of the 2011 NHL Entry Draft. Archibald came to the University of Nebraska-Omaha after playing high school hockey with Brainerd High School in Minnesota. Archibald was a finalist for the Minnesota Mr. Hockey Award in 2011.

name: Josh Ashton

name: Josh Atkinson
description: Joshua Whitehead "Josh" Atkinson (28 March 1902 – 1983) was an English footballer. He began his career with his hometown club Blackpool in 1923, but did not make any League appearances for the Seasiders. He joined Leeds United in 1924, and went on to make 52 League appearances for the club. Four years later, he joined Barnsley, for whom he scored his first League goals: two in 61 appearances. He joined Chester City in 1931, making seven League appearances, before finishing his career back on the Fylde coast with Fleetwood Town.

name: Josh Chapman
description: Josh Chapman (born June 10, 1989) is an American football nose tackle for the Indianapolis Colts. He attended the University of Alabama. Chapman served as the backup to All-American Terrence Cody during the 2008 and 2009 seasons, and was currently regarded as one of the better nose guard prospects in his class. Chapman appeared on the cover of the October 10, 2011 issue of Sports Illustrated after Alabama's 38-10 victory over Florida. The Colts signed him to a four-year, $2.3 million deal.
