description: James Gerald "Junior" Walsh (March 7, 1919 – November 12, 1990) was a Major League Baseball pitcher who played in 1946, and from 1948 to 1951 with the Pittsburgh Pirates. He batted and threw right-handed. He was born in Newark, New Jersey and died in Olyphant, Pennsylvania.

name: Junji Ikoma
description: Junji Ikoma is a Japanese mixed martial artist who competes in the strawweight and flyweight division. He has fought throughout his career exclusively for the Shooto organization and is currently a part of Shooto's provisional association. Ikowa is a former Shooto 114 pound Champion.

name: Junji Nishikawa
description: Junji Nishikawa (西川 潤之) is a former Japanese football player. He has played for Japan national team.

name: Juno Stover-Irwin
description: Juno Stover-Irwin (November 22, 1928 – July 2, 2011) was a four-time Olympic diver for the United States. Primarily a 10-meter platform performer, Irwin was a native of Los Angeles, California; she attended Hoover High School and Glendale Community College.

name: Juraj Šimboch
description: Juraj Šimboch (born January 30, 1992) is a Slovak ice hockey goaltender. He is currently playing with HK Nitra of the Slovak Extraliga. He participated at the 2012 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships as a member of the Slovakia men's national junior ice hockey team.

name: Juraj Dančík
description: Juraj Dančík (born 21 February 1982) is a Slovak football player currently playing for Podbeskidzie Bielsko-Biała.

name: Juraj Faith
description: Juraj Faith is a Slovakian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Juraj Halaj
description: Juraj Halaj is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Juraj Hovančík
description: Juraj Hovančík (born 22 November 1990) is a Slovak football midfielder who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club MFK Košice.

name: Juraj Križko
description: Juraj Križko (born 20 September 1985 in Ilava) is a Slovak football defender who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FK Senica.

name: Juraj Majdan
description: Juraj Majdan (born August 20, 1991) is a Slovak professional ice hockey player. He played with HC Litvínov in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season.

name: Juraj Pilát
description: Juraj Pilát (born 2 February 1992) is a Slovak football midfielder who currently plays for ŠKF Sereď, on loan from the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FC ViOn Zlaté Moravce.

name: Juraj Prokop
description: Juraj Prokop is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Juraj Zemko
description: Juraj Zemko is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Jurickson Profar
description: Jurickson Profar (born February 20, 1993) is a Major League Baseball shortstop for the Texas Rangers. He is listed as the top prospect in baseball.

name: Jurij Goličič
description: Jurij Goličič (born April 6, 1981) is a Slovenian ice hockey player. He participated at the 2003, 2005, 2006, and 2008 IIHF World Championships as a member of the Slovenia men's national ice hockey team.

name: Juris Umbraško
description: Juris Umbraško is a Latvian professional basketball player. He is currently playing for BC Rakvere Tarvas at the guard position.

name: Juron Criner
description: Juron Criner (born December 12, 1989) is an American football wide receiver with the Oakland Raiders. A Las Vegas, Nevada, native, Criner attended Canyon Springs High School and played his college ball at the University of Arizona.

name: Jushar Haschja
description: Jushar Haschja (born 19 September 1926) is an Indonesian fencer. He competed in the individual sabre event at the 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Jussi Aalto
description: Jussi Aalto (born 28 July 1983) is a Finnish footballer who represents FF Jaro of Veikkausliiga.

name: Jussi Halme
description: Jussi Halme is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for Tappara of the SM-liiga.

name: Jussi Näppilä
description: Jussi Näppilä (born June 15, 1987, Finland) is a Finnish footballer, who represents Ikurin Vire in the Kutonen.

name: Jussi Pelli
description: Jussi Pelli (born 4 November 1954) is a Finnish modern pentathlete and fencer. He fenced at the 1976 Summer Olympics and competed in the modern pentathlon at the 1976, 1980 and 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Jussi Pesonen (ice hockey)
description: Jussi Pesonen is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who currently plays for KalPa of the SM-liiga.

name: Jussi Tapio
description: Jussi Tapio is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for TPS of the SM-liiga.

name: Jussiville Partanen
description: Jussiville Partanen is a Finnish ice dancer. With partner Sara Aghai, he is the 2012 Finnish junior champion. They teamed up in 2011.

name: Justann Crawford
description: Justann Crawford is a retired Australian Olympic Boxer. Born and raised in Tasmania, Australia, Justann was trained by Lance Atkinson and Peter Stacey. He then moved to Sydney, NSW under the guidance of Pat Hailwood and Andrew Tatrai. Justann earned 9 international gold medals and represented Australia at the 1992, 1996 Olympic Games and 1994 Commonwealth Games. He also held 9 Australian boxing titles. Justann Crawford's amateur career was cut short because of an eye injury in 1998.

name: Justice Esono
description: Pablo Armando Esono Edjo (born 10 June 1986 in Malabo), better known as Justice, is an Equatoguinean football striker, who currently and playing for

name: Justin Ammar
description: Justin Ammar (born March 25, 1988 in St. Albert, Alberta) is a Canadian soccer player who currently plays for FC Edmonton in the North American Soccer League.

name: Justin Anderson (American football)
description: Justin K. Anderson (born April 15, 1988) is an American football guard for the Indianapolis Colts. He was selected in the seventh round, 208th overall, by the Colts in the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at Georgia.

name: Justin Astley
description: Justin Astley (born 20 May 1983) is an English professional snooker player. He played on Challenge Tour in 2001/02, and first qualified for the Main Tour in 2002/03, but lost his place. Then he played on Challenge Tour again from 2003 to 2005. He returned for the 2005/2006 season, but he couldn't defend his place. In the 2009/2010 season he reached the finals of the last two events of the International Open Series and was ranked seventh in the 2009/2010 PIOS rankings. As a result, Astley qualified for the 2010/2011 professional Main Tour.

name: Justin Bates
description: Justin Jonathon Bates (born 9 April 1976) is a former English cricketer. Bates was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm off break. He was born in Farnborough, Hampshire. Bates made his debut for Sussex in a List A match in the 1996 AXA Equity and Law League against Essex. The following season, he made his first-class debut for the county against Oxford University. He made twenty further first-class appearances for Sussex, the last of which came against Northamptonshire in the 2000 County Championship. In his twenty first-class matches, he scored 411 runs at an average of 13.70, with a high score of 57. This score, which was his only first-class fifty, came against Hampshire in 1999. With the ball, he took 49 wickets at a bowling average of 31.18, with best figures of 5/67. These figures, one of four five wicket hauls he took, came against Northamptonshire in 1998. Having made his List A debut in 1996, Bates would go on to make just seven further appearances in that format, the last of which came against Sri Lanka A in 1999. In his eight List A matches, he scored 47 runs at an average of 9.40, with a high score of 25 not out. With the ball, he took 3 wickets which came at an expensive average of 77.00, with best figures of 2/42. With him featuring on an infequent basis for Sussex, Bates also played for the Sussex Second XI, as well as for the Sussex Cricket Board in the 1998 MCCA Knockout Trophy. He left Sussex at the end of the 2000 season.

name: Justin Bernhardt
description: Justin Bernhardt (born February 25, 1988) is a Canadian ice hockey player who is currently playing for the San Antonio Rampage in the American Hockey League (AHL). On April 13, 2009, the Phoenix Coyotes signed Bernhardt to an entry level contract. On September 8, 2011, the Coyotes traded Bernhardt to the Florida Panthers in exchange for goaltender Marc Cheverie.

name: Justin Bourne
description: Justin Bourne (born December 12, 1982) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey player. He is currently The editor for thescore (backhand shelf)

name: Justin Bower
description: Justin Bower (born 23 May 1978) is a former professional tennis player from South Africa.

name: Justin Bowers
description: Justin Bowers (born March 20, 1985) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the Gwinnett Gladiators in the ECHL. During the 2010–11 season on December 31, 2010, Bowers was signed by the Portland Pirates to a professional tryout from the ECHL's Road Warriors. On July 26, 2012, Bowers signed to a one-year contract with the inaugural San Francisco Bulls of the ECHL. Prior to the 2012–13 season he was announced by the Bulls as their franchise first Captain on October 12th, 2012. Despite leading the Bulls and placing amongst the team leaders in scoring with 29 points in 37 games, Bowers was traded along with Sacha Guimond in a reshuffle by the Bulls to the Gwinnett Gladiators in exchange for three players on January 14, 2013.

name: Justin Brown
description: Justin O'Mara Brown (born April 16, 1982 in Fletcher, Oklahoma) is a professional American, Canadian football and arena football defensive end for the Edmonton Eskimos of the Canadian Football League. He was signed as an undrafted free agent by the Indianapolis Colts in 2005. He played college football for the East Central Tigers. Brown has also played for the Frankfurt Galaxy, Dallas Desperados, New Orleans VooDoo and Calgary Stampeders.

name: Justin Canale
description: Justin Canale (April 11, 1943 - October 11, 2011) was an American collegiate and Professional Football player who played offensive lineman for five seasons in the American Football League (AFL), for the Boston Patriots and Cincinnati Bengals. He also played with the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League, winning a Grey Cup championship in 1970. Canale came back to play two seasons for the Memphis Southmen of the World Football League. Justin Canale died on October 11, 2011 in Memphis, TN. He was one of five brothers who played college football at Mississippi State or at the University of Tennessee. His brother Whit Canale, also a former AFL player.

name: Justin Capicciotti
description: Justin Capicciotti is a gridiron football defensive lineman currently with the Edmonton Eskimos of the Canadian Football League. He has finished his college eligibility with the Simon Fraser Clan. He was selected 14h overall by the Edmonton Eskimos in the 2012 CFL Draft. He was ranked as the 13th best player in the Canadian Football League’s Amateur Scouting Bureau final rankings for players eligible in the 2012 CFL Draft. Capicciotti signed with the Eskimos on June 3, 2012.

name: Justin Cassel
description: Justin J. Cassel (born September 25, 1984 in Los Angeles, California) is an American professional baseball pitcher for the Somerset Patriots of the Atlantic League of Professional Baseball. Prior to beginning his professional career, he played college baseball at the University of California, Irvine. Cassel has also competed for the United States national baseball team.

name: Justin Cole
description: Justin Alexander Cole (born November 22, 1987) is an American football linebacker for the St. Louis Rams of the National Football League. He played college football at San Jose State where in 49 games recovered five fumbles and force another four.

name: Justin Conn
description: Justin Conn (born August 29, 1988) is a professional Canadian football linebacker who is currently playing with the BC Lions. He was drafted 47th overall by the Montreal Alouettes in the 2010 CFL Draft. He played college football for the Bishop's Gaiters.

name: Justin De Fratus
description: Justin Andrew De Fratus (born October 21, 1987) is a Major League Baseball pitcher for the Philadelphia Phillies.

name: Justin Downey
description: Justin Downey (born 11 November 1986) is a South African rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is flanker. He represents the Cheetahs in Super Rugby and the Griquas in the Currie Cup. He previously played for the Sharks.

name: Justin Eilers (footballer)
description: Justin Eilers (born 13 June 1988 in Braunschweig) is a Germany football forward.

name: Justin Engelke
description: Justin Marc Engelke (born 3 April 1976) is a former South African cricketer. Engelke was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium-fast. He was born in Cape Town, Cape Province and educated at Park Town Boys School and Rand Afrikaans University. Engelke made his first-class debut for Transvaal B against Eastern Province B in the 1996/97 UCB Bowl. He made three further first-class appearances for the team in that season, taking 7 wickets at an average of 35.85, with best figures of 2/30. His List debut came for Gauteng (formerly Transvaal) against Easterns in the 1997/98 Standard Bank League. He made sixteen further List A appearances for Gauteng, the last of which came against KwaZulu-Natal in the 1999/00 Standard Bank League. He took 19 wickets in his seventeen List A appearances for the province, which came at an average of 26.73, with best figures of 4/12. He also made a single first-class appearance for Gauteng against 	Griqualand West in the 1998/99 SuperSport Series. He took the wickets of Mickey Arthur and Pieter Barnard in this match, for the cost of 69 runs from 24 overs. In 2000, he played a single List A match in England for Hertfordshire in the 2000 NatWest Trophy against Cambridgeshire, taking the wickets of Simon Kellett, Nigel Gadsby and Ajaz Akhtar. His spell of 10 overs cost only 8 runs, with 8 of his 10 overs being maidens. Despite this, Hertfordshire lost the match by four wickets. Engelke didn't feature in any Minor counties fixtures for the county.

name: Justin Falk
description: Justin Falk is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman for the Minnesota Wild of the National Hockey League (NHL). He was a fourth round selection of the Wild, 110th overall, in the 2007 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Justin Greene
description: Justin Pierre Greene (born August 13, 1989) is an American basketball player, most recently playing for the NCAA Division I Kent State Golden Flashes. On May 20, 2008 Justin committed to attend Kent State University. In his freshmen season, Justin saw limited playing time only averaging 8.8 minutes per game and 2.2 points per game. Justin's minutes per game increased to 28.1 his sophomore season and his points per game also went up to 13.6 to go along 6.9 rebounds per game. In Justin's junior season, he averaged 15.4 points per game, 8.3 rebounds per game and 1.6 assists per game. This was good enough for him to recognized as the Mid-American Conference Men's Basketball Player of the Year.

name: Justin Hilton
description: Justin Hilton (born December 8, 1988) is an American football wide receiver on the Cincinnati Bengals of the National Football League (NFL). Hilton played college football at Indiana State. He is currently on the Practice Squad.

name: Justin Hodgman
description: Justin Hodgman (born June 27, 1988) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who currently plays for Metallurg Magnitogorsk in the Kontinental Hockey League. He was a 3 time Turner Cup champion with the Fort Wayne Komets in the IHL, and is the youngest player to ever win the playoff mvp award at age 19.

name: Justin Houston
description: Justin Houston (born January 21, 1989) is an American football linebacker for the Kansas City Chiefs of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football for the University of Georgia, and earned All-American honors. He was drafted in the third round of the 2011 NFL draft.

name: Justin James
description: Justin Duane James (born September 13, 1981) is an American professional baseball pitcher. He played in Major League Baseball for the Oakland Athletics in 2010. James attended the University of Missouri. He was drafted by the Boston Red Sox in the 6th round of the 2001 MLB Draft, but did not sign. He was selected again by the Toronto Blue Jays in the 5th round of the 2003 MLB Draft, and signed. In 2007, James was traded to the Cincinnati Reds. He played for the Reds organization in 2008, but became a minor league free agent. In 2009, James played for the Kansas City T-Bones of the independent Northern League. The Athletics purchased James' contract in June 2010. He received his first promotion to the major leagues on September 1, 2010, making his major league debut the following day. On November 2, 2010, James was claimed off waivers by the Milwaukee Brewers. He was outrighted to Triple-A on June 27, 2011.

name: Justin Keeler
description: Justin Keeler (born 17 April 1978) is an English footballer who played in The Football League for Bournemouth.

name: Justin Keller
description: Justin Keller (born March 4, 1986) is a Canadian professional ice hockey forward who is currently playing for the EHC Black Wings Linz in the Austrian Hockey League. He was selected by the Tampa Bay Lightning in the 8th round (245th overall) of the 2004 NHL Entry Draft. Prior to signing with Austria's EHC Black Wings Linz for the 2010-11 season, Keller had played 256 games in the American Hockey League with the Springfield Falcons and Norfolk Admirals.

name: Justin Manao
description: Justin Manao (born 25 March 1993) is an American Samoan international footballer who plays college soccer in the United States for PLU Lutes, as a defender.

name: Justin Martin
description: Justin Martin (born May 1, 1975) is an American former professional ice hockey player. He was selected by the Los Angeles Kings in the 7th round (172nd overall) of the 1993 NHL Entry Draft. Martin attended the University of Vermont where he played four seasons with the Vermont Catamounts during his college career. Martin began his profession career with the 1998–99 season, plying with the Birmingham Bulls of the ECHL. He concluded his career after playing the 2002–03 season in the Atlantic Coast Hockey League with the St. Pete/Winston-Salem Parrots.

name: Justin McNulty
description: Justin McNulty is an Irish Gaelic football manager and former player for Armagh. He played football with his local club Mullaghbawn Cúchullain's in Armagh and was a member of the Armagh senior football team from 1995 to 2005. He earned his first and only All-Ireland medal in 2002.

name: Justin Meram
description: Justin Meram (born December 4, 1988 in Shelby Township, Michigan) is an Assyrian -American soccer player currently playing for the Columbus Crew in Major League Soccer.

name: Justin Newell
description: Justin James Newell (born 8 February 1980 in Germany) is a British former professional footballer. He played in the Football League for Torquay United. Newwell joined Torquay as a trainee and made his debut on 27 September 1997 as a second-half substitute, for Tony Bedeau, as Torquay won 2-1 at home to Doncaster Rovers. He was released at the end of the season and joined the Army, playing football when possible. In 2000 he was playing for Newton Abbot Spurs and was still with them in March 2002.

name: Justin Palardy
description: Justin Palardy (born May 24, 1988 in Truro, Nova Scotia) is a professional Canadian football placekicker for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted 36th overall by the Hamilton Tiger-Cats in the 2010 CFL Draft and was used as a punter. After being released by the Tiger-Cats, he was signed by the Blue Bombers as their placekicker. In the 2010 season he set the Blue Bombers single season record for place-kicking accuracy with 86.7%. He played college football for the Saint Mary's Huskies

name: Justin Parrish
description: Justin Parrish (born May 10, 1984) is an American football player for the Jacksonville Sharks of the Arena Football League. He played as a defensive end and linebacker for Kent State University. He was signed as a free agent by the Jacksonville Sharks in 2010. Parrish attended a workout with the Washington Redskins in 2006, but did not make the team.

name: Justin Pender
description: Justin Pender (born October 25, 1988) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman. He is currently playing for the Bakersfield Condors in the ECHL. Prior to turning professional, Pender player major junior hockey in the Quebec Major Junior Hockey League with the Halifax Mooseheads. On November 15, 2011, the Bakersfield Condors claimed Pender off waivers after he was let go by the Toledo Walleye.

name: Justin Pitcher
description: Justin Eugene Pitcher (born 17 February 1987) is a Bermudian cricketer. Pitcher is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium-fast. He was born in Bermuda. In 2009, Pitcher made his debut for Bermuda in a first-class match against Namibia in the 2009-10 Intercontinental Shield at the Wanderers Cricket Ground, Windhoek. Following the match he made his List A debut against the same opponents, making two appearances in that format. The following year, Fray made a further List A appearance against the touring United Arab Emirates, at the National Stadium, Hamilton. He was selected as part of Bermuda's squad for the World Twenty20 Qualifier.

name: Justin Purll
description: Justin Purll is an Australian rugby union player for Union Bordeaux Bègles in the Top 14.

name: Justin Salas
description: Justin Salas (born March 13, 1982) is an American mixed martial artist who competes as a lightweight. He is currently signed with the Ultimate Fighting Championship.

name: Justin Sawyer
description: Justin Sawyer (born October 18, 1985) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who currently plays for the Rapid City Rush of the Central Hockey League.

name: Justin Schultz
description: Justin Schultz (born July 6, 1990) is a Canadian ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing with the Edmonton Oilers of the National Hockey League (NHL).

name: Justin Sellers
description: Justin Ryan Sellers (born February 1, 1986 in Bellflower, California) is a professional baseball infielder for the Los Angeles Dodgers. He is the son of former Boston Red Sox pitcher Jeff Sellers.

name: Justin Shaw
description: Justin Shaw (born September 23, 1982, in Victoria, British Columbia) was a Canadian football linebacker for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers. He was drafted by the BC Lions in the third round of the 2008 CFL Draft. He played CIS Football for the Manitoba Bisons.

name: Justin Soryal
description: Justin Soryal (born June 29, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey Forward who is currently playing with the Charlotte Checkers of the American Hockey League (AHL). He is known as an enforcer.

name: Justin Stein
description: Justin Marion Stein (August 9, 1911 – May 1, 1992) was an infielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Philadelphia Phillies and Cincinnati Reds.

name: Justin Trattou
description: Justin Trattou (born August 28, 1988) is an American football defensive end for the New York Giants of the National Football League (NFL). He was signed by the Giants as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football for the University of Florida.

name: Justin Turner (rugby union)
description: Justin Turner (born 12 March 1990) is an Australian rugby union footballer. His regular playing position is scrum-half. He currently represents the Western Force in Super Rugby. He made his debut for the franchise during the 2010 Super 14 season against the Stormers in Perth. Turner was a member of the Australia under 20 team that competed in the 2010 IRB Junior World Championship.

name: Justin Wilcox
description: Justin Wilcox (born March 12, 1979) is an American mixed martial artist. He is a former professional bodybuilder and a former NCAA Division I wrestler.

name: Justine Bouchard
description: Justine Bouchard (born January 12, 1986) is an Olympic freestyle wrestler for Canada from Calgary, Alberta. Bouchard won a gold medal at the 2010 Commonwealth Games.

name: Justine Lorton
description: Justine Joanna Lorton (born 11 March 1974) is an English footballer, and former England international player. A deep–lying forward player, Lorton enjoyed two spells at Arsenal Ladies as well as playing in Iceland and Sweden.

name: Justo Nguema
description: Justo Nguema Nchama (born 3 December 1988), known as Papu, is an Equatoguinean football midfielder, who plays for Sony de Elá Nguema in the Equatoguinean Premier League.

name: Justo Suárez
description: Justo Suárez (b. Buenos Aires, Argentina, January 5, 1909 - † Cosquín, Córdoba, Argentina, August 10, 1938), nicknamed "El Torito de Mataderos" ("The Little Bull of Mataderos)", was a popular Argentine light weight boxer. His huge popularity was widely greater than his professional achievements as a fighter. Suárez was the first sportsman that became an idol, having gained huge popularity in Argentina during the decade of the 1930s.

name: Justyn Cassell
description: Justyn Cassell (born 25 May 1967) is a former a rugby union player who played for a number of top tier English club sides but was also known as an excellent Rugby Sevens player and in this capacity was capped for England and was part of the team that won the 1993 Rugby World Cup Sevens.

name: Jusu Karvonen
description: Jusu Karvonen (born 17 January 1993) is a Finnish footballer, who currently plays for FC Haka on loan from Taranto Calcio.

name: Jutta Höhne
description: Jutta Höhne (born 26 March 1951) is a German fencer. She competed in the women's team foil event at the 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Juulia Turkkila
description: Juulia Turkkila (November 3, 1994) is a Finnish figure skater. She is the 2012 Nordic champion and a two-time (2012, 2013) Finnish silver medalist.

name: Juuso Akkanen
description: Juuso Akkanen (born December 22, 1983) is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who played with TPS in the SM-liiga during the 2010-11 season.

name: Juuso Honka
description: Juuso Honka (born March 11, 1990) is a Finnish professional ice hockey player who played with HPK in the SM-liiga during the 2010-11 season.

name: Juuso Ikonen
description: Juuso Ikonen (born January 3, 1995) is a Finnish ice hockey player currently playing for Espoo Blues. He played his first men's game in January 2012 and has been part of the team roster since. In the regular season he had four goals and five assists in 20 games. In the playoffs he had four goals and two assists in 15 games. His goals included one overtime game-winner. Ikonen has also been regular in national junior teams. He was selected to 2012 IIHF World U18 Championships. His father Juha Ikonen is former Blues captain and their all-time leading scorer.

name: Juuso Kaijomaa
description: Juuso Kaijomaa is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for SaiPa of the SM-liiga.

name: Juuso Rajala
description: Juuso Rajala is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for Espoo Blues of the SM-liiga. He also used to play for Lukko of the SM-liiga.

name: Juuso Salmi
description: Juuso Salmi (born July 15, 1991) is a Finnish ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing for the HIFK Helsinki of the SM-liiga.

name: Juuso Simpanen
description: Juuso Simpanen (born 8 June 1991) is a Finnish footballer currently playing for Finnish Veikkausliiga club FC Honka. After starting his career with local TiPS, young Simpanen moved to neighbours FC Honka, where he finished his football grooming and raised to the first team squad in 2010. Simpanen was part of the team that won the Finnish League Cup in the same year. He was awarded as man of the match in the final against JJK.

name: Juvitu da Silva
description: Juvitu Correia Da Silva or Juvitu (born January 27, 1987) is a football player. He is the current defender for the Timor-Leste national football team.

name: Juwan Simpson
description: Juwan Simpson (born Juwan Garth on July 8, 1984 in Decatur, Alabama) is a Canadian football linebacker for the Calgary Stampeders of the Canadian Football League. He was signed by the Green Bay Packers as an undrafted free agent in 2007. He played college football at Alabama.

name: Juzefas Jurgelevičius
description: Juzefas Jurgelevičius (1947 – 23 November 2009) was a former football player from Lithuania. Jurgelevičius was elected Lithuanian Footballer of the Year in 1969 and 1980.

name: Jyotsna Patel
description: Jyotsna Patel (also Jyotsana Patel) is a former Test cricketer who represented India. She was born in Indore, Madhya Pradesh and played two Test matches for India.

name: Károly Czanik
description: Károly Czanik (born 13 September 1984 in Komárno) is a Slovak football player who currently plays for Gyirmót SE.

name: Károly Fatér
description: Károly Fatér (born 9 April 1940 in Nyírlak) is a Hungarian footballer. He was born in Veszprém County. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City, where the won a gold medal with the Hungarian team.

name: Károly Graszl
description: Károly Graszl (born 8 January 1985 in Balatonlelle) is a Hungarian football player who currently plays for Cypriot side Nea Salamis Famagusta.

name: Kåre Björkstrand
description: Kåre Björkstrand (born 31 March 1987) is a Finnish footballer currently playing for Finnish Veikkausliiga club FF Jaro.

name: Kévin Bérigaud
description: Kévin Bérigaud (born 9 May 1988 in Thonon-les-Bains) is a French footballer who plays for French club Evian in Ligue 1. He plays as an striker and began his career playing for Swiss club Servette. Bérigaud joined Evian in 2006 and has since amassed over 100 appearances and scored over 30 goals for the club.

name: Kévin Diaz (footballer born 1983)
description: Kévin Diaz (born 11 April 1983) is a French professional footballer who plays for Dutch club Fortuna Sittard, as a striker.

name: Kévin Gomis
description: Kévin Mickael Junior Gomis (born 20 January 1989 in Paris) is a French professional footballer who plays for OGC Nice in Ligue 1, as a central defender.

name: Kévin Malcuit
description: Kévin Malcuit (born 31 July 1991) is a French professional footballer who plays as a striker for Étoile Fréjus Saint-Raphaël.

name: Kęstutis Smirnovas
description: Kestutis Smirnovas is a retired Lithuanian MMA fighter who fought in Pride Fighting Championships, RINGS, Shooto and HERO'S. He holds notable victories over Petras Markevicius and Hiromitsu Miura and also fought other renowned fighters as Kazushi Sakuraba and Yoshihiro Akiyama.

name: Kıvılcım Kaya
description: Kıvılcım Kaya (born March 27, 1992 in Ankara) is a Turkish female hammer thrower. She is the daughter of the former Turkish national wrestler Ziya Kaya. She began working with Artun Talay, who guided to Eşref Apak for Olympics bronze medal in Athens 2004. She made first big step to international scene at 2009 World Youth Championships in Athletics in Brixen, after took the silver medal in the girl's hammer throw competition. Then she broke national junior hammer record in Ankara with a 65.10 meter throw. Kaya, who is considering one of the Turkey's biggest medal hopes at throwing competitions in future major championships, hopes to get an Olympic medal in 2016 Rio de Janeiro. Kıvılcım throwed 72.55 m at Turkish Individual Athletics Championships.

name: K. Depan Sakwati
description: K. Depan Sakwati (born 17 October 1987) is a Malaysian football player, currently playing for Betaria FC.

name: K. J. Wright
description: Kenneth Bernard Wright, Jr. (born July 23, 1989) is an American football linebacker for the Seattle Seahawks of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Seahawks in the fourth round of the 2011 NFL Draft.

name: K. Sasi Kumar
description: K. Sasikumar (born 29 April 1989 in Johor Bahru) is a Malaysian footballer currently playing for Johor FA in Malaysia Premier League.

name: Kaarel Kiidron
description: Kaarel Kiidron (born 30 April 1990) is an Estonian international footballer who plays in Czech Republic for Viktoria Žižkov, as a defender.

name: Kabfah Boonmatoon
description: Kabfah Boonmatoon is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Chainat F.C. in the Thai Premier League. In November 2009 he was called up to the Thailand squad for the 2009 Southeast Asian Games.

name: Kabiru Alausa
description: Kabiru Alausa (born March 28, 1983 is an Nigeria football attacker, currently on the books of Shooting Stars F.C..

name: Kacem Slimani
description: Kacem Slimani (born 1948) is a Moroccan football defender who played for the Morocco in the 1970 FIFA World Cup. He also played for RS Settat. Also, Slimani was a municipal employee.

name: Kaci Sedkaoui
description: Kaci Sedkaoui (born July 4, 1986 in Draâ Ben Khedda) is an Algerian football player. He currently plays for JS Kabylie in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Kada Kechamli
description: Kada Kechamli (born January 12, 1978 in Oran) is an Algerian football player. He currently plays for MC Oran in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Kadeem Atkins
description: Kadeem Atkins (born 1992) is a Barbadian international footballer who plays for Barbados Defence Force, as a striker.

name: Kadima Mungusso
description: Kadima Mungusso (born August 17, 1981) is an Angolan football player. He has played for Angola national team.

name: Kadri Kordel
description: Kadri Kordel is a Turkish amateur boxer in the flyweight (51 kg) division. In 2005 he fought at the world amateur boxing championships in Mianyang, China in the under 48 kilogram division. He was beaten in the quarterfinals. He is currently a member of the Fenerbahçe Boxing squad. A native of Kütahya, he is coached by Muammer Sağlam.

name: Kael Mouillierat
description: Kael Mouillierat (born September 9, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing for the St John's IceCaps in the American Hockey League (AHL). Prior to turning professional, attended Minnesota State University, Mankato where he played four seasons in NCAA Division I with the Minnesota State Mavericks men's ice hockey team. On December 16, 2011, the Bridgeport Sound Tigers signed Mouillierat to a professional tryout agreement.

name: Kaetlyn Osmond
description: Kaetlyn Osmond (born December 5, 1995) is a Canadian figure skater. She is the 2012 Skate Canada champion, the 2012 Nebelhorn Trophy champion and the 2013 Canadian national champion.

name: Kafula Ngoie
description: Kafula Ngoie (born 11 November 1945) is a Congolese football midfielder who played for Zaire in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for TP Mazembe.

name: Kai Heerings
description: Kai Heerings (born 12 January 1990 in the Netherlands) is a Dutch football player who plays as a left back. He currently plays for FC Utrecht in the Eredivisie.

name: Kai Syväsalmi
description: Kai Syväsalmi is a Finnish professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for KalPa of the SM-liiga.

name: Kaia Parnaby
description: Kaia Parnaby is an Australian softball player from New South Wales. She is a pitcher, and earned a scholarship to and played for the Australian Institute of Sport. She is a member of the senior Australia women's national softball team and is on the short list to compete at the 2012 ISF XIII Women's World Championships. She plays university softball for the University of Hawaiʻi team.

name: Kaitlin Cochran
description: Kaitlin Elizabeth Cochran (born February 29, 1987 in Riverside, California) is an American softball player. She attended Rosary High School and Arizona State University. She plays Outfield. With United States women's national softball team she won 2011 World Cup of Softball.

name: Kaká (footballer born 1991)
description: David Leonel Faleiro (born 12 January 1991 in Sapucaia do Sul) is a Brazilian football midfielder who recently played for the Slovak 2. liga club MFK Zemplín Michalovce, on loan from FK Senica.

name: Kakhi Makharadze
description: Kakhi Makharadze (born 20 October 1987) is a Georgian footballer currently playing for Uzbek League club FC Pakhtakor Tashkent as a midfielder.

name: Kako Tomotaki
description: Kako Tomotaki is a Japanese figure skater. She won the silver medal at the 2010 Golden Spin of Zagreb.

name: Kalambay Otepa
description: Paul-Mohamed Kalambay Otepa (born 12 November 1948) is a Congolese football goalkeeper who played for Zaire in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for TP Mazembe.

name: Kaleb Canales
description: Kaleb Canales (born July 7, 1978) is an American basketball coach and a former interim head coach for the Portland Trail Blazers of the NBA.

name: Kaleb Cowart
description: Kaleb Cowart (born June 2, 1992 in Adel, Georgia) is a baseball player who won the Gatorade High School Baseball Player of the Year Award in 2010. Cowart was drafted by the Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim in the first round (eighteenth overall) in the 2010 Major League Baseball Draft out of Cook High School.

name: Kaley Fountain
description: Kaley Fountain (born July 1, 1988) is an American professional soccer player. She previously played for FC Gold Pride, Atlanta Beat, and Western New York Flash of Women's Professional Soccer and was a member of the United States U-20 women's national soccer team squad that won the 2008 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup.

name: Kaliesha West
description: Kaliesha West is a professional female boxer and the current WBO Female Bantamweight Boxing Champion. She was born on February 11, 1988, in South Haven, Michigan. West currently resides in Moreno Valley California, a small suburb between Riverside and Palm Springs. On September 18, 2010, West won the WBO title, becoming the first world boxing champion from the Inland Empire. Her father, Juan West, is her boxing trainer and manager.

name: Kalif Alhassan
description: Kalif Alhassan (born October 15, 1990 in Accra) is a Ghanaian footballer. He currently plays for Portland Timbers of Major League Soccer.

name: Kalifa Faifai Loa
description: Kalifa Faifai Loa (born 28 January 1990) is a New Zealand professional rugby league footballer for the North Queensland Cowboys of the National Rugby League. He primarily plays wing.

name: Kaliova Nauqe Tani
description: Kaliova Nauqe Tani is a Fijian rugby league player who represented his country in the 2008 World Cup. At the time he represented the Fassifern RLFC.

name: Kalle Johansson
description: For the Swedish orienteering competitor, see Karl Johansson. Kalle Johansson Born (1993-01-21) January 21, 1993 (age 20) Östersund, Sweden Height 5 ft 9 in Weight 159 lb Position Defence Shoots Left SuperElit team Brynäs IF NHL Draft, 2007 Playing career –present Kalle Johansson (born January 21, 1993) is a Swedish professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for Brynäs IF in the SuperElit.

name: Kalle Kauppi
description: Kalle Kauppi (born 6 May 1992) is a Finnish footballer currently playing for Finnish Veikkausliiga club FC Inter Turku.

name: Kalle Olsson
description: Kalle Olsson (born January 31, 1985) is a Swedish professional ice hockey player who currently plays for Linköpings HC in the Swedish Elitserien. Olsson was selected by the Edmonton Oilers in the fifth round, 147th overall, of the 2003 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Kaloyan Tsvetkov
description: Kaloyan Tsvetkov (born 21 October 1988) is a Bulgarian footballer, who plays as a midfielder for Svetkavitsa.

name: Kamal Bayramov
description: Kamal Bayramov (born 19 March 1993) is an Azerbaijani football goalkeeper playing currently for Khazar Lankaran.

name: Kamal Djunaedi
description: Kamal Djunaedi is an Indonesian footballer who plays for Persijap Jepara in the Indonesia Super League as a striker.

name: Kamal Kamyabinia
description: Kamaleddin Kamyabinia (born January 18, 1989) is an Iranian footballer who plays for Shahrdari Tabriz F.C. in the IPL.

name: Kamaliele Papani
description: Kamaliele Papani (born 8 April 1984) in Tonga is a footballer who plays as a Defensive midfielder. He currently plays for Lotoha'apai in the Tonga Major League and the Tonga national football team.

name: Kamarul Effandi Abdul Rahim
description: Kamarul Effandi Bin Abdul Rahim (born on 12 April 1987) is a Malaysian Football player who played as a goalkeeper.

name: Kamarulzaman Hassan
description: Kamarulzaman Hassan (born on 17 January 1979) is a former Malaysian footballer. He is a former member of the Malaysian national team. Currently he works as assistant coach and goalkeeping coach in the Suruhanjaya Perkhidmatan Awam FC football team.

name: Kambozia Jamali
description: Kambozia Jamali (9 July 1938 – 24 May 2010) was an Iranian football Midfielder who played for Iran in the 1964 Summer Olympics. He also played for Taj SC.

name: Kamdem Fotou Eric
description: Eric Fotou Kamdem (born 2 January 1986) is a Cameroon-born footballer who has played for the Thai side BEC Tero Sasana F.C. since February 2008.

name: Kamel Al-Mor
description: Kamel Omar Uthman Flata [كامل المر in Arabic] (born 18 July 1982) is a Saudi football player. He currently plays for Al Ahli.

name: Kamel Bouacida
description: Kamel Bouacida (born August 6, 1976) is an Algerian footballer. He has played for the Algeria national team.

name: Kamil Biliński
description: Kamil Biliński (born January 23, 1988 in Wrocław) is a Polish footballer who currently plays for VMFD Žalgiris Vilnius.

name: Kamil Drygas
description: Kamil Drygas (born September 7, 1991 in Poznań) is a Polish professional footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Zawisza Bydgoszcz, on loan from Lech Poznań.

name: Kamil Karaš
description: Kamil Karaš (born 1 March 1991) is a Slovak football midfielder who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club MFK Košice and the Slovakia national under-21 football team.

name: Kamil Kuzera
description: Kamil Kuzera (born March 11, 1983 in Kielce) is a Polish footballer who currently plays for Korona Kielce.

name: Kamil Mingazow
description: Kamil Mingazov (born 21 June 1968) is a former Turkmenistan footballer.

name: Kamil Nitkiewicz
description: Kamil Nitkiewicz (born May 7, 1987 in Milicz) is a Polish footballer who plays for Kolejarz Stróże.

name: Kamil Wenger
description: Kamil Wenger (born December 12, 1991 in Kluczbork) is a Polish footballer who currently plays for MKS Kluczbork, on loan from UKS SMS Łódź.

name: Kamilla Farhad
description: Kamilla Farhad  is an Azerbaijani tennis player.

name: Kamilla Składanowska
description: Kamilla Składanowska (12 January 1948 – 9 September 2010) was a Polish fencer. She competed at the 1968, 1972, 1976 and 1980 Summer Olympics.

name: Kaminieli Aria
description: Kaminieli Tako Aria (born at Nadi, Fiji; died circa 1967 in Fiji) was a Fijian cricketer. Aria made his first-class debut for Fiji in 1948 against Auckland during Fiji's tour of New Zealand. During the tour he played two further first-class matches against Otago and Auckland. In his 3 first-class matches for Fiji he scored 114 runs at a batting average of 19.00, with a high score of 46. With the ball he took 3 wickets at a bowling average of 44.66, with best figures of 3/66. Aria took 4 catches in the field. Aria also represented Fiji in 7 non first-class matches in 1948 during their tour of New Zealand. Aria's date of death is unknown, only that he died circa 1967.

name: Kamo Hovhannisyan
description: Kamo Hovhannisyan (Armenian: Կամո Հովհաննիսյան, born on 5 October 1992) is an Armenian football player who currently plays midfielder for the Armenian national team and for Armenian Premier League club Pyunik Yerevan.

name: Kamohelo Mokotjo
description: Kamohelo Mokotjo is a South African professional footballer who plays for Feyenoord. Mokotjo plays as a defensive midfielder.

name: Kamoliddin Murzoev
description: Kamoliddin Murzoev (born 17 February 1987) is an Uzbekistani professional footballer who currently plays for FC Bunyodkor. He plays in the position of forward.

name: Kamran Mahmood
description: Kamran Tariq Mahmood (born 20 January 1993) is a Danish cricketer. Mahmood is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm fast-medium. He was born at Århus, Århus County. Having represented Denmark at Under-19 level, Mahmood made his full debut for Denmark in the 2011 Nordic Cup against Finland, before playing in the European T20 Championship Division One which was held in Jersey and Guernsey. In March 2012, Denmark took part in the World Twenty20 Qualifier in the United Arab Emirates, having qualified for the event by winning the European T20 Championship. Mahmood was selected in Denmark's fourteen man squad for the qualifier, making his Twenty20 debut against Bermuda at the Sharjah Cricket Association Stadium. He made six further appearances during the competition, the last of which came against Hong Kong, with him scoring a total of 53 runs in the tournament at an average of 10.60, with a high score of 25 not out. His older brother, Rizwan, also plays for Denmark.

name: Kamran Sheeraz
description: Kamran Pasha Sheeraz (born 28 December 1973) is a former English cricketer. Sheeraz was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium-fast. He was born in Wellington, Shropshire. Sheeraz made his debut in county cricket for Bedfordshire against Suffolk in the 1992 MCCA Knockout Trophy. That season he also played 7 Minor Counties Championship matches. He later made his first-class debut for Gloucestershire against Northamptonshire in the 1994 County Championship. He made 12 further first-class appearances, the last of which came against Glamorgan in the 1997 County Championship. In his 13 first-class matches for the county, he took 27 wickets at an average of 40.88, with best figures of 6/67. These figures came against the touring West Indians in 1995, a match in which he also took 5/44 to give him is only 10 wicket haul in a match in his first-class career. He made his List A debut for Gloucestershire against Derbyshire in the 1994 AXA Equity & Law League. He made 19 further List A appearances for Gloucestershire, the last of which came against Pakistan A in 1997. In his 20 List A matches for the county, he took 13 wickets at an average of 50.07, with a best figures of 2/20. Following the end of the 1994 season, Sheeraz played for Rawalpindi B in Pakistan, making 2 List A appearances in the Willis Cup against Islamabad and United Bank Limited, taking 3 wickets in his 2 matches for the team. With opportunities limited at Gloucestershire, he returned to Bedfordshire in 1997, appearing in a single Minor Counties Championship match against Northumberland, before leaving Gloucestershire at the end of the 1998 season. In 1999, he joined Shropshire, making his debut for the county against the Hampshire Cricket Board in the 1999 NatWest Trophy, which was his only List A appearance for Shropshire. In this match he took the wicket of Andrew Perry for the cost of 38 runs from 10 overs, while with the bat he was run out for a duck. He went on to make 2 appearances in the 1999 MCCA Knockout Trophy against the Derbyshire Cricket Board and Cheshire, before making 3 Minor Counties Championship appearances. He made no further Minor counties or List A appearances for Shropshire after this season.

name: Kana Muramoto
description: Kana Muramoto is a Japanese figure skater. She is the 2011 Triglav Trophy silver medalist and the 2011 Crystal Skate of Romania bronze medalist. She is the younger sister of Satsuki Muramoto.

name: Kana Osafune
description: Kana Osafune is a Japanese football defender, currently playing for NTV Beleza in the L. League. She has been a member of the Japanese national team, and took part in the 2010 Asian Games, which Japan won. As an Under-19 international she played the 2008 U-20 World Cup.

name: Kane Douglas
description: Kane Douglas (born 1 June 1989) is an Australian rugby union footballer who currently plays for the New South Wales Waratahs in the international Super Rugby competition and the Wallabies as a lock. His brother is Gold Coast Titans rugby league player Luke Douglas. Douglas played his junior rugby with the Yamba Buccaneers, captaining the Under 17 team to a premiership in 2006. He was named to debut for the Australian Wallabies side to face Argentina on 17 September 2012.

name: Kane Ferdinand
description: Kane Ryan Ferdinand (born 7 October 1992) is a footballer who plays as a midfielder for Peterborough United in the Football League Championship.

name: Kane Hemmings
description: Kane Hemmings (born 8 April 1991) is an English association footballer who plays for Rangers as a striker.

name: Kane Richardson
description: Kane William Richardson (born 12 February 1991) is an Australian cricketer who plays First-class cricket for South Australia and Adelaide Strikers in the Big Bash League and has played for Australia U19s. He was bought for US$700,000 by the Pune Warriors India in the 2013 Indian Premier League auction. On the back of his strong performances for South Australia and the Adelaide Strikers, Richardson replaced the injured Mitchell Starc in the 2nd one day international against Sri Lanka on January 13, 2013, making his international debut. In his first One Day International he got a first ball duck lbw to Lasith Malinga and the fine figures of 6 overs 3 maidens, none for 15 runs when he was removed by umpire Marais Erasmus for repeatedly running on the pitch in his follow through.

name: Kang Chang-Gi
description: Kang Chang-Gi was a South Korean football midfielder who played for the South Korea in the 1954 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Seoul Army Club.

name: Kang Hyun-Su
description: Kang Hyun-Su (born July 16, 1984) is a North Korean football player.

name: Kanstantsin Lepin
description: Kanstantsin Lepin (Belarusian: Канстанцін Лепін; Russian: Константин Лепин; born 17 June 1988) is a Belarusian professional footballer. As of 2012, he plays for Vedrich-97 Rechytsa.

name: Kantapol Sompittayanurak
description: Kantapol Sompittayanurak is a Thai footballer. He currently plays for Thailand Division 1 League clubside Chanthaburi.

name: Kantemir Berkhamov
description: Kantemir Mikhailovich Berkhamov (Russian: Кантемир Михайлович Берхамов; born August 7, 1988 in Moscow) is a Russian footballer who plays for Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League on March 22, 2009 for PFC Spartak Nalchik in a game against FC Rubin Kazan.

name: Kapka Georgieva
description: Kapka Georgieva (later Panayotova, Bulgarian: Капка Георгиева, later Панайотова, born 30 September 1951) is a Bulgarian rower who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics. In 1976 she was the coxswain of the Bulgarian boat which won the silver medal in the coxed fours event.

name: Kaplan Khuako
description: Kaplan Zaurbechevich Khuako (Russian: Каплан Заурбечевич Хуако; born April 17, 1977) is a Russian professional footballer. In 2009, he played for FC Druzhba Maykop. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2007 for PFC Spartak Nalchik.

name: Kara Chesworth
description: Kara Jane Chesworth (née Francis, born 4 January 1972 in Portsmouth, England) is an English-born Welsh racing cyclist. She represented Wales at the 2010 Commonwealth Games. Chesworth took up cycling in 2005 in order to get fit, and first competed in a circuit race in Tywyn in 2007. She placed 8th in the 2010 British Women's road race championships, and won the British women's road race series.

name: Karamoko Kéïta
description: Karamoko Kéïta (born 21 September 1974) is a Malian international footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Harrow Borough in England.

name: Kardo Ploomipuu
description: Kardo Ploomipuu (born 24 March 1988 in Pärnu) is an Estonian swimmer. His first Paralympics was the 2004 Athens Games. He is the current IPC European record holder in 50 and 100 m backstroke (long course; S10).

name: Kareem Harris
description: Kareem Harris (born 6 January 1988 in Saint Kitts and Nevis) is an Kittian international footballer playing as a defender for Washington Archibald HS.

name: Kareem Huggins
description: Kareem Huggins (born May 24, 1986) is an American football running back who is currently a free agent. Huggings graduated from Bayley Ellard High School in New Jersey. He played college football at Hofstra University. Huggins was invited to the New York Jets' rookie mini-camp in 2009, but was not signed. He was later signed by the Tampa Bay Buccaneers as an undrafted free agent prior to the 2009 season. After his September release, Huggins was signed to the Buccaneers' practice squad, where he remained until his activation to the active roster for Week 16 in December. Huggins earned a backup running back spot in camp in 2010, but a week 6 knee injury against the New Orleans Saints ended his season, landing him on injured reserve. The severe knee injury led to the Buccaneers not tendering Huggins a contract for the 2011 season. Huggins was signed by the New England Patriots on August 4, 2012, after spending the 2011 season out of football. He was released the next day on August 5.

name: Kareem Mitchum
description: Kareem Mitchum (born 9 November 1989) is a Saint Kitts and Nevis international footballer who plays for Newtown United, as a defender.

name: Karel Hromas
description: Karel Hromas (born January 27, 1986) is a Czech professional ice hockey forward who currently plays in the Czech Extraliga with HC Sparta Praha. He was selected by the Chicago Blackhawks in the 4th round (123rd overall) of the 2004 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Karel Plášek
description: Karel Plášek (born October 16, 1973) is a Czech professional ice hockey player. He played with HC Plzeň in the Czech Extraliga during the 2010–11 Czech Extraliga season. Plášek previously played for HC Pardubice, HC Znojemští Orli and IHC Písek.

name: Karel Senecký
description: Karel Senecký is a Czech football forward who played for Czechoslovakia in the 1938 FIFA World Cup. He also played for AC Sparta Prague.

name: Karel Vosátka
description: Karel Vosátka (born November 20, 1929 in Plzeň) was a pairs figure skater who competed for Czechoslovakia. With partner Blažena Knittlová, he won the silver medal at the European Figure Skating Championships in 1948 and finished 16th at the 1948 Winter Olympics.

name: Karen Asatryan
description: Karen Asatryan (born 21 December 1974) is an Armenian football player. He has played for Armenia national team.

name: Karen Barbat
description: Karen Barbat (born July 3, 1992) is a professional Danish tennis player and member of the Denmark Fed Cup team. On September 20, 2010, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 474, whilst her highest doubles ranking was 395 on July 25, 2011.

name: Karen Castiblanco
description: Karen Emilia Castiblanco Duarte (born January 9, 1988) is a professional Colombian tennis player and member of the Colombia Fed Cup team. On August 24, 2009, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 414 whilst her best doubles ranking was 247 on July 11, 2011.

name: Karen Elizabeth Landaverde
description: Karen Elizabeth Landaverde Alfaro (born 16 December 1991 in San Salvador) is a Salvadoran football player currently playing for San Salvador of the Division 1 Féminine.

name: Karen Farrell
description: Karen Farrell is an Australian wheelchair basketball player, who won two silver medals at the Paralympic Games.

name: Karen Israelyan
description: Karen Israelyan is an Armenian professional football goalkeeper. He currently plays for Armenian Premier League club Pyunik Yerevan, is also a member Armenia national and U-21 teams.

name: Karen Le Comber
description: Karen Le Comber, is an international cricketer who played 15 ODIs for New Zealand. She represented Canterbury and Central Districts in domestic competitions. Le Comber is a right-hand batsman and a right-arm medium-fast bowler.

name: Karen Moreira
description: Karen Moreira Sánchez is a Spanish football midfielder, currently playing for FVPR El Olivo in Spain's Primera División.

name: Karen Oganyan
description: Karen Gennadyevich Oganyan (Russian: Карен Геннадьевич Оганян; born June 25, 1982) is a Russian professional footballer of Armenian ethnic origin, currently playing for FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok. His previous club was FC Alania Vladikavkaz in Russia. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2001 for FC Torpedo Moscow.

name: Karen Penglase
description: Karen Penglase (born 10 August 1982) is a Scottish female international football defender. She currently plays in the Scottish Women's Premier League for Rangers, having previously played for Kilmarnock, Hamilton Academical and Celtic. She has also played semi-professionally in Iceland with Grindavík and Keflavík. Penglase has represented the Scotland women's national football team at full international level.

name: Karen Price (cricketer)
description: Karen Price (née Hill, 7 May 1955 –) is a former New South Wales Breakers and Australia Women's cricketer. A right-handed batsman and right-arm fast-medium bowler, Price played List-A cricket for the Breakers between 1972 and 1987, and Test cricket from 1975 to 1985. Price was an all-rounder, with both a Test century and five-wicket haul to her name. She took 6/72 against India on 28 January 1984, and scored 104* in the following Test on 3 February. She was less successful with the bat in the one day game, scoring only 94 runs from 23 matches at 6.26, however she was as equal with the ball as she was in Tests: 29 wickets at 16.51.

name: Karen Straker
description: Karen Straker (born 1964) is a British equestrian. She was born in County Durham, England. She won a silver medal in team eventing at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul. She also competed at the 1992, 1996 and 2000 Olympics.

name: Karena Wihongi
description: Karena Wihongi (born 29 September 1979, in New Zealand) is a New Zealand rugby union footballer. He plays as a prop, and has "a reputation for powerful scrummaging courtesy of his hefty 19st 9lb, 6ft 1in frame. " He previously played his club rugby for the Aviva Premiership side Sale Sharks, to whom he was signed in 2010. He came from former French clubs Oyonnax Rugby and CS Bourgoin Jallieu; he is a French qualified player based on residency. The Sale Sharks' coach stated that "He was on my priority list as soon as I was appointed and was delighted when he signed on the dotted line. " He currently plays for Castres Olympique in the Top 14.

name: Kari Sihvonen
description: Kari Sihvonen is a Finnish professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for Pelicans of the SM-liiga.

name: Karim Allawi
description: Karim Mohammed Allawi (born 1 April 1960) is an Iraqi football midfielder who played for Iraq in the 1986 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Al-Rasheed Club.

name: Karim Bennoui
description: Karim Bennoui (born January 26, 1988), also known as "Le Chirurgien", is a French Muay Thai kickboxer, famous for his technical and precise fighting style. He is a former It's Showtime World Champion -61 kg.

name: Karim Boudjema
description: Karim Boudjema (born September 8, 1988 in Lyon) is a French-Algerian footballer. He currently plays for Etoile FC in Singapore's S. League.

name: Karim Coulibaly Diaby
description: Karim Diaby Coulibaly (born 25 December 1989 in Abidjan) is a French-Ivorian football striker who currently plays for the Corgoň Liga club MFK Košice.

name: Karim El Hany
description: Karim El Hany (born 12 January 1988) is a French footballer who currently plays as a midfielder for Belgian Second Division side FC Brussels. Born in Sartène France, El Hany first started playing for Gazélec Ajaccio at the age of 19 before moving to rivals AC Ajaccio.

name: Karim Fegrouche
description: Karim Fegrouche (born 14 February 1982) is a Moroccan footballer. He is currently attached to Greek side PAS Giannina F.C. and also plays in the Moroccan national team.

name: Karim Ghajji
description: Karim Ghajji (born January 16, 1981), is a French kickboxer and B-boy.

name: Karim Izrailov
description: Karim Izrailov (born 14 March 1987) is a Kyrgyzstani professional footballer. Currently he is playing for Abdish-Ata Kant.

name: Karim Laribi
description: Karim Laribi (born 21 April 1991) is an Italian football midfielder of Tunisian and Italian ancestry. He currently plays for Sassuolo, in a co-ownership deal with Palermo.

name: Karim Maamoun
description: Karim Maamoun (born 18 November 1979) is an Egyptian tennis player.

name: Karim Masroor
description: Karim Masroor is a retired Iranian football player. He was known as due to his many goals scored through headers.

name: Karim Mayfield
description: Karim Rasheed Mayfield (born December 14, 1980 in San Francisco, California) is an undefeated boxer in the Welterweight division.

name: Karim Mouzaoui
description: Karim Mouzaoui (born 20 November 1975) is a French football player of Algerian descent. He currently plays for Makedonikos F.C. in the Greek Third Division. Mouzaoui began his professional career with Strasbourg, but only played two Ligue 1 matches for the club, and was loaned out to Laval where he played in 29 Ligue 2 matches. He moved to Greece and played for Apollon Kalamarias in the Greek Beta Ethniki, before moving to Greek Alpha Ethniki side Panionios. While at Panionios, Mouzaoui was suspended for four months after failing a doping test in January 2003. Next, Mouzaoui spent two seasons with Cypriot side Apollon Limassol before returning to Greece where he would play for Apollon Kalamarias and Veria F.C. in the Greek Super League.

name: Karim Oumarou
description: Karim Oumarou (born on 7 January 1985) is a Nigerien football player. He played for the Niger national football team during 2010 FIFA World Cup qualification, scoring an own goal against Benin. He is the current captain of Sahel SC who play in the Niger Premier League. He is known to be a versatile defender, being able to fill in at any position across the back 4, as well as being a useful winger.

name: Karim Shaverdi
description: Karim Shaverdi (born 7 February 1983) is an Iranian footballer who plays for Foolad F.C. in the IPL.

name: Karin Rutz-Gießelmann
description: Karin Rutz-Gießelmann (born 16 January 1948) is a German fencer. She competed at the 1972 and 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Karin Stevens
description: Karin Christiaan Ida Catharina Stevens is a Dutch football striker, currently playing for Lierse in the Belgian First Division. She has been a member of the Dutch national team, and took part in the 2009 European Championship where she scored in Netherlands' debut game against Ukraine. She previously scored three of Netherlands' four goals in the qualifying play-offs against Spain.

name: Karina Szymańska
description: Karina Szymańska is a Polish football midfielder currently playing for Medyk Konin in the Ekstraliga. She is an under-19 international.

name: Karl-Axel Karlsson
description: Karl-Axel Karlsson (5 September 1939 – 3 December 2011) was a Swedish sports shooter. He competed at the 1972 and 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Karl-Heinz Müller
description: Karl-Heinz Müller (born 27 August 1948) is an Austrian fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1972 and 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Karl Chandler
description: Karl Chandler is a former professional American football player who played offensive lineman for six seasons for the New York Giants and Detroit Lions.

name: Karl Erik Rimfeldt
description: Karl Erik Rimfeldt (born 16 February 1980) is a retired Norwegian football defender. He started his career in Kongsvinger IL, and played for Norwegian youth national teams. He joined the senior squad in 1999, and played three Norwegian Premier League games in 1999. He played one more season before leaving. He has later played on lower levels for Sander IL and Vinger FK.

name: Karl Fairbank
description: Karl 'Konkreet' Fairbank (born 1 June 1963) is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1980s and '90s, playing at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Bradford Northern, as a Prop, or Second-row, i.e. number 8 or 10, or, 11 or 12, and coaching at club level for Halifax Under-21s, and Elland ARLFC http://www. pitchero. com/clubs/elland/ open-age.

name: Karl George (American football)
description: Karl Willimann George (November 14, 1894 – December 28, 1979) was a guard in the National Football League. He played for the Racine Legion during the 1922 NFL season.

name: Karl Giesser
description: Karl Giesser (born 29 October 1928) is an Austrian football midfielder who played for Austria in the 1954 FIFA World Cup. He also played for SK Rapid Wien.

name: Karl Hanisch
description: Karl Hanisch (born 20 January 1900, date of death unknown) was an Austrian Olympic fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée and team sabre events at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Karl Holmberg
description: Karl Albin Elis Holmberg (born 3 March 1993) is a Swedish footballer who plays for Örebro SK as a midfielder.

name: Karl Ifwersen
description: Karl Donald Ifwersen (1893–1967) was a New Zealand rugby football player who represented his country in both rugby league and rugby union.

name: Karl Infanger
description: Karl Infanger (born May 17, 1975) is a former professional ice hockey defenceman who played parts of three seasons in the ECHL with the Wheeling Nailers, Mississippi Sea Wolves, and Johnstown Chiefs from 1997–98 to 2000–01. Infanger is currently the head coach of the Natick High School hockey program.

name: Karl Kaschka
description: Karl Kaschka (8 January 1904 – 4 December 1941) was an Austrian fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1936 Summer Olympics. He was killed in action during World War II when his plane was shot down.

name: Karl Kolseth
description: Karl Dickey "Koley" Kolseth (December 25, 1892 – May 3, 1956) was a Major League Baseball first baseman who played for the Baltimore Terrapins of the Federal League in 1915.

name: Karl Max Barthelemy
description: Karl Max Barthelemy also known as Karl Max Dany (born April 18, 1988) is a Chadian football striker who currently plays for Club Africain, from Tunisia. He is also a member of Chad national football team. He has 10 caps for national team and 2 goals and he was a part of qualifying campaign for 2010 World Cup, as well as 2012 Africa Cup of Nations.

name: Karl Meister
description: Karl Daniel Meister (May 15, 1891 – August 15, 1967) was a Major League Baseball center fielder. Meister played in four games for the Cincinnati Reds in 1913.

name: Karl Meltzer
description: Karl Meltzer (born December 8, 1967, nicknamed "Speedgoat Karl") is an ultrarunner and ultrarunning coach based in Sandy, Utah. While many ultramarathoners tend to be vegetarian, vegan, and anti-alcohol or caffeine, Meltzer has been seen with bacon, red bull, and microbrews. Meltzer is known for not only having more 100-mile wins at the ultramarathon event than any other ultramarathoner, but also for his notable speed record attempts at major U.S. trails including both the Appalachian Trail and the Pony Express Trail. Both speed records were supported and fully documented. Meltzer's trail runs have been featured in news outlets from Ultrarunning. com to NBC Sports. Meltzer has been a professional ultramarathoner since 1999, and a coach since 2007. Meltzer is the current Race Director for the Speedgoat 50K at Snowbird Ski Resort, and that self-founded ultramarathon is said to be one of the toughest United States ultras.

name: Karl Nieuwoudt
description: Gerrit Karl Nieuwoudt (born 8 March 1988) is a South African cricketer who played for Boland. He is a right-handed batsman and right-arm fast-medium bowler. Nieuwoudt made his first-class debut for Boland on 16 October 2008 against Griqualand West and went on to play 6 first-class matches for the province.

name: Karl O'Dwyer
description: Karl O'Dwyer was a footballer from Waterville in South Co Kerry. He played with the Kerry team that were shocked by Clare in the 1992 Munster Senior Football Championship final. He later played with Kildare and had much success when his father Mick was manager. In 1998 he helped Kildare to their first Leinster Senior Football Championship title since 1956, he later helped his team to a first All Ireland final since 1928 but lost out to Galway on the day. In the semi final Kildare beat O' Dwyers native Kerry. At the end of the year he picked up an All Star at Full Forward. In 2000 he once again helped Kildare to a Leinster title. Karl O'Dwyer retire from inter county in 2002 following Kildare's defeat to Kerry in the All-Ireland Qualifiers. Before moving to Kildare he played with his local Watervile and with the South Kerry team. In Kildare he first played with Rathangan before joining Round Towers. He won a Kildare Senior Football Championship medal with Round Towers in 2003.

name: Karl Pearson (cricketer)
description: Karl Pearson (born 14 August 1974) is an English cricketer. Pearson is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born at Stourbridge, Worcestershire. Pearson made his debut for Herefordshire in the 1997 Minor Counties Championship against Dorset. From 1997 to 2003, he represented the county in 43 Championship matches, the last of which came against Cornwall. His MCCA Knockout Trophy debut for the county came against the Worcestershire Cricket Board in 1998. From 1998 to 2003, he represented the county in 18 Trophy matches, the last of which came against Staffordshire. He also represented Herefordshire in List A cricket. His debut List A match came against Wiltshire in the 1999 NatWest Trophy. From 1999 to 2002, he represented the county in 8 List A matches, the last of which came against the Durham Cricket Board in the 2nd round of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy, which was played in 2002. In his 8 matches, he scored 115 runs at a batting average of 23.00, with a high score of 35. With the ball he took 4 wickets at a bowling average of 30.25, with best figures of 2/18. He currently plays club cricket for Sevenoaks Vine Cricket Club in the Kent Cricket League.

name: Karl Schnell
description: Karl Otto Schnell (September 20, 1899 – May 31, 1992) was a Major League Baseball pitcher. Schnell attended Saint Mary's College of California. He played for the Cincinnati Reds in 1922 and 1923.

name: Karl Schuelke
description: Karl Schuelke is a former fullback in the National Football League. He was a member of the Pittsburgh Pirates during the 1939 NFL season.

name: Karl Sudrich
description: Karl Sudrich (7 October 1895 – 18 September 1944) was an Austrian fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil and sabre events at the 1936 Summer Olympics. He fought in the Wehrmacht and died from his wounds in a military hospital in Hungary.

name: Karl Swanson
description: Karl Edward Swanson (December 17, 1900 – April 3, 2002) was a second baseman in Major League Baseball. He played for the Chicago White Sox.

name: Karl Thomas (cricketer)
description: Karl Perry Terence Thomas (born 2 June 1973) is a former English cricketer. Thomas was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born in Nottingham, Nottinghamshire. Thomas represented the Nottinghamshire Cricket Board in a single List A match against Scotland in the 1st round of the 1999 NatWest Trophy. In his only List A match he scored 28 runs.

name: Karlen Vartanyan
description: Karlen Sarkisovich Vartanyan (Russian: Карлен Саркисович Вартанян; born July 26, 1993) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Taganrog. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Taganrog on April 18, 2012 in a game against FC Torpedo Armavir.

name: Karlheinz Subklewe
description: Karlheinz Subklewe (born 6 December 1950) is a former German footballer. Subklewe made a total of 42 appearances in the Fußball-Bundesliga and 121 in the 2. Bundesliga during his playing career.

name: Karlo Maquinto
description: Karlo P. Maquinto (born in Lambunao, Iloilo, Philippines on 8 July 1990 - died 3 February 2012) was a super flyweight Filipino boxer who resided in Baguio City, Benguet, Philippines. He died after he collapsed at the end of his 7th professional bout.

name: Karlo Primorac
description: Karlo Primorac (born 1 June 1984 in Osijek) is a Croatian footballer who plays as a forward, currently with Sime Darby F.C. in the Malaysia Premier League. A product of Osijek academy, Primorac joined their first team squad in the 2003–04 season and appeared in 17 matches for the club in his first top-flight season. He went on to establish himself as a regular member of Osijek's starting eleven and he appeared in a total of 136 Prva HNL matches and scored 25 goals before being released from the club in January 2010. He was then picked up by Dinamo Zagreb almost immediately, and he signed for the Blues on a free transfer in February 2010. Primorac was also capped for the Croatia U21 national team, appearing in 9 matches and scoring one goal.

name: Karma Tsewang
description: Karma Tsewang (born 1 October 1988) is an Indian football player who currently plays for Pune F.C. as a Midfielder.

name: Karni Liddell
description: Karni Liddell (born 1 March 1979) is a Paralympic swimming competitor from Australia.

name: Karo Haghverdian
description: Karo Haghverdian (born January 11, 1945) is a retired Iranian Armenian football player.

name: Karolína Nováková
description: Karolína Nováková is a Czech football midfielder, currently playing for Sparta Prague in the Czech First Division. She is an Under 19 international.

name: Karol Biermann
description: Karol Biermann is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Karol Mannion
description: Karol Mannion is a Gaelic footballer for Roscommon and St. Brigids. He first came to prominence with the Roscommon junior team that won Connacht and All-Ireland titles in 2000. He was also part of the Roscommon team that won the Connacht Senior Football Championship in 2010. He plays his club football with St. Brigids with whom he has had much success winning Roscommon Senior Football Championship medals in 2005, 2006, 2007, 2010, 2011 and 2012. He also has won Connacht Senior Club Football Championships in 2006, 2010, 2011 and 2012. He also played in the 2011 All-Ireland Senior Club Football Championship final but lost out to Crossmaglen Rangers. St. Brigids were back in the final again in 2013 and won by one point to become the first team from Roscommon to win an All-Ireland club title. He also picked up the Man of the Match award.

name: Karol Mondek
description: Karol Mondek (born 2 June 1991 in Martin) is a Slovak football midfielder who currently plays for the Corgoň Liga club AS Trenčín.

name: Karol Pavelka
description: Karol Pavelka (born 31 July 1983) is a Slovak football striker who currently plays for the Slovak Corgoň Liga club FC Spartak Trnava.

name: Karol Piątek
description: Karol Piątek (born July 4, 1982 in Luzino) is a Polish footballer who plays for LKS Nieciecza.

name: Karol Sloboda
description: Karol Sloboda (born April 16, 1983) is a Slovak professional ice hockey player who played with HC Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Extraliga.

name: Karolina Bochra
description: Karolina Bochra is a Polish football striker, currently playing for 1. FC Katowice in the Ekstraliga. She previously played for Gol Częstochowa and AZS Wroclaw. She was a member of the Polish national team in the 2008 Algarve Cup, where she scored against host Portugal.

name: Karsten Bailey
description: Karsten Mario Bailey (born April 26, 1977 in Newnan, Georgia) is a former American football wide receiver in the National Football League. He was drafted by the Seattle Seahawks in the third round of the 1999 NFL Draft. He played college football at Auburn. Bailey also played for the Green Bay Packers.

name: Karsten Smith
description: Karsten Smith (born November 13, 1988 in Huntington Station, New York) is an American soccer player currently playing for San Antonio Scorpions in the North American Soccer League.

name: Kashif Ibrahim
description: Kashif Ibrahim (born 16 November 1977) is a former Pakistani cricketer. Ibrahim was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born at Karachi, Sindh Province. Ibrahim made his first-class debut for Karachi Whites against Rawalpindi in 1996/97 season. Ibrahim represented Karachi Whites in 17 first-class matches, Karachi in a single and Karachi Blues in 3. He also represented Pakistan National Shipping Corporation in 9 first-class matches between 1999/00. In final first-class match came in the 2000/01 season for Karachi Whites against Rawalpindi. In total, from 1996/97 to 2000/01 he played 30 first-class matches. In these matches he scored a total of 447 runs at a batting average of 16.44, with high score of 48. With the ball he took 74 wickets at a bowling average of 27.14, with 5 five wicket hauls, one of which resulted in his best figures of 5/25. Ibrahim also mde his debut in List A cricket for Karachi Blues in the 1996/97 season against Bahawalpur. Ibrahim represented the 3 Karachi teams in List A cricket 11 times from the 1996/97 to 1998/99 season. In addition, he also represented Pakistan National Shipping Corporation in 4 matches during the 1999/00 season. His final List-A match in Pakistan came for the Corporation against Pakistan International Airlines in September 1999. During the 2000 English cricket season, Iqbal played a 2 List A matches for the Sussex Cricket Board in the 2000 NatWest Trophy against Herefordshire. and Berkshire, which marked his final List A match. In his total of 17 List A matches, he scored 226 runs at an average of 45.20, with a 2 half centuries and a high score of 63. With the ball he took 22 wickets at an average of 28.45, with a best figures of 3/28.

name: Kaspars Cipruss
description: Kaspars Cipruss is a Latvian basketball player. Currently he has signed a contract with BC Odessa to play in Ukrainian Basketball SuperLeague .

name: Katalin Juhász
description: Katalin Juhász (Hungarian: Juhász Katalin, Tóth Gézáné, born Juhász Katalin; born November 24, 1932, in Hódmezővásárhely) was a Hungarian foil fencer. From 1947, she was the fencer of Szegedi Postás, from 1950 the fencer of Szegedi Haladás, from 1957 she played in OSC (Orvosegyetemi Sport Club, Sport Club of the University of Medicine). From 1957 to 1967, she was a member of the Olympic team of Hungary. During her career, she won two Olympic and seven world championship medals. She stopped active sport in 1967. In 1956, she graduated with a diploma in Chemistry from the University of Szeged. After leaving sport, she became a development engineer of the Accumulator Factory (Akkumulátorgyár) in Budapest. She is retired from 1987.

name: Katarína Bašternáková
description: Katarína Bašternáková (born 12 October 1982) is a former Slovak tennis player. A native of Hurbanovo in Slovakia, she was runner-up at the 1999 Australian Open – Girls' Singles tournament and a quarter-finalist in the 1999 Australian Open – Girls' Doubles. Bašternáková reached a record doubles ranking high of world number 441 during a playing career in which she won two ITF doubles titles.
