Orellana also represented Venezuela at the 2003 Pan American Games in Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic, reaching the third round in the men's singles event and reaching the quarterfinals in the men's doubles event.

name: Kerbi Rodríguez
description: Kelvin Rafael Rodríguez Pichardo commonly known as Kerbi Rodríguez (born 10 December 1985 in Esperanza) is a Dominican international football striker playing for Pantoja in the Dominican first division.

name: Kerem Gürgen
description: Kerem Gürgen is a Turkish amateur boxer in the featherweight (57 kg) division. He is currently a member of the squad at Gençlik Spor İl Müdürlüğü (GSİM) in Siirt.

name: Keron Cummings
description: Keron Cummings (born 28 May 1988), is an international soccer player from Trinidad and Tobago who plays professionally for Central F.C. as a midfielder.

name: Keron Williams
description: Keron Donavan Williams is a Canadian football defensive tackle playing for the BC Lions of the Canadian Football League. He was originally signed by the Calgary Stampeders in 2006. Williams played college football for the UMass Minutemen.

name: Kerri-Anne Connor
description: Kerri-Anne Weston (born 3 April 1963) is an Australian swimmer with paraplegia who won five medals at the 1984 New York/Stoke Mandeville Paralympics.

name: Kerry Boagni
description: Kerry Boagni is a retired American basketball player. A native of California, he played college basketball for the Cal State Fullerton Titans and played professionally in the National Basketball Association (NBA).

name: Kerry Clark (ice hockey)
description: For the New Zealand lawn bowls player, see Kerry Clark. Kerry Clark (ice hockey) Born (1968-08-21) August 21, 1968 (age 44) Kelvington, Saskatchewan, Canada Height 6 ft 1 in Weight 205 lb Position Left wing Shot Right Played for Springfield IndiansPhoenix Roadrunners (1990)Salt Lake Golden Eagles (1990-93)Portland Pirates (1993-95)Orlando Solar Bears (1995-97)Milwaukee Admirals (1997-98) NHL Draft 10th round, 206th overall, 1986New York Islanders Playing career 1988–1998 Kerry Clark is a retired professional ice hockey player, notable as one of the most penalized players in minor league history.

name: Kerry Golding
description: Kerry Joan Modra (née Golding, OAM is an Australian Paralympic tandem cycling pilot. She was born in the New South Wales city of Nowra. She was introduced to Kieran Modra, a visually impaired cyclist, at a friend's 21st birthday party. He convinced her to take up cycling; she had only played netball before then. She became Modra's pilot, and six months later, she won a gold medal with him at the 1996 Atlanta Games in the Mixed 200 m Sprint Tandem open event, for which she won a Medal of the Order of Australia. She married Modra in May 1997, and they have three children. At the 2000 Sydney Games, she did not win any medals. At the games, she was pregnant with the couple's first child, and fainted due to low blood pressure during a quarter-final sprint race; she was replaced as Kieran's pilot by his sister, Tania, for the rest of the games. In 2000, she received an Australian Sports Medal.

name: Kerry Larkin
description: Kerry Kelsall Larkin (born 22 June 1936) was a rugby union player who represented Australia. Larkin, a prop, was born in Brisbane, Queensland and claimed a total of 2 international rugby caps for Australia. He was educated at the Anglican Church Grammar School.

name: Kerry Taylor
description: Kerry Thomas Taylor (born January 25, 1971 in Bemidji, Minnesota) is former Major League Baseball pitcher. Taylor played for the San Diego Padres from 1993 to 1994. He batted and threw right-handed.

name: Kersley Appou
description: Kersley Appou (born April 24, 1970 in Mauritius) is a football player who currently plays for PAS Mates in the Mauritian Premier League as a forward. He has also represented Mauritius internationally with Club M, scoring 10 goals. That is the most goals scored in Mauritius national team history.

name: Kervens Belfort
description: Kervens Fils Belfort (born 16 May 1992) is a Haitian international footballer who plays for French club Le Mans, as a striker.

name: Kervin Godon
description: Kervin Godon (born 3 August 1982) is a Mauritian international footballer who plays as a midfielder. As of August 2011, he has won 31 caps and scored 2 goals for the Mauritius national football team.

name: Kerwin Moore
description: Kerwin Lamar Moore (born October 29, 1970) is a former outfielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Oakland Athletics in 1996.

name: Keryn Jordan
description: Keryn Jordan (born 1 November 1975) is a former South African footballer who last played for Auckland City FC in the New Zealand Football Championship. He announced his retirement on 19 March 2010 due to on-going Knee injuries. He has played at the highest level in South Africa and New Zealand. He holds New Zealand citizenship.

name: Keshawn Martin
description: Keshawn Martin (born March 15, 1990) is an American football wide receiver for the Houston Texans of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Texans in the fourth round of the 2012 NFL Draft. He played college football at Michigan State.

name: Keshorn Walcott
description: Keshorn Walcott ORTT (born 2 April 1993) is a Trinidadian javelin thrower. He is a three-time winner in the Under-20 javelin throw at the CARIFTA Games, setting a new North, Central American and Caribbean Junior record in 2012. He improved this record on 27 May 2012 with 80.11 m in Havana. He won the Olympic gold medal at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London with a result of 84.58 meters, beating Ukraine's Oleksandr Pyatnytsa and Finland's Antti Ruuskanen, becoming the youngest-ever Olympic champion in javelin throw and the second non-European to ever win the Olympic gold in men's javelin throw since Cy Young in Helsinki in 1952. His throw was a new North, Central American and Caribbean Junior record. Walcott is currently coached by Cuban-born Ismael Mastrapa of the Sports Company of Trinidad and Tobago.

name: Keston Williams
description: Keston Williams (born 25 March 1988) is an international soccer player from Trinidad and Tobago who plays professionally for Defence Force as a Defender.

name: Kevan George
description: Kevan Leon George is a Trinidadian footballer who currently plays for the Columbus Crew in Major League Soccer.

name: Kevin Aherne-Evans
description: Kevin Aherne-Evans (born 16 December 1980 in Carmarthen) is a Welsh former professional footballer and Wales Under-21 international. Prior to 2003 he was known as Kevin Evans.

name: Kevin Ashcroft
description: Kevin Ashcroft is a professional rugby league footballer of the 1960s and '70s, and coach of the 1970s, '80s, and '90s, playing at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Rochdale Hornets, Dewsbury, Leigh, Warrington, and Salford, as a Prop, or Hooker, i.e. number 8 or 10, or, 9, during the era of contested scrums, and coaching at club level for Leigh (twice), and Salford.

name: Kevin Bechmann Timm
description: Kevin Bechmann Timm (born 9 July 1989) is a Danish professional football Midfielder/Forward, who currently plays for the Danish 1st Division side Akademisk Boldklub.

name: Kevin Belingon
description: Kevin Belingon (born October 20, 1987) is a Filipino mixed martial artist. Belingon is a powerful striker with superb conditioning, capable of wearing down even the most seasoned of opponents, and he is quickly making a name for himself as one of the most promising bantamweight fighters in the Asia-Pacific.

name: Kevin Bigler
description: Kevin Bigler (born 5 October 1992) is a Swiss footballer who plays for FC Thun in the Swiss Super League.

name: Kevin Blackburn
description: Kevin Richard Blackburn (born 19 August 1968) is a former English cricketer. Blackburn was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm medium pace. He was born at Doncaster, Yorkshire. Blackburn first played county cricket for Cornwall in the 1987 Minor Counties Championship against Shropshire. From 1987 to 1994, he represented the county in 13 Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which came against Herefordshire. He also represented Cornwall in the MCCA Knockout Trophy. His debut in that competition came against Devon in 1992. He represented Cornwall in 2 further Trophy matches against Wiltshire in 1993 and Dorset in 1994. Blackburn later represented the Somerset Cricket Board in 3 List A matches. These came against Bedfordshire in the 1999 NatWest Trophy, Staffordshire in the 2000 NatWest Trophy and Wales Minor Counties in the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 3 List A matches, he scored 26 runs at a batting average of 8.66, with a high score of 20. In 2002, he joined Wiltshire. He made his debut for Wiltshire in the Minor Counties Championship against Dorset. From 2002 to 2005, he represented the county in 11 Championship matches, the last of which came against Devon. He also represented the county in the MCCA Knockout Trophy, representing them in 8 Trophy matches, the last of which came against Norfolk in 2005.

name: Kevin Budinauckas
description: Kevin Budinauckas (born September 16, 1974 in Bellshill) is a former Scottish goalkeeper. Throughout out his career he has played for Stenhousemuir, Partick Thistle, Clyde, Brechin City on loan and Stranraer in the senior game. He also had a couple of spells in junior football at Wishaw and Linlithgow Rose,cumnock,pollok,armadale, .

name: Kevin Clinton
description: Kevin Clinton is a retired American soccer goalkeeper who played professionally in the North American Soccer League and third American Soccer League. Clinton graduated from Ramapo High School where he was an All County goalkeeper his senior season. He then attended Ulster County Community College. In 1979, the Tampa Bay Rowdies selected Clinton in the second round (twenty-third overall) of the North American Soccer League draft. The Hartford Hellions of the Major Indoor Soccer League also drafted Clinton, but he chose to sign with the Rowdies. During his three years with the Rowdies, Clinton spent most of the time as backup to Winston DuBose, seeing playing time only during the indoor seasons. In 1988, he returned to the Rowdies, this time in the American Soccer League, but again spent the season as backup to DuBose. In 1992, Clinton graduated from the University of South Florida with a bachelor's degree in engineering and computer science. Since then he has served in a variety of position in the information technology field.

name: Kevin Coffey
description: Kevin Coffey (1933–1981) was an Irish former sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club Beaufort and was a member of the Kerry senior inter-county team in the 1950s and 1960s.

name: Kevin Coffman
description: Kevin Reese Coffman (born January 19, 1965 in Austin, Texas) is a former pitcher in the MLB, where he played three seasons. He played with the Atlanta Braves from 1987–1988, where he went 2-6 with a 5.46 Earned Run Average. He played in the MLB again in 1990, this time for the Chicago Cubs. He went 0-2 with an 11.29 Earned Run Average, and did not play another year.

name: Kevin Cossette
description: Kevin Cossette (born January 9, 1990 in Greenfield Park, Quebec) is a Canadian soccer player currently on trail with the Montreal Impact in the NASL.

name: Kevin Dickenson
description: Kevin Dickenson (born 24 November 1962) is an English former professional footballer who played as a left back, making over 250 career appearances.

name: Kevin Dillon (Gaelic footballer)
description: Kevin Dillon is an Irish former sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club Clonakilty and was a member of the Cork senior inter-county team from .

name: Kevin Edward
description: Kevin Edward was born on 24 March 1991. He is an international soccer player from Saint Lucia, who plays as a midfielder.

name: Kevin Featherstone
description: Kevin Featherstone (born February 26, 1971) is an American professional wrestler who competes in the Mid-Atlantic and East Coast independent circuit. He is a longtime mainstay of the National Wrestling League and House of Pain Wrestling Federation as one-half of Old School with Scott Vaughn. One of the promotion's most dominant and popular tag teams, they have won the HoPWF Tag Team Championship twice and the NWL Tag Team Championship three times. One of their title reigns lasted a record of 2-years. Featherstone has also held the NWL Tag Team titles with Spazman Anthony and John Rambo as well as being a former 3-time HoPWF Heavyweight Champion. He is also involved with the promotion's wrestling school.

name: Kevin Fennelly (senior)
description: Kevin Fennelly was a hurler from County Kilkenny who played with his local club Ballyhale Shamrocks and with the Kilkenny inter-county team during the 1940s. After his playing days, Fennelly remained very much involved with his club Shamrocks, serving as everything from trainer, chairman, treasurer and trustee. His memory is honoured still in Kilkenny GAA circles in the form of the Kevin Fennelly Memorial Cup. A farmer by trade, Fennelly purchased land in the town of Ballyhale along with his wife Theresa Hoyne in the early 1960s. It was here that he raised his family, and seven of his sons went on to play hurling for club and county - Michael, Seán, Ger, Kevin, Brendan, Liam and Dermot.

name: Kevin Fisher (rugby league)
description: Kevin Lawrence Fisher is a New Zealand former rugby league player, coach and manager who represented his country in the 1977 World Cup.

name: Kevin Flaherty
description: Kevin Frederick Flaherty (born 17 September 1939) is a former English cricketer. Flaherty was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm off break. He was born at Birmingham, Warwickshire. Flaherty made a single first-class appearance for Warwickshire against Cambridge University at Edgbaston in 1969. He wasn't required to bat in the match. With the ball, he took the wicket of Dudley Owen-Thomas in Cambridge University's first-innings, finishing with figures of 1/69 from 27 overs. In their second-innings, he took the wickets of Roger Knight, Bob Short and Jamie McDowall to finish with figures of 3/38 from 9 overs. Warwickshire won the match by the narrow margin of 17 runs. This was his only major appearance for Warwickshire.

name: Kevin Gentle
description: Kevin Gentle (born 31 October 1959) is a former English cricketer. Gentle was a left-handed batsman. He was born in Stotfold, Bedfordshire. Gentle made his debut for Bedfordshire against Suffolk in the 1979 Minor Counties Championship. He played Minor counties cricket for Bedfordshire from 1979 to 1993, making 74 Minor Counties Championship appearances and 14 MCCA Knockout Trophy appearances. He made his only List A appearance against Gloucestershire in the 1985 NatWest Trophy. Opening the batting, he was dismissed stumped by Jack Russell off the bowling of Ian Payn for 13 runs. Bedfordshire lost the match by 141 runs.

name: Kevin Geudens
description: Kevin Geudens is Belgian football (soccer) midfielder. He currently plays for Westerlo after moving from KV Mechelen in 2012.

name: Kevin Gnatiko
description: Kevin Gnatiko (born June 3, 1986 in Lomé) is a Togolese-born American soccer player who currently plays for Crystal Palace Baltimore in the USSF Second Division.

name: Kevin Handlan
description: Kevin Handlan is a retired American soccer defender who played professionally in the North American Soccer League and Major Indoor Soccer League. He currently works for the McInnis Group.

name: Kevin Harbottle
description: Kevin Andrew Harbottle Carrasco (born June 8, 1990 in Antofagasta) is a Chilean footballer currently playing for Colorado Rapids in Major League Soccer.

name: Kevin Hawley
description: Kevin Hawley (born July 30, 1980) is an Anguillan football player. He plays for Anguilla national team.

name: Kevin Higgins (baseball)
description: Kevin Wayne Higgins (born January 22, 1967 in San Gabriel, California) is a Major League Baseball catcher who played for the San Diego Padres in 1993. He hit no homeruns and only drove in thirteen runs making his last career start on October 3rd, 1993.

name: Kevin Hollis
description: Kevin John Hollis (born 5 January 1983) is an English cricketer. Hollis is a left-handed batsman who plays primarily as a wicketkeeper. He was born at Derby, Derbyshire. Hollis represented the Derbyshire Cricket Board in List A cricket. His debut List A match came against Derbyshire in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. From 2000 to 2001, he represented the Board in 4 matches, the last of which came against Bedfordshire in the 1st round of the 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy which was held in 2001. In his 4 List A matches, he scored 18 runs at a batting average of 9.00, with a high score of 7*. Behind the stumps he took a single catch and made 2 stumpings.

name: Kevin Hoskins
description: Kevin Hoskins (born October 12, 1990 in Los Angeles, California) is an undefeated professional boxer in the Super Featherweight division.

name: Kevin House, Jr.
description: Kevin Nathaniel House, Jr. is a professional American football player in the NFL. Four year veteran. He has played professionally for the San Diego Chargers and the Seattle Seahawks.

name: Kevin Jansen
description: Kevin Johnny Jansen (born 8 April 1992 in Hoogvliet) is a Dutch footballer who currently plays as a midfielder for Dutch Eredivisie club ADO Den Haag.

name: Kevin Janssens
description: Kevin Janssens (born 29 May 1986 in Turnhout) is a Belgian professional football player. His best position is left-midfielder. He made his senior debut for K.V. Turnhout in third division, and was transferred to second division team Lierse in December 2008. He achieved promotion with Lierse to the highest level in 2010, but was quickly loaned out to his former club Turnhout, who had also achieved promotion in 2010. With Turnhout, Janssens was relegated back to third division but received a new chance at the highest level of Belgian football when he signed a 2-year deal with Cercle Brugge.

name: Kevin Jurovich
description: Kevin Jurovich (born June 30, 1986) is an American football wide receiver who is currently a free agent. He signed as an undrafted free agent with the Philadelphia Eagles in 2010. He played college football at San Jose State University. Jurovich has also been member of the San Francisco 49ers and Chicago Bears.

name: Kevin Kasuza
description: Kevin Tatenda Kasuza (born June 20, 1993) is a Zimbabwean domestic cricketer. He is primarily a batsman and is a bright prospect for Zimbabwe. He particularly came to the limelight when his twin tons within two weeks, saved his franchise Mountaineers from a crisis situation, and having shown great temperament, both of these tons resulted in a win for his team. He currently represents Zimbabwe at Under-19 level, and subsequent articles in the Zimbabwe Cricket official website say that he may be considered for selection soon.

name: Kevin Kilmurray
description: Kevin Kilmurray is an Irish retired sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club Daingean and was a member of the Offaly senior inter-county team from 1969 until 1980.

name: Kevin Klasila
description: Kevin Klasila (born May 2, 1989 in Santa Monica, California) is an American soccer player currently playing for Charleston Battery in the USL Pro.

name: Kevin Knight
description: Kevin Knight (born 22 October 1976 in Fairfax, Virginia) is an American retired professional soccer defender.

name: Kevin Koetters
description: Kevin Koetters (born September 11, 1968 in Quincy, Illinois) is a retired U.S. soccer midfielder who spent most of his career in the U.S. indoor leagues as well as one with the Kansas City Wiz in Major League Soccer, one in the American Professional Soccer League and one in the USISL. Koetters attended Rockhurst University where he was a 1989 second team NAIA All American. In 1990, he played for the Colorado Foxes in the American Professional Soccer League. In 1991, he signed with the Kansas City Attack in the National Professional Soccer League. He remained with the Attack through the 1998-1999 season. During these years, Koetters would play for the Attack during the winter, then spend time with other teams during the summer season. In 1993, he played for the San Diego Sockers of the Continental Indoor Soccer League. In February 1996, the Kansas City Wiz selected Koetters in the 12th round (116th overall) of the 1996 MLS Inaugural Player Draft. He saw time in 15 games before being released at the end of the season. In 1997, he played for the Rochester Rhinos in the USISL. He then played one game for the Detroit Rockers during the 1999-2000 NPSL season. In 2000, he signed with the St. Louis Steamers in the World Indoor Soccer League. He also played the 2001 season with them. He played for the Kansas City Comets of the Major Indoor Soccer League from 2001 to 2002. In 2005, he became the head coach of Gardner Edgerton High School.

name: Kevin Lefranc
description: Kevin Lefranc (born 1 March 1986) is a French-born association footballer who is currently contracted to SR Delémont in the Swiss 1. Liga Promotion. A football journeyman, Lefranc has played for 10 different clubs in 6 separate countries. He plays as a Striker.

name: Kevin Lloyd (footballer)
description: Kevin Gareth Lloyd (born 26 September 1970 in Llanidloes) is a Welsh former professional footballer.

name: Kevin MacDonald (ice hockey)
description: Kevin Scott MacDonald (born February 24, 1966) is a Canadian ice hockey coach and former professional ice hockey player. With the exception of playing one game in the NHL with the Ottawa Senators during the 1993–94 NHL season, MacDonald was s career minor leaguer. He played in the International Hockey League (IHL), American Hockey League (AHL), and East Coast Hockey League (ECHL).

name: Kevin Malast
description: Kevin Malast (born June 6, 1986 in Manchester, New Jersey) is an American football linebacker for the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League. He was signed by the Chicago Bears as an undrafted free agent in 2009. He played college football for Rutgers. He has also been a member of the Jacksonville Jaguars.

name: Kevin Malget
description: Kevin Malget (born 15 January 1991) is a Luxembourger international footballer who plays club football for F91 Dudelange, as a defender.

name: Kevin Manion
description: Kevin Manion (born on June 24, 1972), nicknamed Bono, is the current NASCAR Sprint Cup Series crew chief for the Earnhardt Ganassi Racing #1 Bass Pro Shops/McDonald's Chevrolet SS driven by Jamie McMurray. Manion led the #1 car to wins in both the 2010 Daytona 500 and the 2010 Brickyard 400.

name: Kevin McGarry
description: Dr J. Kevin McGarry (c. 1925 – August 1995) was a Northern Ireland international footballer who played with Cliftonville from 1949. He played Gaelic football before being convinced to sign amateur forms with Belfast Celtic. He played a few first-team games for Celtic before signing with Cliftonville. At Solitude he was also a prolific goalscorer. He was named as the inaugural Ulster Footballer of the Year for the 1950/51 season. As a student at Queen's University, he was selected by Ireland for an amateur international against England in February 1948: a 5-0 defeat. He was then chosen for an Irish F.A. representative side which beat the United States 5-0, with McGarry scoring twice. In 1952, he was part of the Great Britain squad at the Helsinki Olympics. He was selected for Ireland's 1950/51 Home Nations squad, making his full international debut against Scotland at Hampden Park, in which he scored in a 2-1 defeat. He earned two more caps, also playing in the match against Wales, and then in a friendly against France. He represented the Irish League on numerous occaions, scoring a record twelve goals.

name: Kevin McGehee
description: George Kevin McGehee (born January 18, 1969 in Alexandria, Louisiana) is former Major League Baseball pitcher. McGehee played for the Baltimore Orioles in 1993.

name: Kevin McIntosh
description: Kevin McIntosh is an Australian Paralympic cycling coach.

name: Kevin McKernan
description: Kevin McKernan is a Gaelic football player from County Down, Northern Ireland. He plays for the Down senior inter county football team. He started at centre back in the 2010 All-Ireland Football Final where Down were defeated 0-15 to 0-16 by Cork. Kevin won a Dr McKenna Cup in 2008 scoring 1 point from play he won an Ulster Under-21 Football Championship in 2008 beating Derry 3-11 to 1-14. Kevin's father Brendan was Right Corner Back on the Down Team that won the All Ireland in 1991. In 2011, McKernan was part of the Ireland team that won the 2011 International Rules Series against Australia by 130 to 65. McKernan has been a member of the Down team since 2008 but made his debut in 2007. McKernan can also play Midfield or Half Forward.

name: Kevin Melgar
description: Kevin Melgar (born November 19, 1992) is a Panamanian footballer who plays for Alianza as a goalkeeper. He latest start for Panama was the 10th of January 2013, in which was a shutout for him. Panama beat Guatemala that game 3-0, in Panama.

name: Kevin Molino
description: Kevin Molino (born June 17, 1990) is a Trinidadian footballer who currently plays for Orlando City in the USL Professional Division.

name: Kevin Molloy
description: Kevin Molloy is a Northern Irish sportsperson. He plays hurling with the Antrim senior inter-county hurling team and has been a member of the panel since 2011. He made his senior Antrim debut on 14 May 2011 against Laois in the 2011 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship, starting at left corner back in the 1-21 to 3-12 victory. Kevin plays his club hurling for Dunloy Cuchullains and is considered a hero within the village. He has one senior championship medal, won in 2009. He considers this as the peak of his career. When asked what the lowest point in his career was he replied, 'well there are two moments which stand out to me. When i got sent off against Ballygalget in the 2012 league fixture, i felt as though i let the team and village as a community down but i think the lowest has to be playing for Antrim against Wexford in the Leinster Championship in 2011, Rory Jacob gave me a run around scoring 1-4 from play. ' Kevin would consider himself a club hurler as he prefers playing alongside his friends. He stated that going to training and training with players like Liam Richmond, Joe 'the postman' Smyth and Shane Dooey is what made him the player he is today.

name: Kevin Mombilo
description: Kevin Mombilo (born 6 May 1993) is a Finnish football player of Congolese descent currently playing for Finnish Veikkausliiga side FC Honka.

name: Kevin Mulgrew
description: Kevin Mulgrew is a former association football player who represented New Zealand at international level. Mulgrew made his full All Whites debut in a 2-1 win over China on 20 July 1975 and ended his international playing career with 12 A-international caps and 1 goal to his credit, his final cap a substitute appearance in a 1-2 loss to New Caledonia on 2 October 1976.

name: Kevin Nancekivell
description: Kevin Nancekivell (born 22 October 1971) is a football coach who works for Plymouth Argyle, where he has been a coach since 2005. As a player he was an attacking midfielder. He mainly competed at a semi-professional level, spending most of his career at Tiverton Town, although he had a short spell at Plymouth. A farmer by trade, he played for Bideford before joining Tiverton Town in 1996. Nancekivell was a regular scorer from midfield, finishing as the clubs top goalscorer twice, before being given a chance in the professional game at the age of 28 by Plymouth Argyle manager Kevin Hodges. He made six league appearances as a substitute, scoring his first goal against Hartlepool United on 21 October 2000, but fell out of first team contention after the arrival of Paul Sturrock. He rejoined Tiverton Town on loan in January 2001 and returned to Ladysmead permanently that summer. He scored Tiverton's consolation goal in the FA Cup first round defeat against Cardiff City in November 2001. After retiring, Nancekivell took a job at Plymouth Argyle's youth coaching centre of excellence in 2005. He was promoted to coaching the first team in 2010. In January 2013 he was appointed as joint caretaker manager following the sacking of Carl Fletcher.

name: Kevin Nash (cricketer)
description: Kevin John Nash (born 19 October 1975) is an English cricketer. Nash was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm fast-medium. He was born in Derby, Derbyshire. Nash made his debut in the Minor Counties Championship for Dorset in the 1995 against Herefordshire. From 1995 to 1997, he represented the county in 6 Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which came against Cheshire. He also represented Dorset in the MCCA Knockout Trophy. His debut for Dorset in that competition came against Shropshire. This was the only Trophy match he represented the county in. In 1999, Nash joined Wiltshire where he made his Minor Counties Championship debut for the county against Herefordshire. From 1999 to 2005, he represented the county in 25 Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which came against Berkshire. Nash also represented Wiltshire in the MCCA Knockout Trophy, making his debut for the county in that competition against the Warwickshire Cricket Board in 1999. From 1999 to 2005, he represented the county in 14 Trophy matches, the last of which came against Cornwall. Nash also represented Wiltshire in List A cricket. His List A debut for the county came against Scotland in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. From 1999 to 2005, he represented the county in 6 List A matches, the last of which came against Kent in the 2005 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 6 List A matches, he scored 29 runs at a batting average of 9.66, with a high score of 17. With the ball he took 8 wickets at a bowling average of 28.00, with best figures of 4/46.

name: Kevin Neville
description: Kevin Neville (born February 3, 1953) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey goaltender. He was selected by the Detroit Red Wings in the 10th round (151st overall) of the 1973 NHL Amateur Draft. Neville played junior hockey with the Toronto Marlboros in the Ontario Hockey Association before turning professional in 1973 with the Port Huron Wings of the International Hockey League.

name: Kevin Noreen
description: Kevin Noreen (born 1992) is a basketball player from Minnesota. Noreen played high school basketball at Minnesota Transitions Charter School and broke the state scoring record with an unofficial career total of 4,086 points. In his senior year, he also led the team to the 2010 Class A state championship in Minnesota; he led all scorers in the championship game against Sebeka High School with 24 points, and was named to the All-Tournament team. Kevin Noreen was also named Mr. Basketball in Minnesota in 2010, as well as the Gatorade Minnesota Boys Basketball Player of the Year. Noreen initially committed to play basketball at Boston College, but was allowed to retract his commitment after coach Al Skinner was fired. Noreen then agreed to play for West Virginia. While playing at WVU Kevin has built a huge following amongst the fans.

name: Kevin O'Dwyer
description: For the silversmith, see Kevin O'Dwyer (silversmith) Kevin O'Dwyer{{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=|size=|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}}Personal informationIrish nameCaoimhín Ó Duibhir SportGaelic footballPositionGoalkeeperBornSkibbereen, County CorkHeight5 ft 11 in NicknameWireyOccupationGarda SíochánaClub(s)YearsClub1990s-2000sO'Donovan RossaClub TitlesCork titles1Munster titles1All-Ireland Titles1Inter-county(ies)YearsCountyApps (scores)1995-2005Cork35 (0-00)Inter-county titlesMunster titles4All Irelands0NFL1All Stars1 Kevin O'Dwyer is an Irish former sportsperson. He played Gaelic football with his local club O'Donovan Rossa and was a member of the Cork senior inter-county team from 1995 until 2005.

name: Kevin Pariente
description: Kevin Pariente (born January 19, 1987 in Paris) is a French professional footballer. He currently plays for the Turkish club Bucaspor.

name: Kevin Prindiville
description: Kevin Joseph Prindiville is an Australian former cricketer who played for the Western Australia cricket team from 1978 to 1979. The older brother of Terry Prindiville, who also played cricket for Western Australia, he played mainly as an middle-order batsman, appearing in three first-class matches. He was educated at Aquinas College in Perth.

name: Kevin Radziwon
description: Kevin Radziwon (born July 22, 1984 in Southington, Connecticut) is an American soccer player who currently plays for Western Mass Pioneers in the USL Premier Development League.

name: Kevin Reeves (ice hockey)
description: Kevin Reeves (born October 2, 1958) is a Canadian former ice hockey player. He won the Michel Brière Memorial Trophy as the Most Valuable Player in the Quebec Major Junior Hockey League for his outstanding play with the Montreal Juniors during the 1977–78 QMJHL season.

name: Kevin Roberts (Antigua and Barbudan footballer)
description: Kevin Roberts is an Antigua and Barbudan football player. He has played for Antigua and Barbuda national team.

name: Kevin Rutland
description: Kevin Rutland (born April 2, 1988) is an American football cornerback for the Jacksonville Jaguars of the National Football League. He was signed by the Jaguars as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football at Missouri. Rutland was released by the Jaguars on October 15, 2012 and re-signed on October 26.

name: Kevin Sample
description: Edward Kevin Sample (born 19 February 1961) is a former English cricketer. Sample was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm fast-medium. He was born in Barrow-in-Furness, Lancashire. Sample made his debut for Cumberland in the 1980 Minor Counties Championship against Lincolnshire. Sample played Minor counties cricket for Cumberland from 1980 to 1992, including 31 Minor Counties Championship matches and 4 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. In 1985, he made his List A debut against Middlesex in the NatWest Trophy. He played two further List A matches for Cumberland, against Lancashire in 1986 and Essex in 1992. In his three List A matches, he scored 5 runs at a batting average of 2.50, with a high score of 4. With the ball he took 7 wickets at a bowling average of 21.57. His best bowling figures of 4/58 came against Middlesex in 1985. He also played for a number of first-class counties Second XI's. These included the Warwickshire Second XI, the Worcestershire Second XI, the Derbyshire Second XI and the Glamorgan Second XI.

name: Kevin Santamaria
description: Kevin Oswaldo Santamaría Guzmán is a Salvadoran football midfielder who currently plays for UES in his native country.

name: Kevin Schaeffer
description: Kevin Schaeffer (born October 16, 1984) is a retired American professional ice hockey player who last played for the Las Vegas Wranglers in the ECHL. He was selected by the Nashville Predators in the 6th round (193rd overall) of the 2004 NHL Entry Draft. Unsigned from the Predators from attending Boston University, Schaeffer played 100 games in the American Hockey League with the Providence Bruins, Binghamton Senators, Lake Erie Monsters and the Hartford Wolf Pack before deciding to retire and pursue other opportunities at the end of the 2010–11 season.

name: Kevin Skinner (rugby union)
description: Kevin Lawrence Skinner (born 24 November 1927 in Dunedin) is a former rugby union player from New Zealand who won 20 full caps for the All Blacks, 2 of them as captain. He was also a heavy weight boxer, winning the New Zealand championship in 1947.

name: Kevin Stöger
description: Kevin Stöger (born 27 August 1993 in Steyr) is an Austrian footballer. He plays as a Midfielder for VfB Stuttgart. Pascal Stöger is his brother.

name: Kevin Stanfield
description: Kevin Bruce Stanfield (born December 19, 1955 in Huron, South Dakota) is former Major League Baseball pitcher. Stanfield played for the Minnesota Twins in 1979.

name: Kevin Tamati
description: Kevin Ronald Tamati (born 23 September 1953 in Bridge Pā) is a New Zealander rugby league representative player from 1979 to 1985, and coach of the 1980s, '90s and 2000s, playing at representative level for New Zealand, New Zealand Māori, Auckland, Central Districts and Wellington, and playing professionally at club level for Widnes, Warrington and Salford, Chorley Borough in the Forwards. He has coached the New Zealand Māori, and professionally for Salford, Chorley Borough, Lancashire Lynx, British Army Rugby League and Whitehaven. He is the cousin of fellow international Howie Tamati.

name: Kevin Tilley
description: Kevin Tilley is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League, as a defender.

name: Kevin Todd (footballer)
description: Kevin Todd (born 28 February 1958 in Sunderland, Tyne and Wear) is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League as a forward.

name: Kevin Trapp (soccer)
description: Kevin Trapp (born June 27, 1984 in Minnesota) is an American soccer player, currently without a club.

name: Kevin Venegas
description: Kevin Venegas (born July 29, 1989) is an American soccer player who currently plays for Minnesota Stars FC in the North American Soccer League.

name: Kevin Vinetot
description: Kevin Mathieu Vinetot (born 14 June 1988) is a French footballer who plays for Italian club Crotone on loan from Genoa.

name: Kevin Visser
description: Kevin Visser (born 19 July 1988) is a Dutch professional footballer, who currently plays for ADO Den Haag in the Dutch Eredivisie.

name: Kevin Walker (cornerback)
description: Kevin Walker (born 20 October 1963 in Greensboro, North Carolina) who went to Ben L. Smith High School in Greensboro, North Carolina was an All American defensive back for East Carolina University and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers of the National Football League. He led the nation with nine interceptions in the 1985 college football season.

name: Kevin Weymouth
description: Kevin Weymouth is a football (soccer) player who represented New Zealand at international level. Weymouth made his full All Whites debut in a 2-1 win over China on 20 July 1975 and ended his international playing career with 12 A-international caps and 1 goal to his credit, his final cap an appearance in a 1-1 draw with Australia on 30 March 1977.

name: Kevin Whelan
description: Kevin J. Whelan (born January 8, 1984 in Kerrville, Texas) is an American professional baseball pitcher for the Cincinnati Reds.

name: Kevin Zapata
description: Kevin Zapata is a Mexican football player who currently plays forward for Atlante. He is of Mexican and English descent.

name: Kevin Zeitler
description: Kevin Zeitler is an American football guard for the Cincinnati Bengals of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football for the University of Wisconsin-Madison, and earned All-American honors. He was selected by the Bengals in the first round of the 2012 NFL Draft, and was considered one of the best guard prospects in 2012.

name: Kevon Carter
description: Kevon Carter (born 14 November 1983) is an international soccer player from Trinidad and Tobago who plays professionally for Defence Force as a forward.

name: Kevon Clement
description: Kevon Clement (born October 23, 1983 in Trinidad) is a Trinidad and Tobago football player, who plays as a midfielder for United Petrotrin.

name: Kevon Cooper
description: Kevon Cooper (born 2 February 1989) is a cricketer from Trinidad and Tobago. He plays for Trinidad and Tobago as well as for the Chittagong Kings in the Bangladesh Premier League. He was also signed up to play in the Indian Premier League by Rajasthan Royals during the 2012 auction.

name: Kevon Harris
description: Kevon Harris (born 1 June 1981) is a Jamaican footballer who played one season in the USL First Division and earned one cap with the Jamaica national football team.

name: Khader Yousef
description: Khader Youssef Abu Hamad simply known as Khader Youssef is a Palestinian footballer currently playing for Tarji Wadi Al-Nes of the WBPL as a midfielder. He received his first national team cap for Palestine in 2008 against Jordan in the first FIFA-sanctioned match held in Palestine since the 1930s. He has since played for Palestine at the 2010 WAFF Championship, the qualifying rounds of the 2010 Challenge Cup, 2012 AFC Challenge Cup, and in 2014 World Cup qualifying.

name: Khairan Eroza Razali
description: Khairan Eroza Razali Malaysian footballer currently playing for Penang FA in Malaysia FAM League. He plays as a defensive midfielder. His previous club is Kelantan and Pahang.

name: Khairul Azahar Eidros
description: Khairul Azahar Eidros (born 10 May 1986 in Muar is a Malaysian footballer currently playing for Sarawak FA in Malaysia Super League.

description: Khaled Afarah (born 21 January 1974) is a Yemeni football Defender and Club Al-Tilal.

name: Khaled Al-Awadhi
description: Khaled Al-Awadhi (born 13 September 1964) is a Kuwaiti fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil events at the 1980, 1984 and 1988 Summer Olympics.

name: Khaled Al-Shemmari
description: Khaled Al-Shemmari is a Kuwaitian football Goalkeeper who played for Kuwait in the 1984 Asian Cup.

name: Khaled Al-Zylaeei
description: Khaled Al-Zylaeei (born 1987) is a Saudi Arabian football (soccer) player who currently plays as a midfielder for Al-Nassr. He joined Al-Nassr coming from Abha in the summer of 2009 for SR 800,000. {{#invoke: Navbox | navbox }}

name: Khaled Al Fadhli

name: Khaled Al Shammari

name: Khaled Baleid
description: Khaled Baleid (born 2 November 1986) is a Yemeni football Midfield who is currently playing for Al Tilal Aden. He was also a member of the Yemen national under-17 football team. Baleid played for Yemen at the 2003 FIFA U-17 World Championship in Finland.

name: Khaled El-Ghandour
description: Khaled El-Ghandour (born 27 July 1970) is an Egyptian football Midfielder and Club El-Zamalek، One of the most leader of the team win trophies in the history of El-Zamalek. El-Ghandour scored many goals during his career, as that of the professional Ghandour short trip in the club Kazma .

name: Khaled Fahd Al-Rasheed
description: Khaled Fahd Al-Rasheed (born 1965) is a Saudi Arabian fencer. He competed in the individual foil event at the 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Khaled Gahwji
description: Khaled Gahwji [خالد قهوجي in Arabic] (born 1975) is a Saudi football player. He currently plays for AL-Rbeea.

name: Khaled Gasmi
description: Khaled Gasmi (born 8 April 1953) is a Tunisian football midfielder who played for Tunisia in the 1978 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Club Athlétique Bizertin.

name: Khaled Haj Othman
description: Khaled Haj Othman is a Syrian football goalkeeper. He currently plays for Al-Ittihad, which competes in the Syrian Premier League the top division in Syria, wearing the number 13 jersey for Al-Ittihad and for the Syrian national football team he wears the number 22 shirt.

name: Khaled Khalaila
description: Khaled Khalaila is a footballer playing for Bnei Sakhnin in the Israeli Premier League.

name: Khaled Salem
description: Khaled Salem is a Palestinian professional football player signed to Hebron-based Shabab Al-Dhahrieh of the West Bank Premier League. He is known for his goalscoring with Palestine's national team, scoring twice against Bahrain in 2012 Olympic Qualifying.

name: Khalid Al-Ghamdi
description: Khalid Al-Ghamdi [خالد الغامدي in Arabic] (born 7 June 1988) is a Saudi football player. He currently plays for Al-Nassr FC Club.

name: Khalid Al Romaihi
description: Khalid Al Rowaihi (15 December 1972 - 14 March 1993) was a Saudi Arabian footballer who played for Al-Watani club and Al-Ahli club. He was born in Tabuk (north city) on 15 December 1972 his father from Saudi Arabia and his mother from Jordan.

name: Khalid Askri
description: Khalid Askri is a Moroccan football goalkeeper who plays for Chabab Rif Al Hoceima. He played for FAR Rabat for over 12 years. Throne Cup Incident During the Moroccan Throne Cup semi-finals of 2009, Askri conceded a controversial goal by the opposition's forward, after the claimed "save" which lead the ball inside the net shortly afterwards.

name: Khalid Muftah
description: Khalid Muftah (born 2 July 1992 in Al Wakrah) is a Qatari international footballer who plays professionally for Lekhwiya, as a defender. He also currently plays for the Qatar national team as well as the Qatar U23 team. He has a brother, Yousef Muftah, who is also a footballer.

name: Khalid Sekkat
description: Khalid Sekkat is a Moroccan footballer who is currently attached to French club Stade de Reims. He also plays for the Moroccan national team.

name: Khalil Bani Attiah
description: Khalil Zaid Bani Attiah (born in 1991) is a Jordanian football player who is a Winger for Al-Faisaly, Jordan U-22, and the Jordan national football team. He has a younger brother named Nourideen Bani Attiah, who plays as a goalkeeper for Jordan U-19.

name: Khalil Boukedjane
description: Khalil Boukedjane (born January 27, 1981 in El Biar) is an Algerian footballer. He currently plays for CR Belouizdad in the Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1.

name: Khalil Kallas
description: Khalil Kallas (born 1 July 1942) is a Lebanese fencer. He competed in the individual épée event at the 1968 Summer Olympics.

name: Khama Billiat
description: Khama Billiat (born 19 August 1990 in Harare) is a Zimbabwean professional footballer who currently plays as a midfielder for South African Premier Soccer League club Ajax Cape Town and the Zimbabwe national team.

name: Khari Samuel
description: Khari Iman Mitchell Samuel (born October 14, 1976) is a former American football linebacker who played with the Chicago Bears and Detroit Lions in the National Football League. He played college football at Massachusetts.

name: Kheïreddine Madoui
description: Kheïreddine Madoui (born March 27, 1977 in Sétif) is an Algerian football manager, former player, and current assistant manager of ES Sétif under Alain Geiger. As a player, he spent his entire career between his hometown club of ES Sétif and CR Belouizdad. He also had 12 caps and 3 goals for the Algerian National Team.

name: Kheeston Randall
description: Kheeston Randall (born May 7, 1990) is an American football defensive tackle for the Miami Dolphins. He played college football at Texas. He is considered one of the best defensive tackle prospects for the 2012 NFL Draft.

name: Kheirredine Madoui
description: Kheirredine Madoui (born March 27, 1977) is an Algerian football player. He has played for Algeria national team.

name: Khemais Labidi
description: Khemais Labidi (born 30 August 1950) is a Tunisian football midfielder who played for Tunisia in the 1978 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Jeunesse Sportive Kairouanaise.

name: Khin Maung Lwin
description: Khin Maung Lwin (Burmese: ခင်မောင်လွင်; born 27 December 1988 in Lanmadaw Township) is a Burmese footballer. He is the current captain of the Myanmar national football team.

name: Khoun Laboravy
description: Khoun Laboravy (born August 25, 1988 in Cambodia) is a footballer for Preah Khan Reach in Cambodian League. He plays as a Striker for club.

name: Khris Middleton
description: James Khristian "Khris" Middleton (born August 12, 1991 in Charleston, South Carolina) is an American professional basketball player who currently plays for the Detroit Pistons of the National Basketball Association (NBA). Middleton was selected by the Pistons with the 39th pick of the 2012 NBA draft. He attended Porter-Gaud School, where he was coached by John Pearson. As a junior and senior, he was named South Carolina Player of the year, and was a McDonald's All-American nominee. Middleton chose to matriculate at Texas A&M University, where he started the majority of the games in his freshman year. In his sophomore season, he was named to the All-Big 12 Second Team after leading the Aggies in scoring at a 14.4 point per game clip.

name: Khristo Etropolski
description: Khristo Etropolski (born 18 March 1959) is a Bulgarian fencer. He competed in the individual and team sabre events at the 1980 and 1988 Summer Olympics. He is the twin brother of Vasil Etropolski, who also fenced for Bulgaria at the Olympics.

name: Khristo Khristov
description: Khristo Khristov (Bulgarian: Христо Христов; born 17 April 1951) is a Bulgarian fencer. He competed in the team sabre events at the 1972 and 1976 Summer Olympics.

name: Khuda Bakhsh
description: Khuda Bakhsh (born 10 January 1980) is a Pakistani footballer, who is a member of Pakistan national football team. Bakhsh is a forward who earned his first international cap in 2003 as a substitute, but is wasn’t until 2009 when he picked his first full cap.

name: Khumo Motlhabane
description: Khumo Motlhabane (born 17 February 1981) is a Botswanan footballer. He currently plays for Uniao Flamengo Santos FC in the Mascom Premier League.

name: Khursheed Aslam
description: Khursheed Aslam (April 6, 1936 – 1993) was a field hockey player from Pakistan. He is a gold medalist from 1960 Summer Olympics.

name: Khyzyr Appayev
description: Khyzyr Khakimovich Appayev (Russian: Хызыр Хакимович Аппаев; born January 27, 1990) is a Russian football striker of Balkar descent who currently plays for FC Rotor Volgograd, on loan from FC Krasnodar. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Druzhba Maykop on April 17, 2011 in a game against FC Taganrog. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League for FC Krylia Sovetov Samara on March 6, 2012 in a game against FC Amkar Perm.

name: Kial Stewart
description: Kial Douglas Stewart, OAM is an Australian Paralympic tandem cyclist, who was Anthony Biddle's pilot at the 2004 Athens Games. At the games, he won a gold medal in the Men's 1 km Time Trial Tandem B1–3 event, for which he received a Medal of the Order of Australia, and a bronze medal in the Men's Sprint Tandem B1–3 event.

name: Kiante Tripp
description: Kiante Tripp (born October 7, 1987 in Atlanta, Georgia) is an American football defensive tackle for the Cleveland Browns of the National Football League. He was signed to Cleveland's active roster on November 25, 2011. He was signed by the Atlanta Falcons as an undrafted free agent in 2011. He played college football for the University of Georgia.

name: Kibonge Mafu
description: Joseph Kibongé Mafu (born 12 February 1945) is a Congolese football midfielder who played for Zaire in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for AS Vita Club.

name: Kid McLaughlin
description: James Anson "Kid" McLaughlin (April 12, 1888 – July 12, 1934) was a center fielder in Major League Baseball. He played for the Cincinnati Reds in 1914.

name: Kidumu Mantantu
description: Raoul Albert Kidumu Mantantu (born 17 November 1946) is a Congolese football midfielder who played for Zaire in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for SC Imana.

name: Kieran Culhane
description: Kieran Culhane was a Gaelic footballer from Co Kerry. He played with the Kerry senior team in the late 80's and early 90's. He won a Munster Championship medal at full back in 1991. He played club football with his local Ballylongford team. He won North Kerry Senior Football Championship titles with them in 1993 and 2000. References

name: Kieran Dixon
description: Kieran Dixon (born 22 August 1992 in Hackney) is a professional rugby league footballer, playing at club level for Hemel Stags, and Harlequins/London Broncos, as a Wing.

name: Kieran Fitzgerald (Gaelic footballer)
description: Kieran Fitzgerald is a Gaelic footballer from County Galway, Republic of Ireland. He was played senior inter-county football for Galway between 2000 and 2011. He also plays football with his local club Corofin. He has won one All Ireland medal in 2001 and an All Star the same year. He was named captain of the Galway football team in 2007 and made his debut in the International Rules competition in 2006.

name: Kieran Trippier
description: Kieran John Trippier (born 19 September 1990) is an English footballer who currently plays for Burnley.

name: Kieren Keane

name: Kieron Bernard

name: Kierrie Johnson
description: Kierrie Johnson (born August 4, 1988 in Houston, Texas) is a Canadian football wide receiver who currently plays for the Saskatchewan Roughriders of the Canadian Football League. Johnson signed as a free agent with the BC Lions on May 26, 2011. He played college football for the Houston Cougars. Johnson was released by the Lions on Oct. 25, 2012. Johnson signed with the Saskatchewan Roughriders on Nov. 10, 2012.

name: Kieza
description: Welker Marçal de Almeida, known as Kieza (born on September 24, 1986 in Vitória) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Shanghai Shenxin.

name: Kijuan Franks
description: Kijuan Franks (born 31 May 1981) is a Bermudian international footballer who plays club football for Devonshire Cougars, as a defender.

name: Kikas
description: Luís Filipe Gomes Almeida (born 12 January 1991) known as Kikas, is a Portuguese footballer who plays for Sporting Clube de Portugal B as a midfielder.

name: Kike Rodríguez
description: Enrique Rodríguez Castillo (born September 6, 1991), commonly known as Kike Rodríguez, is a Peruvian footballer who plays as a center back. He currently plays for Colegio Nacional de Iquitos.

name: Kilasu Massamba
description: Kilasu Massamba (born 22 December 1950) is a Congolese football midfielder who played for Zaire in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for AS Dragons.

name: Kilian Keller

name: Kim Böling
description: Kim Böling (born 4 February 1992) is a Finnish footballer who represents Vaasan Palloseura of Veikkausliiga.

name: Kim Beom-Jun
description: Kim Beom-Jun (Hangul: 김범준; born 14 July 1988) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a Midfielder for Pohang Steelers in the K-League.

name: Kim Bong-Man
description: Kim Bong-Man (born 7 April 1963) is a South Korean fencer. He competed in the team épée event at the 1984 Summer Olympics.

name: Kim Carroll (footballer)
description: Kim Carroll (born 2 September 1987) is an Australian football (soccer) player currently playing in the Danish Elitedivisionen for Fortuna Hjørring, with whom she shas also played the Champions League. She previously played in the W-League for Brisbane Roar, and she is a member of the Australian national team since 2005, winning the 2010 Asian Cup and taking part in the 2011 World Cup.

name: Kim Dong-Chan (born 1981)
description: Kim Dong-Chan (born December 19, 1981) is a South Korean footballer who plays for Indonesia Super League side, Persita Tangerang, primarily as a forward.

name: Kim Dong-Hee
description: Kim Dong-Hee (Hangul: 김동희; born 6 May 1989) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a striker for Giravanz Kitakyushu in the J. League Division 2.

name: Kim English (basketball)
description: Kim English Jr. (born September 24, 1988) is an American professional basketball player who currently plays for the Detroit Pistons of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He was selected by the Pistons with the 44th pick in the 2012 NBA Draft. He played college basketball for the University of Missouri.

name: Kim Hwang-Ho
description: Kim Hwang-Ho is a Korean football Goalkeeper who played for South Korea in the 1980 Asian Cup. He also played for Auto Insurance and Korean Navy

name: Kim Hyun
description: Kim Hyun (Hangul: 김현; born 3 May 1993) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a striker for Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors in the K-League.

name: Kim Jae-Hoon
description: Kim Jae-Hoon (Hangul: 김재훈; born 21 February 1988) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a Forward for Daejeon Citizen in the K-League.

name: Kim Jeffrey Kurniawan
description: Kim Jeffrey Kurniawan (born March 23, 1990) is an Indonesian football player, currently playing for the Indonesian football club Persema Malang. He gained fame in Indonesia after the Indonesian Football Association decided to naturalize Kurniawan for their "naturalization program. " On December 6, 2010, he officially holds an Indonesian passport, becoming the first naturalized Indonesian football player after Cristian Gonzáles. Kurniawan will enter the player selection for the under-23 team, who will participate in the 2012 Olympics qualification and the 2011 Southeast Asian Games. Kim speaks German, English, Indonesian, Chinese and Javanese.

name: Kim Jin-Hwan
description: Kim Jin-Hwan (Korean: 김진환; born 1 March 1989) is a South Korean football Defender, who plays for Gangwon FC in the K-League.

name: Kim Jong-Min
description: Kim Jong-Min (born August 11, 1992) is a South Korean football player.

name: Kim Jong-Pil
description: Kim Jong-Pil is a Korean football Defender who played for South Korea in the 1980 Asian Cup. He also played for Korea Electronics

name: Kim Jong-Soo
description: Kim Jong-Soo (Hangul: 김종수; born 25 July 1986) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a centre back for Gyeongnam FC in the K-League.

name: Kim Joon-Tae (footballer)
description: Kim Joon-Tae (Hangul: 김준태; Hanja: 金俊泰, born 31 May 1985) is a South Korean football player who plays as a midfielder for South Korean club that Korea National League side Changwon City FC. He started his career at Korea National League side Changwon City FC. In 17 November 2009, Gangwon called him as extra order at 2010 K-League Draft. His first K-League match was against Seongnam Ilhwa Chunma in Seongnam that Gangwon lose by 0-3 in away game on 27 February 2010. In July 2010, he move back to his previous club, Changwon City FC.

name: Kim Karlsson
description: Kim Karlsson is a Swedish professional ice hockey winger who currently plays for Luleå HF of the Elitserien.

name: Kim Ki Whang
description: Kim Ki Whang (1920 – September 16, 1993), also known in the United States as Ki Whang Kim, was a Korean martial arts grandmaster. He was Chairman in the US of the Tang Soo Do Moo Duk Kwan Association, Chairman of the US Olympic Taekwondo team and helped unify several Korean martial arts into the overall style of taekwondo.

name: Kim Kyung-tae (ice hockey)
description: Kim Kyung-tae (Korean: 김경태 born April 4, 1979 in Seoul) was a Korean professional ice hockey left winger. He played five years for Anyang Halla having joined the team when it was known as Winia. Kim spent the '07-'08 and '08-'09 seasons doing his military service.

name: Kim Seok
description: Kim Seok (born 9 September 1991) is a South Korean football player who plays as a forward.

name: Kim Seok-Won
description: Kim Seok-Won is a Korean football Forward who played for South Korea in the 1984 Asian Cup. He also played for Yukong Kokkiri

name: Kim Soo-Beom
description: Kim Soo-Beom is a South Korean footballer who plays as defender for Gwangju FC in the K-League.

name: Kim Strömberg
description: Kim Strömberg is a Finnish ice hockey player who currently plays professionally in Finland for Tappara of the SM-liiga.

name: Kim Sung-Gan
description: Kim Sung-Gan was a Korean football player. He has played for Japan national team.

name: Kim Sung-Min (footballer)
description: Kim Sung-Min (Hangul: 김성민; born 19 April 1985) is a South Korean footballer who plays as a Forward for Sangju Sangmu Phoenix in the K-League.

name: Kim Tiilikainen
description: Kim Tiilikainen (born 8 July 1975) is a former professional tennis player from Finland. Tiilikainen qualified for his only Grand Slam in 1996, at the French Open. The only Finn in the draw, he was defeated by world no. 27 Andrea Gaudenzi in the opening round. From 1995 to 2003, Tiilikainen appeared in nine Davis Cup ties for Finland. He won nine matches, all in singles. His best performances include a win over Anastasios Vasiliadis in the fifth and deciding rubber against Greece in 1997 and when he came from two sets down to beat Italian Davide Sanguinetti in 2002. He is the current coach of the Finland Davis Cup team and Polish tennis player Jerzy Janowicz.

name: Kim Turner (footballer)
description: Kimberley "Kim" Turner (born 1 February 1985 in Belfast) is an Northern Irish footballer, who currently plays for Blackburn Rovers Ladies and Northern Ireland as a midfielder.

name: Kim Yong-Guk
description: Kim Yong-Guk (born 14 December 1966) is a South Korean fencer. He competed in the individual and team foil events at the 1988 and 1996 Summer Olympics.

name: Kim Yung-Kil
description: Kim Yung-Kil (born 29 January 1944) is a North Korean football defender who played for North Korea in the 1966 FIFA World Cup. He also played for Rodongja Sports Team.

name: Kimami Sitauti
description: Kimami Sitauti (born 12 April 1991) is an Australian rugby union player. He plans to join the Rebels for the 2013 Super Rugby season. His playing position is right-winger. He is of Tongan heritage.

name: Kimberly Couts
description: Kimberly Couts is a professional American tennis player playing in the ITF Women's Circuit. On April 20, 2009, she reached her highest WTA singles ranking of 259. On December 21, 2009, she reached her highest WTA doubles ranking of 165.

name: Kimberly Yokers
description: Kimberly Yokers (born 24 May 1982, in Seattle, Washington) is an American football midfielder who currently plays for FC Gold Pride of Women's Professional Soccer and was a former member of the United States U-21 women's national soccer team. For the California Storm, Yokers played 2 times in 2004 and 9 times in 2007. She scored 3 goals in 14 appearances in 2008.

name: Kimoi Alexander
description: Kimoi Alexander (born November 13, 1985) is an Antiguan footballer who currently plays for Antigua Barracuda FC in the USL Professional Division.

name: Kingshuk Debnath
description: Kingshuk Debnath is an Indian footballer who is currently playing for Mohammedan Sporting Club in the I-League 2nd Division as a Defender.

name: Kinmont Hoitsma
description: Kinmont Hoitsma (born 10 April 1934) is an American fencer. He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1956 Summer Olympics.

name: Kinnie Laisné
description: Kinnie Laisné (born July 11, 1989) is a professional French tennis player. Her highest WTA singles ranking is 295th, which she reached on August 17, 2009. Her career high in doubles is 383st, which she reached on December 7, 2009. Laisné was born in France and is a right-handed player.

name: Kinoto Saito
description: Kinoto Saito (born July 8, 1976) is a Japanese football player. He plays for Ganju Iwate.

name: Kip Dowd
description: James Joseph Dowd (1889–1960), was a Major League Baseball pitcher who played for the 1910 Pittsburgh Pirates in one game on July 5, 1910. He pitched two innings and gave up four runs, all unearned. He attended College of the Holy Cross and played in the minor leagues from 1911-1915. He was the grandfather of actress Ann Dowd.

name: Kirby Fabien
description: Kirby Fabien (born September 10, 1990 in Calgary, Alberta) is a Canadian football offensive lineman who is currently playing CIS football with the Calgary Dinos. He was selected seventh overall by the BC Lions in the 2012 CFL Draft. On May 28, 2012, the Calgary Dinos announced that he would be returning to play another year with them. After the 2011 CIS season, he was ranked as the 15th best player in the Canadian Football League’s Amateur Scouting Bureau final rankings for players eligible in the 2012 CFL Draft, and ninth by players in Canadian Interuniversity Sport.

name: Kirenia Ballar
description: Kirenia Ballar Bell (born in Havana) is a female beach volleyball player from Cuba, who participated in the NORCECA Beach Volleyball Circuit in 2007, playing with Ion Canet and 2009, with Nirian Sinal. At the 2nd. ALBA Games she won the silver medal, playing with Nirian Sinal. She also won the gold medal at Cuban National Games in 2008, playing with Kirenia Reina.

name: Kiril Andonov
description: Kiril Andonov (born 1 November 1967) is a retired Bulgarian football player. Andonov played for Vanspor in during the Turkish Super Lig 1996–97 season. He also played for PFC Botev Plovdiv. Andonov played for Bulgaria at the 1987 FIFA World Youth Championship in Chile.

name: Kiril Andreev
description: Kiril Andreev (born 29 December 1983) is a Bulgarian football player, currently playing for FC Vihren Sandanski as a midfielder

name: Kiril Hristov

name: Kiril Metkov
description: Kiril Metkov (born 1 February 1965 in Sofia) is a Bulgarian ex-football player. Metkov was a good passer and a skilled dribbler. He started his domestic football career in 1983, and during his career played for Lokomotiv Sofia, CSKA Sofia, Gamba Osaka and Slavia Sofia, before retiring in 1996.

name: Kirill Marushchak
description: Kirill Valeryevich Marushchak (Russian: Кирилл Валерьевич Марущак; born May 16, 1985 in Kaliningrad) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays in the Russian First Division for FC Baltika Kaliningrad.

name: Kirill Moryganov
description: Kirill Andreyevich Moryganov (Russian: Кирилл Андреевич Морыганов; born February 7, 1991) is a Russian professional football player. He plays for FC Oktan Perm. He is an identical twin brother of Artyom Moryganov.

name: Kirill Muzyka
description: Kirill Aleksandrovich Muzyka (Russian: Кирилл Александрович Музыка; born November 22, 1990) is a Russian professional football player. He plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Yakutiya Yakutsk. He played for the main squad of FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok in the Russian Cup.

name: Kirill Petrushin
description: Kirill Sergeyevich Petrushin (Russian: Кирилл Сергеевич Петрушин; born October 25, 1987) is a Russian professional football player. Currently, he plays for FC Zvezda Ryazan.

description: Kirill Mikhailovich Podpruzhnikov (Russian: Кирилл Михайлович Подпружников; born January 31, 1984) is a Russian professional football player. He last played for FC Karelia Petrozavodsk.

name: Kirill Pogrebnyak

He is a brother of Pavel Pogrebnyak. His other brother, Nikolai, is also on the roster of FC Tom Tomsk, but is yet to make his professional debut.

name: Kirill Pushkin
description: Kirill Sergeyevich Pushkin (Russian: Кирилл Сергеевич Пушкин; born February 9, 1993) is a Russian football midfielder, who currently plays for FC Avangard Kursk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Avangard Kursk on April 17, 2012 in a game against FC Metallurg-Oskol Stary Oskol.

name: Kirill Romanov
description: Kirill Valeryevich Romanov (Russian: Кирилл Валерьевич Романов; born October 27, 1980) is a Russian professional football player. He plays in the Russian Second Division for FC Zenit-Izhevsk Izhevsk.

name: Kirill Rybakov
description: Kirill Nikolayevich Rybakov (Russian: Кирилл Николаевич Рыбаков; born May 11, 1969) is a retired Russian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet Top League in 1989 for FC Lokomotiv Moscow. He played 1 game in the UEFA Cup 1993–94 for FC Dynamo Moscow.

name: Kirill Shestakov
description: Kirill Sergeyevich Shestakov (Russian: Кирилл Сергеевич Шестаков; born June 19, 1985) is a Russian professional footballer. As of 2009, he plays for FC Stavropol. His father Sergei Shestakov was also a professional footballer.

name: Kirill Sidelnikov
description: Kirill Sidelnikov (born August 17, 1988) is a Russian professional mixed martial artist and grappler, fighting out of Stary Oskol, the same hometown as Fedor Emelianenko with whom he is a training partner. He fights for M-1 Mixfight.

name: Kirill Sidorenko
description: Kirill Sidorenko (born March 30, 1983) is a Russian professional ice hockey forward. He was selected by Dallas Stars in the 6th round (180th overall) of the 2002 NHL Entry Draft. Sidorenko played in the Russian Superleague with Novosibirsk Siber during the 2002-03 season, and with Krylja Sovetov during the 2006-07 season.

name: Kirill Sukhoversha
description: Kirill Alekseyevich Sukhoversha (Russian: Кирилл Алексеевич Суховерша; born April 20, 1986) is a Russian professional football player who last played for FC Yakutiya Yakutsk.

name: Kirill Suslov

name: Kirill Tulupov

name: Kirill Turchin

name: Kirill Voronshchikov
description: Kirill Andreyevich Voronshchikov (Russian: Кирилл Андреевич Воронщиков; born June 30, 1991) is a football forward who last played for FC Nosta Novotroitsk. He made his debut in the Russian Second Division for FC Sokol Saratov on June 23, 2011 in a game against FC Lokomotiv Liski.

name: Kirill Zaika
description: Kirill Anatolyevich Zaika (Russian: Кирилл Анатольевич Заика; born October 7, 1992) is a Russian professional football player currently playing for FC Taganrog on loan from FC Rostov.

name: Kirk Hershey
description: Kirk Hershey was a player in the National Football League. He was drafted in the seventeenth round of the 1941 NFL Draft by the Cleveland Rams and would split that season between the Rams and the Philadelphia Eagles.

name: Kirk Shermer
description: Kirk Shermer is a retired American soccer goalkeeper who was the 1983 Major Indoor Soccer League Rookie of the Year. Shermer attended Fresno State University where he played on the men’s soccer from 1978 to 1981. He was a 1981 Second Team All American. On December 14, 1981, the Tampa Bay Rowdies selected Shermer in the fourth round of the North American Soccer League college draft. He did not sign with the Rowdies. In 1982, the Los Angeles Lazers selected Shermer in the Major Indoor Soccer League draft. He rapidly asserted himself as a top goalkeeper and was named the 1983 MISL Rookie of the Year. He began the 1983-1984 season, played eleven games, then retired.

name: Kirk Stephens
description: Kirk William Stephens (born 27 February 1955 in Coventry), is an English former football player, best known for his time at Luton Town and Coventry City.

name: Kirsten Moore-Towers
description: Kirsten Moore-Towers is a Canadian pair skater. With partner Dylan Moscovitch, she is the 2011 Canadian national champion.

name: Kirsty McBride
description: Kirsty McBride (born 9 September 1985) is a Scottish football defender or midfielder, who plays for Celtic in the Scottish Women's Premier League. She has represented the Scotland women's national football team more than 50 times at senior level.

name: Kirsty Pealling
description: Kirsty Pealling (born 14 April 1975) is a former footballer who spent her entire club career with Arsenal Ladies. She also represented England at full international level.

name: Kirstyn Pearce

name: Kirtley Baker
description: Kirtley Baker (June 24, 1869 – April 15, 1927), was a pitcher in Major League Baseball. He played for the Baltimore Orioles, Pittsburgh Pirates, and Washington Senators.

name: Kishor Patel
description: Kishor Patel (born 16 March 1982) is a former English cricketer. Patel was a right-handed batsman who played primarily as a wicketkeeper. Patel represented the Worcestershire Cricket Board in a single List A match against Staffordshire in the 1st round of the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his only List A match, he wasn't required to bat and in the field he took a single catch.

name: Kisso Kawamuro
description: Kisso Kawamuro was a pioneering Japanese racing cyclist. His name is also rendered "Kiso" ("Kisou" is the correct romanization in modified Hepburn).

name: Kita Sysavanh
description: Kita Sysavanh (born 19 June 1983) is a Lao professional football player. An attacking midfielder who plays on the wings, he is known for his long range shooting, crossing and passing. Sysavanh made his debut for Laos in 2007 and has since become a mainstay in the Laos midfield.

name: Kitwana Jones
description: Kitwana Shaloyd Jones is a Canadian football defensive end who is currently a free agent. He most recently played for the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League. He was signed by the Saskatchewan Roughriders as an undrafted free agent in 2005. Jones has also played professionally for the Edmonton Eskimos. He played college football at the University of North Carolina and Hampton University.

name: Kiyohiro Hirabayashi
description: Kiyohiro Hirabayashi is a Japanese football player who plays for Zweigen Kanazawa

name: Kiyonobu Okajima
description: Kiyonobu Okajima (born June 30, 1971) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Kiyoshi Hatanaka
description: Kiyoshi Hatanaka {{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=|size=|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}}StatisticsReal name Kiyoshi HatanakaRated at super bantamweightHeight 5 ft 7 in Nationality JapaneseBorn (1967-03-07) 7 March 1967 (age 46){{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}}Nishikasugai District (later merged into Kitanagoya), Aichi, Japan{{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}}Stance orthodoxBoxing recordTotal fights 25Wins 22Wins by KO 15Losses 2 Kiyoshi Hatanaka is a retired Japanese boxer who is a former WBC super bantamweight champion. Hatanaka began karate at the first grade of elementary school, and won the Japanese championship in the juvenile division at its sixth grade and the first grade of junior high school. In addition, he began football at the fourth grade of elementary school, and was scouted by a prestigious high school. He also set an interval record in the local ekiden race at the age of a junior high school student. At that time, informed from an acquaintance that a professional boxer got paid 30,000 yen per match in the amount of time, he became interested in boxing and joined Matsuda Boxing Gym. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} He compiled an amateur record of 26–5 (21 KOs){{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} before turning professional. Hatanaka made his professional debut with a first round knockout victory in November 1984, at the age of a high school student. 　He won the annual Japanese boxing series, All-Japan Rookie King Tournament in the super flyweight division in March 1986. He captured the Japanese super flyweight title at the Korakuen Hall in February 1987. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} In his first world title shot against WBC super flyweight champion Gilberto Román in September 1988, Hatanaka entered the ring of the Nagoya Rainbow Hall with full smile. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}}{{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} Román floored Hatanaka in the first round, but was deducted a point for a low blow late in the same round. Though Hatanaka was given a full five minutes to recover, he was hit below the belt again in the third round and took three minutes' rest. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}}{{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} As the rounds rolled on, Román kept his pace to retain his title via a unanimous decision. Hatanaka was so nervous that he remembered almost nothing after the fight. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} After the defeat, Hatanaka decided to become a world champion from his beloved hometown of Nagoya by any means necessary. It was no longer a question of money for him. Hatanaka needed a reliable trainer. He asked Toshihide Tsutsumi three times who once worked as a trainer at Matsuda Boxing Gym, and was at last accepted. He trained with Tsutsumi and did not get anxious anymore. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} Hatanaka moved up two weight divisions and fought against Pedro Rubén Décima for the WBC super bantamweight title at the Nagoya International Exhibition Hall, aka Port Messe Nagoya, on February 3, 1991. He was floored in the first round, but felt calm enough to listen to Tsutsumi's instruction between rounds. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} After knocking down Décima four times in the fourth round, he sent him to the canvas two more times in the seventh and eighth rounds before the referee stopped the bout. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} In his first defense against Daniel Zaragoza on June 14 of that year, Hatanaka was cut on the corner of his left eye from an accidental head butt in the fourth round, and the referee took a point away from Zaragoza. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} From the seventh or eighth round, Hatanaka had triple vision in his right eye, and the blood flowed into his left eye. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} Finally, Zaragoza was crowned the new champion via a split decision in front of 9,000 spectators at the Nagoya Rainbow Hall. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} In 2007, ESPN wrote it as many Asians' consideration, "the best fight of the decade". Although Hatanaka desired a rematch with Zaragoza, he suffered from ophthalmoplegia caused by this fight, and retired as a boxer after four months. {{#invoke:Footnotes|sfn}} Currently he is the president of Hatanaka Boxing Gym in Nagoya. Hatanaka Promotions has provided a boxing television program Soul Fighting on Chubu-Nippon Broadcasting. Toshihide Tsutsumi who was presented with the tenth Eddie Townsend Award in 1999, serves as a trainer at that gym.

name: Kiyotaka Miyoshi

His was the younger brother of Brann legend Roald «Kniksen» Jensen.

name: Klaus Allisat
description: Klaus Allisat (born 8 May 1938) is a German fencer. He represented the Unified Team of Germany at the 1964 Summer Olympics and West Germany at the 1968 Summer Olympics in the team sabre events.

name: Klaus Dietrich
