description: Klaus Heinlein (born 23 December 1953) is a German former professional footballer who played in Germany for SpVgg Greuther Fürth and in the North American Soccer League for the Edmonton Drillers.

name: Klaus Wischniewski
description: Klaus Wischniewski (born 8 December 1954) is a retired German football midfielder.

name: Kleber Rogerio do Carmo Silva
description: Kleber Rogerio do Carmo Silva (born April 14, 1981) is a former Brazilian football player.

name: Kleber Romero
description: Kleber Romero (born February 14, 1976) is a former Brazilian football player.

name: Kleiton Domingues
description: Kleiton Domingues Barbosa, known simply as Kleiton Domingues, (born 2 April 1988) is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays for Ituano, as an Attacking Midfielder. He is Leandro Domingues' brother, who is also a footballer.

name: Klemen Pretnar
description: Klemen Pretnar (born August 31, 1986) is a Slovenian ice hockey player. He participated at the 2011 IIHF World Championship as a member of the Slovenia men's national ice hockey team.

name: Kliment Nastoski
description: Kliment Nastoski is a Macedonian football midfielder playing with Anagennisi Epanomi in the Greek Football League. After playing in the youth teams of FK Partizan, he begin his senior career playing with another Serbian club FK Dinamo Vranje. In 2007, he returned to Macedonia and signed with Macedonian First League club FK Pobeda where he stayed two seasons. In summer 2009 he moved to FK Olimpik Sarajevo playing in the Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina, but next winter he moved to Slovenia, to NK Krško. Since January 2011 he will play with FK Metalurg Skopje in the Macedonian First League. In summer 2011 he moved to Albania, where he represented two clubs during the 2011–12 Albanian Superliga season, KS Pogradeci and Shkumbini Peqin. In summer 2012 he moved to Greece and joined Football League side Anagennisi Epanomi F.C.. He represented regularely the youth teams of Macedonia.

name: Kliment Taseski
description: Kliment Taseski (born 27 May 1991) is an Australian football (soccer) player, currently playing for Richmond SC in the Victorian Premier League.

name: Kline Gilbert
description: Kline Gilbert (November 22, 1930 – June 1987) was a professional American football offensive tackle in the National Football League. He played five seasons for the Chicago Bears (1953–1957).

name: Klodian Skënderi
description: Klodian Skënderi (born 12 January 1984) is an Albanian football player. The midfielder currently plays for KS Apolonia Fier.

name: Klondike (boxer)
description: Klondike (1 January 1878 - 3 February 1949) was an African American boxer billed as "The Black Hercules" who declared himself the black heavyweight champion (not to be confused with the World Colored Heavyweight Championship, which he officially fought for just once and unofficially another time). Born John Haines or John W. Haynes, the 6' tall Klondike fought out of Chicago as a heavyweight at a weight of 190 to 200 lbs. from 1898 to 1911. He took the nickname because he was supposed to be a great find. He made his pro boxing debut against future two-time colored heavyweight champ Frank Childs on 8 January 1898 at Chicago's 2nd Regiment Armory (a fight erroneously credited to lightweight Frank Young Haines). He was K.O. -ed by Childs. Later that month, on the 29th, Childs won the world colored heavyweight title from Bob Armstrong and his first defense of the title was against Klondike on February 26. Childs won by a T.K.O. in the fourth round of the scheduled six-round bout when the referee stopped the fight. The fought again four times, as African American boxers were forced to fight one another often due to the color bar. Childs won every fight. Klondike fought many of the top black heavyweights of his generation, including Johnson, the first black man to win the world heavyweight championship. Ironically, Klondike would first declare himself the black heavyweight champion after beating Johnson in the future world heavyweight champ's third pro fight at Chicago's Howard Theater on 8 May 1899. It was only Klondike's eighth pro bout, himself. According to the Chicago Tribune, "... Johnson knocked Haines down in Round one with an uppercut, and only the bell saved Klondyke... " Klondike and Johnson fought again twice, with one bout ending as a draw and the third with Johnson winning by a T.K.O.

name: Knuckles Nelson
description: Brendan Higgins (born September 26, 1963), best known by his ring name Knuckles Nelson is a retired American professional wrestler, promoter and trainer who wrestled throughout the North American independent circuit during the 1990s and 2000s. He competed in several regional promotions such as the Century Wrestling Alliance, the National Wrestling Alliance and the United States Wrestling Association. He also briefly appeared in World Championship Wrestling and the World Wrestling Federation as well as touring Japan as Super Destroyer between 1997 and 1999. He was a founding member of Tony Rumble's The Brotherhood, a "heel" stable which dominated NWA New England during the late 1990s, and which included Eric Sbraccia, Dukes Dalton and Rick Fuller. He and Sbraccia won the NWA World Tag Team Championship in 1998, and defended both the World and NWA New England titles with Sbraccia and other Brotherhood members in their home promotion for almost two years. Following Rumble's death, Nelson helped run NWA New England for a time and later became a full time booker and promoter for Wrestling Star Wars until his retirement in 2003. As head of "The Combat Zone" wrestling school, he was involved in training several independent wrestlers, most notably, Yankee Pro Wrestling veteran "Big Gun" Jim Sergeant.

name: Knud Børge Overgaard
description: Knud Børge Overgaard (March 21, 1918 – October 20, 1985) was a Danish amateur footballer who played 8 games for the Denmark national football team, and won a bronze medal at the 1948 Summer Olympics. He played his club football with B.93. Overgaard was an excellent wing half-back with good physicality and tackling ability. He started his career with Aarhus club AGF, but was not selected for the Danish national team, until he moved to Copenhagen club B.93. Overgaard got his international debut for Denmark in 1945, but had to compete with Børge Mathiesen, Ivan Jensen, and Viggo Jensen for the wing half-back spot. Just before the 1948 Summer Olympics, regular Danish defender Knud Bastrup-Birk was injured, and Overgaard was moved out of position to cover as a full-back. In a defensive pairing with Viggo Jensen, the two out-of-position players did better than expected, and Denmark won bronze medals at the tournament. Following the Olympics, Overgaard's international career ended.

name: Knud Bastrup-Birk
description: Knud Bastrup-Birk (12 December 1919 – 25 August 1973) was a Danish amateur footballer, who played 18 games for the Denmark national football team. Bastrup-Birk was born in Gentofte, and played club football with Akademisk Boldklub (AB). Bastrup-Birk was a talented boxer, a good rower, and an excellent 100 m sprinter and long jumper. He played as a full-back, but his footballing style was ahead of its time. He played almost as an attack-minded libero, dribbling and passing the ball upfield when he had dispossessed an opposing player, but the attacking fashion was criticized by the leaders of both AB and the national team. He made his international debut in 1943, but due to injury, he was an unused substitute in the Danish team that won bronze medals at the 1948 Summer Olympics. He played his last game for Denmark in 1951.

name: Knud Blak Jensen

name: Knut Dørum Lillebakk

name: Knut Hovel Heiaas
description: Knut Hovel Heiaas (born 21 April 1977) is a Norwegian football striker who currently plays for Nesodden IF. He hails from Dalefjerdingen. His first senior club was Strømmen, where he played from 1995 to 1999. Ahead of the 2000 season he joined Vålerenga IF, where he got five Norwegian Premier League games in 2000 and fourteen in 2002. After the 2002 season he joined Hønefoss BK. At the same time he rejected Moss FK, but he joined this club two years later. In late 2006 he spent time on loan at IL Hødd, and ahead of the 2007 season he moved permanently to Drøbak/Frogn IL. In 2009 he returned to his old club Strømmen. After the season he went on to Nesodden IF.

name: Knut Nordholm
description: Knut Nordholm (24 August 1904 – 5 January 1981) was a Swedish fencer. He competed in the team sabre event at the 1936 Summer Olympics.

name: Ko Quaye

name: Koen van der Biezen
description: Koen van der Biezen (born July 10, 1985 in Nuland) is a Dutch footballer who currently plays for German club Karlsruher SC.

name: Koffi Dan Kowa

name: Koji Funamoto
description: Koji Funamoto (船本幸路, born 12 August 1942) is a former Japanese footballer who played goalkeeper for the Toyo Kogyo football club from 1961 to 1975 and for the Japan national team from 1967 to 1975. Funamoto was born and raised in Hiroshima, Japan. He played youth football at Hiroshima University Fuzoku High School before starting his club career with Toyo. He and high school teammates were central figures in the golden era of football in Hiroshima from 1958 to 1972. Following his playing career, he coached goalkeepers for Toyo Kogyo and for the Japan national team, coached youth soccer in Hiroshima, and worked in the business office at the Mazda Motor Corporation (formerly Toyo Kogyo) until his retirement. After his retirement from Mazda, he served as match commissioner of the J League until 2007 and has served as match commissioner of the Japan Football League since 2008.

name: Koji Yoshinari
description: Koji Yoshinari (born May 19, 1974) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Kola Adedoyin
description: Kola Adedoyin (born 8 April 1991) is a British track and field athlete who competes in the triple jump and has a personal record of 16.50 metres. Kola is the 2012 & 2013 UK Indoor Champion.

name: Kolby LaCrone
description: Kolby LaCrone (born September 12, 1986 in Zanesville, Ohio) is an American soccer player for Dayton Dutch Lions in the USL Professional Division.

name: Kolnago Ferante
description: Antuna Kolnago Ferante (11 July 1907 in Split – 15 May 1969 in Belgrade) was a Croatian football player. He has one cap for the Yugoslav national team. Playing mostly as a central defender he started to play in the youth teams of HNK Hajduk Split but failed to debut in the first team. Afterwords, he moved to Zagreb where he signed with HŠK Concordia. It was while he was playing with SK Soko from Belgrade that he played his only match for the Yugoslav national team. It was on May 19, 1929 in Paris that Yugoslavia had archived its first win over the "tricolor" by 3-1 and Ferante´s brilliant exhibition on the match didn´t pass unnoticed, having earned him a call to join, together with Ivica Bek, Olympique de Marseille, where he would play two seasons. Between 1931 and 1938 he played with Rapid Bucharest in Romania. After a heavy injury, he retired and returned to Belgrade where he begin working as a bank employee.

name: Kolten Solomon
description: Kolten Solomon (born July 16, 1989 in Regina, Saskatchewan) is a professional Canadian football wide receiver for the Saskatchewan Roughriders of the Canadian Football League. He was attended the Roughriders' 2011 training camp but, following a training camp injury, he was released. After the completion of his junior career in 2011, Solomon signed with Saskatchewan on December 11, 2011. He was later released on May 11, 2012 and joined the Regina Rams of the CIS. He re-signed with the Roughriders on December 19, 2012. He played junior football for the Regina Thunder of the Canadian Junior Football League from 2009-2011.

name: Kompayak Porpramook

name: Konstantin Konoplyov

As of August 2009, he is a free agent. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2001 for FC Zenit St. Petersburg. He played 1 game for FC Zenit St. Petersburg in the UEFA Cup 2002–03.

name: Konstantin Kovalenko
description: Konstantin Valeryevich Kovalenko (Russian: Константин Валерьевич Коваленко; Belarusian: Канстанцін Валер'евіч Каваленка; born 2 February 1975 in Rahachow) is a Belarusian professional footballer. He made his professional debut in the Soviet Second League in 1991 for FC Kuban Barannikovsky. He played 1 game in the UEFA Cup 1996–97 for FC Spartak Moscow. His brother Andrei Kovalenko also played football professionally. On 27 October 2008 he punched referee Sergei Timofeyev in the face in the Russian Second Division game FC Sochi-04 - FC Olimpia Volgograd. He was banned from football for a year.

name: Konstantin Kozlov

name: Konstantin Kudryavtsev

Currently, he plays for FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast. He made his debut in the Russian Premier League in 2003 for FC Rotor Volgograd. He played 2 games in the UEFA Cup 2006–07 with FC Rubin Kazan.

name: Konstantin Yavorskiy

name: Konstantine Darsania
description: Konstantine Darsania (Georgian: მიხეილ აშვეთია; born 29 May 1984) is a Georgia footballer who currently is a free agent.

name: Konstantinos Efraimoglou
description: Konstantinos Efraimoglou is a male former tennis player from Greece. Efraimoglou represented his native country in the doubles competition at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, partnering Anastasios Bavelas. The pair was eliminated in the second round there. The right-hander Efraimoglou represented Greece in the Davis Cup from 1984–1996, posting a 10–10 record in singles and a 12–11 record in doubles in twenty-six ties played. Efraimoglou's highest ranking in singles was World No. 745, which he reached on March 18, 1985. His highest doubles ranking was World No. 854, which he reached on January 3, 1983.

name: Konstantinos Kotzias
description: Konstantinos Kotzias (Greek: Κωνσταντίνος Κοτζιάς; 1892–1951) was a Greek fencer. He competed at the 1912 and 1924 Summer Olympics. In 1934 he was elected Mayor of Athens. In the dictatorial Metaxas Regime, he served as Minister for the Capital District. Following the death of dictator Ioannis Metaxas in January 1941, he was sounded out by King George II of Greece to head a new cabinet, but refused. During the Axis Occupation of Greece, he lived in the United States. He was elected an MP for Athens in 1950 and was re-elected as the city's mayor in 1951, shortly before his death.

name: Konstantinos Kritikos
description: Konstantinos Kritikos (born October 21, 1991) is a Greek footballer who is a right-back defender for the Greek club Zakynthos and is on loan from Olympiacos FC. He is 1.86 metres tall. Kritikos has been loaned to Zakynthos for one year from Olympiacos.

name: Koray İçten
description: Koray İçten (born 24 August 1987) is a Turkish professional footballer who currently plays as a left back for Bucaspor in the Süper Lig.

name: Korey Lindsey
description: Korey Lindsey (born February 3, 1989) is an American football cornerback for the Washington Redskins of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted 207th overall by the Cincinnati Bengals in the 2011 NFL Draft. He played college football for the Southern Illinois University. He has also been a member of the Arizona Cardinals, Indianapolis Colts, and Jacksonville Jaguars.

name: Korkrirk Petchkongthong
description: Korkrirk Petchkongthong is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Sriracha in the Thailand Premier League.

name: Kory Blackwell
description: Kory L. Blackwell (born August 3, 1972) is a former American football cornerback who played with the New York Giants and the Cleveland Browns in the National Football League. He played college football at Massachusetts.

name: Kory Karlander

name: Kosala Kulasekara
description: Chamith Kosala Bandara Kulasekara (born 15 July 1985, in Mavanalle) is a Sri Lankan cricketer. He is an all-rounder, batting right-handed and bowling right-arm fast medium. He plays domestic cricket for the Nondescripts Cricket Club and the Ruhuna Rhinos. He has played in one Test and several One Day Internationals (ODIs) for Sri Lanka.

name: Kosawat Wongwailikit
description: Kosawat Wongwailikit is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Osotsapa in the Thailand Premier League.

name: Kosei Nakamura
description: Kosei Nakamura (born 5 April 1981) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Kosmas Tsilianidis
description: Kosmas Tsilianidis (Greek: Κοσμάς Τσιλιανίδης; born 9 May 1994) is a Greek footballer who currently plays for Aiginiakos in the Greek Football League 2 on loan from Iraklis 1908 FC.

name: Kostadin Adzhov
description: Kostadin Adzhov (Bulgarian: Костадин Аджов; born 19 May 1991) is a Bulgarian footballer, who currently plays as a forward for Septemvri Simitli.

name: Kostadin Bashov
description: Kostadin Ivanov Bashov (Bulgarian: Костадин Башов; born 26 November 1982 in Gotse Delchev) is a Bulgarian footballer who plays as a forward for AEP Paphos.

name: Kostadin Katsimerski
description: Kostadin Rosenov Katsimerski (Bulgarian: Костадин Кацимерски; born 7 February 1987 in Blagoevgrad) is a Bulgarian footballer who plays as a midfielder.

name: Kostadin Kostadinov
description: Kostadin Stefanov Kostadinov (Bulgarian: Костадин Стефанов Костадинов) (born 25 June 1959 in Plovdiv) is a retired Bulgarian football player. Kostadinov was a forward. During his career, he played for Trakia Plovdiv in Bulgaria and made 350 appearances in the Bulgarian championship, scoring 106 goals. Kostadinov also played for Bulgaria national football team (48 caps/10 goals) from 1979 to 1986.

name: Kostadin Markov
description: Kostadin Markov (Bulgarian: Костадин Марков; born 18 February 1979) is a Bulgarian footballer who plays for Lokomotiv Plovdiv in the Bulgarian A PFG. Mainly a right back, he can also play as a midfielder and winger.

name: Kostas Kapetanos
description: Kostas Kapetanos (Greek: Κώστας Καπετάνος; born 27 October 1984 in Ptolemaida) is a Greek footballer currently playing for Olympiakos Volou 1937 F.C..

name: Kostas Manolas
description: Konstantinos "Kostas" Manolas (Greek: Κωνσταντίνος "Κώστας" Μανωλάς, born 14 June 1991) is a Greek professional footballer. Kostas Manolas is a nephew of Greek football and AEK legend Stelios Manolas. Manolas also wears the number 4, previously worn by his uncle. He currently plays for Olympiacos.

name: Kostas Peristeridis
description: Konstantinos Peristeridis (Greek: Κώστας Περιστερίδης; born 5 July 1991) is a Greek footballer who plays as a Goalkeeper for Panionios G.S.S.

name: Kostas Stafylidis
description: Kostas Stafylidis is a Greek footballer who plays for PAOK F.C. in the Greek Superleague on loan from Bayer Leverkusen.

name: Kosuke Taketomi
description: Kosuke Taketomi (武富 孝介, born September 23, 1990) is a Japanese football player.

name: Kota Yanagisawa
description: Kota Yanagisawa (born April 8, 1982) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Kouadio Pascal Doubaï
description: Kouadio Pascal Doubaï, also known just as Pascal Doubaï (born 22 May 1992) in Yamoussoukro, Cote d'Ivoire, is a Cote d'Ivoireian association footballer currently playing for BSC Young Boys in the Swiss Super League. He plays in the Midfield, as either a Central Midfielder or an Attacking Midfielder.

name: Kouch Sokumpheak

name: Koupossitéré Camara
description: Koupossitéré Camara (born 15 December 1986) is a Togolese international footballer who plays as a midfielder for ASKO Kara.

name: Kozo Hosokawa
description: Kozo Hosokawa (born August 3, 1971) is a former Japanese football player.

name: Kozo Kinomoto
description: Kozo Kinomoto (born 8 January 1949) is a former Japanese football player. He has played for Furukawa Electric.

name: Kraesher Mooke
description: Kraesher Mooke Watson (born 13 March 1984) is a Costa Rican professional football player. He normally plays as left midfielder. He is well known for his control of the ball on the field and for his participation in the Costa Rican minor leagues.

name: Kraikitti In-utane
description: Kraikitti In-utane is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Chonburi in the Thailand Premier League.

name: Kraisorn Sriyan
description: Kraisorn Sriyan is a Thai footballer. He is currently playing for Army United F.C. in the Thai Premier League, on loan from Buriram PEA.

name: Krasimir Borisov
description: Krasimir Borisov Georgiev (Bulgarian: Кpacимиp Бopиcoв Георгиев) (born 8 April 1950) is a former Bulgarian football midfielder who played for Bulgaria in the 1974 FIFA World Cup. He also played for PFC Levski Sofia.

name: Kreshnik Sinanaj
description: Kreshnik Sinanaj (born 31 January 1986) is an Albanian football player. The defender currently plays for KF Tirana in the Albanian Superliga. He has previously played for Flamurtari, Dinamo Tirana, KS Besa Kavaje, Teuta Durres and more recently KS Kamza.

name: Kriangkrai Chasang
description: Kriangkrai Chasang is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Songkhla United in the Thailand Premier League.

name: Krikor Alozian
description: Krikor Alozian (born 24 April 1979) is a Lebanese footballer of Armenian descent who currently plays for Hekmeh FC. Alozian previously played for Homenetmen Beirut and Olympic Beirut. He also represented the Lebanon national football team from 2002 to 2004.

name: Kris Foucault
description: Kristopher Foucault (born December 12, 1990) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player. He is currently playing with the Houston Aeros of the American Hockey League (AHL) as a prospect for the Minnesota Wild of the National Hockey League (NHL). Foucault was selected by the Minnesota Wild in the 4th round (103rd overall) of the 2009 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Kris Fredheim
description: Kris Allen Fredheim (born February 23, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player currently playing for the Houston Aeros of the American Hockey League (AHL) as a prospect for the Minnesota Wild of the National Hockey League (NHL). He was selected by the Vancouver Canucks in the 6th round (185th overall) of the 2005 NHL Entry Draft. Kris played collegiate hockey at Colorado College of the Western Collegiate Hockey Association. On November 16, 2011, the Minnesota Wild signed Fredheim to an entry level contract. On November 17, 2011, he made his National Hockey League debut recordeding 10:13 of ice time for the Wild.

name: Kris Goossens
description: Kris Goossens (born 20 February 1974) is a former professional tennis player from Belgium.

name: Kris Kalifatidis
description: Kris Kalifatidis is an Australian former footballer who played one match for the Australia national association football team.

name: Kris Kocurek
description: Kris Kocurek (born November 15, 1978) is a former American football defensive tackle and current defensive line coach for the Detroit Lions of the National Football League. He was drafted by the Seattle Seahawks in the seventh round of the in 2001 NFL Draft. He played college football at Texas Tech. Kocurek also played for the Tennessee Titans. Kocurek was hired by the Detroit Lions in 2009 as assistant defensive line coach and was promoted to head defensive line coach in 2010 after the retirement of Bob Karmelowicz.

name: Kris Odegard
description: Kris Odegard (born February 29, 1980) is a Canadian professional racquetball player from Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. Odegard has won four Canadian Championships - two in singles and two in doubles. He also won the 2006 Pan American Championships, which was his first time on Team Canada.

name: Krishana Singh
description: Krishana Raj Singh (born 19 December 1982) is an English cricketer. Singh is a right-handed batsman who bowls leg break. He was born in Westminster, London. While studying for his degree at Loughborough University, Singh made his first-class debut for Loughborough UCCE against Sussex in 2005. He made a further two first-class appearances for the team in 2005, against Nottinghamshire and Worcestershire. In his three first-class matches, he scored 54 runs at an average of 13.50, with a high score of 29*.

name: Krishmar Santokie
description: Krishmar Santokie is a cricketer who plays for Jamaica and has represented the West Indies at international level. He bowls left-arm medium pace and is a lower order batsman. His debut for the West Indies came in a Twenty20 International against England in September 2011, he finished with bowling figures of 1/17 in a West Indies victory.

name: Krishnendu Roy
description: Krishnendu Roy is an Indian football Defender who played for India in the 1984 Asian Cup. He also played for Mohun Bagan.

name: Kristín Ýr Bjarnadóttir
description: Kristín Ýr Bjarnadóttir (born 1 February 1984) is an Icelandic football player who plays as a striker. Kristín is currently part of Iceland women's national team and was a squad member at UEFA Women's Euro 2009. Kristín was top scorer in Valur in 2001 and 2003 but got badly injured in 2004 and quit football after that, returning to training with Afturelding in 2007 without playing for them and then transferring back to Valur to play with them as of the 2008 season. She was the top scorer in Iceland in both 2009 and 2010 with 23 league goals in 18 games in both seasons. She played for Avaldsnes IL in Norway for the 2012 season but returned to Valur after the season.

name: Krista Donnenwirth
description: Krista Lynn Donnenwirth (born June 12, 1989, in Torrance, California) is an All-American softball player. She attended Capistrano Valley High School. After graduating from high school, she went on to attend Arizona State University, where she plays shortstop and third base.

name: Kristen Mewis
description: Kristen Anne Mewis (born February 25, 1991) is an American professional soccer player. She currently plays as a midfielder for FC Kansas City in the National Women's Soccer League and for the United States women's national soccer team.

name: Kristers Freibergs
description: Kristers Freibergs (born July 3, 1992) is a Latvian professional ice hockey defenceman. He is currently playing for HK Riga of the Russian Minor Hockey League. Freibergs made his European Elite debut with HK Liepājas Metalurgs of the Belarusian Extraleague during the 2010-11 season. He participated at the 2012 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships as a member of the Latvia men's national junior ice hockey team.

name: Kristhian Ramón Reyes
description: Kristhian Ramón Reyes Prudencio (Born February 25, 1982 in Santa Rosa de Lima) is a Salvadoran footballer, who most recently played for Pasaquina in the Salvadoran second division.

name: Kristiāns Pelšs
description: Kristiāns Pelšs (born September 9, 1992) is a Latvian ice hockey player. He is currently playing for the Oklahoma City Barons of the American Hockey League (AHL) as a prospect of the Edmonton Oilers of the National Hockey League. Pelss was selected by the Edmonton Oilers in the 7th round (181st overall) of the 2010 NHL Entry Draft.

name: Kristi Harvey
description: Kristi Harvey (born 30 November 1988) is an Australian football (soccer) player currently playing for Australian W-League team Adelaide United.

name: Kristian Bell
description: Kristian Martin Bell (born 15 April 1972) is a former Welsh cricketer. Bell was a right-handed batsman who bowled leg break. He was born in Cardiff, Glamorgan. Bell made his debut for Wales Minor Counties in the 1992 Minor Counties Championship against Berkshire. He played Minor counties cricket for Wales Minor Counties from 1992 to 2001, which included 58 Minor Counties Championship matches and 13 MCCA Knockout Trophy matches. He made his List A debut for Wales Minor Counties against Sussex in the 1993 NatWest Trophy. He made 7 further List A appearances for the county, the last coming against Leicestershire in the 2001 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy. In his 8 List A matches, he scored 123 runs at a batting average of 15.37, with a high score of 39.

name: Kristian Cox
description: Kristian Cox (born 28 September 1992) is an English former football striker who played for Port Vale in 2011.

name: Kristian Hristianov
description: Kristian Hristianov (born 11 September 1978) is a Bulgarian footballer currently (as of July 2010) playing for Nesebar as a forward.

name: Kristian Matte
description: Kristian Matte (born September 3, 1985) is a professional Canadian football offensive linemen for the Montreal Alouettes of the Canadian Football League. He was drafted seventh overall by the Alouettes in the 2010 CFL Draft and signed with the team after attending mini camp with the NFL's Houston Texans. He played college football for the Concordia Stingers.

name: Kristian Näkyvä
description: Kristian Näkyvä (born November 18, 1990)is a Finnish professional ice hockey defenceman who currently plays for JYP Jyväskylä of the SM-liiga.

name: Kristian Platt
description: Kristian Platt is a defender, currently playing for Stalybridge Celtic. Platt made his professional debut as a 17 year old substitute for Shaun Kelly against Darlington on 3 May 2009 in Chester's final match in The Football League following relegation. Prior to his debut, Platt had been linked to moves to Premier League clubs and had played for the first-team in a friendly match against Southport.

name: Kristian Tuohilampi
description: Kristian Tuohilampi (born November 8, 1989) is a Finnish ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing for the HIFK Helsinki of the SM-liiga.

name: Kristian Volokhov
description: Kristian Eduardovich Volokhov (Russian: Кристиан Эдуардович Волохов; born December 4, 1991) is a Russian professional football player who plays for FC Smena Komsomolsk-na-Amure in the Russian Second Division.

name: Kristien Elsen
description: Kristien Elsen is a Belgian football midfielder currently playing in the Belgian 1st Division for Lierse SK. She has also played the European Cup with Rapide Wezemaal. She is a member of the Belgian national team. As a junior international she played the 2006 U-19 European Championship, scoring Belgium's only goal in the competition.

name: Kristiene Gong
description: Kristiene Gong (born March 2, 1993) is an American figure skater.

name: Kristin Demann
description: Kristin Demann is a German football defender, currently playing for Turbine Potsdam in Germany's Frauen Bundesliga. She was a member of the German Under-19 national team that won the 2011 U-19 European Championship.

name: Kristin Frey
description: Kristin Frey {{#invoke:InfoboxImage|InfoboxImage|image=|size=|sizedefault=frameless|alt=|suppressplaceholder=yes}}Personal informationNationality AmericanBorn (1984-01-11) January 11, 1984 (age 29)IllinoisWebsite {{#invoke:URL|url|1=www. kristinfrey. com|2=}}SportSport Tower running, Stair climbing, Marathon running Kristin Frey is an elite US stair climber and tower runner who also competes in road races ranging from 5k to the marathon and duathlons. Kristin started competing in tower running in 2010, when she did Hustle Up the Hancock for the first time. Since then she has climbed all of the major towers in Chicago. In 2012, Kristin set the course record of 10:49 at the Step Up for Kids Climb held at the Aon Center in Chicago. That same year, she also won Hustle Up the Hancock with a time of 10:56. She has participated twice in the very prestigious Empire State Building Run-Up in NYC where she placed 5th in 2012. Kristin has also completed several other tower races around the US including the Stratosphere in Las Vegas, the Aon Building in Los Angeles and multiple towers in Seattle. She also participated in tower races in Bogota, Colombia for the Towerrunning World Cup Championships and in São Paulo, Brazil for the Vertical World Circuit Championship, where she placed 2nd. Despite being ranked number two in the world among women tower runners in 2011 Frey could not find a sponsor.

name: Kristin Luckenbill
description: Kristin Luckenbill (born 28 May 1979) is an American professional soccer goalkeeper and Olympic gold medalist. She previously played for the Boston Breakers and Sky Blue FC of Women's Professional Soccer as well as the Carolina Courage of the WUSA. She is a former member of the United States women's national soccer team.
